preference.preference_description: Registration of the Change Details stylesheet for ScheduleTask objects.

preference.name: ICS_classifiable_types
preference.preference_description: Identifies whether the particular type can be classified or not. It's recommended that this be set to Item/ItemRevision.

preference.name: ICS_FilterBy_Library_types
preference.preference_description: Identifies the Library types that will be used as filters by the Dictionary dialog user interface.

preference.name: ICS_GraphicsBuilder
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the preference that points to the graphics builder utility that is used by Classification to enable the graphic creation functionality in the Classification application.

preference.name: ICS_Print_HeaderLabel_Style
preference.preference_description: Indicates how the headers in the Classification application should be displayed for the Print function. Valid values are HEADER_UNCT, HEADER_NAME, HEADER_SHORTNAME or HEADER_ANNOTATION.

preference.name: ICS_SysCopy_HeaderLabel_Style
preference.preference_description: Indicates how the headers in the Classification application should be displayed for the SysCopy function. Valid values are HEADER_UNCT, HEADER_NAME, HEADER_SHORTNAME or HEADER_ANNOTATION.

preference.name: ICS_Table_HeaderLabel_Style
preference.preference_description: Indicates how the headers in the Classification application should be displayed for the Table. Valid values are HEADER_UNCT, HEADER_NAME, HEADER_SHORTNAME or HEADER_ANNOTATION.

preference.name: ICS_active_unit_search
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default search unit system that is initially used for a classification class that is defined to hold both metric and non-metric values. Valid values are: metric non-metric both

preference.name: ICS_admin_requires_dba
preference.preference_description: Give NON-DBA users access to the Classification Admin. Application. Valid values are true/false. true - User requires dba privileges to access Classification Admin. false - User has access to Classification Admin. If you allow non-dba users to log into Classification Admin., please note that the users will have full read/write access! To protect the hierarchy, the dictionary, and the KeyLOVs from unauthorized access, they need to be protected using the AccessControl tab.

preference.name: ICS_allow_deprecated_lovs_on_copy
preference.preference_description: Allows "Save As" and "Revise" actions on an Item or Item Revision to create a copy of a Classification object already classified using deprecated Key LOV values. If set to "true", the Classification system will allow any of these actions to create a copy of a Classification object already classified using deprecated Key LOV values. If set to "false", the Classification system will prevent these actions from creating a copy of any Classification object already classified using deprecated Key LOV values.

preference.name: ICS_allow_deprecated_lovs_on_update
preference.preference_description: Enforces the usage of non-deprecated Key LOV values for the Classification properties during Classification object update. If set to "false", the Classification system will not allow a save of the Classification object that is already classified using deprecated Key LOV values. If set to "true", the Classification system will allow a save of the Classification object that is already classified with deprecated Key LOV values.

preference.name: ICS_allow_min_max_range_override
preference.preference_description: Enforces the minimum and/or maximum constraints override boundary on Class and/or View attributes. If set to "true", the Classification system will allow Classification administrator to specify the minimum and/or maximum constraints values to Class/View attribute outside the range of Dictionary/Class attribute minimum and/or maximum constraints respectively. If set to "false", the Classification system will enforce Classification administrator to specify the minimum and/or maximum constraints values to Class/View attribute within the range of Dictionary/Class attribute minimum and/or maximum constraints respectively.

preference.name: ICS_array_attribute_value_separator
preference.preference_description:
Defines a separator to be used when listing the values of a variable length array attribute in the table in the Classification application.
The default value of the separator is ",".

preference.name: ICS_attribute_displayable_properties
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of Classification Attribute properties to be displayed on Classification properties tooltip in the Classification user application.

preference.name: ICS_attribute_mapping_trim_zeros
preference.preference_description: Controls if leading (and trailing) zeros will be removed from number values in ICOs when sending the values to NX for Attribute Mapping. Valid values are keep/leading/both. keep: Do not trim, leading: trim leading zeros, both: trim leading and trailing zeros. This is a user preference.

preference.name: ICS_attribute_mapping_unit_support
preference.preference_description: Specifies the dataset and item types for which Classification unit support, including optimization, is active when mapping attributes to NX. Subtypes of provided types are not considered.

preference.name: ICS_autocompute_validate
preference.preference_description: Enables the auto-compute data validation during the auto-compute engine initialization. If set to "true", all the input data that are provided in auto-compute custom logic are validated. If set to "false", no validation of such data happens.

preference.name: ICS_classify_immediately
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default setting of the "Classify Immediately" checkbox on the New Item, Save As, and Revise dialogs. Note: This checkbox is displayed only if ICS_classify_new is set to Item or ItemRevision. Valid values are 0/1. 0 - Do Not send new or revised object to in-CLASS for immediate classification. 1 - Send new or revised object to in-CLASS for immediate classification.

preference.name: ICS_classify_immediately_NX
preference.preference_description: Specifies if new Items or ItemRevisions are classified when they are saved from NXManager Unigraphics. Valid values are 0/1. If a value 1 is specified and NXManager Unigraphics is started from Teamcenter Rich Client and save a newly created part in Unigraphics, the user will be asked in Rich Client to classify the new item / item revision. 0 - Do not classify from Unigraphics (default value). 1 - Classify from Unigraphics.

preference.name: ICS_classify_new
preference.preference_description: When objects are created or revised, specifies whether an immediate-classify option is to be presented to the user, and further specifies whether it is the Item or the ItemRevision that is to be classified. Valid values are Item or ItemRevision. If defined to one of these values, a "Classify Immediately" checkbox option will appear on the New Item, Save As, and/or Revise dialogs as appropriate. Default setting of this checkbox is controlled by the ICS_classify_immediately preference variable.

preference.name: ICS_classify_sendto
preference.preference_description: Controls which available applications are to be displayed in the "Send to" button in applications Classification and Resource Manager. Valid values are either the application identification or the application name.

preference.name: ICS_datasettype_for_class
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: ICS_default_class_document
preference.preference_description: Controls which of the available documents (see ICS_presented_class_documents) is displayed by default when you select a class.

preference.name: ICS_default_instance_document
preference.preference_description: Controls which of the available documents (see ICS_presented_instance_documents) is dislayed by default when you view an ICO.

preference.name: ICS_disable_class_viewer_show_images
preference.preference_description: Disables the class image viewer in the Classification and Classification Admin applications. Valid values are: * true: class image viewer is disabled. * false: class image viewer is enabled. This is the default value.

preference.name: ICS_disable_default_classifiable_types
preference.preference_description: Deactivates the usage of the default classifiable types. The default classifiable types are: MEOP, MEOPRevision, MEProcess, MEProcessRevision, MEWorkarea, MEWorkareaRevision, MEActivity, MEActivityRevision. Valid values are true and false (default value).

preference.name: ICS_disable_instance_viewer_show_images
preference.preference_description: Disables the instance image viewer in the Classification application. Valid values are: * true: instance image viewer is disabled. * false: instance image viewer is enabled. This is the default value.

preference.name: ICS_display_unformatted_numbers
preference.preference_description: Deactivates the removal of leading 0s for numeric Classification properties. Valid values are: * a list of Attribute Ids for which leading 0s will be shown * true: leading 0s will be shown for all numeric properties * false: the leading 0s will be suppressed for all numeric properties.(Default value). This is a user preference.

preference.name: ICS_enable_graphical_browser
preference.preference_description: Enables the optional graphical hierarchy browsing feature in Classification. Valid values are TRUE to enable, FALSE to disable.

preference.name: ICS_enforce_min_max_constraints_on_copy
preference.preference_description: Prevents the "Save As" and "Revise" action on classified Items or Item Revisions to create a copy of a Classification object which properties values do not conform to the minimum and/or maximum constraints. Valid values are: * true: the Classification system will not allow creating a copy from an existing Classified object which properties values do not conform to the minimum and/or maximum constraints. * false: the Classification system will allow creating a copy from an existing Classified object which properties values do not conform to the minimum and/or maximum constraints. The default value is set to "false".

preference.name: ICS_enforce_min_max_constraints_on_update
preference.preference_description: Enforces to provide the value to the Classification properties within minimum and/or maximum constraints range during a "Classification object update" operation. If set to "true", the Classification system will not allow a Classification object to be saved during update, if the Classification properties values do not conform to the minimum and/or maximum constraints. If set to "false", the Classification system will allow a Classification object to be saved during update, if the Classification properties values do not conform to the minimum and/or maximum constraints.

preference.name: ICS_favorites_separator
preference.preference_description:
Defines the separator character to be used when storing the favorites in Classification application.
The default value of the separator is ",".

preference.name: ICS_force_mandatory_attribute_check
preference.preference_description: Activates the check that all mandatory attributes contain values during the creation of any Classification object. This check occurs regardless of the import/creation method. Valid values are true or false (default value).

preference.name: ICS_hierarchy_sort_option
preference.preference_description: Determines what attribute will be used to sort the displayed classification hierarchy tree. The tree is sorted in alphanumerically ascending order. Valid values are : "-600" : sort on the class/view ID. This is the default. "-607" : sort on the class/view name. "-608" : sort on the short name of the class/view. "-612" : sort on the user data 1 property of the class/view. "-613" : sort on the user data 2 property of the class/view. This is a site preference.

preference.name: ICS_ico_action_after_revise
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the classification record is to be carried forward after a revise operation. If nothing is defined the value from ICS_ico_action_after_saveas will be taken. Valid values are: - "copy": Creates a copy of the original classification record with a resource ID matching the ID of the new object, thus classifying the new object. - any other value - Deletes the IMAN_classification relation between the new object and the classification record of the original object. The new object can then be classified using standard Classification procedures. - empty value: The value will be taken from the ICS_ico_action_after_saveas preference.

preference.name: ICS_ico_action_after_saveas
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the classification record is to be carried forward after a save-as operation. Valid values are: - "copy": Creates a copy of the original classification record with a resource ID matching the ID of the new object, thus classifying the new object. - any other value (including empty): Deletes the IMAN_classification relation between the new object and the classification record of the original object. The new object can then be classified using standard Classification procedures.

preference.name: ICS_ico_id_case_sensitive
preference.preference_description: Determines whether the ID supplied for Classification object creation is case sensitive. Valid values are: * true: The ID is case sensitive. This means, for example, that Classification objects with IDs "abc", "ABC", "AbC", etc. can be created. This is the default value. * false: The ID is case insensitive. This means in the example above, that only one object with ID "abc" (regardless of the case) can be created.

preference.name: ICS_import_attribute_find_free_dbindex
preference.preference_description: Specifies that Teamcenter should find the next free dbindex position in the database if the specified dbindex position is already in use when importing Classification Administration data using PLM XML or XML data. Teamcenter only evaluates this preference if the "ICS_import_attribute_use_dbindex preference" is set.

preference.name: ICS_import_attribute_use_dbindex
preference.preference_description: Specifies the use of the dbindex position in the database when importing Classification Administration data. When you import PLMXML or XML data in Classification Administration, the dbindex position is used. To disable this, set this preference to False.

preference.name: ICS_instance_image_revision_rule
preference.preference_description:
Specifies the revision rule for displaying an image of the Classified Object in the Classification application. This preference is only applicable to the Rich client.
The default value is "Latest Working".

preference.name: ICS_itemrev_master_dataset_relation
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: ICS_localization_feature_enabled
preference.preference_description: Enables the visualization of translation information. Valid values are true or false (default value).

preference.name: ICS_mapping_target_type
preference.preference_description: Identifies whether the mapping target item or item revision shall be classified. Supported values are Item and ItemRevision. It's recommended that this be set to ItemRevision.

preference.name: ICS_master_datasettypes_for_itemrev
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: ICS_max_number_of_components
preference.preference_description: Controls the number of assembly components to be shown without warning in the Classification Instance Viewer. Set the value to 0 if the warning message should not be displayed.

preference.name: ICS_override_unit_definition_precision
preference.preference_description: Enables overriding the unit definition precision that is set in the unit definition class. Valid values are true/false. Default value is false. true: Overrides the unit definition. false: Displays the number of decimal places specified in the unit definition.

preference.name: ICS_presented_class_documents
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of named references that will be available for the class viewer to display in the Classification application. The system searches through the dataset of the class looking for named references. If the file type of the named reference found is contained in this list, the class viewer will show a tab for it. Possible values are all named references of the dataset type ICSClassFiles.

preference.name: ICS_presented_instance_documents
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of named references that will be available for the instance viewer in the Classification application to display. The system searches through all the datasets of the workspace object looking for named references and if the file type contained in this named reference is contained in this list, the instance viewer in the Classification application shows a tab for it. Possible values are all named references and the following values: BOMAssembly - If you want to display BOM Assemblies. JTAssembly - If you want to display JT Structure assemblies.

preference.name: ICS_reference_attribute_use_format_for_display
preference.preference_description: Specifies that the reference attribute format is used to determine the size of the text field when searching in the Classification application. Valid values are: * true: the format of the dictionary attribute is used to determine the size of the text field. * false: the size of the text field of a reference attributes is always 256 characters. This is the default value.

preference.name: ICS_search_filter_by_read_access
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether Classification searches filter out Classification objects for which the user does not have read access, while performing the search. Privileges on the class definition are not honored when this preference is set. Caution: Setting this preference to true has a negative performance impact on the search mechanism. Valid values are: * true: the user read access privilege is assessed. * false: the user read access privilege is not assessed. This is the default value.

preference.name: ICS_search_image_order
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: ICS_search_use_revision_rule
preference.preference_description: Preference is used to enable/disable the revision rule functionality for the search in Classification application.

preference.name: ICS_show_autofilter
preference.preference_description: Enables the auto-filter functionality in Classification forms. Values are TRUE to enable, FALSE to disable.

preference.name: ICS_synchronize_automatically
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the in-CLASS hierarchy data is to be shared to the selected sites (in ICS_synchronized_sites) whenever the data is saved. Valid values are 0/1. 0 - Does not share the data. 1 - The in-CLASS hierarchy data will be shared.

preference.name: ICS_synchronize_sites
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of sites that will be used for sharing of in-CLASS hierarchy data. Do not forget to enter the site names in the database (via Organization application and Sites node).

preference.name: ICS_table_header_style
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the in-CLASS table page header should display short or long topic names. This is applicable only in Classification Web. Valid values are Long/Short/ID. Long - Display long attribute names. Short - Display short attribute names. ID - Display attribute IDs.

preference.name: ICS_table_pagesize
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default number of initial rows for the in-CLASS table page. This is applicable only in Classification Web.

preference.name: ICS_unit_active
preference.preference_description: Specifies the active system of measurement that is initially displayed when a classification class is defined to hold both metric and non-metric values. Valid values are: 0 : metric 1 : non-metric

preference.name: ICS_unit_default
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default system of measurement when creating a class in the Classification Administration application. Valid values are: 0 : metric 1 : non-metric 2 : both(metric and non-metric)

preference.name: ICS_use_access_control
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: ICS_web_preferred_jt_image
preference.preference_description: Controls what JT image will be displayed in Classification Web when the user clicks on View-TcVis in the menu bar. If the classified object has only a single JT (in a DirectModel dataset), this JT will be displayed. If the classified object is a BOM assembly, the JTs of the BOMLines will be displayed. If the classified object has both (single JT and BOM Assembly), you can control with this preference what JT should be displayed. Valid values are BOM_Assembly/Single_JT. BOM_Assembly - Display the BOM Assembly JTs. Single_JT - Display the single JT.

preference.name: ICS_web_preferred_unit
preference.preference_description: Specifies the unit system in which to display a selected classification object (ICO) in the Classification thin client application. If this preference is not defined, Teamcenter displays ICOs in the unit system of measurement associated with the class. If the class is configured to use both unit systems of measurement, the ICOs are initially displayed in the metric unit system of measurement. Valid values are: * metric: Displays an ICO in the metric system. * non-metric: Displays an ICO in a non-metric system. By default, there is no value.

preference.name: ICS_web_search_in_unit_system
preference.preference_description: Specifies the unit system when searching for classification objects (ICOs) in the Classification thin client application. If this preference is not defined, Teamcenter uses the value specified by the "ICS_web_preferred_unit" preference. Valid values are: * metric: Searches using the metric system only. * non-metric: Searches using the non-metric system only. * both: Searches using both the metric and non-metric systems, with switching enabled in the "Query" tab. By default, there is no value.

preference.name: icm0.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the Dataset type to be used for the summary rendering of Classification objects (internal type name icm0). The default value for this user preference is icm0Summary (Classification Summary).

preference.name: icm0Summary.SUMMARY_REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Indicates the types to which the icm0 Summary stylesheet can be applied.

preference.name: ICS_allow_remote_parent
preference.preference_description: ICS_allow_remote_parent is used to control that classes and views can not be added under not locally owned classes. Possible values are true/false. true defines that it is possible to add classes/views to a not locally owned site. false defines that it is not possible. This is a site preference.

preference.name: ICS_allowed_chars_for_class_id
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of special characters that are permissible in the Group IDs/Class IDs within a Classification hierarchy. By default, you cannot use a space or any of these special characters "|%*:(){}[] \"(ignore quotes) in Group IDs/Class IDs during their creation. Specify all the special characters on the same value.

preference.name: ICS_copy_classid_pattern
preference.preference_description: ICS_copy_classid_pattern is used for the copy class operation to create a new class id. Beside any valid text the pattern can contain the following placeholders: ${P}/${NN}/${CID}. ${P} represents the class id of the parent class. ${NN} represents a two digit sequence number. Any number of digits can be defined. ${CID} represents the original class id. This is a user preference.

preference.name: ICS_import_view_drop_attributes_not_in_class
preference.preference_description: Enables the PLMXML import of views to continue when the operation encounters an attribute not contained in the class. Valid values for this site preference are: true: the attribute is ignored and the import continues. false: the import aborts if it encounters a superfluous attribute. This is the default value.

preference.name: ICS_keylovs_allowing_undefined_values
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of Key LOV IDs (negative integers) that allows the use of temporarily undefined Key LOV entries during the creation and edition of Classification objects. Caution: Adding a key LOV ID to this list can cause data integrity problems.

preference.name: ICS_migrate_classid_pattern
preference.preference_description: ICS_migrate_classid_pattern is used for the migrate subclass operation to create a new class id. Beside any valid text the pattern can contain the following placeholders: ${P}/${NN}/${CID}/${SID}. ${P} represents the class id of the parent class. ${NN} represents a two digit sequence number. Any number of digits can be defined. ${CID} represents the original class id. ${SID} represents the original class id of the SML-SubClass to be migrated. This is a user preference.

preference.name: ICS_new_classid_pattern
preference.preference_description: ICS_new_classid_pattern is the general pattern for creating a new class id. Beside any valid text the pattern can contain the following placeholders: ${P}/${NN}. ${P} represents the class id of the parent class. ${NN} represents a two digit sequence number. Any number of digits can be defined. This is a user preference.

preference.name: ICS_perform_xmlschema_validation
preference.preference_description: Activates schema validation during a "Classification XML Import" operation. The default value of this site preference is true.

preference.name: ICS_searchindex_view_visible
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the "Search Index View" type is available in the list of Classification View types that users can create. The default value is "false": the view is not available.

preference.name: ICS_use_view_attributes_when_moving_icos
preference.preference_description: ICS_use_view_attributes_when_moving_icos is used for moving ICOs to define whether only the values of the attributes that the current user can see through his view or all values will be set when an ICO is moved to a different class. Valid values are true/false. true defines that only the values of the attributes that the current user can see through his view will be set. false defines that all values will be set. This is a site preference.

preference.name: ICS_view_selection_order
preference.preference_description: Defines the order in which Classifation views are searched to match the logged in user.

preference.name: CONDVALIDATION_Keep_PrevRev_Results
preference.preference_description: This preference is used to control whether BOM grading keeps the results generated by previous checker revisions. If set to false BOM results generated by Checker/A are deleted when BOM is validated against Checker/B.

preference.name: CondValAgent.CREATERENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the create stylesheet for Condition Validation Agent Item objects.

preference.name: CondValAgent.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Condition Validation Agent objects.

preference.name: CondValAgentCreate.CREATE_REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Indicates the type to which the Condition Validation Agent Item create stylesheet can be applied.

preference.name: CondValAgentRevSummary.SUMMARY_REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Indicates the types to which the Condition Validation Agent Revision summary stylesheet can be applied.

preference.name: CondValAgentRevision.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Condition Validation Agent Revision objects.

preference.name: CondValAgentSummary.SUMMARY_REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Indicates the types to which the Condition Validation Agent summary stylesheet can be applied.

preference.name: CondValData.CREATERENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the create stylesheet for Condition Validation Data Item objects.

preference.name: CondValData.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Condition Validation Data objects.

preference.name: CondValDataCreate.CREATE_REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Indicates the type to which the Condition Validation Data Item create stylesheet can be applied.

preference.name: CondValDataRevSummary.SUMMARY_REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Indicates the types to which the Condition Validation Data Revision summary stylesheet can be applied.

preference.name: CondValDataRevision.REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Indicates the types to which the Condition Validation Data Revision stylesheet can be applied.

preference.name: CondValDataRevision.RENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of properties stylesheet for Condition Validation Data Revision objects.

preference.name: CondValDataRevision.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Condition Validation Data Revision objects.

preference.name: CondValDataSummary.SUMMARY_REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Indicates the types to which the Condition Validation Data summary stylesheet can be applied.

preference.name: CondValResult.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Defines the name of the summary stylesheet for condition validation result objects.

preference.name: CondValResultSummary.SUMMARY_REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Indicates the type to which the condition validation result summary stylesheet can be applied.

preference.name: CondValidation_NoData
preference.preference_description: Property to define company policy towards no-data results in condition validation results. Valid values are PASS, FAIL and NODATA.

preference.name: ConditionValidationResultColumnPreferences
preference.preference_description: The list of property names to be displayed as columns in condition validation results table.

preference.name: ConditionValidationResultColumnWidthPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths of the shown columns in condition validation results table.

preference.name: TYPE_DISPLAY_RULES_list_types_of_subclasses
preference.preference_description: Preferences for Type Display Rules This is a site preference. For all the entries under this preference the user interface for Type Display Rule shows the types implemented by the subclasses too.

preference.name: ASSIGNED_ITEM_ID_MODIFIABLE
preference.preference_description: Determines whether an automatically generated Item ID can be modified by users after it has been generated. The default value is 0. Valid values are 0/1. 0 - When the item ID is generated by clicking the Assign button, the system generated item ID cannot be modified by the user. 1 - When the item ID is generated by clicking the Assign button, the system generated item ID can be modified by the user.

preference.name: ASSIGNED_ITEM_REV_MODIFIABLE
preference.preference_description: Determines whether an automatically generated Item revID can be modified by users after it has been generated. The default value is 0. Valid values are 0/1. 0 - When the item rev ID is generated by clicking the Assign button, the system generated item ID cannot be modified by the user. 1 - When the item rev ID is generated by clicking the Assign button, the system generated item ID can be modified by the user.

preference.name: AltIdentifier_require_on_create
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of identifiable types (item types for now) that require a user to create an alternate id in Teamcenter rich client.

preference.name: BMF_CUSTOM_IMPLEMENTOR_PATH
preference.preference_description: Specifies the full directory path to the custom libraries (where any custom methods for the BMF are maintained). This is a site preference only.

preference.name: BMF_SUPPRESS_ACTION_RULES_DISPLAY
preference.preference_description: Controls the display of Action Rules tab in the Business Modeler application. Valid values are ON/OFF. OFF - Turns off the suppression of the Action Rules tab in the Business Modeler application i.e. Action Rules tab will be displayed. ON (or not defined) - Supresses the Action Rules tab in the Business Modeler application i.e. Action Rules tab will not be displayed. This is a site preference only.

preference.name: BMIDE_ALLOW_FULL_DEPLOY_FROM_CLIENT
preference.preference_description: Allows the full deployment from the Business Modeler application. In a production server, this can be set to false so that only TEM can do install or upgrade, and so that BMIDE client can do only Live Update deployment. Valid values are: * true: possible to perform the full deployment from the BMIDE client. This is the default value. * false: impossible to perform the full deployment from the BMIDE client. If this site preference is not created, the behavior will be the same as if it existed and were set to true.

preference.name: BMIDE_ALLOW_LIVE_UPDATES
preference.preference_description: Allows the Live Update deployment from the Business Modeler application and TEM. In a production server, this can be set to false so that TEM and BMIDE client cannot perform Live Updates. Valid values are : * true: possible to perform Live Updates from TEM and BMIDE client. This is the default value. * false: impossible to perform Live Updates from TEM and BMIDE client. If this site preference is not created, the behavior will be the same as if it existed and were set to true.

preference.name: Bypass_property_rules
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the property rules should be bypassed or not. Valid values are 0/1. 0 - Do not bypass property rules. 1 - Bypass property rules. This is a site preference only.

preference.name: ITEM_autogenerate_id
preference.preference_description: What item types must automatically generate the item_id and item_revision_id in portal user interface.

preference.name: IdentifierContextPref
preference.preference_description: What character do you want to use in the Object column to separate the context name from identifier id?

preference.name: IdentifierContextTypeDefault
preference.preference_description: Default Alternate Id Context type. This will be used for PLMXML import/export of Alternate ID

preference.name: IdentifierLengthPref
preference.preference_description: What is the maximum length of context name you want to display in the Object column for an Identifier?

preference.name: IdentifierTypeDefault
preference.preference_description: Default Alternate Identifier type. This will be used for PLMXML import/export of Alternate ID

preference.name: Live Update
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of elements allowed for Live Updates. Any modification to this preference needs to be made in the Live Update Panel of the "Options" command. This is a site preference.

preference.name: METHOD_CM_execute_before_custom
preference.preference_description: Setting this preference to 1 will execute canned methods before custommethods. 1 = Execute canned methods before custom methods 0 = Execute custom methods before canned methods.

preference.name: TC_dataset_deep_copy_rules
preference.preference_description: Allows certain secondary datasets to be deep copied during Revise or Save As operation on an item revision. The valid format for each entry is: PRIMARY DATASET TYPE:RELATION TYPE:SECONDARY DATASET TYPE. The primary Dataset is attached to the Item Revision, whereas the secondary Dataset is related to the primary Dataset through the specifed Relation type. A relation refers to a GRM Relation and its type should be one of the defined Relation types under Admin. The default values for this preference are: UGMASTER:IMAN_Rendering:DirectModel UGPART:IMAN_Rendering:DirectModel UGALTREP:IMAN_Rendering:DirectModel DirectModel:TC_Derived:NXDerived FullText:Fnd0_Symbolic_Link:Image FullText:DMI_markup:Markup FullText:DMI_markup:Fnd0ReqMarkup

preference.name: TYPE_DISPLAY_RULES_list_of_primary_types
preference.preference_description: This is a site preference. This is the list of primary types on which the Type Display Rules can be configured.

preference.name: MetaDataStamp_template
preference.preference_description: Specifies the Item ID of the Item Revision that provides the MetaDataStamp Template dataset. The MetaDataStamp Template drives the formatting styles used in rendering the text and watermark stamp content.

preference.name: SecondaryVMUDatasets
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of non-VMU Dataset types that could contain VMU Datasets.

preference.name: TC_DIS_2D_named_ref
preference.preference_description: 2D file custom reference names can be added from VMU_FileSearchOrder list to this list so as to enable markup functionality for these 2D files when loaded in the Viewer.

preference.name: TC_DIS_3D_named_ref
preference.preference_description: 3D file custom reference names can be added from VMU_FileSearchOrder list to this list so as to enable markup functionality for these 3D files when loaded in the Viewer.

preference.name: TC_DIS_Search
preference.preference_description: List of valid search schemas.

preference.name: TC_show_open_in_vmu_button
preference.preference_description: Specifies if the "Open in VMU" button should be displayed in the Teamcenter Rich Client. Valid values are true/false.

preference.name: VIS_DirectModelAssembly_attach_relation_type
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relation between an Item Revision and a DirectModelAssembly dataset.

preference.name: VIS_OpenSupportedTypes
preference.preference_description: Lists the types of objects that can be opened by the Teamcenter Visualization Client.

preference.name: VIS_view_nx_prt_as_2d
preference.preference_description: Allows visualization of part files (.prt extension) with embedded CGM data in either 2D or 3D format in Lifecycle Visualization. Valid values are: * true: to view in 2D * false: to view in 3D. This is default value.

preference.name: VMU_Datasets
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of Datasets that can be directly launched in VisMockup by performing "File->Open In VMU" in the Teamcenter Rich Client. If a site wishes to open PDF, Tiff etc type of data in VisMockup, then the DatasetTypes used to manage these files, would need to be added to this list. Web Note: In Teamcenter Thin Client, the corresponding syntax is the Dataset's "View" link.

preference.name: VMU_FileSearchOrder
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of valid named reference types for the VMU datasets.

preference.name: VMU_RelationSearchOrder
preference.preference_description: Defines the ordered list of relations used for searching relations between visualization datasets and item/item revisions. Any such new relation needs to be added to the list.

preference.name: Baseline_create_snapshot_folder
preference.preference_description: 0 - Do not create the snapshot folder after Baseline Creation. 1 - Create snapshot folder after Baseline Creation.

preference.name: Baseline_precise_bvr
preference.preference_description: Valid values are 0/1/2. 0 - Create an ImPrecise Baseline. 1 - Create a Precise Baseline. 2 - Do not allow users to choose precise/imprecise and always create precise

preference.name: Baseline_release_procedures
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of Baseline Release procedures.

preference.name: AE_dataset_id_gen_by_type
preference.preference_description: Indicates if each dataset type has to have its own id counter. Valid values are ON/OFF.

preference.name: AE_dataset_id_postfix
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the Dataset ID generator postfix mechanism is to be turned on. One postfix is used for all dataset types. This postfix will be used only when a dataset is created, but not owned by any item or item revision. Valid values are ON/OFF.

preference.name: AE_dataset_id_prefix
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the Dataset ID generator prefix mechanism is to be turned on. One prefix is used for all dataset types. This prefix will be used only when a dataset is created, but not owned by any item or item revision. Valid values are ON/OFF.

preference.name: AE_dataset_id_separator
preference.preference_description: Specifies the separator between dataset id and revision during new dataset id generation. See the DisplayName constant in BMIDE to change how this gets displayed in the UI.

preference.name: AE_dataset_id_usage
preference.preference_description: Specifies if the Dataset Identification mechanism is to be turned on/off. Valid values are ON/OFF.

preference.name: AE_dataset_id_use_rev
preference.preference_description: Indicates if ItemRevision is to be used to generate Dataset ID. Valid values are ON/OFF.

preference.name: AE_default_dataset_type
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of preferred dataset types per file extensions. These dataset types will be listed first before any other matching dataset types, when retrieving them by file extension. Valid values have the following pattern: "file_extension:dataset_type" (e.g. "doc:MSWORD").

preference.name: Baseline_allow_edits
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether it is allowed to edit the Item ID of Items that are baselined. If this preference is ON, the User will be allowed to edit the Item ID of Items that have been baselined. Once the Item is released, the User will not be allowed to edit the Item ID.

preference.name: Baseline_allowed_baserev_statuses
preference.preference_description: The list of Status types that an Item Revision can have, to be able to create a baseline. If no status type is mentioned and if the Item revision has a status, then the user would not be able to create a baseline for it.

preference.name: Baseline_check_all
preference.preference_description: Allows the baseline operation to check synchronization between NX and BOMViewRevision even when the ItemRevision cannot be baselined. Valid values are: false - Do not check synchronization on ItemRevisions that cannot be baselined. This is the default value. true - Check synchronization on ItemRevisions that cannot be baselined.

preference.name: Baseline_dryrun_always
preference.preference_description: 0 - Do not perform Dry Run operaton before Baseline Creation. 1 - Perform Dry Run operation before Baseline Creation.

preference.name: Baseline_nxmanager_refile
preference.preference_description: Valid values are 0/1. 0 - Do not synchronize assembly using ugmanager_refile program. 1 - Synchronize assembly using ugmanager_refile program.

preference.name: Baseline_precondition_validation_rule_item_revision
preference.preference_description: Validation Rule item revision for baseline preaction handler.

preference.name: Baseline_refile_not_required_item_types
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of Item types for which refile would NOT be run during Baseline creation. E.g. Baseline_refile_not_required_item_types=Document. NOTE: This is valid only when the Baseline_nxmanager_refile is set to 1.

preference.name: Baseline_refile_required_dstypes
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of the ONLY dataset types which would force a refile to be performed for the Item types that are not listed by Baseline_refile_not_required_item_types. E.g. Baseline_refile_required_dstypes=UGMASTER,UGPART. NOTE: This is valid only when the Baseline_nxmanager_refile is set to 1.

preference.name: Bitmap_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relation that has to be created when an object is pasted under an object of type Bitmap. The relation specified for this preference will be the default relation that will be created between the source and the target Bitmap.

preference.name: DirectModel_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relation that has to be created when an object is pasted under an object of type DirectModel. The relation specified for this preference will be the default relation that will be created between the source and the target DirectModel.

preference.name: DrawingSheet_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relation that has to be created when an object is pasted under an object of type DrawingSheet. The relation specified for this preference will be the default relation that will be created between the source and the target DrawingSheet.

preference.name: FullText_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relation that has to be created when an object is pasted under an object of type FullText. The relation specified for this preference will be the default relation that will be created between the source and the target FullText.

preference.name: GIF_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relation that has to be created when an object is pasted under an object of type GIF. The relation specified for this preference will be the default relation that will be created between the source and the target GIF.

preference.name: ITEM_smart_baseline
preference.preference_description: Valid values are 0/1: 0 to create new baselines, 1 to allow smart copy between baselines.

preference.name: Image_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relation that has to be created when an object is pasted under an object of type Image. The relation specified for this preference will be the default relation that will be created between the source and the target Image.

preference.name: JPEG_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relation that has to be created when an object is pasted under an object of type JPEG. The relation specified for this preference will be the default relation that will be created between the source and the target JPEG.

preference.name: JtSimplifications_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relation that has to be created when an object is pasted under an object of type JtSimplifications. The relation specified for this preference will be the default relation that will be created between the source and the target JtSimplifications.

preference.name: MSWordX_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relation that has to be created when an object is pasted under an object of type MSWordX. The relation specified for this preference will be the default relation that will be created between the source and the target MSWordX.

preference.name: MSWord_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relation that has to be created when an object is pasted under an object of type MSWord. The relation specified for this preference will be the default relation that will be created between the source and the target MSWord.

preference.name: PDF_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relation that has to be created when an object is pasted under an object of type PDF. The relation specified for this preference will be the default relation that will be created between the source and the target PDF.

preference.name: TC_Dataset_Import_Exclude_Wildcard
preference.preference_description: Excludes the wildcard character "*" as a matching criteria when searching for relevant dataset types using file extension. For example, if this preference is activated, a "doc" file extension excludes all types that use "*" as their file extension for relevant types. The default value is false.

preference.name: TIF_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relation that has to be created when an object is pasted under an object of type TIF. The relation specified for this preference will be the default relation that will be created between the source and the target TIF.

preference.name: baselineDryRun
preference.preference_description: Valid values are 0/1. 0 - Do not perform Dry Run of Baseline Creation. 1 - Perform Dry Run of Baseline Creation.

preference.name: Dataset_indexed_properties
preference.preference_description: Specifies the properties to be indexed to the Autonomy database for Dataset object type.

preference.name: TC_FTS_LongString_AND_Operator_Char
preference.preference_description: Defines the value for the "AND" token to separate multiple entries for the keyword search's entry which data type is longstring. Entries are connected with the "AND" operator.

preference.name: TC_FTS_LongString_OR_Operator_Char
preference.preference_description: Defines the value for the "OR" token to separate multiple entries for the keyword search's entry which data type is longstring. Entries are connected with the "OR" operator.

preference.name: TC_FTS_associated_relation_index
preference.preference_description: Activates the Full Text Search (FTS) engine to perform associated index by object relations during indexing. Valid values are: * false: The Full Text Search (FTS) engine will not check object relations to index associated objects. This is default value. * true: The Full Text Search (FTS) engine will check object relations to index associated objects.

preference.name: TC_FTS_indexable_relations
preference.preference_description: Specifies relations that can be detected as index candidates during indexing of the database for the Full Text Search (FTS) capacity.

preference.name: TC_fts_aci_port
preference.preference_description: Specifies the Autonomy Content Infrastructure (ACI) port number. This port is used by the Full Text Search framework to send query commands to the Autonomy server.

preference.name: TC_fts_any_language
preference.preference_description: Enables to return documents in any language for your query rather than only in the query's language. Valid values are true and false (default value).

preference.name: TC_fts_database_name
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the Autonomy database in which Teamcenter database objects are indexed.

preference.name: TC_fts_default_AND_operator
preference.preference_description: Activates the default logical operator of keyword search to "AND". Valid values are: * true: the default logical operator is set to AND. * false: the default logical operator is OR by Autonomy. This is the default value. This is a site preference.

preference.name: TC_fts_enforce_master_language
preference.preference_description: Specifies the language to be used when indexing into the Full Text Search (FTS) database for unlocalized properties. If no value is specified, unlocalized properties are indexed using the site master language. Valid value is one of the following as a single string value: czechUTF8 germanUTF8 englishUTF8 spanishUTF8 frenchUTF8 italianUTF8 japaneseUTF8 koreanUTF8 polishUTF8 portugueseUTF8 russianUTF8 chineseUTF8

preference.name: TC_fts_engine
preference.preference_description: Specifies the search engine used by Teamcenter's Full Text Search framework.

preference.name: TC_fts_fsf_host
preference.preference_description: Specifies the IP address of the host machine running the Autonomy File System Fetch (FSF).

preference.name: TC_fts_fsf_port
preference.preference_description: Specifies the Autonomy File System Fetch (FSF) port number. This port is used by the Full Text Search framework to index document(s) to the Autonomy IDOL server.

preference.name: TC_fts_hierarchical_index_delete
preference.preference_description: Specifies if the Full Text Search (FTS) index and delete operations are hierarchical. For example if the type "Item" is in the preference "TC_fts_indexed_types", its subtypes are valid index/delete types. Valid values are: * true: The subtypes are valid index/delete types. This is default value. * false: The subtypes are not valid index/delete types, and the FTS engine ignores them.

preference.name: TC_fts_host
preference.preference_description: Specifies the IP address of the host machine running the Autonomy Server.

preference.name: TC_fts_index_port
preference.preference_description: Specifies the index port number. This port is used to index documents for the Autonomy Server.

preference.name: TC_fts_indexed_types
preference.preference_description: Specifies types whose objects can be indexed.

preference.name: TC_fts_max_results
preference.preference_description: Specifies the maximum number of results returned by the Full Text Search (FTS) engine.

preference.name: TC_fts_query_port
preference.preference_description: Specifies the query port number. This port is used by the index utility to query index status from the Autonomy server.

preference.name: TC_fts_real_time_indexing
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether objects should be indexed real time into the FTS database. Valid values are true/false.

preference.name: TC_fts_realtime_delete_cache_size
preference.preference_description: Specifies the cache size (number of objects) for real-time Full Text Search (FTS) delete.

preference.name: TC_fts_realtime_index_dt_cache_size
preference.preference_description: Specifies the cache size (number of objects) for real-time Full Text Search (FTS) dataset index. When the value is larger, less autonomy calls are made to generate the indexing, which may remove duplicated objects. If defined too large, objects will be unindexed for a long period of time, which will lead to FTS search needing a relatively long time to flush the cache. The default value is 10.

preference.name: TC_fts_realtime_index_item_cache_size
preference.preference_description: Specifies the cache size (number of objects) for real-time Full Text Search (FTS) item index. When the value is larger, less autonomy calls are made to generate the indexing, which may remove duplicated objects. If defined too large, objects will be unindexed for a long period of time, which will lead to FTS search needing a relatively long time to flush the cache. The default value is 10.

preference.name: TC_fts_result_latest_ItemRevision
preference.preference_description: Activates keyword searches to only return the latest Item Revisions. Valid values are true and false (default value).

preference.name: TC_fts_service_port
preference.preference_description: Specifies the service port number.

preference.name: TC_fts_shared_tmp_dir_autonomy_path
preference.preference_description: Specifies the temporary exchange directory path for the machine where the Autonomy server is running. The user who started the Autonomy server must have write privileges to this directory. The value specified in this preference will override the ones defined in the "TC_fts_shared_tmp_dir_wnt" and "TC_fts_shared_tmp_dir_unix" preferences. A valid value can be a UNC path or a local path, using the "/" as a separator. E.g.: "//myserver/shared", "F:/shared", "/tmp".

preference.name: TC_fts_shared_tmp_dir_unix
preference.preference_description: Specifies the temporary exchange directory for the UNIX machine where the Teamcenter server or Autonomy server are running. The user who started the server must have write privileges to this directory. The separator used in the preference value must be "/", e.g. "/mynetwork/mysite/myfolder"

preference.name: TC_fts_shared_tmp_dir_wnt
preference.preference_description: Specifies the temporary exchange directory for the Windows machine where the Teamcenter server or Autonomy server are running. The user who started the server must have write privileges to this directory. The separator used in the preference value must be "\", e.g. "\\mynetwork\mysite\myfolder".

preference.name: TC_fts_supported_files
preference.preference_description: Specifies types of files that can be indexed. Valid values are file extensions (e.g. ".txt").

preference.name: TC_fts_synonym_search
preference.preference_description: Enables synonyms usage in Search operations. Synonyms are defined in the "tc_synonyms_example.txt" file located under the "idol/content" directory of the FTS installation. Users can add more synonyms or replace it with their own synonym file by changing the "IDOL.cfg" configuration file located in the same directory. Valid values are true and false (default value).

preference.name: TC_fts_use_asso_search
preference.preference_description: Activates the Full Text Search (FTS) searches metadata against associated objects or not. Valid values are: * false: The Full Text Search (FTS) engine will search metadata against main objects. This is default value. * true: The Full Text Search (FTS) engine will search metadata against associated object.

preference.name: TC_fts_use_shared_tmp_dir
preference.preference_description: Specifies if the Autonomy server uses a network-shared folder as a temporary work directory. If the Teamcenter server and the Autonomy server are installed on different machines, this preference must be set to true. Valid values are true and false (default value).

preference.name: TC_fts_windows_autonomy_server
preference.preference_description: Specifies if the Autonomy server is installed on a Windows platform. Valid values are true (default value) and false.

preference.name: TC_saved_query_show_all_fields
preference.preference_description: Enables the More button of the "Search" panel to display all fields. Valid values are true/false.

preference.name: LDAP_admin_dn
preference.preference_description: Defines the name of the LDAP administrator. Value is the Distinguished Name (DN) of an LDAP user who has search and read permissions in the LDAP directory service.

preference.name: LDAP_admin_pw
preference.preference_description: Specifies the password for the LDAP administrator, as defined by the "LDAP_admin_dn" preference.

preference.name: LDAP_cert_db_path
preference.preference_description: Specifies the path to the certificate database. This should be the path to the directory containing the cert7.db file. This preference is ignored if the preference "LDAP_use_ssl" is set to FALSE.

preference.name: LDAP_port_number
preference.preference_description: Defines the port number used when connecting to the LDAP directory server. The value is used in conjunction with the value given by the "LDAP_service_hosts" preference.

preference.name: LDAP_service_hosts
preference.preference_description: Lists the host or hosts that provide an LDAP directory service for this installation. Valid inputs are host names or IP addresses. The value is used in conjunction with preference " LDAP_port_number" to connect with the LDAP directory server.

preference.name: LDAP_use_ssl
preference.preference_description: Specifies if a connection to an LDAP directory uses SSL encryption. Valid values are 'TRUE' or 'FALSE'.

preference.name: LDAP_group_attr_mapping
preference.preference_description: Lists the entries that define a mapping of LDAP object attributes for Teamcenter Group synchronization. Each attribute mapping consists of three strings: an attribute identifier, a mapped LDAP attribute name, and a default value.

preference.name: LDAP_group_base_dn
preference.preference_description: Defines the distinguished name (DN) of one or more nodes in the external LDAP directory where the Group synchronization process should begin. This preference is used to limit the extent of the LDAPSync group search.

preference.name: LDAP_group_object_class
preference.preference_description: Defines the LDAP object class used by a customer to model Teamcenter groups that will be synchronized. If a customer uses multiple classes which all represent Teamcenter groups, this preference should specify the common base class of those classes.

preference.name: LDAP_group_query_filter
preference.preference_description: Specifies a set of conditions which an LDAP object must satisfy in order to be matched as a group object for synchronizing with Teamcenter. The preference is defined in LDAP query filter syntax.

preference.name: LDAP_role_attr_mapping
preference.preference_description: Lists the entries that define a mapping of LDAP object attributes for Teamcenter Role synchronization. Each attribute mapping consists of three strings: an attribute identifier, a mapped LDAP attribute name, and a default value.

preference.name: LDAP_role_object_class
preference.preference_description: Defines the LDAP object class used by a customer to model Teamcenter roles that will be synchronized. If a customer uses multiple classes which all represent Teamcenter roles, this preference should specify the common base class of those classes.

preference.name: LDAP_role_query_filter
preference.preference_description: Specifies a set of conditions which an LDAP object must satisfy in order to be matched as a role object for synchronizing with Teamcenter. The preference is defined in LDAP query filter syntax.

preference.name: LDAP_member_list_attr
preference.preference_description: Defines the LDAP attribute that contains a list of member DNs for this object. This preference is only used if the "LDAP_member_type_attr" preference is set.

preference.name: LDAP_member_type_attr
preference.preference_description: Defines the LDAP attribute that contains membership type (direct or indirect) for this object. This preference is used in conjunction with the "LDAP_member_list_attr" preference. For example, if "LDAP_member_type_attr" is set to 'memberType', then the LDAP object should have an attribute by that name. The LDAP value in 'memberType' will be the string "true" for indirect children or "false" for direct children.

preference.name: LDAP_object_type_attr
preference.preference_description: Defines the LDAP attribute that contains the object type for this object. For example, if "LDAP_object_type_attr" is set to 'objectType', then the LDAP group or role should have an attribute by that name. The LDAP value in 'objectType' will be the string "group" or "role".

preference.name: LDAP_sync_group_flags
preference.preference_description: Specifies the group synchronization setting flags. The supported group synchronization flags are: s synchronize c create u update e externalize

preference.name: LDAP_sync_member_flags
preference.preference_description: Specifies the group member synchronization setting flags. The supported group member synchronization flags are: s synchronize c create d deactivate e externalize

preference.name: LDAP_sync_role_flags
preference.preference_description: Specifies the role synchronization setting flags. The supported role synchronization flags are: s synchronize c create u update e externalize

preference.name: LDAP_sync_user_flags
preference.preference_description: Specifies the user synchronization setting flags. The supported user synchronization flags are: s synchronize c create d deactivate u update e externalize

preference.name: LDAP_attribute_mapping
preference.preference_description: Lists the entries that define a mapping of LDAP object attributes for Teamcenter User synchronization. Each attribute mapping consists of three strings: an attribute identifier, a mapped LDAP attribute name, and a default value.

preference.name: LDAP_base_dn
preference.preference_description: Defines the distinguished name (DN) of one or more nodes in the external LDAP directory where the User and Person synchronization process should begin. This preference is used to limit the extent of the LDAPSync User and Person search.

preference.name: LDAP_ignore_users
preference.preference_description: Lists the Teamcenter user-ids which should not be processed by the LDAPSync utility. This list would normally contain Teamcenter user-ids used for administrative purposes that do not have corresponding entries in the LDAP repository. The LDAPSync utility will always ignore the 'infodba' user.

preference.name: LDAP_person_attr_mapping
preference.preference_description:
Lists the entries that define a mapping of LDAP object attributes for Teamcenter Person synchronization. Each attribute mapping consists of three strings: an attribute identifier, a mapped LDAP attribute name, and a default value.
The generic person attributes are as follows: PA1 Address PA2 City PA3 State PA4 Zip Code PA5 Country PA6 Organization PA7 Employee Number PA8 Internal Mail Code PA9 E-Mail Address PA10 Phone Number

preference.name: LDAP_user_object_class
preference.preference_description: Defines the LDAP object class used by a customer to model Teamcenter users that will be synchronized. If a customer uses multiple classes which all represent Teamcenter users, this preference should specify the common base class of those classes.

preference.name: LDAP_user_query_filter
preference.preference_description: Specifies a set of conditions which an LDAP object must satisfy in order to be matched as a user object for synchronizing with Teamcenter. The preference is defined in LDAP query filter syntax.

category.name: Configuration.Language
category.category_description: Defines parameters for the session langage.

preference.name: TC_language_data_entry
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of locales that should be used by end-user for data entry. Note that there is no enforcement that this is respected. The values given for this preference should be consistent with the encoding of the database instance. Valid values are a 5-letter Java standardized code representing the chosen language. The out-of-the-box values are cs_CZ, de_DE, en_US es_ES, fr_FR, it_IT, ja_JP, ko_KR, pl_PL, pt_BR, ru_RU, zh_CN and zh_TW.

preference.name: TC_language_force_thin_client_locale
preference.preference_description: Forces the Thin client to start with the default language (as defined by the environment variable "TC_language_default") regardless of the language requested in the URL parameter or the languages specified in the browser language preference. Valid values for this site preference are: * true: the Thin client will always start with the default locale. * false: the Thin client will start with the specified language. This is the default value.

preference.name: TC_language_force_thin_client_locale_no_warning
preference.preference_description: Prevents a warning message that the Thin client is being forced to start with the default language. This happens when the preference "TC_language_force_thin_client_locale" is set to true. The default value is false: the warning message is always displayed when the Thin client language is forced. This is a site preference.

preference.name: TC_language_localization_display
preference.preference_description: Enables the visualization of translation information as read only for properties that are localizable. Valid values are true or false (default value).

preference.name: TC_language_localized_property_value_display
preference.preference_description: Specifies the ordered list of languages to use for displaying localized property values. Valid values are a 5-letter Java standardized code representing the chosen language. The out-of-the-box values are cs_CZ, de_DE, en_US es_ES, fr_FR, it_IT, ja_JP, ko_KR, pl_PL, pt_BR, ru_RU, zh_CN and zh_TW. Use the TXTSRV_get_localized_property_value_display_languages ITK function or LanguageInformation::getLanguagesList SOA operation to retrieve the languages to use, since those will carry out the following checks: concatenate the values from the user, group, role, site; retain only the ones supported by the system; if the list is empty, the connection locale is returned.

preference.name: TC_language_localized_property_value_entry
preference.preference_description: Specifies the data entry locale (master locale) of the logged in user. The master locale is the one used by the user to create and edit data in a localized property. A valid value should be one of the values defined in the TC_language_data_entry preference, if this preference is set. It is a 5-letter Java standardized code representing the chosen language. The out-of-the-box values are cs_CZ, de_DE, en_US es_ES, fr_FR, it_IT, ja_JP, ko_KR, pl_PL, pt_BR, ru_RU, zh_CN and zh_TW. Use the TXTSRV_get_localized_property_value_entry_language ITK function or LanguageInformation::getLanguagesList SOA operation to retrieve the languages to use, since those will carry out the following checks: concatenate all the preference values from user, group, role and site, append the values from the TC_language_data_entry preference, and append the connection locale; retain only the values that are supported by the system and that are mentioned in the TC_language_data_entry preference; return the first value of that list.

preference.name: TC_language_no_encoding_discrepancy_warning_message
preference.preference_description: Prevents the display of the warning message regarding discrepancy between the Teamcenter server encoding and the database encoding. The default value is false: the warning message is always displayed.

preference.name: TC_language_search
preference.preference_description:
Specifies the locale used in doing search operations. The search criteria specified by the user is assumed to be in this locale. If the value is not set, the search locale defaults to the client locale.
Caution: If localization for Classification is enabled, selecting the search language in the attribute dictionary in the Classification Administration application changes the value of the TC_language_search preference interactively for all Teamcenter applications.
Warning: Do not change the protection scope of this preference. The system selectively applies this preference for a variety of applications, and changing the scope could have unintended and undesirable consequences.
Valid values are codes representing languages (including the ones listed in environemnt variable TC_language_default).

preference.name: TC_no_obsolete_message
preference.preference_description: Suppresses the obsolete or deprecated messages coming from the Teamcenter server process which are printed on its console window. The default value is false (messages are printed) and out-of-the-box it can be set through an environment variable of the same name.

preference.name: license_warning_level
preference.preference_description: Defines a threshold of available Teamcenter feature licenses. The administrator is warned when creating or modifying a user if the number of available licenses is less than or equal to this value.

preference.name: TC_external_Requirements_proxy_props_external
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: TC_external_Requirements_proxy_props_internal
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: TC_external_application_names
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: TC_external_application_types
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: TC_external_default_launch_ui
preference.preference_description: Specifies the User Interface to be used for launching remote TC links. Valid values are dynamic/rich/thin. dynamic - Specifying this would launch the remote TC link based on the current UI. Rich Client would launch the remote TC link in Rich Client. Similarly, Thin Client would launch the remote TC link in Thin Client. rich - Specifying this would invoke Rich Client for launching remote TC links. thin - Specifying this would invoke Thin Client for launching remote TC links.

preference.name: TC_external_local_app_guid
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: TC_external_proxiable_objects
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: Mail_internal_mail_activated
preference.preference_description: Defines if Teamcenter internal mail functionality is available when using the "notify" Workflow Handler. Valid values are true or false (default). When the value is false, Teamcenter internal mail will not be sent to the user's Teamcenter mailbox. This is a site preference.

preference.name: Mail_server_charset
preference.preference_description: Specifies the Teamcenter mail server character set used to send OS mail.

preference.name: Mail_server_name
preference.preference_description: Information about the mail gateway server. This is a site preference. It can be set to either a mail server name or to a numeric IP address. The mail server name should be a machine running a send mail daemon. Leaving it as "your mail server machine" while the "Mail_OSMail_activated" preference is true may give you errors telling you to set this preference if you try to use the "Send" command.

preference.name: Folder_mail_properties
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: Mail_OSMail_activated
preference.preference_description: Defines if the OS Mail functionality is available. This is a site preference. Valid values are true (default) or false. When the value is false, the value given to preference "Mail_server_name" is not taken into account.

preference.name: Mail_OS_from_address
preference.preference_description: Defines a "From" e-mail address for OS notification e-mails. Valid vallues are: * a valid email address: this value appears in the e-mail header "From" line. * an empty value: the "From" email address is taken from the sender's Person definition. This is the default value.

preference.name: Mail_send_file_attachments_activated
preference.preference_description: Activates the sending of Dataset attachments as normal e-mail file attachments, when the Envelope functionality is sending messages directly to an e-mail address instead of a Teamcenter user. Valid values are: * true: external recipients of e-mails will receive Dataset files as attachments, instead of Teamcenter client links to the Envelope. Furthermore, the recipient is able to open the attached files without needing a Teamcenter login or privileges. Therefore, consider site security guidelines before setting this preference to true. This is the default value. * false: external recipients of e-mails receive only Teamcenter client links to the attached Datasets, and not the actual files. When the mail is sent to a Teamcenter user, this preference has no impact, and the user will always receive links to the Envelope object.

preference.name: Mail_server_port
preference.preference_description: Sets the port number used by the SMTP mail server to send OS mail. This is a site preference. The default value is 25.

preference.name: TC_mail_interval
preference.preference_description: Indicates default value (in minutes) for Teamcenter to check for new mail every X minutes.

preference.name: TC_use_tc_alias_in_pa8
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the longer (>32) email id in pa8 attribute is to be used or not. Valid values are ON/OFF. ON - Users can specify alias in the pa8 attribute of person. This alias is intended to contain longer email ID (>32) that cannot be directly specified in the pa8 attribute. It should be noted however that if this alias matches the external alias (external to Teamcenter and specific to the organisation) then the pa8 attribute will use the internal alias to send the notifications.

preference.name: PASSWORD_minimum_alpha
preference.preference_description: Specifies the minimum number of alpha characters that need to be included in the password. 0 indicates no minimum.

preference.name: PASSWORD_minimum_characters
preference.preference_description: Specifies the minimum length for a new password. 0 indicates no minimum

preference.name: PASSWORD_minimum_digits
preference.preference_description: Specifies the minimum number of digits that need to be included in the password. 0 indicates no minimum.

preference.name: PASSWORD_minimum_special_chars
preference.preference_description: Specifies the minimum number of characters from PASSWORD_special_characters that need to be included in the password. 0 indicates no minimum.

preference.name: PASSWORD_mixed_case_required
preference.preference_description: Specifies if mixed case required in a password. Valid values are true/false.

preference.name: CRF_CUSTOM_REPORT_id_prefix
preference.preference_description: Specifies the ID prefix used for creation of Custom Report objects. This is a site preference.

preference.name: CRF_ITEM_REPORT_id_prefix
preference.preference_description: Specifies the ID prefix used for creation of Item Report objects. This is a site preference.

preference.name: CRF_SUMMARY_REPORT_id_prefix
preference.preference_description: Specifies the ID prefix used for creation of Summary Report objects. This is a site preference.

preference.name: Crf_Report_Excel_Use_OOXML
preference.preference_description: Forces the report builder to generate Excel reports using Office Open XML (OOXML) format. The default value is false (the Excel reports are generated using the single spreadsheet xml format).

preference.name: Crf_Report_latest_data
preference.preference_description: Activates the export of refreshed objects that are reported by the report builder from the Generate Report command. The default value is false (the objects are not refreshed before export).

preference.name: Crf_Report_objects_limit
preference.preference_description: Controls the maximum number of objects that can be reported by the report builder.

preference.name: Crf_report_pff_delimit
preference.preference_description: Specifies the delimiter used to delimite the report ID/PFF (Property Finder Formatter) name pair.

preference.name: Crf_report_pff_map
preference.preference_description: Stores the report builder reports ID/PFF (Property Finder Formatter) name pair. Values are in the format "<report_ID><Delimiter><PFF_name>" (e.g. "TC_9_00_SUM_RPT_0003#ItemOwnership"). The delimiter is defined by the preference "Crf_report_pff_delimit".

preference.name: Crf_report_use_pff_rp
preference.preference_description: Activates report builder reports to support using PFF (Property Finder Formatter). The default value is false (report builder reports do not support PFF).

preference.name: Default_Crf_OfficeTemplate_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relationship between the report definition and the associated Microsoft Office template.

preference.name: Enable_ReportBuilder_Reports_By_Source
preference.preference_description: Controls the list of reports displayed in the "Tools->Reports->Report Builder Reports" menu.

preference.name: Enable_ReportDesigner_Reports
preference.preference_description: Controls generation of legacy reports. Default value is false.
