preference.name: TC_CRF_TIE_Integration
preference.preference_description: Sets the usage of TIE as an export format for CRF Reports. Valid values are: TRUE: chooses TCXML as the export format. FALSE: chooses PLMXML as the export format. This is the default value. This is a site preference.

preference.name: TC_CRF_overwrite_existing_dataset_content
preference.preference_description: Specifies if a newly generated report replaces the contents of the specified dataset. Default value is true (replace).

preference.name: TC_RA_server_parameters
preference.preference_description: Specifies the configuration for eQube by allowing the system administrator to change the Application server Protocol, Host, Port, eQube installation location and eQube servlet name. By default, the following rules are provided: Protocol:http, Host:localhost, Port:80, Context:eQube, ServletName:eQubeServlet, ServiceDashboard:action=Dashboard. Valid values for Protocol are http or https.

preference.name: Valid_ReportBuilder_Sources
preference.preference_description: List of all valid sources available to the Common Reporting Framework(CRF) reporting engine.

preference.name: QRY_latest_ItemRevision_limit
preference.preference_description: Controls the maximum number of objects that can be loaded for Revision check to retrieve the latest Item Revision of the search results. The default value is 3000. If defined too large, more memory is required to load all objects and process the Revision check.

preference.name: Search_result_load_all_limit
preference.preference_description: Determines the maximum number of found objects for "Load All" operation in "Search Result" view. Setting a larger value will have performance impact when clicking "Load All" button in "Search Result" view.

preference.name: TC_QRY_display_latest_dataset_only
preference.preference_description: Enables the display of only the latest version of dataset objects in results of queries with search class as super class of Dataset or its descendant classes (e.g. queries with search class as WorkspaceObject). Valid values are: 0 - to display all versions of the dataset (default value). 1 - to display only the latest version of dataset objects.

preference.name: MSS_set_display_limit
preference.preference_description: Controls the number of saved searches shared by others to be displayed in the "My saved searches" panel. Setting a larger value will have performance impact at login time. The recommended value is 25.

preference.name: Open_previous_open_search
preference.preference_description: Activates the display of previous search results when closing current search results in the Search Result view. Valid values are: * false: previous search results will not be displayed. * true: previous search results will be displayed. This is the default value.

preference.name: QRYColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of default (Favorite) saved queries used for both Teamcenter Rich/Thin clients. The values of this preference should be the localized query names.

preference.name: QRY_allow_modification_before_run_mss
preference.preference_description: Allows modification of search criteria before running query from "My Saved Search". The default value is false (modifications are not allowed).

preference.name: QRY_lov_show_inactive_user_projects
preference.preference_description: Activates the display of inactive projects in the LOV "Fnd0UserProjectsLOV" (User Projects List Of Values) in the Search panel of the rich and thin clients. The default value is false.

preference.name: TC_QRY_search_by_rev_rule
preference.preference_description: Specifies the Revision Rule used for the "Latest Item Revision(s)" query. Acceptable values are all Revision Rules defined in the database (e.g. "Latest Working"). Note that values are case sensitive.

preference.name: TC_QRY_search_result_display_mode
preference.preference_description: Specifies the search result display mode. Valid values are: * 1: The total number of found objects is not displayed. This is the default value. * 2: The total number of found objects only accounts for objects for which the user has access privileges.

preference.name: ContentManagement_feature_installed
preference.preference_description: Indicates that Content Management feature is installed. Do not modify this preference manually.

preference.name: ContentManagerShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths for the Publication Structure shown Columns (left-to-right order).

preference.name: CUSTOM_NOTES_REV_RULE
preference.preference_description: Specifies the internal name of the revision rule used when objects of type "Fnd0ListsCustomNotes" are associated to an Item or an Item Revision through the "Fnd0ListsParamReqments" relation. The value should match the internal name of one of the revision rules defined in the Structure Manager application. If the value is set to "Imprecise", the "Fnd0ListsCustomNotes" object itself is associated, not any of its revisions. The default value is "Imprecise".

preference.name: CrossProbing_AllowedRelationTypes
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relation names displayed in the "Allowed Relations" list of the "Cross Probing" option page. These relations can then be selected by the end-user so that to be part of the cross probing search mechanism.

preference.name: CrossProbing_RelationDepthTraversal
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relation traversal depth that will be used in cross probing search mechanism. Valid values are: * -1: Search All * Any integer number other than 0: The requested relation traversal depth. The default value is 1.

preference.name: CrossProbing_RelationTraversalType
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relation traversal type that will be used in cross probing search mechanism. Valid values are: * 1: Find Source(s). * 2: Find Target(s). * 0: Both. This is the default value.

preference.name: CrossProbing_SelectedRelationTypes
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relation names that are part of the cross probing search mechanism. These relations are used by the "Find In" operation in order to find related nodes in open structures.

preference.name: PARAM_REQ_REV_RULE
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the revision rule used when objects of type "Fnd0ParamReqment" are associated to an Item or an Item Revision through the "Fnd0ListsParamReqments" relation. The value should match the name of one of the revision rules defined in the Structure Manager application. If the value is set to "Imprecise", the "Fnd0ParamReqment" object itself is associated, not any of its revisions. The default value is "Imprecise".

preference.name: REQ_ExportToExcel_add_level_column
preference.preference_description: Determines the behavior of structure export to Excel from the Requirement Management application, when a structure exceeds 8 levels (which is the MS Excel outlining feature limit). If the selected structure exceeds that level and that preference is set to true, it is exported as a flat list with the "Level" column added. If the selected structure exceeds that level and that preference is set to false, it is exported as a flat list.

preference.name: REQ_checkout_objects_before_export
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default selection of the "check-out objects before export" option in the "Export to Word" command in the Systems Engineering application. Valid values are: * default: the user will be able to toggle the checkbox selection * default_hide: the checkbox will be unchecked and disabled. * default_checkout: the checkbox will be checked and disabled. This is the default value.

preference.name: TcAllowedImportExportPeakSpecObject
preference.preference_description: Specifies the allowed object types that can be used as the top line for importing or exporting a document in the Systems Engineering application. The format for valid values are "object_internal_type_name:true" or "object_internal_type_name:false". If the value is "true", the specified type and its sub-types are considered as top lines for import/export purposes. If the value is "false", only the specified type (and not its sub-types) are considered.

preference.name: TraceReportTable_ColumnPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of columns to be displayed for defining and complying traceability report.

preference.name: TraceReportTable_ColumnWidthPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths of the columns for the column names as defined in TraceReportTable_ColumnPreferences preference.

preference.name: TraceReport_Default_Expansion_Level
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default level of expansion for trace report tree. If the traceability report is also showing trace link objects, the depth of the report will be multiplied by 2. For example, if the preference value is 3 and the traceability report will contain 6-level deep trace report for trace links. For single-object trace reports, the tree is expanded to the mentioned level. For multiple-objects trace reports, each tree node is expanded to the specified level in each root. The default value is 2. Positive integer value greater than 0 are valid values for this preference.

preference.name: TraceReport_Default_Sort_Property
preference.preference_description: Specifies default name of property to sort Trace report. This sort property should be persists in current Trace report column configuration.

preference.name: TraceReport_Default_TraceLink_Type
preference.preference_description: Specifies the type of Trace Link created by default.

preference.name: TraceReport_Filter_Available_Object_Types
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of object types to be shown as "Available" in the "Trace Report Filter Criteria" dialog. From this list, users can select the object types to be shown in traceability report.

preference.name: TraceReport_Filter_Available_TraceLink_Types
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of Trace Link types to be shown as "Available" in the "Trace Report Filter Criteria" dialog. From this list, users can select the Trace Link types to be shown in traceability report.

preference.name: Default_Transient_Volume_Id
preference.preference_description: Defines the transient volume identifier of an FMS transient volume on the Corporate server. This site preference will be set by the installer.

preference.name: TC_relation_required_on_export
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of default relations required for "export" operation.

preference.name: TC_relation_required_on_transfer
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of default relations required for "transfer of ownership" operation.

preference.name: IDSM_Compression
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the built-in compression feature is to be enabled for Remote Import/Export. Valid values are TRUE/FALSE. If this preference is enabled at a site, the user has to enable even the preference IDSM_Compression_Type. This is a site preference.

preference.name: IDSM_Compression_Type
preference.preference_description: Specifies the compression type to be used. Valid value is "InfoZip". This is a site preference.

preference.name: IDSM_do_not_resend_up_to_date_file
preference.preference_description:
Specifies whether Teamcenter must prevent the retransmission of a replicated file that is still current at the time an attempt to re-import or re-send the file is made. Set this preference value to TRUE to prevent retransmission. This preference applies whether or not transfer of site ownership is involved. If no value is set for the preference,Teamcenter always retransmits the files.
WARNING:If this preference value is set to TRUE at a site, instruct the site's users NOT to delete replicas if they intend to re-import the object. This can cause new metadata but without the required file. If a missing file occurs, temporarily disable this preference, re-import the dataset, and then re-enable the preference.

preference.name: IDSM_dsa_sites_permitted_to_push_admin_data
preference.preference_description: Specifies a list of site names that are authorized to send system administration data to this site via Distributed System Administration (DSA) "distribute" functionality. If this preference is not defined, no remote site can send system administration data to this site. This is a site preference.

preference.name: IDSM_exclude_unpublished_components
preference.preference_description: When performing a remote import of an assembly via Multi-Site, by default all components will be included regardless of whether the component item has been published or not. Specifying a value "TRUE" will prevent unpublished components from getting included. This is a site preference.

preference.name: IDSM_ft_buffer_kb
preference.preference_description: Specifies the buffer size to be used by Multi-Site high performance file transfer option. Refer to the documentation for calculation of optimal value. Note that the default value is 64 (64 kilobytes). This is a site preference.

preference.name: IDSM_ft_client_timeout
preference.preference_description: Specifies the timeout value used by socket commands for high performance file transfer. Default value is 30. This is a site preference.

preference.name: IDSM_ft_get_port_number_from_services
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the port number is to be retrieved from system32/drivers/etc/services file. The default service name is idsmft in tcp mode. Service name can be selected with the IDSM_FT_SERVICE_NAME environment variable. This setting overrides the IDSM_ft_port_number preference. Default value is FALSE. This is a site preference.

preference.name: IDSM_ft_port_number
preference.preference_description: Specifies the IP port number which high performance file transfer will use. Recommended to specify the port in the range of 1024 to 49151. This port number should not conflict with the established system services. Check with your network administrator. Default port number is 47953. This is a site preference.

preference.name: IDSM_ft_server_timeout
preference.preference_description: Specifies the timeout value used by socket commands for high performance file transfer. Default value is 30. This is a site preference.

preference.name: IDSM_ft_use_rpc_mode
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the original RPC file transfer method is to be used (TRUE/FALSE). Default value is FALSE. This is a site preference.

preference.name: IDSM_global_dsa_set_local_volume_on_import
preference.preference_description: Defines the default local volumes used for initial import by the importing site of Users and Groups. Valid values follow the format "Group name:Volume name". E.g. "Engineering:DrawingVol".

preference.name: IDSM_global_dsa_set_volume_on_import
preference.preference_description: Defines the default volumes used for initial import by the importing site of Users and Groups. Valid values follow the format "Group name:Volume name". E.g. "Engineering:DrawingVol".

preference.name: IDSM_global_dsa_sites_permitted_to_push_admin_data
preference.preference_description: Defines the remote sites that are permitted to use Global organization to push organization data to the local site. This enforces site-level security: if a remote site is not defined in this preference, that site cannot perform Global organization functions that affect the local site.

preference.name: IDSM_permitted_checkout_sites
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of ONLY sites (by names as specified in the IDSM database) which the IDSM will allow to perform remote Check-Out of objects currently owned by the site serviced by the IDSM. If not defined, no remote site will be able to perform remote Check-Out of objects. This is a site preference.

preference.name: IDSM_permitted_sites
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of ONLY sites (by names as specified in the IDSM database) which the IDSM will serve. This is a site preference.

preference.name: IDSM_permitted_transfer_sites
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of ONLY sites (by names as specified in the IDSM database) which the IDSM will allow to transfer ownership of objects currently owned by the site serviced by the IDSM. If not defined, no remote site will be able to transfer ownership of objects. This is a site preference.

preference.name: IDSM_proxy_server_type
preference.preference_description: Sets up an IDSM proxy. Must be defined only at the Proxy server node. Defaults to Relay.

preference.name: IDSM_restricted_sites
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of sites (by names as specified in the IDSM database) to which the IDSM will reject service. This is a site preference.

preference.name: ITEM_id_allow_if_registry_down
preference.preference_description: By default, Item creation will fail if the registry server is unavailable. Setting this to TRUE will allow the Item to be created even when the registry is unavailable. This is a site preference.

preference.name: ITEM_id_always_register_on_creation
preference.preference_description: Indicates if newly created Items will have their item ids automatically registered with the registry server (TRUE/FALSE). Default value is FALSE. This is a site preference.

preference.name: ITEM_id_registry
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the Central Item Id Registry is activated for this site (TRUE/FALSE). If this is set to FALSE, all ITEM_id_xxx preferences are ignored). This is a site preference.

preference.name: ITEM_id_registry_site
preference.preference_description: Specifies the site that will serve as the registry server. This must be set if ITEM_id_registry is set to TRUE. The registry site must be running a valid ODS server process instance. A single ODS server process can function as both an ODS server and a Registry server. An ODS server process can also be dedicated to being a Registry server. This is a site preference.

preference.name: ITEM_id_unregister_on_delete
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the item ids are to be automatically unregistered from the registry server when their Item is deleted (TRUE/FALSE). Default value is FALSE. This is a site preference.

preference.name: ODS_max_query_results
preference.preference_description: Specifies the maximum number of results returned by the Object Directory Services (ODS) to a client for a single remote query. When specified, the remaining results are not returned. When the value is not defined or less than 1, the number of returned results is unlimited. This is a site preference.

preference.name: ODS_multiprocess_idle_subprocess_timeout
preference.preference_description: A subprocess idle timeout for the set of subprocesses above the minimum, up to the maximum, which are created "on demand" based on the number of concurrent outstanding client requests. The timeout is specified in minutes and defaults to 10. Any subprocess in this "on demand" set which is idle for this period of time will be taken out of service and terminated. This is a site preference.

preference.name: ODS_multiprocess_initial_subprocess_count
preference.preference_description: Specifies the minimum number of ODS subprocesses for multiprocess ODS mode. Default value is set to 5. This is a site preference.

preference.name: ODS_multiprocess_max_subprocess_count
preference.preference_description: Specifies the maximum number of ODS subprocesses for multiprocess ODS mode. Default value is set to 10. This is a site preference.

preference.name: ODS_multiprocess_mode
preference.preference_description: Indicates if ODS process is to be run in a multiprocess mode (TRUE/FALSE). This is a site preference.

preference.name: ODS_permitted_sites
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of sites (by names as specified in the ODS database) which the ODS will serve. This is a site preference.

preference.name: ODS_proxy_server_type
preference.preference_description: Sets up an ODS proxy and must be defined only at the Proxy server node. Defaults to Relay.

preference.name: ODS_publication_sites
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of ODS capable site names to be used when publishing to multiple sites. This is a site preference.

preference.name: ODS_restricted_sites
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of sites (by names as specified in the ODS database) to which the ODS will reject service. This is a site preference.

preference.name: ODS_searchable_sites
preference.preference_description: Specifies the ODS sites that Teamcenter searches for published remote objects during a remote search. The sites set in this preference are listed in the Shown column for the ODS Searchable Sites section in the Options dialog box. Add or remove values from Shown column to set the values at the user location and override the site location setting. Restrictions: *Values that appear in ODS_searchable_sites site preference are mutually exclusive from the values in ODS_searchable_sites_excluded site preference. *Values that appear in ODS_searchable_sites user preference are mutually exclusive from the values in ODS_searchable_sites_excluded user preference. Valid values are: *Accepts one or more strings as values, each string must be a valid Teamcenter site name as defined in the Organization application.

preference.name: ODS_searchable_sites_excluded
preference.preference_description: Specifies the sites that Teamcenter does not include in searches for published remote objects during a remote search. The sites set in this preference are listed in the Shown column for the ODS Searchable Sites Excluded section in the Options dialog box. Add or remove values from Shown column to set the values at the user location and override the site location setting. Restrictions: *Values that appear in ODS_searchable_sites_excluded site preference are mutually exclusive from the values in ODS_searchable_sites site preference. *Values that appear in ODS_searchable_sites_excluded user preference are mutually exclusive from the values in ODS_searchable_sites user preference. Valid values are: *Accepts one or more strings as values, each string must be a valid Teamcenter site name as defined in the Organization application.

preference.name: ODS_site
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default ODS site. This is a site preference.

preference.name: ODS_suppress_pubrec_if_no_access
preference.preference_description: This is valid only at an ODS site. Valid values are TRUE/FALSE. TRUE - Remote sites will not be aware of any Publication Record which they have no access to. Without this, users at remote sites will see "ACCESS DENIED" for any Publication Record which they have no access to. This is a site preference.

preference.name: TC_EMAIL_AFTER_BACKGROUND_REMOTE_IMPORT
preference.preference_description: Specifies if email notification is to be sent on the results of all background remote import operations (TRUE/FALSE). This is a user level preference.

preference.name: TC_Populate_FSC_Server_Targets
preference.preference_description: Defines, from an importing site point of view, if the exporting site should populate the files to the specific FSC server target (cache) during a "Multi-Site on line import/export" operation. This preference can be left unset to pick up the default FSC populate targets. This preference does not apply to GMS.

preference.name: TC_always_exclude_dataset_files_on_export
preference.preference_description: Defines, from an importing site point of view, if the exporting site should exclude dataset files during a "Multi-Site off line import/export" operation. This preference can be left unset. When set to "true", the exporting site will be forced to exclude named reference files. This preference does not apply to GMS.

preference.name: TC_background_object_export_dir
preference.preference_description: Specifies the directories where background export (from Teamcenter Rich Client) will create export directories. If the preference is not defined, the default is /tmp directory. This is a site preference.

preference.name: TC_check_remote_user_priv_from_sites
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of ONLY sites (by names as specified in the IDSM database), for the users of which the IDSM will perform extra privilege checks.If not defined, for no remote site's users extra privilege check will be done at the IDSM site. This is a site preference.

preference.name: TC_directly_transferable_classes
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of classes that can be directly exported with transfer of ownership. If a class is not in this list, it may still be transferable but only as part of transferring site ownership of an item. If the Item is on the list, ItemRevision is automatically considered as part of the list. Use this to prevent remote users from transferring site ownership of an item attachment without transferring the item itself. If this is not defined, all classes are considered directly transferable. This is a site preference.

preference.name: TC_disallowed_replica_relations
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of relation types that cannot be used for attaching objects to a replica item or revision. The only allowable values are the ones given in the sample below. This applied only when attaching objects to a replica obtained from another site. Objects that are already attached to the master copy when the replica was obtained are not subject to these restrictions. Allowed values are IMAN_manifestation, IMAN_UG_altrep and IMAN_reference.

preference.name: TC_do_not_define_sites_on_import
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of sites connected to the hub site as external and internal sites, which will be unknown to one another. Sites not specified in this site preference at the hub location are known to one another, which is not recommended.

preference.name: TC_follow_ownership_chain_max_site_count
preference.preference_description: Defines the maximum hops the system should take when following trails to find ownership of objects while performing an "On demand synchronization" operation. If not set, the default is a big number that sets no limit. This is a site preference.

preference.name: TC_force_remote_sites_exclude_files
preference.preference_description: Defines, from an importing site point of view, if the exporting site should exclude dataset files during a "Multi-Site on line import/export" operation. This preference can be left unset. When set to "true", the exporting site will be forced to exclude named reference files. This preference does not apply to GMS.

preference.name: TC_hub_groups
preference.preference_description: Modifies the traditional behaviour of Hub replication and publication by assigning Hub clients into Hub groups (not related to Teamcenter groups). For sites in the same Hub group, the Hub will re-direct replication requests so that the sites will directly replicate from each other instead of from the Hub. A site can be in more than one Hub group. NOTE: The Hub site itself should NOT be in the list. Example: CompanyA:hub_group1, CompanyB:hub_group1, etc.

preference.name: TC_identify_plmxml_import_dataset
preference.preference_description: Indicates the Dataset type, Relation name and Named Reference combination to identity Dataset objects with PLM XML files for synchronization of listed Item Revisions. The format is "Relation_name:Dataset_type:Named_Reference". This is a site preference.

preference.name: TC_idsm_proxy_server_site_table
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of sites that are allowed to access an IDSM proxy server. This is valid only at the Proxy server node and only when IDSM_proxy_server_type=Relay. Format is <Site ID>:<Node Name>. Example: 123456789:sun_node1 or 123456789:111.222.33.444.

preference.name: TC_ods_proxy_server_site_table
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of sites that are allowed to access an ODS proxy server. This is valid only at the Proxy server node and only when ODS_proxy_server_type=Relay. Format is <Site ID>:<Node Name>. Example: 123456789:sun_node1 or 123456789:111.222.33.444.

preference.name: TC_on_demand_sync_broadcast_mode
preference.preference_description: Turns on the broadcasting mode during a "synchronize on demand" operation. If not set, the functionality is turned on. This is a site preference.

preference.name: TC_org_export
preference.preference_description: Defines the operation type used by the rich client during a "Remote export" operation for Organization objects. The value is to be set by the code, and application users are not to manually change it. Valid values are: * 0: the operation type is set to OBJIO_TC_org_export_reset. This is the default value. * 1: the operation type is set to ALL_ROLES_DEFAULT_GROUP * 2: the operation type is set to ALL_ROLES_ALL_GROUPS * 3: the operation type is set to DEFAULT_GROUP_EXPORT * 4: the operation type is set to CUSTOM_GROUP_EXPORT * 5: the operation type is set to ROLE_IN_GROUP * 6: the operation type is set to SINGLE_ROLE * 7: the operation type is set to PERSON * 8: the operation type is set to OBJIO_RAC_ORG_EXPORT

preference.name: TC_plmxml_sync_dataset
preference.preference_description: Indicates the Dataset type, Relation name and Named Reference combination to create or update Dataset objects with PLM XML files for synchronization. The format is "Relation_name:Dataset_type:Named_Reference". This is a site preference.

preference.name: TC_post_export_script
preference.preference_description: Specifies a script that will be executed right after local export is performed. This includes either interactive object export, item_export or any ITK program that exports objects via OBJIO functions. This excludes remote import operations. The full path name of the script should be given. If only the script name is given, the script will be assumed to be in the TC_BIN directory. The sample script standard_post_export_script is provided with COTS Teamcenter. It can be used as it is or it can serve as a sample for a customer written script. This is a site preference.

preference.name: TC_pre_import_script
preference.preference_description: Specifies a script that will be executed right before local import is performed. This includes either interactive object import, item_import or any ITK program that imports objects via OBJIO functions. This excludes remote import operations. The full path name of the script should be given. If only the script name is given, the script will be assumed to be in the TC_BIN directory. The sample script standard_pre_import_script is provided with COTS Teamcenter. It can be used as it is or it can serve as a sample for a customer written script. This is a site preference.

preference.name: TC_publish_item_or_itemrev
preference.preference_description: Defines the publication behavior for Item Revision objects. Valid values are: 1 - only the Item Revision object is published. This is the default value. 2 - only the parent Item of the Item Revision object is published. 3 - both the Item Revision and its parent Item are published.

preference.name: TC_publishable_classes
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of classes that can be published to the ODS. If only the value NONE is set, then publishing will not be permitted from the site. Other multi-site functionality will still be allowed. This is a site preference.

preference.name: TC_replica_volume
preference.preference_description: Specifies the volumes where the imported files will be directed to. This list can contain either volume names or special values like "OWNING_USER_DEFAULT_VOLUME" or "OWNING_GROUP_DEFAULT_VOLUME". The order of the values in the list determines the precedence of use. The first value found to be usable in selecting an ImanVolume for a given ImanFile being imported will be used. For the hardcoded volume names, a check will be done to see if the named volume is usable by the logged in user. OWNING_USER_DEFAULT_VOLUME - Tries to use the default volume of the owning user of the ImanFile being imported and will own the ImanFile after import. The volume must also be usable by the logged in user. OWNING_GROUP_DEFAULT_VOLUME - Tries to use the default volume of the owning group of the ImanFile being imported and will own the ImanFile after import. The volume must also be usable by the logged in user. When pushing the data to a remote site, the logged in user doing the import will be the user under which the IDSM server process logs in. So this user would need to have the access to the volumes involved. This is a site preference.

preference.name: TC_retain_group_on_import
preference.preference_description: When importing an object into a site, the replica's owning group will be set to the importing user's group if both original user AND group are not defined locally. If you wish to preserve the replica's group ownership even if the original owning user is not defined locally but the group is defined in the local database, then set the following preference to TRUE. Valid values are TRUE/FALSE. This is a site preference.

preference.name: TC_secondary_revision_selector
preference.preference_description: Defines the fallback value of revision selector for secondary objects during an Export operation. If there is no revision satisfying the user-selected revision selector for secondary objects, this revision selector is applied instead during an Export operation. Valid values are: 0 for 'Latest Revision'. 1 for 'Latest Working' . 2 for 'Latest Released'. 3 for 'Latest Working\Any Released Status'. This is a site preference.

preference.name: TC_sst_record_relation_primary
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of valid primary object types for the relation TC_sst_record. Format is <Relation Name>_relation_primary=List of valid primary object types.

preference.name: TC_stub_dataset_files_after_ownership_transfer
preference.preference_description: Defines if the exporting site should stub the replica named references(Imanfile objects) and purge the files from the volume during a "Multi-Site on line import/export with transfer of ownership" operation. This preference can be left unset. When set to "true",the exporting site will stub the named references and purge the files from the volume. This preference does not apply to GMS.

preference.name: TC_transfer_area
preference.preference_description: Specifies the location for client/server staging directories for Multi-site Import/Export. If the list contains multiple values, Teamcenter will use the first value which is valid for the platform. This is a site preference.

preference.name: TC_truncate_file_name
preference.preference_description: Indicates if truncation of original file name is necessary. Valid values are TRUE/FALSE. TRUE - Truncate the original file name to the length of 30. FALSE - Do not truncate the original file name to the length of 30. This is implemented mainly for Multi-Site Collaboration to transport data between releases. It should only be set to FALSE if all sites have been moved up to v7.0. This is a site preference only.

preference.name: TC_validate_stub_tickets
preference.preference_description: This preference when set to "true", validates the stub tickets. If invalid, a new stub ticket is generated from whichever site or location the associated file has been transferred. This does not apply to GMS.

preference.name: Tc_export_pfmember_replica
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the part family member replicas present in the assemblies can be exported to sites other than the owning site when transferring assemblies with the include BOM option (TRUE/FALSE). This is a site preference.

preference.name: Tc_preserve_replica_pfmember_ownership
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the NX part family members created at a site based on a replica NX part family template should be owned by the owning site of the template (TRUE/FALSE). This is a site preference.

preference.name: Tc_publish_pfdata_with_assemblies
preference.preference_description:
Determines how part family data is published when publishing assembly Items with the "include BOM" option. The value can also be set through the NX Part Families page in the "Edit/Options" command.
Valid values are: * Members: Publishes part family member components in the assembly. * Templates: Publishes part family templates rather than the part family member components in the assembly. * Both: Publishes both part family member components and part family templates in the assembly. * None: Publishes neither part family member components nor part family templates in the assembly. This is the default value.

preference.name: Tc_publish_pfmembers_with_pftemplate
preference.preference_description:
Activates the publication of related part family member items when publishing part family template Items. The value can also be set through the NX Part Families page in the "Edit/Options" command.
Valid values are: * true: Publishes the corresponding part family member Items. * false: Does not publish the corresponding part family member Items. This is the default value.

preference.name: Tc_publish_pftemplate_with_pfmember
preference.preference_description:
Activates the publication of corresponding part family templates when publishing part family member Items. The value can also be set through the NX Part Families page in the "Edit/Options" command.
Valid values are: * true: Publishes the corresponding part family templates. * false: Does not publish the corresponding part family templates. This is the default value.

preference.name: IMAN_STEP_GIVE_DEBUG
preference.preference_description: Turns on/off the debug logging for STEP. Default value is set to FALSE. Valid values are TRUE and FALSE.

preference.name: STEP_DMI_markup
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: STEP_FILETYPE_2_DATATYPE
preference.preference_description: Finds the dataset type based on the extension for STEP import.

preference.name: STEP_approved_status
preference.preference_description: Release Statuses that need to be interpreted as "approved".

preference.name: STEP_cad_filename_pref
preference.preference_description: Indicates the mapping between STEP document types and Teamcenter datasettype. Maps cad file in STEP to UGMASTER datasettype in Teamcenter.

preference.name: STEP_default_datasettype
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default datasettype to STEP import a product as.

preference.name: STEP_default_item_type
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default Item Type to STEP import a product as.

preference.name: STEP_design_specification_pref
preference.preference_description: Indicates the mapping between STEP document types and Teamcenter datasettype. Maps design specification in STEP to Text datasettype in Teamcenter.

preference.name: STEP_drawing_pref
preference.preference_description: Indicates the mapping between STEP document types and Teamcenter datasettype. Maps drawing in STEP to UGPART datasettype in Teamcenter.

preference.name: STEP_existing_data
preference.preference_description: Configures the behavior for item id collisions. Valid values are: FAIL_IF_PART_EXISTS: Import fails if the item id exists. This is the default value. FAIL_IF_REV_EXISTS: Import fails if the item revision id exists. OVERWRITE_EXISTING: Import overwrites the existing item. USE_EXISTING: Imports keeps the existing item without change.

preference.name: STEP_informative_doc_role
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: STEP_not_yet_approved_status
preference.preference_description: Release Statuses that need to be interpreted as "not_yet_approved"

preference.name: STEP_part_items
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: Step_export_data_format
preference.preference_description: Sets the default STEP export format. Valid values are AP203 or AP214

preference.name: TC_organization_id
preference.preference_description: Specifies the ID of the organization. Applicable only for STEP.

category.name: DecisionApps.RelationBrowser.Preferences
category.category_description: Preferences for Decision Apps Relation Browser.

preference.name: RV1_DARB_Concentrated
preference.preference_description: Specifies the concentrated display mode for the edge in Relation Browser. The default value is false.

preference.name: RV1_DARB_Expand_All_1_Level_Command_Visible
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether to enable the Expand All 1 Level command in Relation Browser. The default value is false.

preference.name: RV1_DARB_Expand_Incoming_Levels
preference.preference_description: Specifies the values used for the "Expand Incoming Relations" menu in the Relationship Viewer application in the Active Workspace client. The menu will support 1-5 command values. Any values after the first 5 will be ignored.

preference.name: RV1_DARB_Expand_Outgoing_Levels
preference.preference_description: Specifies the values used for the "Expand Outgoing Relations" menu in the Relationship Viewer application in the Active Workspace client. The menu will support 1-5 command values. Any values after the first 5 will be ignored.

preference.name: RV1_DARB_Expand_Selected_1_Level_Command_Visible
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether to enable the Expand Selected 1 Level command in Relation Browser. The default value is false.

preference.name: RV1_DARB_Expansion_timeout
preference.preference_description: Specifies the time-out in seconds for network expansion in the Relation Browser server in the Active Workspace client.

preference.name: RV1_DARB_Filter_Properties
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of properties for the "Filter" panel in Relation Browser.

preference.name: RV1_DARB_GraphStyle_file_name
preference.preference_description: Registers the name of dataset which stores an XML file containing the Relation Browser graph style definition.

preference.name: RV1_DARB_Hide_Unhide_List_Order_Incoming_First
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether the Relations menu will display the nodes with the Incoming relations first or the Outgoing relations first. If the node has both incoming and outgoing relations, those nodes will be displayed between the incoming and outgoing nodes regardless of which set of nodes is displayed first. Value of true indicates incoming nodes will be displayed first, else the outgoing nodes will be first in the displayed list with the nodes designated as both will always be the second set of nodes. The default value is false.

preference.name: RV1_DARB_PresentationRule_file_name
preference.preference_description: Registers the name of dataset which stores an XML file containing the Relation Browser client presentation rule.

preference.name: RV1_DARB_RelationBrowserViews.Architecture
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of view names for "Architecture" tab in the RelationBrowser client. The view names are defined in the Relation Browser UI configuration file, which is stored in the dataset named by the value of preference "RV1_DARB_UI_configuration_file_name".

preference.name: RV1_DARB_RelationBrowserViews.Relations
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of view names for "Relations" tab in the RelationBrowser client. The view names are defined in the Relation Browser UI configuration file, which is stored in the dataset named by the value of preference "RV1_DARB_UI_configuration_file_name".

preference.name: RV1_DARB_Sorted_Layouts
preference.preference_description: Specifies the layout mode for cells in Relation Browser. A value of true will indicate that as cells are expanded, they will be displayed in a sorted order. The only layouts available for this mode are: Top-to-Bottom, Right-to-Left, Left-to-Right, Bottom-to-Top. The default value is false.

preference.name: RV1_DARB_Tooltip_Max_Row

preference.name: get6DrsPush_DrawingSheet_ets_dst_ds_type
preference.preference_description: The destination dataset type under which the result of a SIEMENS ge_pdf translation of an MSWordX dataset will be stored. If no destination dataset type is specified, the configuration is invalid and will be reported as an error.

preference.name: get6DrsPush_DrawingSheet_ets_dst_nr_type
preference.preference_description: The destination named reference type under which the result of a SIEMENS ge_pdf translation of an MSWordX dataset will be stored. If no destination named reference type is specified, the configuration is invalid and will be reported as an error.

preference.name: get6DrsPush_DrawingSheet_ets_dst_relation_to_src
preference.preference_description: The relation is to be created between the MSWordX source dataset and destination dataset.

preference.name: get6DrsPush_DrawingSheet_ets_dst_relation_type
preference.preference_description: The relation type of the relation to be created between the source dataset item revision and the destination dataset. If the source and destination dataset types are the same, this preference is ignored. If the source and destination dataset types are different, this preference must be specified; otherwise the configuration is invalid and will be reported as an error.

preference.name: get6DrsPush_DrawingSheet_ets_nr_types
preference.preference_description: The source dataset named references necessary for translation. All dataset named reference types specified by this preference must exist for the MSWordX dataset to be valid for translation. If no named reference types are specified, the configuration is invalid and will be reported as an error.

preference.name: CATIA_V4_checkin_generate_vis_data_priority
preference.preference_description: The scheduling priority for Catia V4 to JT check-in and/or save translations. The valid values of this preference are 0,1,2, and 3 corresponding to OFF, low, medium, and high priority. If this preference is not specified, no visualization data will be generated for check-in and/or save.

preference.name: CATIA_V4_translation_service_name
preference.preference_description: The TSTK provider name and service name of translator to be used for Catia V4 to JT translation. This preference value is specified using the provider and service attribute values from the corresponding translator element in the TSTK Module configuration translator.xml file (e.g. EDS.catiav4tojt). WARNING: If this preference is not specified, requests for Catia V4 to JT translations will be ignored.

preference.name: CATIA_checkin_generate_vis_data_priority
preference.preference_description: The scheduling priority for Catia V5 to JT check-in and/or save translations. The valid values of this preference are 0, 1, 2, and 3 corresponding to OFF, low, medium, and high priority. If this preference is not specified, no visualization data will be generated for check-in and/or save.

preference.name: CATIA_translation_service_name
preference.preference_description: The TSTK provider name and service name of the translator to be used for Catia V5 to JT translation. This preference value is specified using the provider and service attribute values from the corresponding translator element in the TSTK Module configuration translator.xml file (e.g. SIEMENS.catiav5tojt). WARNING: If this preference is not specified, requests for Catia V5 to JT translations will be ignored.

preference.name: CM_Cm0ActionItemRevision_Relations_To_Propagate
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of relations to be propagated when deriving from a Cm0ActionItem Revision.

preference.name: CM_Cm0DevRqstRevision_Relations_To_Propagate
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of relations to be propagated when deriving from a Change Request Revision.

preference.name: COMMONcatiatojtV4_ets_ds_types
preference.preference_description: The dataset type names of the Catia V4 datasets that can be translated by the Catia V4 to JT translator. If no dataset types are specified, no dataset type validation is performed. Additional named reference type validation can be configured for the datasets specified by this preference value.

preference.name: COMMONcatiatojt_CATPart_ets_nr_types
preference.preference_description: The Catia V5 CATPart dataset named references necessary for translation. All named reference types specified by this preference must exist for a dataset of this type to be translated. If no named reference types are specified, no named reference type validation is performed.

preference.name: COMMONcatiatojt_CATProduct_ets_nr_types
preference.preference_description: The Catia V5 CATProduct dataset named references necessary for translation. All named reference types specified by this preference must exist for a dataset of this type to be translated. If no named reference types are specified, no named reference type validation is performed.

preference.name: COMMONcatiatojt_catia_ets_nr_types
preference.preference_description: The Catia V4 catia dataset named references necessary for translation. All named reference types specified by this preference must exist for a dataset of this type to be translated. If no named reference types are specified, no named reference type validation is performed.

preference.name: COMMONcatiatojt_ets_ds_types
preference.preference_description: The dataset type names of the Catia V5 datasets that can be translated by the Catia V5 to JT translator. If no dataset types are specified, no dataset type validation is performed. Additional named reference type validation can be configured for the datasets specified by this preference value.

preference.name: Cfg0CompoundOptionValueMemberTypes
preference.preference_description: Defines the type of member option values that a Compound Option Value can hold. Valid values are in the format "CompoundOptionValue::OptionValue".

preference.name: Cfg0ConfigurationRetentionPeriod
preference.preference_description: Defines the time interval in seconds by which the Configurator data cache (e.g. for variant options and constraint rules) has to age before the system considers a refresh. This limits the frequency of updating the Configurator data cache to a maximum of once in this interval.

preference.name: Cfg0ConfigurationViewDisplayColumn
preference.preference_description: Specifies if only the ID column, or only the Name column, or all the columns are to be displayed in the "Variant Configuration" view in the Product Configurator application. Valid values are "All" , "NameOnly" or "IDOnly" (default value). Values specified in this preference are applicable for Option Values and are case insensitive.

preference.name: Cfg0DefaultLoadCount
preference.preference_description: Defines the initial number of search results to be returned in one page. This number may increase for subsequent pages based on the value of the Cfg0DefaultLoadCountIncreaseRate preference.

preference.name: Cfg0DefaultLoadCountIncreaseRate
preference.preference_description: Defines the increase in the number of search results displayed in one page compared to the one in the previous page. The number of values for the first page is controlled by the "Cfg0DefaultLoadCount" preference. The value indicates a percentage: * less than 100: less results are displayed (in the given percentage) * 100: the number of displayed results is the same * more than 100: more results are displayed (in the given percentage).

preference.name: Cfg0EnableFeasibilityRules
preference.preference_description: Enables Feasibility Rules authoring feature in the Product Configurator application. The valid values are: - true : Enables authoring of feasibility rules. - false: Disables authoring of feasibility rules. This is the default value.

preference.name: Cfg0EnableValidateAndSaveConfigObj
preference.preference_description: Enables the validation of the configurator rules and variant expressions in the Product Configurator along with Save operation. The preference is used in SOA operation configuration. The valid values are: -true: Performs the validation before the save operation. This is the default value. -false: Performs only the save operation.

preference.name: Cfg0MinimumCacheRetentionPeriod
preference.preference_description: Defines the time interval in seconds by which the Configurator data cache (e.g. for variant options and constraint rules) has to age before the system considers a refresh. This limits the frequency of updating the Configurator data cache to a maximum of once in this interval.

preference.name: DefaultLoadCountIncreaseRate
preference.preference_description: Defines the increase in the number of search results displayed in one page compared to the previous one. The number of values for the first page is controlled by the "DefaultLoadCount" preference. The value is a percentage that indicates a ratio: * less than 100: less results are displayed (in the given ratio) * 100: the number of results is the same * more than 100: more results are displayed (in the given ratio).

preference.name: DefaultMaximumLoadSize
preference.preference_description: Defines the maximum number of search results to be returned in one page. The search results page size will grow with each page based on the value of the "DefaultLoadCountIncreaseRate" preference until it reaches this limit.

preference.preference_description: The destination named reference type under which the result of a SIEMENS tozipfile translation of an MSWordX dataset will be stored. If no destination named reference type is specified, the configuration is invalid and will be reported as an error.

preference.preference_description: The relation is to be created between the MSWordX source dataset and destination dataset.

preference.name: SIEMENStozipfile_MSWordX_ets_dst_relation_type
preference.preference_description: The relation type of the relation to be created between the source dataset item revision and the destination dataset. If the source and destination dataset types are the same, this preference is ignored. If the source and destination dataset types are different, this preference must be specified; otherwise the configuration is invalid and will be reported as an error.

preference.name: SIEMENStozipfile_MSWordX_ets_nr_types
preference.preference_description: The source dataset named references necessary for translation. All dataset named reference types specified by this preference must exist for the MSWordX dataset to be valid for translation. preference.name: TCCheckoutReserveOnly
preference.preference_description: Specifies Business Objects for which a restore copy will not be created during Check-Out. If the Business Object supports Sequences, a new sequence will not be created during Check-Out. Cancel Check-Out will not be available for these Business Objects. Valid values are Business Objects for which Check-Out is allowed. NOTE: Adding ItemRevision to TcCheckoutReserveOnly impacts the DisplayName Business Object constant for ItemRevision. Please refer to Teamcenter Documentation for DisplayName Business Object constant for instructions about how to remove sequence_id, if desired.

preference.name: TCDefaultKeepLimit
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default keep limit for Sequences in Teamcenter. The given value is used to initialize the keep limit when a Business Object is created if no specific keep limit is defined using TCDefaultKeepLimitByType preference. For Sequences, the keep limit is defined as the number of sequences retained after a Check-In operation. This preference is not applicable to Datasets. AE_dataset_default_keep_limit preference is used to specify the number of Dataset versions retained with each Dataset. Valid values are positive integers greater than 0.

preference.name: TCDefaultKeepLimitByType

For each entry, the keep limit is applicable for that Business Object and any Business Objects inheriting from it. An inherited value of keep limit may be overridden by specifying a keep limit for the inheriting Business Object. For Sequences, the keep limit is defined as the number of sequences retained after Check-In. Valid values are space delimited Business Object-integer pairs. For example, Business Object A 3 or MyBusinessObject 2.

preference.name: UGALTREP_saveas_pattern
preference.preference_description: Defines the pattern string of the names of new UGALTREP dataset objects during a "Save As" operation. Value may contain text and also refer to the content of some of the object's properties using the ${PropertyName} format, with PropertyName being ItemID, RevisionID or UserText. Existing dataset names are expected to match this pattern. If the existing dataset names do not match the pattern, then the new dataset names will not follow this pattern. Example: ${UserText}-${ItemID}/${RevisionID} where the site has decided that the ${UserText} at the beginning is intended to be the name of the dataset, and the minus sign is literal text. Suppose a user is saving item revision 001234/B to item revision 002345/A. If a dataset's existing name is "altrep-001234/B" then the name is said to 'match' against the pattern. Since the ${UserText} at the start of this pattern matches any string, dataset name "fea-001234/B" would also match against the pattern. However, "altrep_001234/B" would not match the pattern as the minus sign is required, and "altrep-001235/B" would not match since the ItemID is incorrect. Once an original dataset name has been matched against the pattern, the new dataset name is generated by replacing the ${ItemID} and ${RevisionID} with the new revision and ItemID in the pattern, and all occurrences of ${UserData} with whatever text they matched against in the original name. This new name can then be used for saving the new dataset. Using the example above, the two datasets would be saved as "altrep-002345/A" and "fea-002345/A". This is a site preference.

preference.name: UGMASTER_DefaultChildProperties
preference.preference_description: List of properties that can be used as children for the indicated type i.e. UGMASTER. The format of the preference follows: <TypeName>_DefaultChildProperties=my_property.

preference.name: UGMASTER_saveas_pattern

Value may contain text and also refer to the content of some of the object's properties using the ${PropertyName} format, with PropertyName being ItemID, RevisionID or UserText. Existing dataset name is expected to match this pattern. If the existing dataset name does not match the pattern, then the new dataset name will not follow this pattern. Example: ${UserText}-${ItemID}/${RevisionID} where the site has decided that the ${UserText} at the beginning is intended to be the name of the dataset, and the minus sign is literal text. Suppose a user is saving item revision 001234/B to item revision 002345/A. If a dataset's existing name is "master-001234/B" then the name is said to 'match' against the pattern. Since the ${UserText} at the start of this pattern matches any string, dataset name "fea-001234/B" would also match against the pattern. However, "master_001234/B" would not match the pattern as the minus sign is required, and "master-001235/B" would not match since the ItemID is incorrect. Once an original dataset name has been matched against the pattern, the new dataset name is generated by replacing the ${ItemID} and ${RevisionID} with the new revision and ItemID in the pattern, and all occurrences of ${UserData} with whatever text they matched against in the original name. This new name can then be used for saving the new dataset. Using the example above, the dataset would be saved as "master-002345/A". This is a site preference.

preference.name: UGPART_saveas_pattern
preference.preference_description: Defines the pattern string of the names of new UGPART dataset objects during a "Save As" operation. Value may contain text and also refer to the content of some of the object's properties using the ${PropertyName} format, with PropertyName being ItemID, RevisionID or UserText. Existing dataset names are expected to match this pattern. If the existing dataset names do not match the pattern, then the new dataset names will not follow this pattern. Example: ${UserText}-${ItemID}/${RevisionID} where the site has decided that the ${UserText} at the beginning is intended to be the name of the dataset, and the minus sign is literal text. Suppose a user is saving item revision 001234/B to item revision 002345/A. If a dataset's existing name is "drawing-001234/B" then the name is said to 'match' against the pattern. Since the ${UserText} at the start of this pattern matches any string, dataset name "fea-001234/B" would also match against the pattern. However, "drawing_001234/B" would not match the pattern as the minus sign is required, and "drawing-001235/B" would not match since the ItemID is incorrect. Once an original dataset name has been matched against the pattern, the new dataset name is generated by replacing the ${ItemID} and ${RevisionID} with the new revision and ItemID in the pattern, and all occurrences of ${UserData} with whatever text they matched against in the original name. This new name can then be used for saving the new dataset. Using the example above, the two datasets would be saved as "drawing-002345/A" and "fea-002345/A". This is a site preference.

preference.name: ARM_archive_operation

preference.name: ARM_bom_compare
preference.preference_description: Activate the BOM compare performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time between the beginning of the operation and the completion of the comparison. Valid values are: * ON: Enables the performance monitoring of the BOM compare performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses the performance monitoring of the BOM compare performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_checkin_objects
preference.preference_description: Activates the system's check-in objects performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time from the beginning of the operation to when all objects are checked-in. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the check in objects performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the check in objects performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_checkout_objects
preference.preference_description: Activates the system's check-out objects performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time from the beginning of the operation to when all objects are checked-out. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the check out objects performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the check out objects performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_copy_objects
preference.preference_description: Activates the system's copy objects performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time from the beginning of the operation to the display of all objects. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the copy objects performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the copy objects performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_create_changeitem
preference.preference_description: Activates the "Create Change Object" performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time from the beginning of the operation to the insertion of the initial task into all target inboxes. This action occurs only when the "Start Process On Create" option is checked while creating a new change. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the "Create Change Object" performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the "Create Change Object" performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_create_dataset
preference.preference_description: Activates the "Create Dataset" performance transaction. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the "Create Dataset" performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the "Create Dataset" performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_create_item

preference.name: ARM_create_itemrev
preference.preference_description: Activates the "Create Item Revision" performance transaction. preference.name: ARM_create_supersedure

preference.name: ARM_cut_objects

Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the cut objects performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the cut objects performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_delete_objects

preference.name: ARM_display_changeitem

Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the display change performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the display change performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_display_form
preference.preference_description: Activates the system's display form performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time from the beginning of the operation to the display of all objects. preference.name: ARM_display_genealogy

This measures the elapsed time from the selection of the superseded item to when the genealogy is displayed. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the display genealogy performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the display genealogy performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_display_prop
preference.preference_description: Activates the system's display of object properties performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time from the beginning of the operation to the display of all objects. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the display object properties performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the display object properties performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_expand_bomview
preference.preference_description: Activates the BOM view expansion performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time between the beginning of the operation and the display of top-level components. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the BOM view expansion performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the BOM view expansion performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_expand_object
preference.preference_description: Activates the Expand Object performance transaction. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the expand folder performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the expand folder performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_export_dataset
