preference.name: ARM_idsm_import
preference.preference_description: Activates the performance monitoring of the Teamcenter remote import function. For client processes, the transaction reports the duration of time required to perform a remote import operation on the selected objects. For ODS processes, the transaction reports the time required to locate and transfer the selected remote objects and to report operation status back to the requesting client process. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the Teamcenter remote import function. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the Teamcenter remote import function.

preference.name: ARM_idsm_version_check
preference.preference_description: Activates the performance monitoring of the Multi-Site Collaboration internal version check function. For the client process, the transaction reports the duration of time required to perform a version request of the IDSM server at a remote node. For the IDSM process, the transaction reports the time required to respond to the version check request. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the Multi-Site Collaboration internal version check function. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the Multi-Site Collaboration internal version check function.

preference.name: ARM_import_dataset
preference.preference_description: Activates the import dataset performance transaction. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the import dataset performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the import dataset performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_initiate_process
preference.preference_description: Activates the process initiation performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time from the beginning of the operation to the insertion of the initial task into all target inboxes. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the process initiation performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the process initiation performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_launch_mynavigator
preference.preference_description: Activates the rich client's launch My Teamcenter performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time for loading the "My Teamcenter" application. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the launch My Teamcenter performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the launch My Teamcenter performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_load_lov
preference.preference_description: Activates the Portal's load LOV performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time from selecting an LOV to the display of all objects in the list. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the load LOV performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the load LOV performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_ods_publish
preference.preference_description: Activates the performance monitoring of the Multi-Site Collaboration publish object function in both the Teamcenter server and the ODS service. For client processes, the transaction reports the duration of time required to perform a publish object operation on the selected objects. For ODS processes, the transaction reports the time required to create the publication records for the objects and to report operation status back to the requesting client process. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the Multi-Site Collaboration publish object function in both the Teamcenter server and the ODS service. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the Multi-Site Collaboration publish object function in both the Teamcenter server and the ODS service.

preference.name: ARM_ods_remote_find
preference.preference_description: Activates the performance monitoring for the Multi-Site Collaboration remote find function in both the Teamcenter server and the ODS service. For client processes, the transaction reports the duration of time required to perform a remote find operation for the published objects that match the query parameters. For the ODS process, the time required to perform the remote find operation on the objects that match the query parameters is reported. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring for the Multi-Site Collaboration remote find function in both the Teamcenter server and the ODS service. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring for the Multi-Site Collaboration remote find function in both the Teamcenter server and the ODS service.

preference.name: ARM_ods_unpublish
preference.preference_description: Activates the performance monitoring of the Multi-Site Collaboration unpublish object function in both the Teamcenter server and the ODS service. For client processes, the transaction reports the duration of time required to perform an unpublish object operation on the selected objects. For ODS processes, the transaction reports the time required to remove the publication records for the objects and to report operation status back to the requesting client process. Operation status or error code metrics can also be reported for both client and server processes. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the Multi-Site Collaboration unpublish object function in both the Teamcenter server and the ODS service. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the Multi-Site Collaboration unpublish object function in both the Teamcenter server and the ODS service.

preference.name: ARM_open_dataset
preference.preference_description: Activates the system's open dataset performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time from the beginning of operation to the display of all objects. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the open dataset performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the open dataset performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_open_inbox
preference.preference_description: Activates the open inbox performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time to open a user inbox. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the open inbox performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the open inbox performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_open_task2perform
preference.preference_description: Activates the performance transaction for the opening of the Tasks to Perform folder. This measures the elapsed time to expand the folder. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the Tasks to Perform folder expansion performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the Tasks to Perform folder expansion performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_open_task2track
preference.preference_description: Activates the performance transaction for the opening of the Tasks to Track folder. This measures the elapsed time to expand the folder. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the Tasks to Track folder expansion performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the Tasks to Track folder expansion performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_paste_objects
preference.preference_description: Activates the system's paste objects performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time from the beginning of the operation to the display of all objects. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the paste objects performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the paste objects performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_perform_signoff
preference.preference_description: Activates the perform signoff performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time from the perform signoff to the insertion of the process's next task into all target inboxes. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the perform signoff performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the perform signoff performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_print_file
preference.preference_description: Activates the Print File performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time between selecting the Print command to the appearance of the Print dialog box. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the print file performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the print file performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_restore_operation
preference.preference_description: Activates the performance monitoring of restore operations. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of restore operations. * OFF: Disables performance monitoring of restore operations.

preference.name: ARM_save_bomview
preference.preference_description: Activates the save BOM view performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time between the beginning of the operation and the completion of the save operation. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the save BOM view performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the save BOM view performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_saveas_item
preference.preference_description: Activates the Teamcenter's "Save As" performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time from the beginning of the operation to the display of all objects. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the "Save As" performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the "Save As" performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_search_object
preference.preference_description: Activates the system's search performance transaction. This measures the elapsed time from the search request to the display of search results. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the search performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the search performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_session_login
preference.preference_description: Defines if Teamcenter login transaction should be enabled for Application Response Measurement (ARM). Valid values are: ON to enable login transaction for ARM. OFF to disable login transaction for ARM. This is the default value.

preference.name: ARM_session_logout
preference.preference_description: Activates the log-off performance transaction. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the log off performance transaction. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the log off performance transaction.

preference.name: ARM_tcfs_export_file
preference.preference_description: Enables or suppresses performance monitoring of FMS file export operations in the Teamcenter server. Valid values are: ON to enable performance monitoring of FMS file export operations in the Teamcenter server. OFF to suppress performance monitoring of FMS file export operations in the Teamcenter server. This is the default value. The preference scope is All (the value can also be supplied using an environment variable).

preference.name: ARM_tcfs_import_file
preference.preference_description: Enables or suppresses performance monitoring of FMS file import operations in the Teamcenter server. Valid values are: ON to enable performance monitoring of FMS file import operations in the Teamcenter server. OFF to suppress performance monitoring of FMS file import operations in the Teamcenter server. This is the default value. The preference scope is All (the value can also be supplied using an enviromnent variable).

preference.name: ARM_tcfs_open_close
preference.preference_description: Enables or suppresses performance monitoring of FMS file open and close operations in the Teamcenter server. Valid values are: ON to enable performance monitoring of FMS file open and close operations in the Teamcenter server. OFF to suppress performance monitoring of FMS file open and close operations in the Teamcenter server. This is the default value. The preference scope is All (the value can also be supplied using an environment variable).

preference.name: ARM_tcsync_object_file_transfer
preference.preference_description: Activates the performance monitoring of the Multi-Site Collaboration object file transfer function by the tc_sync utility. Object file transfer is a subtransaction of the ARM tc_sync update transaction. This transaction reports the duration of time required to transfer the files associated with a remote object to a specific site. There is no corresponding server-side transaction. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the Multi-Site Collaboration object update function by the tc_sync utility. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the Multi-Site Collaboration object update function by the tc_sync utility.

preference.name: ARM_tcsync_update
preference.preference_description: Activates the performance monitoring of the Multi-Site Collaboration object update function by the tc_sync utility. For the tc_sync process, the transaction reports the duration of time required to synchronize each modified, published object from the client node operation to the selected sites. There is no corresponding server-side transaction. Valid values are: * ON: Enables performance monitoring of the Multi-Site Collaboration object update function by the tc_sync utility. * OFF: Suppresses performance monitoring of the Multi-Site Collaboration object update function by the tc_sync utility.

Background tasks should provide their own application-specific notification. The valid values for this user preference are: NONE: The user will not be notified. SUCCEED: The user will be notified when a background operation succeeds. FAIL: The user will be notified when a background operation fails. BOTH: The user will be notified when a background operation completes with either success or failure. This is the default value.

preference.name: AbsOccGrmCopyRules
preference.preference_description: Determines what action to take when revising a context BVR (Bom View Revision) which copies the Absolute Occurrence GRMs forward to new Item Revision of the BVR. The format is "className1:className2:Relation:RelationType:Action" where: - className1 - Is always class.AbsOccData. - className2 - Is either a class.Form or class.Dataset or * for either one. This is used for secondary object. - Relation - Not changeable and should always be Relation for GRM types. All other types are ignored. - RelationType - Type of relation as defined in the database under Admin->Types. - Action - Action to take with the secondary object. - Clone - Create a new GRM that points to copied secondary (form or dataset). - Ignore - The GRM is not copied to the new BVR. The default action is Ignore. - Reference - Create a new GRM that points to the old form or dataset. This mechanism will be used only for Absolute Occurrence GRMs that has either Forms or Datasets as secondary objects. For all other objects, the system will apply the default action (i.e. Ignore). Duplicate entries will take action from the first match from top. Default Rules and their Meanings: class.AbsOccData:class.Form:Relation.TC_Feature_Form_Relation:Clone GRM Primary = class named AbsOccData Secondary = class named Form Relation = TC_Feature_Form_relation Action = Clone - Will copy to the new revision class.AbsOccData:class.Form:Relation.IMAN_master_form:Clone GRM Primary = class named AbsOccData Secondary = class named Form Relation = IMAN_master_form Action = Clone - Will copy to the new revision class.AbsOccData:*:Relation.IMAN_Rendering:Ignore GRM Primary = class named AbsOccData Secondary = Any class Relation = IMAN_rendering Action = Ignore - This GRM is ignored class.AbsOccData:*:Relation.DependentOn:CloneRelationsToAbsOcc Similar to above, except that GRM primary and secondary are absolute occurrence GRM anchor and absolute occurrence respectively CAUTION - The preference specification is case sensitive and trailing blanks are not allowed. CAUTION - If secondary object is something other than Form or Dataset the system may error when trying to Clone that object. It is recommended to only Clone a Form or Dataset. All other objects should be Reference or Ignore for its action. CAUTION - If you add new copy rules, please verify it by Revising an Item Revision at least once and check the syslog to make sure there are no errors thrown while reading these preferences. Note that you need an assembly with absolute occurrence attachments to test this.

preference.name: AbsOccGrmSecondaryCopyRules
preference.preference_description: Determines what action to take when revising a context BVR (Bom View Revision) which copies the Reverse Absolute Occurrence GRM overrides forward to the new Item Revision of the BVR. The format is "className1:className2:Relation:RelationType:Action" where: - className1 - This is used for secondary object (example ItemRevision). - className2 - Is always class.AbsOccData. - Relation - Not changeable and should always be Relation for GRM types. All other types are ignored. - RelationType - Type of relation as defined in the database under Admin->Types. - Action - Action to take with the primary object. - Ignore - The GRM is not copied to the new BVR. The default action is Ignore. - Reference - Create a new GRM that points to the same primary object that was defined on the orginal Absolute Occurrence GRM. Default Rules and their meanings: class.Form:class.AbsOccData:Relation.TC_Feature_Form_Relation:Reference class.Form = (GRM Primary) - class named Form class.AbsOccData = (GRM Secondary) - class named AbsOccData Relation.TC_Feature_Form_Relation = (GRM Type) - TC_Feature_Form_relation Reference = (action) Reference - will reference original GRM Primary to the new GRM that is attached to the new Item Revision class.ItemRevision:class.AbsOccData:Relation.FND_TraceLink:Ignore class.ItemRevision = (GRM Primary) - class named ItemRevision class.AbsOccData = (GRM Secondary) - class named AbsOccData Relation.FND_TraceLink = (GRM Type) - IMAN_rendering Ignore = (action) Ignore - will not reference original GRM Primary to the new Item Revision CAUTION: The preference specification is case sensitive and trailing blanks are not allowed. CAUTION: If you add new copy rules, please verify it by Revising an Item Revision at least once and check the syslog to make sure there are no errors thrown while reading these preferences. Note that you need an assembly with absolute occurrence attachments to test this.

preference.name: Briefcase_pkg_file_name

The format is based on the keywords ItemID (Item ID), RevID (Revision ID), ItemName (Item name), TargetSite (Remote site) and TimeStamp (time stamp) of the object being exported. The format is any combination of one or more of the above specified keywords. Any other word specified in the format will be treated as a constant. For example a value "BCZ:ItemId:RevId:TargetSite:TimeStamp" would result in the following generated filename: "BCZ_00001_A_Site1_31-Sep-2011_19-48-30.bcz". This is a site preference.

preference.name: DesignContextPickUpNewBackgroundAppearances
preference.preference_description: This indicates whether unselected Background Appearance information would be saved along with the Search Criteria Proximity Filter. Valid values are TRUE/FALSE. A value of TRUE could result in heavy volume of data created and stored in Teamcenter Database. Default value for the preference is FALSE.

preference.name: DesignContextPreciseRevRule.Alpha Best_App.PRECISE
preference.preference_description: Allows the search of Product Structure based on certain revision rules which have the special clauses for which there are no Appearance Sets available, whereas Appearance Sets are available for a revision rule which have all the clauses leaving the Special Clause e.g. "Precise" Clause. Please make sure that a stripped down version of Revision Rule exists and is used for creating an Appearance Set. Here in this example "Alpha Best_App" is a stripped down version of revision Rule "Alpha Best", which has all clauses of "Alpha Best" other than the "Precise" clause. Syntax: DesignContextPreciseRevRule.<RuleName>.Suffix. Supported suffix constants are: ".PRECISE"

preference.name: DesignContext_ItemID_Revision_Query_lookup_string
preference.preference_description: This is used for defining the look-up string corresponding to the saved query to find - EngChange Revisions (if "PortalDesignContextECObject.TYPE" defines an ItemRevision type) and/or - QPL-searchable ItemRevisions by "ItemID" and "Revision" entries. The default search used by DesignContext is "Item Revision...", which corresponds to the lookup string "k_find_itemrevision_name". The Saved Query corresponding to this string is looked up from TC_ROOT/lang/textserver/<language>/qry_text_locale.xml file. If the User desires to use a separate Query for this purpose, the user should ensure that the query corresponds to the String defined for the following Preference and that it contains entries for "ItemID" and "Revision".

preference.name: DesignContext_Type_Name_Query_lookup_string
preference.preference_description: This is used for defining the look-up string corresponding to the saved query to find - EngChange Revisions (if "PortalDesignContextECObject.TYPE" defines a type other than an ItemRevision type), - Variant rules referenced on QPL search indexes, and/or - Workflow processes by "Type" and "Name" entries. The default search used by DesignContext is "General...", which corresponds to the lookup string "k_find_general_name". The Saved Query corresponding to this string is looked up from TC_ROOT/lang/textserver/<language>/qry_text_locale.xml file. If the User desires to use a separate Query for this purpose, the user should ensure that the query corresponds to the String defined for the following Preference and that it contains entries for "Type" and "Name".

This preference is applicable only to the System Engineering application's Requirement View. Valid values are: * true: The objects checked out will not have the backup copy. The backup copy of the object is created only when the given reserved object is modified. * false: This is the default value. This will use the regular reservation operations.

preference.name: Enable_Server_Image_Processing
preference.preference_description:
By default, the "MyTeamcenter" application shows preview images (jpeg, png and bmp formats) in the Preview area of the Summary tab. Enabling the thumbnail functionality to view these preview images is not needed.
This preference enables the thumbnails functionality, which converts all images associated with Item Revisions to small thumbnail images that are displayed in the Preview area of the Summary tab, in the header of the Summary page, and in the search results. Administrators must perform multiple configurations to enable thumbnails functionality (c.f. the "Getting Started with Document Management" chapter in the technical documentation). Performance and resource implications must also be assessed.
Valid values are: * true: Enables server processing of images to generate thumbnail datasets. * false: Disables server processing of images to generate thumbnail datasets.

preference.name: ITEM_do_not_export_relation_if_type_excluded
preference.preference_description: When a relation type is excluded during an export/import operation, the relation object itself is exported by default but the secondary object is not. During import, the relation type as stored in the relation object is checked to make sure it exists and if the relation type is missing, the import operation cannot proceed. To avoid the export of relation objects when the relation type is excluded, set this preference to the name of the relation types. Although this may include pre-defined relation types such as IMAN_reference, this preference would be normally used for custom relation types that are not defined at remote sites. This is a site preference.

preference.name: ITEM_relation_types_update_lmd
preference.preference_description: Determines which relation types trigger the update of the last modification date of the parent object when the secondary object of class dataset or class form is modified, or if the relation is added/removed from the parent object. If the relation is added/removed, the last modification date of the parent object is updated regardless of the class of the secondary object. This is a site preference.

preference.name: LHN_Applications_List
preference.preference_description: Defines the applications displayed in the Left Hand Navigation (LHN) pane. The format of values for this preference is "perspectiveId:DisplayMode". For example, for setting the "My Teamcenter" perspective as primary and the "Getting Started" perspective as secondary, the preference values would be: com.teamcenter.rac.ui.perspectives.navigatorPerspective:primary com.teamcenter.rac.gettingstarted.GettingStartedPerspective:secondary If any conflict is found in the preference values then that value will be skipped. The preference does not have any value by default, which means that all applications are loaded as default in Teamcenter. If the value is "EMPTY", no application is displayed in the LHN. After modifying the preference, the rich client needs to be restarted. Preference values are only to be configured by a system administrator.

preference.name: LicenseUsage_hours_warning_level

preference.name: LicenseUsage_module_usage_warning_level

preference.name: MEAccountabilityCheckDynamicIDICProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of BOM Line properties used by accountability check dynamic equivalence criteria when searching for equivalent BOM Lines. By default the BOM Line property "bl_item_item_id" is always included in dynamic equivalence criteria, unless certain structure search friendly properties are provided: - internal BOM Line properties pointing to Occurrence Note - compound property on a Form - property on an Item type, description or name ( e.g. "bl_item_object_type" ) - property on an Item Revision type, description or name ( e.g. "bl_rev_object_name") If none of these is available, the property "bl_item_item_id" will be used in conjunction with any other specified properties. The first cacheless(structure) search property in the preference is used as an initial property to collect the BOM Lines on which the other properties are evaluated. Empty property values are not considered as equal during compare. An example for a value to search for absolute transformations, the entry "bl_plmxml_abs_xform" can be added.

preference.name: MEActivity.CREATERENDERING

preference.name: MEAlignmentNumberToSearch
preference.preference_description: Defines the number of lines to search for at a time in the "Align Selected Lines" dialog of the Manufacturing Process Planner application. If negative, the buttons for chunking the search results will be disabled and the search results for all the selected lines will be shown.

preference.name: MECTCNRevisionDetailsProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of properties to be compared on revisions in a Change Notice folder when searching by Change Notice in the Change Tracker. If the values are different, the property is listed in the Change Tracker Details panel. In the Change Tracker Details panel, properties of child lines are also compared. Valid values are internal names of Item Revision properties.

preference.name: MECTCompareAssignmentsFavorite
preference.preference_description: Defines which Accountability Check Favorite is to be used to compare assignments in the Change Tracker. Value can be of any of the below two forms : a) <uid>:<Favorite name> b) <uid> where uid is the UID of the dataset and Favorite name is the name of the favorite.

preference.name: MECTExcludeLinesBelowOccTypes
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of occurrence types that are to be excluded from the Manufacturing Change Tracker search results. Valid values are the internal names of any occurrence type.

preference.name: MECTRevEffectivityAdditionalProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines a list of properties to include in the "Change Tracker Revision Details Report" and in the "MESINTEG_ValidateReleaseAndExport" and "ME-create-revision-change-xml-AH" workflow handlers delta XML. The properties are listed for "Revised Lines" and "Changed Lines" in Excel in the "Additional Properties" column, and in "AdditionalProperties UserData" elements in the XML. Valid values are property internal names for a BOM Line.

preference.name: MECTRevEffectivityChildLineCompareProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines a list of properties to display in the "Change Tracker Revision Details Report" and in the "MESINTEG_ValidateReleaseAndExport" and "ME-create-revision-change-xml-AH" workflow handlers delta XML. The properties are compared for all children of "Revised Lines" and listed if they are different. They appear as new rows with "Modified Properties" of "Changed Lines" in the excel, and in "AdditionalProperties UserData" elements in the XML. Valid values are property internal names for a BOM Line.

preference.name: MECTRevEffectivityDetailsProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of properties to be compared on Revised Lines in addition to "bl_rev_item_revision_id" (Revision), "bl_rev_last_release_status" (Release Status), and "bl_revision_effectivity" (Revision Effectivity). If the values are different, the property is listed in the "Change Tracker Details" panel, in the "Change Tracker Revision Details Report", and in the "MESINTEG_ValidateReleaseAndExport" and "ME-create-revision-change-xml-AH" workflow handlers delta XML. In the "Change Tracker Details" panel, properties of child lines are also compared. Valid values are property internal names for a BOM Line.

preference.name: MECTRevEffectivityLineIdentificationProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of properties in addition to "bl_indented_title" (BOM Line) to include for identifying every revised and changed line in the "Change Tracker Revision Details Report" and in the "MESINTEG_ValidateReleaseAndExport" and "ME-create-revision-change-xml-AH" workflow handlers delta XML. The properties are listed in the "Revised Lines" and "Changed Lines" columns in the Excel file, and in "LineIdentificationProperties UserData" elements in the delta XML. Valid values are property internal names for a BOM Line.

preference.name: MEConfiguringStructuresMode
preference.preference_description:
Defines what configuring structures mode will be used when loading structures into the Manufacturing Process Planner. If the value is set to "AllToAll", then all loaded structures should configure all loaded BOP structures. If the value is set to "RelatedStructuresOnly", then only the structures related to some BOP structure should have it configured. For example: * Associated Target and Work Area structures configure the associated Process structure. * All structures contained within a Collaboration Context configure the BOP structures from that same Collaboration Context.
The default value is "AllToAll".

preference.name: MEEffectivityAssignmentMode
preference.preference_description: Defines the assignment behavior from Engineering BOM (EBOM) to Manufacturing BOM (MBOM), for the BOMLine property "bl_occ_effectivity". Valid values are: * 0 (default value): if the source EBOM line has an occurrence effectivity defined, the occurrence effectivity of the source line is assigned to the target line; otherwise, an empty occurrence effectivity is assigned to the target. * 1: if the source EBOM line has an occurrence effectivity defined, the occurrence effectivity of the source line is assigned to the target line; otherwise, the system finds the source line's closest parent which has an occurrence effectivity and assigns that to the target line. Note that when this preference is set to true, the source line and target line may not have the same occurrence effectivity, and an alignment check or accountability check may detect differences between the two lines for property "bl_occ_effectivity". * 2: the net effectivity of the source EBOM line is computed and assigned to the target MBOM line. Note that when this preference is set to 1 or 2, the source line and target line may not have the same occurrence effectivity, and an alignment check or accountability check may detect differences between the two lines for property "bl_occ_effectivity".

preference.name: MELineLinkedIconsProperty
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the system is to show "linked" icons for BOM Lines within Manufacturing applications. Valid values are "fnd0bl_assigned_as": the "linked" icons will be displayed in a reference window (Product or Work Area), indicating if a Product or Work Area component is linked (consumed, used, etc.) in a usage window (Process). no value given: the "linked" icons will not be displayed. This is the default value. NOTE: Giving a value to this preference slows down the Product/Process structure loading.

This site preference will be used when the value for preference OCS_use_email_property is set to false. For example, if your company email ID is info@siemens.com, the preference value should be set to siemens.com.

preference.name: OCS_use_email_property

If it is set to false, then the domain string value specified in the preference OCS_company_email_domain will be used, and therefore needs to be set. This is a site preference.

preference.name: PIE_allow_import_with_different_sml
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether PLMXML import will be allowed if the site master language in the xml file does not match the site master language in the importing site. true: the import will be allowed even if the languages do not match (this is the default value). false: disables this possibility.

preference.name: PLMXML_IC_Delta_export_transfermodes
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of Transfer modes for which Incremental Change (IC) based delta export is to be triggered. By default, only objects which are directly or indirectly affected by ICs will be exported out. The filtering of unaffected lines can be controlled by specifying the mode in this preference. Setting the mode to "Full" will do a full structure export along with all the associated ICs. Setting the mode to "Delta" will export only IC affected structure along with all the associated ICs. The format for the valid values is "Transfer_mode:Export_mode", where "Transfer_mode" can be the any Transfer mode available in the database and "Export_mode" can be "Delta" or "Full".

preference.name: PLMXML_export_key_properties
preference.preference_description: Activates export of Multi-Field Key properties in PLMXML file. The default value is true (activated).

preference.name: PLMXML_import_default_password
preference.preference_description: Initializes the password while importing a new user by PLMXML. The default value is blank. Because of security reasons, PLMXML does not export passwords to xml file. By default, during import, we create users with password same as user name. But if the strong password preferences are set at the target site, importing users may fail. If you have strong password rules, you need to define the value of this preference that satisfies your rules. All user objects imported would have same password (the preference value) and users should change the passwords to desired value upon initial login.

preference.name: PLMXML_log_file_content
preference.preference_description: Indicates the level of reporting written to the PLMXML translation User Log file. Valid values are: basic, summary or detailed. The default value is 'summary'. basic=Header+Errors, summary=Header+Errors+Warnings+Summary, detailed=Header+Errors+Warnings+Summary+Details+ClosureRulesAnalysis

preference.name: PLMXML_pre_expand_batch_size
preference.preference_description: Sets batch size for each single expansion. Structures as a target for export can be fully expanded prior to their export step, as an optimization which provides a performance improvement. However, there are memory concerns with large structures, that a full expansion may take more than the available memory of the system. This preference sets a limit. Values MUST be greater than 0. The smaller the batch size, the more likely the PLMXML_pre_expand_max_line_limit will not be exceeded, but at the cost of less performance gain.

preference.name: PLMXML_pre_expand_bop
preference.preference_description: Determines if the pre-expand functionality is run prior to a PLMXML expand operation. If the value of the PLMXML_pre_expand_max_line_limit preference is 0 and this preference value is true, the pre-expansion will happen (the PLMXML_pre_expand_batch_size preference will be set to its maximum value and the value of the PLMXML_pre_expand_max_line_limit preference will be disregarded).

preference.name: PLMXML_pre_expand_max_line_limit
preference.preference_description: Sets the maximum number of lines to pre-expand before an export. Structures as targets for export can be fully expanded prior to their export step, as an optimization which provides a performance improvement. However, there are memory concerns with large structures, that a full expansion may take more than the available memory of the system. This preference sets a limit. If the value is 0, no lines will be pre-expanded. If the value is -1, there is no limit on the number of lines to pre-expand.

preference.preference_description: Enables the Branch Based configuration feature. This feature supports grouping multiple working Item Revisions with certain intent, and configure those as necessary. This provides a general capability to create "Branch" definitions and utilize those Branches during Revision configuration of a product structure. The default value is false.

preference.name: PSE_enable_related_substitutes

preference.name: PSM_classic_variants_date_families
preference.preference_description:
Manually controls variant option value mode detection for select variant option families in configurators "Teamcenter Classic Variant" or "Teamcenter Classic Effectivity". By default, a classic option family is recognized as a date family if all values are formatted as a date (as specified by ISO-8601). A value is considered to be formatted as a date if it matches the following pattern: dddd [{-}] dd [{-}] dd T dd [{:}] dd [{:}] ddZ, where d stands for a digit (e.g. "1975-04-28T02:20:00Z").
This is a site preference.

preference.name: PSM_global_option_item_ids
preference.preference_description: Lists the Items for which Variant options will be available globally. Values for this preferences are set by the following command: "Tools/Variants/Set/Unset Global Option Item IDs". The format for a valid value is: * either a string in the format "object_string[itemuid]" where object string is the display name of the Item in user interface. E.g., for an Item, it will default to item_id-name and the UID is the unique identifier of the Item ID. * or it can be an Item ID. User is not encouraged to add Item ID manually. Custom code which reads this preference should parse the value to retrieve the UID between the square brackets.

preference.name: PS_ShowUnreadablePlaceholder
preference.preference_description: Activates the display of unreadable lines in applications leveraging Indexed BOM. Valid values are: - true: Unreadable lines are displayed with the name <<UNREADABLE>>. This is the default value. - false: Unreadable lines are not visible.

preference.name: RDV_default_variant_condition
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default variant condition for NULL Variant Projects. Valid values are under the format "ItemInfo:OptionName:OptionValue", where: * In a non-MFK (Multifield key) environment, "ItemInfo" is the ID of any item that exists in the database (e.g. "GMC00723:Color:Red"). * In an MFK environment, "ItemInfo" is the key of any item which uniquely identifies the item (e.g. "item_id=GMC00723,object_name=topitem,object_type=Item:Color:Red"). The key is a delimited string which contains name/value pairs of item attributes usually of the form attr1=value1,attr2=value2.... etc, where attr1, attr2 are property internal names (e.g. "item_id=GMC00723,object_name=topitem,object_type=Item"). To include a delimiter character (e.g. ',' or '=') in a key, it should be escaped by a backslash character ('\'). E.g.: * if the item ID contains an equals sign (123=456), the key string would be: "item_id=123\=456,object_type=Document". * if the item ID contains a backslash (123\456), the key string would be: "item_id=123\456,object_type=Document".

preference.name: Rollup_Variant_Feature
preference.preference_description: Activates the functionality of rolling up variant conditions, which sums up variant conditions of all parent BOM Lines of the selected BOM Line with its own variant condition. The resultant variant condition is coined the "Rollup Variant Condition" of the target BOM Line. Roll up of variant conditions is performed when a user executes the "Assign", "Compare" or "Propagate" action in the context of the linked EBOM and MBOM use cases. The same is applicable for allocation of processes or operations in EBOP structures as well. This feature works only with classic variants.

preference.name: Rollup_Variant_Traverse_Level_Is_InstallationAssembly
preference.preference_description: Specifies the upward traverse scope up to which line roll up variant conditions needs to be calculated. This preference will be considered only when the preference "Rollup_Variant_Feature" is set to true. Valid values are: * true: The roll up variant conditions are calculated up to the Installation Assembly in the BOM structure, if it exists. Otherwise, the roll up variant conditions are calculated up to the top line of the loaded structure. * false: They are calculated up to top line of the loaded structure. This is the default value.

preference.name: TC_Default_Solve_Type
preference.preference_description: Defines the default solve type value to be used while setting effectivity configuration. Valid values can be combinations of any of the following: * 1 - Mismatch: Conditions that do not match the solve criteria * 2 - Explicit: Conditions that explicitly match the solve criteria * 4 - Coprime: Conditions that are coprime to the solve criteria * 8 - True: Conditions that always satisfy the solve criteria * 16 - False: Conditions that never satisfy the solve criteria * 32 - Condition: Conditions that are non-constant * 64 - Error check: Conditions that return error * 128 - No condition: No conditions * 256 - No effectivity configuration behaviour: Objects that do not support effectivity configuration behaviour * 512 - Invert: Inverts the filter results The default value is 529, which corresponds to a partial solve type: Mismatch + False + Invert. This is a site preference.

Valid values are: * true: Only the "Reposition" dialog is visible in graphics menu. * false: Only the "Transformation" dialog is visible in graphics menu. This is the default value. This is a site preference.

preference.name: TC_Edit_Option_Startup_Panel

preference.name: TC_EffectivityConfigurable_MaxCacheSize
preference.preference_description: Sets the limit of the number of configurable objects for which effectivity data is cached by the Teamcenter server. The Teamcenter server caches effectivity data for configurable objects to prevent repeated frequent database queries for the same set of configurable objects. This has an impact on the memory footprint of the server process and on the performance due to change in the number of run SQL queries. If the value is equal to or less than zero, or if the preference is not defined the default value of 50,000 applies. The cache is automatically purged on a last-accessed basis. Cached values are automatically refreshed for loaded and up-to-date objects when a cached value is accessed that has changed since it was cached.

preference.name: TC_Feature_Form_Relation_relation_primary
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of valid primary object types for the relation TC_Feature_Form. Format is <Relation Name>_relation_primary=List of valid primary object types.

preference.name: TC_Fnd0Booleansolve_EffectivityDateRangeFromTo
preference.preference_description: Activates the inclusion of the end value for the display property of effectivity conditions in 4G Designer(4GD) application. Valid values are: * false: Date value ranges are displayed in an Effect-In/Effect-Out paradigm and objects, for which the effective date range is displayed like "Date=2011-04-01..2011-05-01", are not effective for Date=2011-05-01. This is the default value. * true: Date value ranges are displayed in a From/To paradigm and objects, for which the effective date range is displayed like "Date=2011-04-01..2011-04-30", are indeed effective for Date=2011-04-30 or if the date range is displayed like "Date=2011-04-01..2011-04-30T17", the objects are effective until the end of hour 17 on that day Date=2011-04-30.

preference.name: TC_Fnd0Booleansolve_EffectivityIntegerRangeFromTo
preference.preference_description: Activates the inclusion of the end value for the display property of effectivity conditions in 4G Designer(4GD) application. Valid values are: * false: Integer value ranges are displayed in an Effect-In/Effect-Out paradigm and objects, for which the effective unit range is displayed like "Unit=1..10", are not effective for Unit=10. * true: Integer value ranges are displayed in a From/To paradigm and objects, for which the effective unit range is displayed like "Unit=1..10", are indeed effective for Unit=10. This is the default value.

preference.name: TC_Fnd0SoaConfigFilterCriteria_AutoCheckinRevisable
preference.preference_description: Activates the automatic check-out/check-in of POM revisable objects whenever needed by Teamcenter. Valid values are: * true: POM revisable objects can be checked-out and then checked-in whenever needed, causing the revision number to increase. This causes changes to be immediately visible to other users (provided they have READ access). If the object is already in a "Private Edit" state beforehand, it will not be checked-in. This is the default value. * false: No check-in is made. Users can accumulate more changes for revisable objects before performing a manual check-in so that to commit all "Private Edit" changes and to publish these changes to other users (provided they have READ access).

Also, a runtime property TC_Is_Represented_By gets created for the Business Objects listed in the value of this preference.

preference.name: TC_RelationBrowser_Context
preference.preference_description: Defines the default context to be selected in the "Relation Browser" view of the Rich client. The valid value can be found in "Context" tag of graph_config.xml. The default is "com.teamcenter.rac.tcgrb.ctx.Default".

preference.name: TC_Report_Transfer_Area
preference.preference_description: Preference for creating a directory.

preference.name: TC_ReviseTogether
preference.preference_description: Allows a TC_DrawingOf relation between datasets to be propagated when the corresponding TC_DrawingOf relation between the Item Revision and the Drawing Revision are revised together. When user revises an Item Revision side object with intention to revise together its related Drawing Revision (as defined through BMIDE setting of the Deep Copy rule), the value of TC_ReviseTogether indicates if performing revise together on the dataset level is necessary (true) or not (false). When selecting a Drawing Revision and revising it, both TC_DrawingOf and TC_DrawingUsing relations are propagated regardless if TC_ReviseTogether is set to true or false. It is necessary to create a Deep Copy Rule through BMIDE to revise together an Item Revision and its Drawing Revision. Here is an example of the parameters for such a Deep Copy Rule as defined in BMIDE: Operation Type : Revise Target Type : ItemRevision Relation Type : TC_DrawingOf Object Type : Drawing Revision Condition : isTrue Action : ReviseAndRelateToLatest Is Target Primary : false Copy Properties on Relation : true Required : true Secured : false

preference.name: TC_TransferMode_XMLReport
preference.preference_description: Preference for a transfer mode used in TCMWEB Reports.

preference.name: TC_UI_SmartNavigator_Pagination_Enabled

preference.name: TC_UI_SmartNavigator_Pagination_Size

The default value is 80. Valid values are 1 to 99, inclusive. This value must be less than the value in preference TC_VOLUME_MONITOR_CRITICAL_LEVEL.

preference.name: TC_allow_modifying_only_checked_out_objects

This preference applies only to the objects for which reservation is supported. Default value of this preference is FALSE.

preference.name: TC_allow_project_admins_modify_rules

Valid values are: * true: all project administrators are allowed to edit the access rules. * false: only project administrators members of the dba group are allowed to edit the access rules. This is the default value.

preference.name: TC_aqa_date_range
preference.preference_description: Several tuning parameters used when auditing the querying of appearances and checking appearances based on the audit statistics. The statistics take the form of histograms along the lines of "N queries have been performed (on a given AppearanceRoot) for a date between D1 and D2 and/or a unit-no between U1 and U2". The width of each histogram block (D2-D1) and (U2-U1) is specified by TC_aqa_date_range and TC_aqa_unit_no_range.

preference.name: TC_aqa_default_validation_worthiness_threshold
preference.preference_description: When looking for ones to check, the code starts by searching for those with a validationWorthiness above the default_validation_worthiness_threshold.

preference.name: TC_aqa_freshness_factor
preference.preference_description: After checking appearances, the validationWorthiness (adjusted for staleness) is increased by the freshness factor.

preference.name: TC_aqa_initial_validation_worthiness
preference.preference_description: Finding out which haven't been checked recently is done by using the ApprQueryAudit's lastWorthinessUpdateDate and validationWorthiness. When such an object is created, its lastWorthinessUpdateDate is set to its creation-date and its validationWorthiness is given an initial value.

preference.name: TC_aqa_minimum_validation_worthiness_threshold
preference.preference_description: Minimum validation worthiness threshold.

preference.name: TC_aqa_staleness_factor
preference.preference_description: Deciding which appearances to check is along the lines of "check those which have been queried most, and most recently, and which haven't been checked recently". Finding out which have been queried most is a simple matter of looking for the largest values of N, adjustment for "most recently" is done by dividing the stored value of N by the staleness decay factor once for every day since N was last incremented (so that the older the audit, the less interesting it is).

preference.name: TC_aqa_unit_no_range
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: TC_aqa_validation_worthiness_threshold_adjustment
preference.preference_description: if it finds none, then it adjusts the threshold down by multiplying by the threshold adjustment and repeats the search.

Setting this preference to ON will not create create an object if it already exists, otherwise it will create the required objects. ON = Do not create the object, if it already exists with Item or ItemRevision OFF = Create the object, even it exists with Item or ItemRevision.

preference.name: TC_checkout_and_export

preference.name: TC_cms_relation_optset_map

preference.name: TC_config_condition_max_normalization_effort
preference.preference_description: Selects the strategy for normalizing configuration expressions such as variant conditions. This nornalization process is executed as part of saving the expression and automatically transforms the configuration expression into one or more Normal Forms (Conjunctive Normal Form - CNF or Disjunctive Normal Form - DNF). A CNF based normalization strategy is used if the estimated number of DNF terms (without removing redundancy) is less than the value defined by this preference. If the estimated number of DNF terms exceeds the preference value a DNF based strategy is selected, which is expected to result in a (usually significantly) smaller normalization result, but which is less optimal when evaluating configuration criteria. Since the estimate cannot take the effect of redundancy removal into account (a welcome by-product of the normalization process), the preference value significally overshoots the actual result. However, how much overshoot is acceptable depends on the nature and complexity of the configuration expression. Empirical analysis suggests that a good value is 30000 to reach a reasonable balance between save performance and configuration criteria evaluation performance. Valid values are all positive integer numbers greater or equal to 2. However, values less than the value for the preference "TC_max_cnf_count_for_condition_normalization" are not practical.

preference.name: TC_convert_text_file
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the system has to convert the EOF marker while transferring a file of a dataset. Valid values are 0/1. 0 - Do not convert but transfer the file as is. 1 - Convert text file when transferring a file from/to client to/from server.

preference.name: TC_copy_security_data_exclusion_list
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of security properties that are not copied over to the new object during the "Save As", "Revise" and "Baseline" operations. The default values are "project_list" and "owning_project".

preference.name: TC_current_role
preference.preference_description: Specifies if ACCESS MANAGER should strictly enforce object access based on the user's current role. Valid values are true/false. true - Strictly enforce object access based on user's current role. false - Perform access control as done in previous releases.

preference.name: TC_default_export_sites

This preference will be used only if the environment variable TC_USE_DEFAULT_EXPORT_SITES is defined and set to any value. NOTE: NOT used with interactive Teamcenter and is intended only for compatibility with pre-V4.0 ITK programs. This is a site preference.

preference.name: TC_default_part_type
preference.preference_description: Defines the default Item type used in NX. A valid value is the Item type internal name. This is a User preference.

preference.name: TC_deliverable_class_list

preference.name: TC_disallow_release_status_on_replica
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether replicas are allowed to be released (have a release status). Valid values are: - true: Prevents replicas from being released. - false: Allows replicas to be released (have a release status).

preference.name: TC_discipline_member_relation_primary

The default value is set to false and system will handle the co-existance of new ProjectObjectRelation and un-migrated ProjectObjectRelation objects and will not have any functional impact on the system. Valid values are: * true: migration of ProjectObjectRelation is enabled this will trigger migration of ProjectObjectRelation whenever it is encountered. * false: no migration of ProjectObjectRelation will be performed when legacy ProjectObjectRelation is encountered.

preference.name: TC_gms_export_default_transfermode
preference.preference_description: Defines the default transfer mode to be used when exporting objects in online-GMS and Briefcase export. Valid value is any TCXML export transfer mode that exists in database.

preference.name: TC_max_cnf_count_for_condition_normalization
preference.preference_description: Defines the maximum number of sub-expressions that are accepted as a result from normalizing a configuration expression such as a variant condition. This normalization process is executed as part of saving the expression and automatically transforms the configuration expression into one or more Conjunctive Normal Forms (CNF) that are optimized for evaluating configurtion criteria. The number of sub-expressions that result from this normalization depends on the nature and complexity of the configuration expression. If the normalization process produces more sub-expressions than defined by this preference, a different strategy is applied which (usually significantly) reduces the number of sub-expressions, but which is less optimal when evaluating configurtion criteria. Empirical analysis suggests that a good value is 500 to reach a reasonable balance between scalability (by setting this upper bound for the sub-expression count) and performance (during configuration criteria evaluation). Valid values are all positive integer numbers greater or equal to 2. However, values less than 10 or greater than 10000 are not practical.

preference.name: TC_org_chart_group_bg
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: TC_org_chart_role_bg
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: TC_overwrite_protection
preference.preference_description: This preference is used to indicate that the same property of the object has been modified concurrently by another user. A message will be displayed that will inform the user to discard their edits and update the property with latest value. When the preference is FALSE, the property value will be saved without any indication about concurrent modification. This will overwrite the property values modified by another user. Default value of this preference is FALSE. Applicable to Properties dialog, Form dialog, Viewer view, Summary view, Properties view and Details View inside My Teamcenter, BOM Window view within System Engineering, Office Live and Requirements applications.

preference.name: TC_preserve_original_owner_on_sync

preference.name: TC_propagation_exclusion_list

preference.name: TC_relation_export_hidden

preference.name: TC_remote_checkin_assy_option

Valid values are: * 0: Checkin will exclude components. * 1: The components will be sent as replicas. This is the default value. * 2: The components will be sent with transfer of ownership. This is a User preference.

preference.name: TC_retain_saveas_replica_dataset_name

preference.name: TC_schmgtwfd_sleep_minutes

preference.name: TC_setProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the overall behavior of object properties setting from Excel Live and Word Live. VALID VALUES - SET_PROPERTIES: indicates that all properties are set without any query or confirmation from the user regarding properties that have been overwritten since the export. This is the default value. - QUERY_AND_SET_ALL: indicates that all objects will be queried to check if they have been overwritten since the export. This option behaves like SET_PROPERTIES if no objects are found to be have been overwritten. If objects have been found, values for ALL objects will be set only after confirmation from the user. This option will work only when the preference TC_overwrite_protection is turned on. - QUERY_AND_SET_OVERWRITTEN: indicates that all objects will be queried to check if they have been overwritten since the export. This option behaves like SET_PROPERTIES if no objects are found to have been overwritten. If objects have been found, values for OVERWRITTEN objects will be set only after confirmation from the user. Values that have not been overwritten will be automatically updated without confirmation. This option will work only when the preference TC_overwrite_protection is turned on.

preference.name: TC_shared_server_metadata_cache_mgr_sleep_minutes

This results in one TNF clause to be generated regardless how long it takes. * 0 : Immediate time-out. No TNF is ever generated. * Any positive value.

preference.name: TcServices_array_separator
preference.preference_description: TcServices condensed property XML sends property data in the format is_modifiable FIELD_SEPARATOR ui_value FIELD_SEPARATOR prop_value PROPERTY_SEPARATOR ... etc. If prop_value is an array, an ARRAY_SEPARATOR string is used to separate the values. This preference controls the character used for ARRAY_SEPARATOR. This preference is not intended for customer use.

preference.name: TcServices_escape_character
preference.preference_description: TcServices condensed property XML sends XML property data as a single string with separators. The TcServices_escape_character is the character used to escape the property value strings containing the separator values. This preference is not intended for customer use.

preference.name: TcServices_field_separator
preference.preference_description: TcServices condensed property XML sends property data in the format is_modifiable FIELD_SEPARATOR ui_value FIELD_SEPARATOR prop_value PROPERTY_SEPARATOR ... etc. If prop_value is an array, an ARRAY_SEPARATOR string is used to separate the values. This preference controls the character used for FIELD_SEPARATOR. This preference is not intended for customer use.

preference.name: TcServices_property_name_separator
preference.preference_description: TcServices condensed property XML sends the names of properties for a condensed property object in the format prop_name PROP_NAME_SEPARATOR ... etc. PROP_NAME_SEPARATOR is a single character. This preference is not intended for customer use.

preference.name: TcServices_property_separator
preference.preference_description: TcServices condensed property XML sends property data in the format is_modifiable FIELD_SEPARATOR ui_value FIELD_SEPARATOR prop_value PROPERTY_SEPARATOR ... etc. If prop_value is an array, an ARRAY_SEPARATOR string is used to separate the values. This preference controls the character used for PROPERTY_SEPARATOR. This preference is not intended for customer use.

preference.name: Tc_allowed_rdv_configured_plmxml_dataset_types
preference.preference_description: This preference is set to enable which dataset type the user wants to see in thin client while using adhoc configurator function in DesignContext module. This should be "ON" to see the dataset containing preconfigured plmxml file and "OFF" to see the dataset with unconfig plmxml file

preference.name: TechnicalPortfolioTransferMode_IMAN_MEWorkInstruction
preference.preference_description: Sets the transfermode of the specified technical portfolio. Valid value is name of transfermode existed in database.

preference.name: TechnicalPortfolioTransferMode_TC_ProductManual
preference.preference_description: Sets the transfermode of the specified technical portfolio. Valid value is name of transfermode existed in database.

preference.name: TemplateCloneForceAbsoccId
preference.preference_description: Preference for template clone of absocc ID this is a site preference which, if set to TRUE (default) forces generation of absocc UID string as absocc ID (important for accountability check etc.) some customers might want to turn this off in order to disbale generation of user-readable IDs

preference.name: Thumbnail_Source_relation_primary

preference.name: Tracelink_Edit_enabled
preference.preference_description: Enables users to perform any operations related to Tracelinks. The default value is false. This is a user preference.

preference.name: Treat_Curr_Rev_As_Any_Rev
preference.preference_description: Defines if any letter can be entered for the naming of new object Revisions for the Revision naming rules with "CurrentRevLetter" supplemental types. Letters controlled by the TcRevisionSkipLetters LOV cannot be used. The default value is true. This is a site preference.

preference.name: Treat_Next_Rev_As_Any_Rev
preference.preference_description: Defines if any letter can be entered for the naming of new object Revisions for the Revision naming rules with "NextRevLetter" supplemental types. Letters controlled by the TcRevisionSkipLetters LOV cannot be used. The default value is true. This is a site preference.

preference.name: UGALTREP_DefaultChildProperties
preference.preference_description: List of properties that can be used as children for the indicated type i.e. UGALTREP. The format of the preference follows: <TypeName>_DefaultChildProperties=my_property.

preference.name: UGPART_DefaultChildProperties
preference.preference_description: List of properties that can be used as children for the indicated type i.e. UGPART. The format of the preference follows: <TypeName>_DefaultChildProperties=my_property.

preference.name: UNLOAD_LOGGING_LEVEL
preference.preference_description: Controls the volume of information logged-in. A valid value is an integer between 0 and 4, where 0 is for no logging, 1 is for minimal amount of logging and 4 is only for troubleshooting. This is a user preference.

preference.name: UNLOAD_MINIMUM_LIFE
preference.preference_description: Defines the amount of time in seconds after objects' creation before they can be unloaded regardless of memory size. This is a user preference.

preference.name: UNLOAD_OBJECTS
preference.preference_description: Offers the capability to disable the automatic unloading of objects. Valid values are: true: object unloading happens. This is the default behavior. false: object unloading is disabled.

preference.name: UNLOAD_TRIGGER_CEILING
preference.preference_description: Defines the maximum size (in kilo bytes) that loaded objects can reach before the "Unloading" operation begins. This is a user preference.

preference.name: UNLOAD_TRIGGER_FLOOR
preference.preference_description: Defines the size (in kilo bytes) that loaded objects can drop to before the "Unloading" operation stops. This is a user preference.

preference.name: Usage_CompareResultView_Type
preference.preference_description: Specifies the appearance group type that will be used to create Usage compare result view and its subgroups. Defaulted to UsageCompareResultView.

preference.name: Use_DataShare_Manager
preference.preference_description: Activates the use of the Data Share Manager (asynchronous file transfer) for the upload/download of files. Valid values are: *true: the Data Share Manager is used. *false: the FMS (File Management System) is used. This is the default value.

preference.name: User.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for User objects.

preference.name: UserInboxSummary.SUMMARY_REGISTEREDTO

preference.preference_description: Indicates the type to which the UserSummary stylesheet can be applied.

preference.name: User_Inbox_ColumnWidthPreferences
preference.preference_description: In-Box Column widths displayed, in left-to-right order.

preference.name: VISTopLevelRef_relation_primary
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of valid primary object types for the relation VISTopLevelRef. Format is <Relation Name>_relation_primary=List of valid primary object types.

preference.name: VIS_LAUNCH_LOGIN_PROMPT
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the user needs to login when launching the standalone viewer from Teamcenter unless TcSS (Single Sign On) is enabled. It is recommended to keep this preference set to true. Valid values are: *true: Users need to identify. If TcSS (Single Sign On) is enabled, no identification is required. This is the default value. *false: Users do not need to identify.

preference.name: VIS_Persistent_Transform_To_Part_Level
preference.preference_description: Activates the save of the transform at the part level. Valid values are: * true: the transform is saved at the part level. * false: the transform is not saved. This is the default value.

preference.name: VIS_VVI_CREDTOKEN_EXPIRATION
preference.preference_description: Indicates the time (in seconds) before the credential token expires for Teamcenter Visualization. If the expiration is not set or set to 0 or less (invalid time), the token will not be generated and the end-user may be asked to authenticate to the Teamcenter server.

preference.name: VIS_expand_below_batch_size
preference.preference_description: Defines the batch size of BOM Lines to expand for all Teamcenter Visualization "Expand" operations. These operations expand the lines in each level in batches, with the batch size defined by this preference. A value of -1 indicates that there is no maximum batch size and that all lines in a single level will be processed in one batch. The default value is 50. This is a user preference.

preference.name: VIS_mmv_use_lwb
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the Light-weight BOM is to be used to configure occurrences for massive model display. Valid values are: *true: the Light-weight BOM is used which provides higher performance but currently has some feature limitations (no effectivity support). *false: the regular BOM is used, which provides full BOM feature support but has reduced performance. This is the default value.

preference.name: VIS_mmvindexgen_admin_group
preference.preference_description: Lists the name of user group that is authorized to run the mmvindexgen translator from the Translation menu in the Rich client.

preference.name: VIS_multi_file_datasettypes
preference.preference_description: Lists the Datasettypes that can contain more than one visualizable named references. This allows users to view the selected named reference in the My Navigator Viewer tab.

preference.name: VIS_simpgen_admin_group
preference.preference_description: Lists the name of user group that is authorized to run simpgen translator from RAC Translation Menu.

preference.name: Vis_Doc_OpenOption
preference.preference_description: Specifies the behavior for opening the document by the embedded or standalone Lifecycle Visualization, in case the same document is already opened by that viewer. Valid values are: * "CreateNewDocument": to create a new document/view pair. * "ActivateExistingDocument": to activate the existing document/view pair. This is a default value.

preference.name: Vis_InteropWith3DSnapshots
preference.preference_description: Indicates if 3D Snapshot dataset should be sent to TcVis with ItemRev/BVR in InterOpt. Valid values are TRUE/FALSE.

preference.name: Vis_InteropWithMotion
preference.preference_description: Indicates if motion data should be sent to TcVis with 3D Snapshot Dataset in InterOpt. Valid values are TRUE/FALSE.

preference.name: Vis_SendViewToSMTempFolder
preference.preference_description: Defines the name of the Teamcenter folder where the transient Product View dataset is stored while sending a 3D view from Teamcenter Visualization to Rich Client Structure Manager viewer. The temporary Product View dataset is removed after it is applied in the Structure Manager viewer.

preference.name: VisualReportDefinition_OpenByName_ColumnPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the columns to be displayed for the dialog "Open By Name" for Visual Report Definitions. The format for valid values is "TypeName.PropertyName", where "TypeName" is the Visual Report Definition internal name (VisualReportDefinition) and "PropertyName" is the internal name of the property to be displayed.

preference.name: VisualReportDefinition_OpenByName_ColumnWidthPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths of the columns to be displayed for the column names as defined in the "VisualReportDefinition_OpenByName_ColumnPreferences" preference.

preference.name: VisualReport_Use_Classification
preference.preference_description: Activates the usage of the Classification search for loading visual reports. Valid values are: * true: The Classification search is used to load reports. * false: The reports are searched based on names. This is the default value.

preference.name: VolumeSummary.SUMMARY_REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Indicates the type to which the VolumeSummary stylesheet can be applied.

preference.name: WEB_EnablePSEVisualization
preference.preference_description: Activates the display of the "View -> Show/Hide Viewer" menu option in Structure Editor within the web client. Valid values for this user preference are 0 or 1 (default value).

preference.name: WEB_EnableVisualization
preference.preference_description: Activates the display of the viewer tab in the Summary in My Teamcenter within the web client. Valid values for this user preference are 0 or 1 (default value).

preference.name: WEB_IWantToDefaultActions
preference.preference_description: Default actions for I Want To Panel in thin client, Syntax-Localization Key for Action Text:Image Name:Action

preference.preference_description: Shows the Audit report in HTML format from Thin client.

preference.preference_description: MS Office Integration true - enable it false - disable it.
