preference.name: WEB_rdv_attach_unconfig_plmxml_relation
preference.preference_description: This preference is for thin client in DesignContext Module while using adhoc configurator to invoke the type of relation with which the dataset should be diaplayed

preference.name: WEB_show_context_menu_in_tree_view
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether contextual menus should be displayed for nodes in the tree view of the Teamcenter web client. Valid values for this site preference are true (default) or false.

preference.name: WEB_show_summary
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether summary information should be displayed or not upon the selection of an object( 1/0).

preference.name: WEB_show_toolbar_in_summary_pane
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether the toolbar should be displayed in the summary panel of the Teamcenter web client. Valid values are true (default) and false.

preference.name: WEB_ui_suppressed_actions
preference.preference_description: This is applicable only for legacy (HTML) Teamcenter Web. Suppress the ability to Cut any object => Cut Suppress the ability to copy any object => Copy Suppress the ability to revise an Item => ReviseItem Suppress the ability to create new Item => NewItem Suppress the ability to create new Form => NewForm Suppress the ability to Paste any object => Paste Suppress the ability to Initiate Process => InitiateProcess Suppress the ability to append any object => Append Suppress the ability to Delete any object => Delete Suppress the ability to do a paste target => PasteTarget Suppress the ability to Create new folder => NewFolder Suppress the ability to Import NX Assembly => ImpUgAssly Suppress the ability to export NX Assembly => ExpUgAssly Suppress the ability to create new Dataset => NewDataset Suppress the ability to do Where Referenced => WhereRef Suppress the ability to create new web links => NewWebLink Suppress the ability to do a paste reference => PasteReference Suppress the ability to launch DesignContext => DesignContext Suppress the ability to do Save-As on any object => SaveAs Suppress the ability to export Config NX Assembly => ExportConfigUGAssly Suppress the ability to copy revision for any object => CopyRev Suppress the ability to append revision for any object => AppendRev Suppress the ability to View Product Structure Editor => ViewPSE Suppress the ability to Edit Product Structure Editor => EditPSE Suppress the ability to Create Product Structure Editor => CreatePSE Suppress the ability to do Where Used (One) on any object => WhereUsedOne Suppress the ability to do Where Used (Top) on any object => WhereUsedTop Suppress the ability to do Where Used (All) on any object => WhereUsedAll Suppress the ability to launch external structure viewers => ExtStrViewers Suppress the ability to view the product in 3 Dimensional => ThreeDimView Suppress the ability to create workflow process from Inbox => WrkFlw Suppress the ability to view Item Properties for any object => ItemProp Suppress the ability to view object properties of any object => ObjProp Suppress the ability to launch NX against a selected object => PVUG Suppress the ability to Create new Product Vision Markup by uploading a file => ProdVisMarkup Following is the example which shows how to set these values. The values can be set to a single as well as multiple values. This example shows how to suppress the functionalities of workflow and deleting an object: WEB_ui_suppressed_actions= WrkFlw Delete

preference.name: WEB_use_lhn_home_component
preference.preference_description: Defines if the home folder content will be loaded in the LHN pop up window on Web UI. Valid values are 0/1. Default value is 1.

preference.name: WEB_use_lhn_inbox_component
preference.preference_description: Defines if the worklist folder content will be loaded in the LHN pop up window on Web UI. Valid values are 0/1. Default value is 1.

preference.name: WRKFLW_PKI_user_validation_fieldname
preference.preference_description: Defines the fieldname from the client certificate to be used for user authentication. Accepts a single string as a value. The string must be a valid field name from the client certificate. For example, the valid values in the Siemens PKI certificate are SERIALNUMBER, CN(Common name), SN(Surname), G(Given name) and O(Orgnaization name) Default value is "NONE". By default, the authentication is performed using client certificate.

preference.name: WRKFLW_allow_checked_out_targets
preference.preference_description: Enables the workflow handler to attach checked-out objects as targets. This is currently supported for the "EPM-attach-related-objects" handler. Valid values are: * true: Enables adding checked-out targets as attachments. * false: Disables adding checked-out targets as attachments.

preference.name: WRKFLW_allow_signoff_assignment_to_OOO_user
preference.preference_description: Controls the task assignment of a signoff when the delegate is already a member of the signoff team. Valid values are: * true: Assigns the signoff to the out-of-office user because the delegate is already a member of signoff team. * false: Assigns the signoff to the resource pool belonging to the out-of-office user. This is the default value.

preference.name: WRKFLW_allow_skipped_task_restart
preference.preference_description: Controls the restart behavior of a skipped task. Valid values are: * 1: Restart the skipped task. This is the default value. * 2: Restart the skipped task only if the task has multiple successors. * 3: Do not restart the skipped task.

preference.name: WRKFLW_auto_subscribe_to_resource_pools
preference.preference_description: Activates the display of the inbox content of all the Resource pools which Group and/or Role match the Group and/or Role of the logged-in user. Valid values are: * true: Show the inbox content of Resource pools. This is the default value. * false: Show the inbox content of manually subcribed Resource pools.

preference.name: WRKFLW_multitask_reassign_consolidated_email
preference.preference_description: Controls if a consolidated email notification to the new assignee should be sent in case of multiple task reassignments. Valid values are: * true: A single consolidated email is sent to the new assignee. * false: A separate email is sent for each task to the new assignee, if a notify handler is configured on the task's start action. This is the default value.

preference.name: WSOM_find_bomLoadLimit
preference.preference_description: Indicates the number of objects to load out of a BOM for limiting a query in each pass. The larger the number the quicker the load time, but less control the user has to abort.

preference.name: WSOM_find_pffdtd
preference.preference_description: Indicates the location for the pff_def.dtd file.

preference.name: WSOM_find_qry_filerunner_dtd

preference.name: WSOM_report_add_duplicate_rows

preference.name: Word_Show_Display_Name
preference.preference_description: Controls how object names are shown in the tree pane of an exported Word document, in the Office client application. This option is valid only for the structure editing mode of "Export To Word" operation. Valid values are: * true: The display name is as configured in BMIDE. This is the default value. * false: The display name is a combination of the object's ID and name.

preference.name: ETS_released_status_type_names
preference.preference_description: The released status types to be copied from the item revision to a visualization dataset whenever ETS creates or modifies a visualization dataset. The specified status type name values are used to filter the setting of the released date and released status types for a visualization dataset. Only in the case that an item revision released status type name matches one of these preference values will the released date and released status be copied to the visualization dataset.

preference.name: AIE_batch_mode
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the execution needs to be done in a batch mode with AIE. Valid values are YES/NO.

preference.name: AIE_em_installed
preference.preference_description: Specifies if a site has AIE Encapsulation Manager installed or not. Valid values are YES/NO.

preference.name: AIE_export_read_only
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the system has to export files from read-only datasets as read-only files on the client. Valid values are true/false.

preference.name: AIE_file_types_to_ignore
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of file extensions that will be ignored if found in the client connection directories.

preference.name: AIE_import_master
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the user has permissions to modify import information in the xml files when importing them back to Teamcenter. Valid values are Application/both. Application - User is not allowed to change the import information from Teamcenter. both - User is allowed to modify import information from Teamcenter.

preference.name: AIE_installed
preference.preference_description: Indicates if a site has AIE (Application Integration Environment) installed or not. Valid values are YES/NO.

preference.name: AIE_master_family_list
preference.preference_description: Lists all the AIE (Application Integration Environment) families. For e.x. NX, etc.

preference.name: AIE_named_refs_to_export
preference.preference_description: Preference that allows a user to specify the named references to export to a connection. Valid values are all/select/primary. all - All the named references in the dataset will be exported. select - A dialog will be displayed that will provide an option to the user to select the named references. primary - Primary named reference for the dataset will be exported.

preference.name: AIE_no_BVR_edit
preference.preference_description: If the following list of dataset type names appear under the same Item revision as the AIE dataset, then the corresponding BOM line will not be deleted.

preference.name: AIE_overwrite_default_import_item_types
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the user is allowed to use item types other than the default item type (first entry in Data Model Service (DMS)). Valid values are true/false. true - The user can choose from all item types listed in the DMS for new to be imported files as well as previously exported files. false - The user cannot choose from any item type. New files will be imported using the default item type only. Previously exported files go back to their existing item type.

preference.name: AIE_save_transaction_log
preference.preference_description: Preference that indicates if we need to save the transaction log after the connection has been deleted. Valid values are true/false.

preference.name: HM_AIE_ENCAPSULATION
preference.preference_description: HyperMesh AIE Encapsulation Specific Preference Variables.

preference.name: AnalysisEditorColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of column names that will be displayed in the Analysis/Composite tree table in CAESE application. Possible values are me_cl_display_string to display the "Line" column, me_cl_object_desc for "Description" and al_context for "Relation".

preference.name: AnalysisEditorShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the column widths for the column names (identified by AnalysisEditorColumnsShownPref) that will be used by the Analysis/Composite tree table in CAESE application.

preference.name: CAEAnalysisRevision_CAEAnalysisRevision_default_relation
preference.preference_description: As specified by the Simulation Process Management data model, the default relationship created when an object of type CAEAnalysisRevision is pasted under an object of type CAEAnalysisRevision. The default value of the relation is "TC_CAE_Include".

preference.name: CAEAnalysisRevision_CAEGeometryRevision_default_relation
preference.preference_description: As specified by the Simulation Process Management data model, defines the default relationship created when an object of type CAEGeometryRevision is pasted under an object of type CAEAnalysisRevision. The default value of the relation is "TC_CAE_Source".

preference.name: CAEAnalysisRevision_CAEModelRevision_default_relation
preference.preference_description: As specified by the Simulation Process Management data model, the default relationship created when an object of type CAEModelRevision is pasted under an object of type CAEAnalysisRevision. The default value of the relation is "TC_CAE_Defining".

preference.name: CAEAnalysisRevision_CAEResultRevision_default_relation
preference.preference_description: As specified by the Simulation Process Management data model, the default relationship created when an object of type CAEResultRevision is pasted under an object of type CAEAnalysisRevision. The default value of the relation is "TC_CAE_Results".

preference.name: CAEAnalysisRevision_DirectModel_default_relation
preference.preference_description: As specified by the Simulation Process Management data model, the default relationship created when a dataset of type DirectModel is pasted under an object of type CAEAnalysisRevision. The default value of the relation is "IMAN_Rendering".

preference.name: CAEAnalysisRevision_ItemRevision_default_relation
preference.preference_description: As specified by the Simulation Process Management data model, the default relationship created when an object of type ItemRevision is pasted under an object of type CAEAnalysisRevision. The default value of the relation is "TC_CAE_Target".

preference.name: CAEGeometryRevision_ItemRevision_default_relation
preference.preference_description: As specified by the Simulation Process Management data model, the default relationship created when an object of type ItemRevision is pasted under an object of type CAEGeometryRevision. The default value of the relation is "TC_CAE_Source".

preference.name: CAEModelRevision_CAEGeometryRevision_default_relation
preference.preference_description: As specified by the Simulation Process Management data model, the default relationship created when an object of type CAEGeometryRevision is pasted under an object of type CAEModelRevision. The default value of the relation is "TC_CAE_Source".

preference.name: CAEModelRevision_DirectModel_default_relation
preference.preference_description: As specified by the Simulation Process Management data model, the default relationship created when a dataset of type DirectModel is pasted under an object of type CAEModelRevision. The default value of the relation is "IMAN_Rendering".

preference.name: CAEModelRevision_ItemRevision_default_relation
preference.preference_description: As specified by the Simulation Process Management data model, the default relationship created when an object of type ItemRevision is pasted under an object of type CAEModelRevision. The default value of the relation is "TC_CAE_Target".

preference.name: CAEResultRevision_DirectModel_default_relation
preference.preference_description: As specified by the Simulation Process Management data model, the default relationship created when a dataset of type DirectModel is pasted under an object of type CAEResultRevision. The default value of the relation is "IMAN_Rendering".

preference.name: CAE_Inspector_summary_dataset_name
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the dataset in which the "Inspector Summary" will be saved as a named reference.

preference.name: CAE_Product_Structure_Default_Actions
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default actions for a criteria executed in the CAE Manager's Inspector view on the product structure. The format for the default value is "Criteria::DefaultAction" where the valid values with criteria are "Product with no Model" and "Missing Model Components". The valid values for both the criteria for DefaultAction are "Do Nothing", "Use New Model", "Use Model Related to Product Item", "Use Model Related to Product Revision" and "Use Revised Model". The default values for both the criteria are "Do Nothing".

preference.name: CAE_Root_BOMLineAction_Preference
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default actions for a criteria executed on the root BOM Line in the CAE Manager's Inspector view. The valid values are "Do Nothing", "Use Revised Model" and "Use New Model".The default value for the action is "Do Nothing".

preference.name: CAE_Root_Item_Type_Preference
preference.preference_description: Specifies the Item type that will be created for a New Model Action executed on a root BOM Line in CAE Manager's Inspector view. The valid and default value for Item type is "CAEModel".

preference.name: CAE_Simulation_Structure_Default_Actions
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default actions for a criteria executed in the CAE Manager's Inspector view on the simulation structure. The format for the default value is "Criteria::DefaultAction" where the valid values for the criteria are "Model With Different Product Revision Target", "Model With No Product" and "Extra Model Components". The valid values for Criteria "Model With Different Product Revision Target" are "Do Nothing", "Use New Model", "Use Model Related to Product Item", "Use Model Related to Product Revision", "Use Revised Model", "Replace Relationship" and "Add Relationship". The valid values for Criteria "Model With No Product" are "Do Nothing", "Add Relationship" and "Remove Model". The valid values for Criteria "Extra Model Components" are "Do Nothing" and "Remove Model". The default value for all the Criteria is "Do Nothing".

context.name: Teamcenter
context.value: Model With Different Product Revision Target::Do Nothing

preference.name: CAE_action_highlight_color
preference.preference_description: Specifies the highlight color used by Simulation Process Management operations to indicate that an action is needed on an object. The valid value is a triplet of integer values from 0 to 255 separated by the ";" character. The default value is "255;0;0".

preference.name: CAE_always_remesh
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether to remesh or not all the components. Valid values are true/false.

preference.name: CAE_analysis_tools
preference.preference_description: List of CAE analysis tools. The value is to be modified solely through the usage of the CAE tool options. There is no out-of-the-box value. This is a site preference.

preference.name: CAE_ancestorMapping_level
preference.preference_description: Specifies the maximum levels of ancestors to include in an XML node during Ancestor Mapping in the CAE application.

preference.name: CAE_apply_reuse_rules_to_sub_assemblies
preference.preference_description: Applies Structure Map Reuse Rules to product sub-assemblies. The valid values are: * true: this is the default value * false: the Reuse Rules will not be applied to product sub-assemblies

preference.name: CAE_attribute_propagate_summary_dataset_name
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the dataset in which the "CAE Attribute Propagate Summary" will be saved as a named reference.

preference.name: CAE_available_simulation_folder
preference.preference_description: Teamcenter folder containing the simulation template datasets.

preference.name: CAE_batch_meshing_always_create_new
preference.preference_description: Specifies that the re-use check should be done when set to "false". Command creates a new CAEModel object when set to "true".

preference.name: CAE_batch_meshing_attribute
preference.preference_description: Specifies Attribute Values to be set for CAEModel/CAEModelRevision , following the format "Toolname::Attribute::Value".

preference.name: CAE_batch_meshing_import_file_extensions
preference.preference_description: Specifies the file extensions for output files to be imported back to Teamcenter as named references of CAEMesh Dataset, following the format "Toolname::extn1,extn2...".

preference.name: CAE_batch_meshing_root_dir
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: CAE_batch_meshing_sizes
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: CAE_batch_meshing_tools
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: CAE_cautionary_highlight_color
preference.preference_description: Specifies the highlight color used by Simulation Process Management operations to indicate that caution is needed on an object. The valid value is a triplet of integer values from 0 to 255 separated by the ";" character. The default value is "255;255;0".

preference.name: CAE_confirm_settings
preference.preference_description: Controls whether a confirmation panel is displayed prior to launching the analysis application.

preference.name: CAE_create_GeneratedByRelationship
preference.preference_description:
Activates the creation of a CAE-specific relationship between CAEModel Item Revision (or any of its sub-type) and a referenced StructureMap Item Revision where the CAEModel Item Revision is the primary contributor to the relationship.
The default value is 1 (creation activated).

preference.name: CAE_current_application
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: CAE_dataMapping_file
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the file that contains data mapping.

preference.name: CAE_datamap_files_location
preference.preference_description: Defines the UID of the Item or Item Revision used to manage the Data Map definition files.

preference.name: CAE_datamap_object_creation_limit
preference.preference_description: Sets the limit of objects that can be created in memory for Data Mapping before committing the objects to the database. The default value is 5000.

preference.name: CAE_datamap_output_object_location
preference.preference_description: Defines the folder where data map will place the output root item revision. The valid values are: * "Newstuff": the data will be in the user's"Newstuff" folder. This is the default value. * The UID of an alternative folder: For this, use the Rich client user interface through the Edit/Options panel. * "None": output objects will not be placed in any folder.

preference.name: CAE_default_analysis_tool
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default CAE analysis tool. The value is to be modified solely through the usage of the CAE tool options. There is no out-of-the-box value. This is a site preference.

preference.name: CAE_default_batch_meshing_tool
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default CAE batch meshing tool.

preference.name: CAE_derivation_log_content_scope
preference.preference_description: Defines the scope of the Derivation log content. The value is leveraged by the "CAE_persist_derivation_log" preference, and persisted within the dataset identified by the "CAE_derivation_log_dataset" preference. Valid values are "Summary" (default value) and "Detailed".

preference.name: CAE_derivation_log_dataset
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the dataset in which the "Derivation Summary" will be saved as a named reference. The default value is "CAE Structure Derivation Summary Log".

preference.name: CAE_derivative_rules_datasets
preference.preference_description: Defines the UIDs of datasets having the definition of Derivative rule. Values are in the pair format of Derivative Rule names and their corresponding dataset UIDs, separated by a pipe ("|| ").

preference.name: CAE_derivative_rules_groupslist
preference.preference_description: Contains the list of group names, for which derivative rules are created.

preference.name: CAE_derivative_rules_list
preference.preference_description: Contains the list of Derivative Rule names which are defined either at group level or at User level.

preference.name: CAE_derivative_rules_location
preference.preference_description: Identifies the Item Revision used to manage the CAE Derivative Rules definition datasets.

preference.name: CAE_derivative_rules_sitelist
preference.preference_description: Contains the list of Derivative Rule names which are configured with scope as Site.

preference.name: CAE_enable_AncestorMapping
preference.preference_description: Enables ancestor mapping, which adds NodeXML interpretations of all the BOM line ancestors of BOM lines to the execution of StructureMaps in the CAE Manager application.

preference.name: CAE_enable_context_based_menu
preference.preference_description: Enables the context based menu for simulation tool launch. Tools whose configured input types do not match the selected input Item Revisions will be disabled. The default value is true.

preference.name: CAE_enable_mark_up_to_date
preference.preference_description: Enables the "Mark up-to-date" feature in the Simulation application. The functionality should be disabled in order to improve the performance of data mapping against large structures. Valid values are true and false. The default value is false.

preference.name: CAE_execute_server
preference.preference_description: Identifies the Server for Batch Mesh functionality,following the format "Toolname::Server".This Preference is deprecated in Teamcenter version TC2007.1 MP2 and no longer supported in TC2008.

preference.name: CAE_external_template
preference.preference_description: Identifies the path and name of the external simulation template currently selected.

preference.name: DATASET_saveas_pattern
preference.preference_description: Specifies the pattern string consisting of literal text and the following tokens: ${UserText}, ${ItemID} and ${RevisionID}. Existing dataset names are expected to match this pattern, where ${ItemID} and ${RevisionID} match the item id and revision id of the owning item revision respectively, and ${UserText} matches any text in the original name. If the existing dataset names do not match the pattern, then the new dataset names will not follow this pattern. Example: ${UserText}-${ItemID}/${RevisionID} where the site has decided that the ${UserText} at the beginning is intended to be the name of the dataset, and the minus sign is literal text. Suppose a user is saving item revision 001234/B to item revision 002345/A. If a dataset's existing name is "drawing-001234/B" then the name is said to 'match' against the pattern. Since the ${UserText} at the start of this pattern matches any string, dataset name "fea-001234/B" would also match against the pattern. However, "drawing_001234/B" would not match the pattern as the minus sign is required, and "drawing-001235/B" would not match since the ItemID is incorrect. Once an original dataset name has been matched against the pattern, the new dataset name is generated by replacing the ${ItemID} and ${RevisionID} with the new revision and ItemID in the pattern, and all occurrences of ${UserData} with whatever text they matched against in the original name. This new name can then be used for saving the new dataset. Using the example above, the two datasets would be saved as "drawing-002345/A" and "fea-002345/A". According to preference DATASET_saveas_allow_name_modification, the user may be allowed to modify these generated names. However, if DATASET_saveas_force_name_validation is true, the user-edited name is still required to match the pattern. The preferences DATASET_saveas_pattern, DATASET_saveas_allow_name_modification, DATASET_saveas_force_name_validation, DATASET_saveas_always_copy, DATASET_saveas_never_copy, DATASET_saveas_owner, DATASET_saveas_allow_duplicates are currently only used by USER_copied_datasets_details and USER_copied_dataset_name, and these are only currently called by NXManager Unigraphics.

preference.name: TC_NX_ATTRIBUTES_FORM

preference.name: TC_NX_Database_Attributes_For_Load
preference.preference_description:
Specifies the set of customer-defined, non-standard database attributes that are retrieved for each Item type/Dataset type whenever a part is loaded. The following standard database attributes are always loaded for all contexts and do not have to be specified by this preference: DB_PART_NAME, DB_PART_DESC, DB_PART_NO, DB_PART_REV, DB_PART_TYPE, DB_UNITS
The value format is three keywords (ItemType, DatasetType, AttributeTitle) and their values (enclosed in quotation marks). An empty string ("") can be applied to either or both of ItemType and DatasetType. The wild card designation, "*", can be specified as the value of AttributeTitle to indicate that all database attributes for that context are loaded when opening a Part in NX. Here is an example of a valid value: ItemType="NXPart"DatasetType="UGMASTER"AttributeTitle="Attribute1"
This is a user preference.

preference.name: TC_NX_Foreign_Datasets
preference.preference_description: Specifies the non-NX dataset types available to NX when it lists the datasets in an Item Revision. The value format is four keywords (DatasetType, NamedReference, NamedReferenceFormat, NamedReferenceTemplate) and their values (enclosed in double quotation marks). The format informs NX precisely which named references of the dataset contain the CAD data. Valid values for the "NamedReferenceFormat" keyword are "BINARY" or "TEXT". Valid values for the "NamedReferenceTemplate" keyword are the extension for files of that type. The values are case sensitive, and each value refers to a dataset type. Following are examples for values: DatasetType="DirectModel" NamedReference="JTPART" NamedReferenceFormat="BINARY" NamedReferenceTemplate="jt" DatasetType="SE PART" NamedReference="SE-Part" NamedReferenceFormat="BINARY" NamedReferenceTemplate="par"

preference.name: TC_NX_Navigator_Override_NX_Load_Option
preference.preference_description: Specifies what configuration to load when an assembly is opened in NXManager Unigraphics from Teamcenter Rich Client. The value specified here will have effect only when a dataset is opened from Navigator application. If the dataset is opened from PSE application, the Latest Revision rule set in PSE prevails. Valid values for this preferences is "As Saved", "Latest", or "None". "As Saved"-> This will load the Part file as saved in NXManager Unigraphics. Latest-> This will load with the latest revision rule. None-> This will ignore the "As Saved" keyword in the bookmark file.

preference.name: TC_NX_Supports_NXTCXML_Interop

Preference to show/hide Swing AbstractAIFDialog for single file drag and drop. The value can be true/false. If the value is set to "false", then the multiple file drag and drop JFace Dialog will be displayed for single file drag and drop event. If the value is set to "true" then the Swing AbstractAIFDialog will be displayed for the single file drag and drop event. Default value is false.
Please note that support for this preference and Swing dialog will be removed in Teamcenter 12. The JFace dialog is the preferred dialog.

preference.name: Select IR
preference.preference_description: At any time one of the two preferences 'Selection Criteria'or "Select IR" must be set, else Check-In/Out of Item revisions will not work. The values set by the user interactively in an Teamcenter session take precedence over values set by these two preferences. If this preference is set to 'Yes', the Item revision is selectedand is not selected if it is set to 'No'.If this preference is not set (or commented) and the"Selection Criteria" preference is set, then the ItemRevision willnot get selected, but the ItemRevision attachments get selectedbased on the specified Selection criteria.

preference.name: Selection Criteria
preference.preference_description: Sets the criteria used for pre-selection of attachments for Item Revision objects for Check-in/Out. For example, for the below case, all the objects of type UGMASTER having a IMAN_specification relation with the Item Revision object will be pre-selected. Valid values are in the format TypeInternalName followed by 10 spaces and then, RelationInternalName. At all times, one of the two preferences "Selection Criteria" or "Select IR" must be set, otherwise the "Check-In/Check-Out" of Item Revision objects will not work. However, this preference's values take precedence over values of these other two preferences. If this preference is not set and "Select IR" preference is set ,then only the Item Revision objects are selected and not their attachments.

preference.name: TC_Auto_Checkout
preference.preference_description: If this preference is ON, non-NX datasets will be automatically Checked-Out when a user opens that dataset. This will prevent another user from gaining write access to this dataset until the first user closes the dataset.

preference.name: TC_ContextMenuSuppression
preference.preference_description: Manages the Context Menu in the rich client via a dataset name. To enable the Context Menu Suppression feature, the valid name of a "Context Menu Suppression" dataset type must be provided to this preference.

preference.name: TC_Enable_Implicit_CO
preference.preference_description: Useful in cases where the user does not want to do an explicit check-out but still wants to edit the object. Allows for editing of same object by different users simultaneously. During Save in such concurrent editing if changes by another user have already been committed, then TC_overwrite_protection preference will determine if current user's Save will overwrite those changes or if the current user needs to redo his changes. Applicable to Properties dialog, Form dialog, Viewer view, Summary view, Properties view and Details View inside My Teamcenter, BOM Window view within System Engineering, Office Live and Requirements applications.

preference.name: TC_Enable_LegacySaveAs
preference.preference_description: Activates the display of the Legacy Save As dialog for all types in the Teamcenter Rich Client. Starting Teamcenter 11, this preference will be removed.

preference.name: TC_Enable_Legacy_Create
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether the legacy dialog box or the generic dialog box is displayed for the rich client File-New menu command for Item, Folder, and Form objects. If a value is not listed, the new (starting Tc10.1.0) generic dialog is used for that menu command. Valid values are "Item", "Folder" and "Form". Please note that support for this preference will be removed in Teamcenter 12.

preference.name: TC_GROUP_PFILE
preference.preference_description: Specifies the directory where the group preference files are located.

preference.name: TC_Graph_Node_Thumbnail_Shown
preference.preference_description: Indicates if existing preview thumbnail image is shown with type icon and object name representing each graph node in Generic Relation Browser. True means showing the image; False means not showing the image.

preference.name: TC_ImpactAnalysis_Display_Limit
preference.preference_description: Defines the maximum number of objects that can be displayed in the Teamcenter Rich Client "Impact Analysis" view when users perform a "Where Referenced" all level search. Increasing from the default value (500) may cause Rich Client to fail displaying due to its current memory allocation.

preference.name: TC_Project.REGISTEREDTO

preference.preference_description: Registration of stylesheet for TC_Project objects.

preference.name: TC_ROLE_PFILE
preference.preference_description: Specify the directory in which to find role preference files This is a Site Preference Only.

preference.name: TC_Text_Default_View_Tool
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default tool to be used when datasets of this type are viewed. Format is TC_AE_<datasettype>_Default_View_Tool.

preference.name: TC_Text_Tool
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default tool to be used when datasets of this type are opened. Format is TC_<datasettype>_Tool

preference.name: TC_UGMASTER_Tool
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default tool to be used when datasets of this type are opened. Format is TC_<datasettype>_Tool

preference.name: TC_UGPART_Tool
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default tool to be used when datasets of this type are opened. Format is TC_<datasettype>_Tool

preference.name: TC_UI_DisplayMaxColumnsForItemIDNameFields
preference.preference_description: Specifies if max length should be used for item id and name text field length in new item wizard.

preference.name: TC_UI_LOVComboBox_SizingBasedOn
preference.preference_description: Specifies parameter for the calculation of the threshold width for LOVComboBox objects in the Rich client. This preference value is only taken into account if the TC_UI_LOVComboBox_SizingPolicy preference is set to "FitToLength". Supported values are: - ScreenSize: The dimension of the primary monitor is used to determine the threshold width. - ParentSize: The dimension of the Rich client window is used to determine the threshold width. The default value for this user preference is "ScreenSize"

preference.name: TC_UI_LOVComboBox_SizingPolicy
preference.preference_description: Specifies the sizing policy of the LOVComboBox in the Rich client. Valid values are: - Default: Uses a default width of 32 characters - FitToLength: The size of the LOVComboBox is determined based on the width of the selected value. If the width required to accomodate the selected value exceeds the threshold width, the system uses the threshold width. The threshold width is defined to be 70 percent of the ScreenSize or ParentSize which is specified in the preference TC_UI_LOVComboBox_SizingBasedOn. The default value for this user preference is "FitToLength"

preference.name: TC_UI_LOVControl_SizingPercentage
preference.preference_description: Specifies the percentage to be used for the calculation of the threshold width for LOV Controls in the Rich client. This percentage is applied against the ScreenSize or ParentSize which is specified in the preference TC_UI_LOVComboBox_SizingBasedOn. Valid values should be between 30 and 100 (inclusive). If the specified value is outside this range, a default percentage of 70 would be used. The default value for this user preference is "70"

preference.name: TC_USER_PFILE
preference.preference_description: Specify the directory in which to find user preference files.

preference.name: TC_VALIDATION_FILE_TYPES
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of qualified file types for validation ext rule files and validation reports. System will identify the required dataset type for the supplied file ext.

preference.name: TC_VALIDATION_STYLESHEET_DATASETNAME
preference.preference_description:
Specifies a list of stylesheet datasets information (blank separated list of dataset type, reference type name, named reference name, stylesheet file name, and validation result log file extension that is used to match this stylesheet dataset). Only the validation result log file extension in each list entry is used to look up the stylesheet and the first one of the matched list entries will be used to render the validation result log file display. For example, NX Check-Mate result log is in PLMXML format with .xml as an extension. It needs a stylesheet (checkmate_log.xsl) for a tool (Internet Explorer for instance) to display its contents in a pre-defined format. This preference is also used to import stylesheet files into the database as stylesheet datasets during installation or upgrade (post schema upgrade) process.
Format is "dataset_type dataset_reference_type_name dataset_name stylesheet_name.extension validation_result_file_extension".

preference.name: TC_VALIDATION_duplicate_nx_valdata_error_on_import
preference.preference_description: Indicates if an error should be returned when importing an NX validation checker that has the same checker name as an existing NX validation checker. The default value is false.

preference.name: TC_Web_Browser_Home_URL
preference.preference_description: Defines the home URL of the Teamcenter web browser. This is a user preference.

preference.name: TC_auto_login
preference.preference_description: Administrators can use this preference to enable auto-login facility. Valid values are TRUE/FALSE. TRUE - Auto login via OS user name is in effect. FALSE - Auto login via OS user name is not in effect. This is a site preference only.

preference.name: TC_check_out_dir
preference.preference_description: Specifies the directory where files will be exported when a dataset is checked-out. The value must match the path format for the client operating system (OS).

preference.name: TC_confirm_paste_operation
preference.preference_description: Enables the confirmation dialog for every "Paste" operation in the Rich Client.

preference.name: TC_control_wildcard
preference.preference_description: Control the number of required characters before a wildcard character is allowed. The default is 0, which allows wildcard as the first character. For example, set to 2 means "AB*" is allowed and "A*" or "*" is not allowed. This is a site preference.

preference.name: TC_control_wildcard_exception
preference.preference_description: The wildcard exceptions specified here take precedence over TC_control_wildcard preference. This preference can be used to control the number of required characters before a wildcard for a specified class and attribute. Format of the preference value is: <Class name>.<Real attribute name>:<Number>. This is a site preference.

preference.name: TC_days_non_login_timeout
preference.preference_description: Used to disable the inactive use accounts. This option determines whether to allow user logon, based on the number of days that have passed since the user's last recorded logon. This is used as a security method to disable logon for users who have not logged into the system for a specified number of days. This is site preference only.

preference.name: TC_display_group_names_limit
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: TC_display_real_prop_names
preference.preference_description: Indicates if Teamcenter has to display the real property names.

preference.name: TC_display_thumbnail_in_UI
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the Thumbnail view is enabled in Teamcenter Rich client.

preference.name: TC_ignore_case_on_search
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the system needs to ignore case while performing a "Find" in Teamcenter (0/1). 0 - Use the exact case as typed in by the user. 1 - Perform a case-insensitive search.

preference.name: TC_markup_named_ref
preference.preference_description: Defines all the named references that have viewable image file. For a dataset that needs to do View/Markup, its named references must be defined in this list.

preference.name: TC_max_display_thumbnails
preference.preference_description: Indicates the maximum number of thumbnails that will be displayed in the Viewer tab when selecting multiple objects.

preference.name: TC_max_number_of_retries
preference.preference_description: Retry Control. If Teamcenter cannot lock an object, how may times should it try before reporting an error.

preference.name: TC_name_delimiter
preference.preference_description: The delimiter used in the Person.name. Example: in Smith, John, the delimiter is ,. This is a STEP preference.

preference.name: TC_name_sequence
preference.preference_description: Name sequence.

preference.name: TC_pattern_match_style
preference.preference_description: Indicates the pattern matching style to use. Valid values are 1/2/3. 1 - use "%" for multi-char replacement, use "_" for single char replacement. 2 - use "*" for multi-char replacement, use "." for single char replacement. 3 - use "*" for multi-char replacement, use "?" for single char replacement.

preference.name: TC_remote_import_check_grm_constraints
preference.preference_description: Controls whether to check for GRM rules during remote import.The default value is false (no check).

preference.name: TC_remove_file_on_check_in
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the system has to delete the exported files in the OS while performing a Check-in on a dataset which has been checked-out with "Export" option. This preference is also used to determine if the exported files in the OS should be deleted if the user cancels the Check-Out. Valid values are 0/1. 0 - Do not remove the exported OS files on Check-In. 1 - Remove the exported OS files on Check-In.

preference.name: TC_retry_time
preference.preference_description: Indicates the number of seconds to pause between each retry of locking an object.

preference.name: TC_runtimeTypeToExpand
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of runtime properties to be expanded in the deep copy tree. Valid values are runtime properties internal names. This is a site preference.

preference.name: TC_show_checkedout_icon
preference.preference_description: Enables the display of the checked-out icon in BOM trees, Attachment trees, Activity trees and Occurrence Group trees.

preference.name: TC_suppress_inactive_group_members
preference.preference_description: Used to suppress inactive group members. This is a user preference and it will be considered only from Group Administrators and System Administrators. In the case of normal users, the value of the preference will not be considered. Valid values are 0/1. 0 - SA/GA can see both active and inactive group members. 1 - SA/GA cannot see the inactive group members in Group Members dialog in SA applications. The default value is 1.

preference.name: TC_thumbnail_tooltip_properties
preference.preference_description: Lists the name of properties to be displayed in the tool tip in the Thumbnail view in Rich client.

preference.name: TC_wc_allow_subgroup_default
preference.preference_description: Defines the default setting for the Subgroup Members Allowed checkbox in the New Work Context dialog window.This option determines whether sub-group members of the selected group are allowed to perform a task.

preference.name: TC_wc_setting_modifiable_default
preference.preference_description: Defines the default setting for the "User Settings Modifiable" checkbox in the New Work Context dialog.This option is used to specify if the user settings defined via the work context can be changed once the work context is set as Current Work Context.

preference.name: TC_wc_show_all
preference.preference_description: Defines the content of the list of Work Contexts associated to a user. Valid values for this site preference are: - FALSE (default) to display only Work Contexts related to the tasks in the user's Task to Perform folder. - TRUE to display Work Contexts related to the tasks in the user's Task to Perform folder, followed by any other Work Contexts created by the user.

preference.name: TOOL_object_columns_hidden
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of column names that will be hidden for Tool objects.

preference.name: TOOL_object_columns_shown
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of column names that will be hidden for Tool objects.

preference.name: TOOL_object_widths_hidden
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths of the hidden columns for Tool objects (identified by TOOL_object_columns_hidden).

preference.name: TOOL_object_widths_shown
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths of the shown columns for Tool objects (identified by TOOL_object_columns_shown).

preference.name: TimeSheetEntry.REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Indicates the types to which the TimeSheetEntry stylesheet can be applied.

preference.name: TimeSheetEntry.RENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of properties stylesheet for TimeSheetEntry objects.

preference.name: Tool.REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Indicates the types to which the Tool stylesheet can be applied.

preference.name: Tool.RENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of properties stylesheet for Tool objects.

preference.name: USER_object_columns_hidden
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of column names that will be hidden for User objects.

preference.name: USER_object_columns_shown
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of column names that will be shown for User objects.

preference.name: USER_object_widths_hidden
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths of the hidden columns for the User objects (identified by USER_object_columns_hidden).

preference.name: USER_object_widths_shown
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths of the shown columns for User objects (identified by USER_object_columns_shown).

preference.name: User.REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Indicates the types to which the User stylesheet can be applied.

preference.name: User.RENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of properties stylesheet for User objects.

preference.name: Volume.REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Indicates the types to which the Volume stylesheet can be applied.

preference.name: Volume.RENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of properties stylesheet for Volume objects.

preference.name: WHERE_REFERENCED_RELATIONS_FILTER
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relations displayed in the "Where-Referenced" relation filter combo box, which is used to select relation filter criteria. This enables showing such relations in the combo box, while preventing them to be displayed in the "Paste As" dialog or in defined as child relations. Vertical industry solutions can leverage this preference by adding relations. Valid value of relations are relation internal names (e.g. CP_Has_Has_Copy_Element, CP_Has_Package_Concept).

preference.name: WORKSPACEOBJECT_object_columns_hidden
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of hidden columns for workspace object.

preference.name: WORKSPACEOBJECT_object_columns_shown
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of column names to be used for displaying the workspace objects.

preference.name: WORKSPACEOBJECT_object_widths_hidden
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths for the columns (identified by WORKSPACEOBJECT_object_columns_hidden).

preference.name: WORKSPACEOBJECT_object_widths_shown
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths for the columns (identified by WORKSPACEOBJECT_object_columns_shown).

preference.name: WSColumnsHiddenPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of workspace columns not displayed.

preference.name: WSColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of Workspace columns to be displayed (left-to-right order).

preference.name: WSDisplayTypePref
preference.preference_description: Indicates the type of display that the users see in the workspace. Valid values are 1/2/3. 1 - Vertical Tree. 2 - Horizontal Tree. 3 - Indented BOM.

preference.name: WSOM_find_editUserList
preference.preference_description: A list of priviliged users who get a quick edit button of the SEARCH panel.

preference.name: WSOM_find_list_separator
preference.preference_description: Indicates the token to separate multiple entries for queries. No token disables multiple entries.

preference.name: WSOM_find_set_pff_displaydata_limit
preference.preference_description: Limits the number of objects to be loaded when clicking the "Load All" button in the display data of search results view. Giving a higher number (above 1000) significantly slows the system response.

preference.name: WSOM_find_set_search_limit
preference.preference_description: Set a limit on the number of objects to be loaded after a Find before asking for confirmation.

preference.name: WSOM_find_set_total_limit
preference.preference_description: Set a site limit for the total number of objects to be loaded after a Search operation. Note : This is different from the number of objects loaded per page.

preference.name: WSOM_only_edit_effectivity_in_ecm
preference.preference_description: Allow editing of effectivity data outside an ECM process. Valid values are yes/no.

preference.name: WSShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths for the shown workspace columns (WSColumnsShownPref).

preference.name: WS_icon_placement
preference.preference_description: Indicates the position of the Icon to be placed with the workspace display. Valid values are 1/2/3/4. 1 - Above. 2 - Right. 3 - Below. 4 - Left.

preference.name: WhereUsedReportPropertyList
preference.preference_description: Stores the name of the properties selected while creating a "Where Used" report. Values for this preference are set automatically by the code.

preference.name: WsoFolderSavePref
preference.preference_description: Indicates when to save changes in Workspace. Valid values are 1/2/3. 1 = Save on every change. 2 = Only save when manually prompted. 3 = Prompt the user on close if they want to save.

preference.name: WsoInsertNoSelectionsPref
preference.preference_description: When no object selected, which folder/object should have a reference to it. Valid values are 1/2/3. 1 - Newstuff folder. 2 - RootFolder. 3 - None (place in database, but with no references to it).

preference.name: WsoInsertSelectionsPref
preference.preference_description: When a new object is created, which folders/objects should have a reference to it. Valid values are 1/3/4. 1 - All selected Folders. 3 - Newstuff folder. 4 - None (place in database, but with no references to it).

preference.name: browserWindowMode
preference.preference_description: Determines how the browser window will be displayed (e.g. from QuickLinks open a weblink). Valid values are 1/2/3. 1 - Launch externally (default). 2 - Launch in a single internal browser window. 3 - Launch in a separate internal browser window.

preference.name: com.teamcenter.rac.classification.icadmin.ICAAdminApplication\\Engineering\\*\\HIDDEN_COMMANDS
preference.preference_description: Defines the suppression of specified commands in the Classification Administration application for the Engineering group.

preference.name: com.teamcenter.rac.classification.icadmin.ICAAdminApplication\\Project Administration\\*\\HIDDEN_COMMANDS
preference.preference_description: Defines the suppression of specified commands in the Classification Administration application for the Project Administration group.

preference.name: com.teamcenter.rac.classification.icadmin.ICAAdminApplication\\Simulation Administration\\*\\HIDDEN_COMMANDS
preference.preference_description: Defines the suppression of specified commands in the Classification Administration application for the Simulation Administration group.

preference.name: com.teamcenter.rac.classification.icadmin.ICAAdminApplication\\Validation Administration\\*\\HIDDEN_COMMANDS
preference.preference_description: Defines the suppression of specified commands in the Classification Administration application for the Validation Administration group.

preference.name: com.teamcenter.rac.classification.icadmin.ICAAdminApplication\\dba\\*\\HIDDEN_COMMANDS
preference.preference_description: Defines the suppression of specified commands in the Classification Administration application for the DBA group.

preference.name: com.teamcenter.rac.classification.icadmin.ICAAdminApplication\\system\\*\\HIDDEN_COMMANDS
preference.preference_description: Defines the suppression of specified commands in the Classification Administration application for the System group.

preference.name: com.teamcenter.rac.classification.icm.ICMApplication\\Engineering\\*\\HIDDEN_COMMANDS
preference.preference_description: Defines the suppression of specified commands in the Classification application for the Engineering group.

preference.name: com.teamcenter.rac.classification.icm.ICMApplication\\Project Administration\\*\\HIDDEN_COMMANDS
preference.preference_description: Defines the suppression of specified commands in the Classification application for the Project Administration group.

preference.name: com.teamcenter.rac.classification.icm.ICMApplication\\Simulation Administration\\*\\HIDDEN_COMMANDS
preference.preference_description: Defines the suppression of specified commands in the Classification application for the Simulation Administration group.

preference.name: com.teamcenter.rac.classification.icm.ICMApplication\\Validation Administration\\*\\HIDDEN_COMMANDS
preference.preference_description: Defines the suppression of specified commands in the Classification application for the Validation Administration group.

preference.name: com.teamcenter.rac.classification.icm.ICMApplication\\dba\\*\\HIDDEN_COMMANDS
preference.preference_description: Defines the suppression of specified commands in the Classification application for the dba group.

preference.name: com.teamcenter.rac.classification.icm.ICMApplication\\system\\*\\HIDDEN_COMMANDS
preference.preference_description: Defines the suppression of specified commands in the Classification application for the System group.

preference.name: search_automatic_wildcard
preference.preference_description: Controls the automatic addition of wildcard to string attributes of saved queries and overrides other wildcard checks. Valid values are: - 0: the user search criteria are not altered. This is the default value. - 1: the search engine will suffix * to user values (e.g. "part" would become "part*"). - 2: the search engine will prefix * to user values (e.g. "part" would become "*part"). - 3: the search engine will prefix and suffix * to user values (e.g. "part" would become "*part*"). - Any other value is considered as 0. This is a site preference.

preference.name: Cfg0ExpressionGridColumnProperties
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of option properties displayed in addition to the object ID in the "Expression Editor" View in the Product Configurator application. The properties should be added in the format "BusinessObject.PropertyName", where "BusinessObject" is the Business Object internal name and "PropertyName" is the property internal name.

preference.name: Cfg0ExpressionGridSelectionCharacters
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of characters that will be displayed in the "Variant Expression Editor" view to represent variant expression selections in the Product Configurator application. Two character values should be specified, the first one for positive selections and the second one for negative selections.

preference.name: Cfg0OptionsViewHistoryUIDs
preference.preference_description: Contains the history of last 20 objects opened within the Variant Options view. The objects are recorded as UIDs. This preference is populated internally and is not meant to be modified by users.

preference.name: ImpactMatrixShowLeafLevelPartitionOnly
preference.preference_description: Activates the display of all the partitions under a selected Product Architecture Model (PAM) when its impact matrix is opened. This preference also governs the display of all child partitions in an impact matrix, when the impact matrix is opened by selecting an intermediate partition. Valid values are: * true: all the partitions are displayed. This is the default value. * false: only the leaf level partition are displayed

preference.name: MDL_default_attribute_group_types
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of managed attribute group types available for this role. Valid values are internal type names of attribute group and managed attribute group defined in the "4G Designer" application.

preference.name: MDL_include_attribute_group_inherit_properties
preference.preference_description: Defines a list of inherited properties to be made available for viewing Attribute Groups within the Content Explorer view. By default the Column Management wizard for Content Explorer view displays only the properties directly defined on an Attribute Group. In this preference you can list an additional set of properties from the parent hierarchy of Attribute Groups. These set of properties will then be available for selection in the Column Management wizard of Content Explorer view. For example, 'object_string' property is inherited from 'WorkspaceObject'. To make 'object_string' property available for Attribute Groups, include this property name in the preference value list.

preference.name: PartitionableModelHistoryUIDList
preference.preference_description: Contains the history of last 20 objects opened within the "Content Explorer" view for a Partition Template and its contents. The objects are recorded as UIDs. This preference is populated internally and is not meant to be modified by users.

preference.name: Ptn0ViewUnPartitionedElementTypes
preference.preference_description: Defines the Business Object types of unpartitioned model elements to be searched in a model.

preference.name: ReportDefinition_ColumnPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of columns to be displayed for objects of type ReportDefinition

preference.name: ReportDefinition_ColumnWidthPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths of the columns for the column names as defined in ReportDefinition_ColumnPreferences preference

preference.name: ReportGenerationDlg_ColumnPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of columns to be displayed for objects of type ReportDefinition in the Generate Report Dialog

preference.name: ReportGenerationDlg_ColumnWidthPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths of the columns for the column names as defined in ReportGenerationDlg_ColumnPreferences preference

preference.name: Change_Search_Default
preference.preference_description: Sets the default search that will take effect the next time the user logs in.

preference.name: TC_QRY_suppress_inactive_user
preference.preference_description: Suppresses the visibility of inactive users in queries. Valid values are: * 0: Users can see both active and inactive users in user LOV for query. * 1: Users cannot see the inactive users in user LOV for query. This is the default value.

preference.name: RDVThinClientBomlinePropsDisplay
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of BOM Line properties to be used for displaying BOM Lines in the Design Context Web client. Valid values are all valid BOM Line properties and Occurrence Notes. The property bl_ia_name is always displayed as the last column and hence not added in the property list.

preference.name: WEB_DC_ColumnWidthPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths (in pixels) for the columns displayed in the Design Context Web client. The columns are specified by the values of the preference RDVThinClientBomlinePropsDisplay. There is always one more value than the number of values declared in the preference RDVThinClientBomlinePropsDisplay, in order to accomodate for the property bl_ia_name, which is always displayed as the last column in the Design Context Web client.

preference.name: WebDesignContextDefaultSearchDistance
preference.preference_description: The default search distance for RDV Thin Client searches.

preference.name: WEB_create_Item_exclude_types
preference.preference_description: Filters the type list presented in the Thin Client New Item dialog. This is the first preference of the general format WEB_create_<Class>_exclude_types. Others can be created corresponding to the Thin Client's additional object creation interfaces.

preference.name: WEB_create_WorkspaceObject_exclude_types
preference.preference_description: Filters the type list presented in the Thin Client New Other dialog for WorkspaceObjects.

preference.name: WEB_default_site_server
preference.preference_description: Defines the URL of the default site server used for mail notifications (CR-Notify) and other server oriented tasks. The format is for instance "www.foo.com:8080".

preference.name: WEB_NX_UseBookmark
preference.preference_description: Enables the use of legacy UGM Bookmark (.ugmbkm) file formats instead of NX PLMXML (.nxplmxml) for NX interoperability.

preference.name: WEB_add_rac_suppressions
preference.preference_description: Defines the behavior of command suppression in the Thin Client. Valid values are: * true: the rich client command suppressions are added to the Thin Client command suppressions defined in the preference "WEB_menu_entry_suppressions". * false: This is the default value. If the preference "WEB_menu_entry_suppressions" is set, the specified menu entries are suppressed, and any rich client suppression is ignored. Otherwise, the rich client suppression is used.

preference.name: WEB_auto_assign_ds_id
preference.preference_description: If dataset ID is used - should the web try and auto generate if ones aren't provided? 1 = try auto gen 0 = always ask User to provide.

preference.name: WEB_column_one_new_window
preference.preference_description: The first column links of table-based pages are to be opened in a new window where possible. (1 is yes, 0 is no).

preference.name: WEB_core_help_server
preference.preference_description: Defines the URL of the site's Teamcenter online help page (used to create help::Tc link). A valid value is in the format "http://[host]:[port]/tdoc/tc/[tc-release]/help/", where: * [host] is the PLM Documentation Server host name * [port] is the port used by the PLM Documentation Server * [tc-release] is the Teamcenter release level (e.g. 10.1.0).

preference.name: WEB_create_Requirement_exclude_types
preference.preference_description: Filters the type list presented in the Thin Client System Engineering New Requirement dialog.

preference.name: WEB_dataset_shown_relations
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relations to be displayed on expansion of a dataset. Add "Version" to this preference list to display dataset versions

preference.name: WEB_dataset_upload_mode
preference.preference_description: site pref for setting the default dataset upload mode 0 - the dataset need not be Checked-Out to be able to upload a file to it 1 - the dataset must be Checked-Out to be able to upload a file to it.

preference.name: WEB_default_site_deployed_app_name
preference.preference_description: Defines the name of the deployed application. Application name is chosen at installation time; the default name is 'tc'. It appears in Thin Client URLs like this: http://server:port/<app_name>/webclient.

preference.name: WEB_displayed_new_menu_objects
preference.preference_description: Sets the list of object types displayed in the "New" menu of the Thin client.

preference.name: WEB_fnd0Branch_DefaultChildProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of properties that can be used as children for the Fnd0Branch type. The format of the preference follows: <TypeName>_DefaultChildProperties=my_property.

preference.name: WEB_fnd0Branch_Fnd0Branch_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relation that has to be created when a Fnd0Branch is pasted under a Fnd0Branch. The relation specified for this preference will be the default relation that will be created between the source Fnd0Branch and the target Fnd0Branch.

preference.name: WEB_fnd0Branch_ItemRevision_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relation that has to be created when an ItemRevision is pasted under a Fnd0Branch. The relation specified for this preference will be the default relation that will be created between the source ItemRevision and the target Fnd0Branch.

preference.name: WEB_fnd0Branch_PseudoFolder
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of properties that can be displayed as a pseudo-folder under a node for Fnd0Branch objects.

preference.name: WEB_fnd0Branch_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relation that has to be created when an object is pasted under an object of type Fnd0Branch. The relation specified for this preference will be the default relation that will be created between the source and the target Fnd0Branch.

preference.name: WEB_help_server
preference.preference_description: Defines the URL of the Teamcenter thin client online help. A valid value is in the format "http://[host]:[port]/tdoc/tc/[tc-release]/help/#filename:thin_client_dhtml:getting_started", where: * [host] is the PLM Documentation Server host name * [port] is the port used by the PLM Documentation Server * [tc-release] is the Teamcenter release level (e.g. 10.1.0).

preference.name: WEB_item_default_relation
preference.preference_description: The default paste relation for item. You can use WEB_typename_default_relation to customize by type. Note that for the old page set, this is the option selected by default from the paste relation listbox. In the new page set, this is the relation used when you paste directly to an Item or Revision rather than a pseudo-folder.

preference.name: WEB_item_shown_relations
preference.preference_description: These are the relation types which will be shown in the Teamcenter Thin Client interface. You can customize by type using WEB_<typename>_shown_relations. if we can't find those this list will be picked up. NOTE: As of V7, "ALL" is no longer a valid value.

preference.name: WEB_itemrevision_default_relation
preference.preference_description: The default paste relation for item. You can use WEB_typename_default_relation to customize by type. Note that for the old page set, this is the option selected by default from the paste relation listbox. In the new page set, this is the relation used when you paste directly to an Item or Revision rather than a pseudo-folder.

preference.name: WEB_login_page
preference.preference_description: Page to load in new web on login

preference.name: WEB_menu_entry_new_window
preference.preference_description: List the title of any menu entries to be opened in a new window

preference.name: WEB_menu_entry_suppressions
preference.preference_description: Lists the key values (found in the menu xml) for Thin Client menu entries to be suppressed. If this preference is unset (default), the Rich Client Command Suppression settings will be applied to the Thin Client. If set, RAC Command Suppression settings are ignored.

preference.name: WEB_package_multipart
preference.preference_description: Multipart packaging. These *must* leave the package in the same directory. If this undefined, the download and edit do not appear in web pages.

preference.name: WEB_packaging_extension
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: WEB_processes
preference.preference_description: Filters the processes offered to the user in the "new job" dialog. Leaving it blank will list all processes.

preference.name: WEB_protocol
preference.preference_description: Sets the Teamcenter web server protocol. Ex http:// or https://

preference.name: WEB_recent_menu_objects
preference.preference_description: Maintains the list of recently created objects in the Teamcenter web client, for the specified types. Valid values are Business Object's internal names.

preference.name: WEB_show_export_nx_assy_menu
preference.preference_description: Enables the display of the ExportNxAssembly menu item in Thin client.

preference.name: WEB_show_impactanalysis
preference.preference_description: Activates the display of the Impact Analysis tab in the Summary in My Teamcenter within the thin client. The default value is true (display activated).

preference.name: WEB_show_unconfigured_revs
preference.preference_description: While navigating in the DHTML UI, you can choose to see all Item Revisions upon Item expansion or only the Revision configured by the current revision rule. Set this preference to 1 to see all revisions, or to 0 to see only the configured revisions.

preference.name: WEB_status_icons
preference.preference_description: Lists the status icons to be displayed in the thin client. Note that the name given here is used to look for an image of the same name. For example, if "my_custom_rel_status" is specified, the image "my_custom_rel_status.png" (or "my_custom_rel_status.gif" for Internet Explorer) is displayed. These files must, therefore, be copied in the directory "TC_ROOT/web/htdocs/tc/webtier_static/teamcenter/dhtml/icons". Once done, re-generate the WAR/EAR file, and deploy it to the web tier.

preference.name: WEB_style_sheet
preference.preference_description: Thin Client style sheet (CSS) currently set

preference.name: WEB_style_sheet_list
preference.preference_description: List of customized alternate stylesheets (CSS files). The style sheet choice is presented to the user in the Thin Client Options dialog, under the Advanced tab. The preference values can be URLs or paths to the CSS files.

preference.name: WEB_style_sheet_list_names
preference.preference_description: List of the display names for the customized alternate stylesheets defined by the WEB_style_sheet_list preference. They must correspond 1 to 1.

preference.name: WEB_title_contents
preference.preference_description: Specifies the contents of web title bar. Valid values are: "application", "object", "user", "group", "role", "site", "rev_rule", "version", "location_code". These values must be on a line by themselves, anything else will be rendered as literal text with single-space separators.

preference.name: WEB_unpackage_multipart
preference.preference_description: Multipart unpackaging. These *must* leave the unpackaged files in the same directory. If this is undefined, then the download and edit do not appear in web pages.

preference.name: WEB_fullsize_image_generate_type
preference.preference_description: List of full-size image types (in MIME format) to be generated.

preference.name: WEB_image_size_horiz
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: WEB_image_size_vert
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: WEB_thumbnail_image_display_type
preference.preference_description: List of thumbnail image types (in MIME format) to be displayed in order of preference, first type found is displayed.

preference.name: WEB_thumbnail_image_generate_type
preference.preference_description: All image types should be specified as MIME type/subtype. examples: (image/jpeg, image/tiff, image/gif, image/cgm, x-world/x-vrml, media/x-3dx, media/x-am3) thumbnail image type (in MIME format) to be generated. Only one type.

preference.name: WEB_Applications_List
preference.preference_description: Lists the applications to be displayed in the Navigation panel of the Teamcenter Web client. The applications are further categorized to be displayed as primary or secondary. The format for valid values is "application_name:[primary|secondary]", where "application_name" is the application name, which can be found in the Web Client file "toolbar.xml", as value of the attribute "name" of the "panel" tag.

preference.name: WEB_DSM_install_link
preference.preference_description: Defines the download URL of the Data Share Manager installer.

preference.name: WEB_Nav_Items_List
preference.preference_description: Lists the items to be displayed in the Navigation panel of the Teamcenter Web client. The items in the panel will be ordered in the same way as they are entered in this preference. Values for this preference are the item names, which can be found in the Web Client file "toolbar.xml", as value of the attribute "id" of the "section" tag.

preference.name: WEB_View_Dataset_Warn_List
preference.preference_description: Lists the file extensions that triggers a displayed warning message when Datasets containing such files are directly opened from the Teamcenter Web client. Values for this preference are the file extensions.

preference.name: WEB_hide_quicklinks
preference.preference_description: Lists the items to be hidden in the "Quick Links" section of the Teamcenter Web client. Values for this preference are the "Quick Links" id names, which can be found in the Web client file "toolbar.xml", as value of the attribute "id" of the "tool" tag.

preference.name: MEIdGenerationAllowDuplicates
preference.preference_description: Allows duplicate values for IDs generated for BOM Line properties based on the "MEIdGenerationPropertySetting" preference. The default value is false.

preference.name: MEIdGenerationInSharedAssembly
preference.preference_description: Some engineering bills of material (EBOMs) contain shared assemblies. The same assembly is used multiple times in the EBOM but only one is configured in and assigned to the manufacturing BOM (MBOM). If you set the MEIDGenerationInSharedAssembly preference to true, at the time of assignment, Teamcenter searches the EBOM for all other visible (configured in by revision rule or any of the Show Unconfigured... buttons) instances of the same assembly and stamps them with the same IDIC.

preference.name: MEIdGenerationOnAssignEnabled
preference.preference_description: Controls whether the preference "MEIdGenerationPropertySetting" will be used to generate absolute occurrence values during assignment action. The default value is false.

preference.name: MEIdGenerationPropertySetting
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of BOM Line properties, for which the values are to be formulated using the specified property values of constituent BOM Lines. This is customizable based on Item type. If the Item type is not found by exact match, the closest parent type will be used. The format is: [type:ItemType,key:KeyEntry(,prop:PropEntry)+] E.g. "type:Item,key:bl_usage_address,prop:bl_item_item_id,prop:bl_item_object_type" means that the values for the property "bl_usage_address" on BOM Lines of type "Item" will be formulated using the values for the properties "bl_item_item_id" and "bl_item_object_type". "type:Item,key:bl_abs_occ_id,prop:bl_item_item_id,prop:bl_plmxml_abs_xform" means that the values for the property "bl_abs_occ_id" on BOM Lines of type "Item" will be formulated using the values for the properties "bl_item_item_id" and "bl_plmxml_abs_xform".

preference.name: ArcWeldRevision_shown_relations
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relations to show when expanding an Arc Weld Revision object (type ArcWeldRevision).

preference.name: DatumPointRevision_shown_relations
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relations to show when expanding a Datum Point Revision object (type DatumPointRevision).

preference.name: MEAssignmentStateEnable
preference.preference_description: Enables the "Assignment State" feature for Resolved Assigned Occurrence objects in Enterprise Bill of Process (EBOP) structures in the Manufacturing application. Valid values are: *false: the "Assignment State" feature is not enabled. This is the default value. *true: the "Assignment State" feature is enabled.

preference.name: MEAssignmentStateInitial
preference.preference_description: Specifies the initial value given to "Assignment State" of Resolved Assigned Occurrence objects during a "Resolve Logical Part Assignments" operation in Enterprise Bill of Process (EBOP) structures in the Manufacturing application. Valid values are: *No State *Pending: this is the default value. *Accepted *Rejected

preference.name: MEConstraintViewPreloadedPredecessorLevels
preference.preference_description: Defines the number of levels of predecessors for the scope object are initially displayed when a new scope is set in the constraints view of the Manufacturing Process Planner application. The default value is 2.

preference.name: MEConstraintViewPreloadedSuccessorLevels
