preference.preference_description: Defines the number of levels of successors for the scope object are initially displayed when a new scope is set in the constraints view of the Manufacturing Process Planner application. The default value is 2.

preference.name: MEMBOM_Mirror_AlignProperties
preference.preference_description: Enables the alignment of properties on "Make" Items and Revisions created in Manufacturing BOM (MBOM), during a mirror operation through the utility "me_create_mbom". These "Make" nodes are of different types compared to the original Engineering BOM (EBOM) nodes. The following formats are allowed (the character ':' is the separator in each of them): * "Relation:<InternalRelationName>:<list of secondary types separated by comma>:<Skip/Reference>" (e.g. Relation:IMAN_Rendering:DirectModel:Reference): These relation types are skipped or referenced on Items and Revisions of the exact specified secondary types (i.e. does not apply to sub-types). If secondary types are not specified, all relations of that type are referenced. * can be used for relation type and/or secondary type wildcard. The "Relation" elements are ordered. * "Item:[InternalEBOMItemType,InternalMBOMItemType:(EBOMInternalPropertyName,MBOMInternalPropertyName)+]" (e.g. "Item:Item,Document:fnd0is_monolithic,fnd0is_monolithic"): The EBOM and MBOM Items for which the underlying property types match, will have their values aligned. * "Revision:[InternalEBOMItemType,InternalMBOMItemType:(EBOMInternalPropertyName,MBOMInternalPropertyName)+]" (e.g. "Revision:ItemRevision,DocumentRevision:ebomRevProp,mbomRevProp"): The EBOM and MBOM Item Revisions for which the underlying property types match, will have their values aligned.

preference.name: MEMBOM_Mirror_Align_Existing_Mbom_Items
preference.preference_description: Defines the alignment of top level context IDs (IDIC) of Manufacturing BOM (MBOM) lines based on their corresponding Engineering BOM (EBOM) lines. Valid values are: * 0: no alignment. This is the default value. * 1: alignment of IDIC values of MBOM lines only for EBOM lines that have an IDIC value. * 2: alignment of IDIC values of MBOM lines using the EBOM lines. If no IDIC value exists on an EBOM node, the Item ID and transform values are used for equivalence.

preference.name: MEMBOM_Mirror_IgnoreRules
preference.preference_description: Defines the BOM Line properties and their corresponding values used to determine the action to undertake on Engineering BOM nodes (when the utility "me_create_mbom" is invoked) for each BOM Line that matches the criteria. Valid values are in the format "KEY:<BOMLinePropertyInternalName>,VALUE:<PropertyValue>,ACTION:<Skip/Traverse>," (e.g. "KEY:GCS CP,VALUE:Phantom,ACTION:Traverse"). If more than one value for a given property can determine the action, the operator OR ('|') can be used as follows: "KEY:<BOMLinePropertyInternalName>,VALUE:<PropertyValue1>,ACTION:<Skip/Traverse>|VALUE:<PropertyValue2>,ACTION:<Skip/Traverse>" (e.g. "KEY:GCS CP,VALUE:Phantom,ACTION:Skip|VALUE:Phantom1,ACTION:Traverse"). The ACTION keyword allows one to skip (Skip action) an EBOM node, or to traverse (Traverse action) below an EBOM node, while ignoring that EBOM node itself. The children of that EBOM node will end up as children of the corresponding MBOM parent. The default action is "Skip".

preference.name: MEMBOM_Mirror_MakeRules
preference.preference_description: Defines the key/value pairs of BOM Line properties and their corresponding values used to determine if a new Manufacturing BOM node is to be created (when the utility "me_create_mbom" is invoked) for each BOM Line that matches the criteria. Valid values are in the format "KEY:<BOMLinePropertyInternalName>,VALUE:<PropertyValue>" (e.g. "KEY:GCS CP,VALUE:Make"). If more than one value for a given property can determine the new "Make" item, the operator OR ('|') can be used as follows: "KEY:<BOMLinePropertyInternalName>,VALUE:<PropertyValue1>|VALUE:<PropertyValue2>" (e.g. "KEY:GCS CP,VALUE:Make|VALUE:Phantom"). If there is no preference value, the item is shared between Engineering BOM (EBOM) and Manufacturing BOM (MBOM) structures.

preference.name: MEMBOM_Mirror_RemoveLineWithIDIC
preference.preference_description: Enables the deletion of Manufacturing BOM (MBOM) Lines that have ID in context value (top level) and that do not match existing Engineering BOM (EBOM) Lines, during MBOM update from EBOM through the utility "me_create_mbom". The default value is false.

preference.name: MEMBOM_Mirror_ReplaceMakeOnChange
preference.preference_description: Enables the removal of Manufacturing BOM (MBOM) Lines that were changed from "Make" to "Buy" in Engineering BOM (EBOM), during MBOM update from EBOM through the utility "me_create_mbom". The default value is false.

preference.name: MEMBOM_Mirror_TypePrefixSuffix
preference.preference_description: Defines the type of item to be used when creating an item in a Manufacturing BOM through the utility "me_create_mbom". It also defines the prefix and suffix for the name of the item instance. Valid values are in the format "ItemType,Prefix,Suffix". The character ',' is the separator. The prefix or the suffix are optional. The default value is "Item,M_".

preference.name: MEMaxOpenViewsSameType
preference.preference_description: Defines how many open structures of any given type the Dynamic Framework applications support. The default value is 10. This is a site preference.

preference.name: MEOperationWeldReportPartsOcc
preference.preference_description: Specifies a list of occurrence types for which parts table in the Process Weld report (Operation page) will be populated.

preference.name: MEOperationWeldReportResourceOcc
preference.preference_description: Specifies a list of occurrence types for which resources table in the Process Weld report (Operation page) will be populated.

preference.name: MEProcessResourcesViewColumnsShownWidthPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the width in pixel of the columns displayed in the "Process Resources" view of Manufacturing Process Planner application, as defined by the "MEProcessResourcesViewDisplayNameColumnsShownPref" preference.

preference.name: MEProcessResourcesViewDisplayNameColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the columns to display in the "Process Resources" view of Manufacturing Process Planner application. Valid values are the ordered list of properties to be displayed as column, using the format "ObjectTypeName.PropertyName", where "ObjectTypeName" is object type name and "PropertyName" is name of property for the object. The default value is false (stamping is disabled).

preference.name: MEProcessWeldReportPartsOcc
preference.preference_description: Specifies a list of occurrence types for which parts table in the Process Weld report (Index page) will be populated.

preference.name: MEProcessWeldReportResourceOcc
preference.preference_description: Specifies a list of occurrence types for which resources table in the Process Weld report (Index page) will be populated.

preference.name: MEReplaceAssemblyInContext_AlignProperties
preference.preference_description: Enables the alignment of properties on Items and Revisions created in Manufacturing BOM (MBOM), during a replace assembly with any item type operation. The following formats are allowed (the character ':' is the separator in each of them): * "Item:[InternalEBOMItemType,InternalMBOMItemType:(EBOMInternalPropertyName,MBOMInternalPropertyName)+]" (e.g. "Item:Item,Document:fnd0is_monolithic,fnd0is_monolithic"): The EBOM and MBOM Items for which the underlying property types match, will have their values aligned. * "Revision:[InternalEBOMItemType,InternalMBOMItemType:(EBOMInternalPropertyName,MBOMInternalPropertyName)+]" (e.g. "Revision:ItemRevision,DocumentRevision:ebomRevProp,mbomRevProp"): The EBOM and MBOM Item Revisions for which the underlying property types match, will have their values aligned.

preference.name: MEResolveBypassICForReleaseStatus
preference.preference_description: Bypasses the changes to be tracked in Incremental Change (IC) context during resolve command in Enterprise Bill of Process (EBOP) structures in the Manufacturing application. Valid values are all the release statuses for which IC needs to be turned off. If the value is "No_Status", IC will be turned off for all structures that are not released. If there is no value or an empty value for this preference, IC will be turned on for every release status and for structures with no release status.

preference.name: ME_angular_tolerance
preference.preference_description: Defines the tolerance value (in degrees) under which small variations in the rotation section of a transform are seen as equal. This value is used to normalize Euler angles of the rotation vector to the closest integer (floor). The default value is 0.1 degree.

preference.name: ME_reuse_assm_xform_precision
preference.preference_description: Allows the customer to set the precision for transformation values to be used to find patterns in the Manufacturing BOM shared assembly module. Transformation values with differences smaller than the specified precision will be treated as identical when comparing. The default value is 1e-6.

preference.name: ME_translation_tolerance
preference.preference_description: Defines the tolerance value (in millimeters) under which small variations in the translation section of a transform are seen as equal. This value is used to normalize translation vector to the closest integer (floor). The default value is 0.001 mm.

preference.name: Mfg0TCContextFeatureFormRel_relation_primary
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of valid primary object types for the relation Context Feature Form Relation (TCContextFeatureFormRel).

preference.name: OccurrenceGroup_Expansion_EXCLUDETYPES
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of object types not to be displayed in Manufacturing "Expand To Type" dialog when the structure is of type "Occurrence Group". For a given value, its associated subtypes will also to be considered for the exclusion.

preference.name: ProcessStationForAutomatedMfgAssignment
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of object types and their properties that are supported by the "Automated Manufacturing Feature Assignment" operation in the Process Structure application. Valid values are in the format "TypeInternalName:PropertyInternalName". The default values are "MEProcess:Mfg0allocated_time" and "Mfg0MEProcStatn:Mfg0allocated_time".

preference.name: ProductStructure_Expansion_EXCLUDETYPES
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of object types not to be displayed in Manufacturing "Expand To Type" dialog when the structure is of type "Product Structure". For a given value, its associated subtypes will also to be considered for the exclusion.

preference.name: TC_suppress_report_designs
preference.preference_description: Preference for Hiding of Reports

preference.name: WEB_MELocateCompOp_Reports
preference.preference_description: Preference for CD Lead sheet to be fired from MELocateCompOp Process while generating ebop Reports

preference.name: WEB_MEPrPlantProcess_Reports
preference.preference_description: Preference for MEPrPlantProcess Process while generating ebop Reports

preference.name: WEB_MEWeldOp_Reports
preference.preference_description: Preference for MEWeldOp Process while generating ebop Reports

preference.name: WEB_StationProcess_Reports
preference.preference_description: Preference for MEPrStatnProcess Process while generating ebop Reports

preference.name: WEB_ZoneProcess_Reports
preference.preference_description: Preference for MEPrZoneProcess Process while generating ebop Reports

preference.name: WeldTimeForAutomatedMfgAssignment
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of Manufacturing Feature object types and their properties that are supported by the "Automated Manufacturing Feature Assignment" operation in the Process Structure application. Valid values are in the format "TypeInternalName:PropertyInternalName".

preference.name: WEB_max_search_results
preference.preference_description: The default number of objects for the Search page to load before giving up.

preference.name: CM_change_derivations
preference.preference_description: Defines the type of change to create from a given source type during the Derive Change process. The format for valid values is "source_type/derived_type", where: source_type is the type of change from which to derive change, and derived_type is the type of change which will be created. This is a site preference only.

preference.name: TC_audit_manager
preference.preference_description: Activates auditing. Valid values are: * ON: The auditing mechanism is enabled. This is the default value. * OFF: The mechanism is turned off.

preference.name: TC_audit_avoid_delegation_for_audit_access
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of Audit Log types for which the default audit log access delegation mechanism is disabled. For these types, the access rights defined in the Access Manager application apply. Valid values are Audit Log types (for example Fnd0OrganizationAudit, Fnd0GeneralAudit).

preference.name: TC_audit_batch_size
preference.preference_description: Specifies the number of audit records to be inserted into the database in a single batch call. The records are buffered and inserted at the end of SOA or thin client call. If the batch size is exceeded within the SOA or thin client call, then the limit number of records are written and the remaining ones are accumulated again. The default size is 5 (minimum is 1, maximum is 20).

preference.name: TC_audit_buffer_size
preference.preference_description: Specifies the maximum number of audit records in the buffer.

preference.name: TC_audit_delimiter
preference.preference_description: Specifies the delimiter for text file format. It is only used when TC_audit_file_format=0. Although it is not enforced, usually the delimiter is single character because some spreadsheet programs such as Excel do not allow multiple character delimiter. If the delimiter is changed to other than ^, the user also needs to manually modify the delimiter in the first line of TcAuditLog.txt.

preference.name: TC_audit_display_gmt
preference.preference_description: Specifies if logged dates in audit logs are displayed in GMT time zone. Valid values are: true or false. true - Logged dates are in GMT time zone. false - Logged dates are in local server time zone. This is the default value.

preference.name: TC_audit_file_format
preference.preference_description: Specifies the audit file format. Valid values are 0/1. 0 - Indicates text format(.txt). 1 - Indicates XML format(.xml).

preference.name: TC_audit_log_dir
preference.preference_description: Specifies the audit log directory.

preference.name: TC_audit_manager_version
preference.preference_description: Activates a particular version of auditing. Valid values are: * 1 - Legacy auditing mechanism is enabled * 2 - Audit Manager is enabled * 3 - New Audit Manager is enabled. This is the default value.

preference.name: TC_audit_number_of_logs_to_load
preference.preference_description: Specifies the maximum number of audit records to be displayed.

preference.name: TC_audit_track_changed_properties_only
preference.preference_description: Specifies if audit logs should be written when there are no changes in any tracked attribute value. This applies only to "Modify" event type. Valid values are: true - Audit logs are written only when a tracked attribute value changes. false - Audit logs are written irrespective of changes in tracked attributes' value.

preference.name: Default_Transient_Server
preference.preference_description: FMS uses this preference to set the default transient file server for the site. This is a URL to an FSC, used for the 4-tier transient volumes. This should point to a valid address of a deployed FSC that has access to the transient volume. OS Environment variable settings override the preference.

preference.name: FMS_SAF_Batch_Transfer_Enabled
preference.preference_description: Enables FMS Store and Forward in batch transfer mode. Valid values are true or false (default value).

preference.name: Fms_BootStrap_Urls
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of FSC Bootstrap servers. Starting with V10, FMS is being used by Multi-Site to transfer bulk data files between sites which are V10 or greater. During the local import phase when pulling data via a remote import, or during the import phase at this site when it is the target site to which data is being pushed from another site (via the data_sync utility for example), FMS servers will be used to transfer the bulk data files involved. Check with your site admin or FMS installer to get hostname(s) and port number(s) of the appropriate FSC "Bootstrap Servers" for this site. For example, if your nearest FSC server is running on a host named hostabc and listening on port 4447, the value for this preference can be defined as http://hostabc:4447.

preference.name: TC_Store_and_Forward
preference.preference_description: Indicates that FMS Store and Forward should be enabled. Valid values are TRUE/FALSE.

preference.name: TC_Store_and_Forward_Transfer_Delay
preference.preference_description: Indicates the amount of time in minutes that the FMS Store and Forward transfer task should be delayed. This keeps quickly purged versions from being transferred.

preference.name: Ticket_Expiration_Interval
preference.preference_description: FMS uses this time interval in seconds to set the ticket expiration time. If this value is not set the ticket expiration interval is set to 28800 seconds (8 hrs) by default.

preference.name: Transient_Volume_RootDir
preference.preference_description: This preference is defined as a multivalue preference, to support a Unix and Windows NT heterogeneous site. FMS will use the first value which is valid for the platform, Unix or NT, where the validity check is simply the presence or absence of a backslash \ character. This preference is used with both 2 tier and 4 tier. For 4 tier you have to additionally configure transient volume FSC process. Also for 4 tier the process owner for transient volume FSC process and tcserver should be the same owner.

preference.name: DM_Write_Ticket_Expiration_Interval
preference.preference_description: Determine the time interval (in seconds) used by FMS (File Management System) in order to set the Download Manager write ticket expiration time. If this value is not set, the ticket expiration interval is set to 259200 seconds (72 hrs) by default.

preference.name: Multisite_Ticket_Expiration_Interval
preference.preference_description: FMS uses this time interval in seconds to set the multisite ticket expiration time. If this value is not set the ticket expiration interval is set to 259200 seconds (72 hrs) by default.

preference.name: TC_Cache_Allowed
preference.preference_description: Indicates if local file caching is enabled or not.

preference.name: TC_Cache_Protection
preference.preference_description: Indicates the operating system protection applied to the files stored in the file cache.

preference.name: TC_Volume_Failover_Trigger
preference.preference_description: Indicates the % full of a volume at which the failover volume will be used for new file imports.

preference.name: TC_Volume_Failover_Volume_Map
preference.preference_description: Specifies a mapping of failover (alternate) volumes for one or more volumes in the system. This can be used in cases when a volume has been marked as read-only or otherwise inaccessible for new write operations. Specifying the alternate volume here would ensure that future writes are done to this alternate volume rather than the currently set volume. Each value should be in the format "SourceVolume:DestinationVolume". The mappings can be cascaded such that an entry of the form VolA:VolB and VolB:VolC would indicate that the system should use VolC when VolA is the current volume.

preference.name: TC_Volume_Failover_Volume_Name
preference.preference_description: Indicates the failover volume. If this is not set, volume failover is not enabled.

preference.name: TC_Volume_Status_Resync_Interval
preference.preference_description: Indicates the minimum amount of time in seconds before the volume status information is refreshed from FMS.

preference.name: Ticket_Expiration_Resolution
preference.preference_description: Indicates the resolution (minimum amount of time in seconds) before the FMS ticket expiration is changed. Setting this value advances the computed expiration time up to the value set, and limits the change in expiration time by the resolution. This value can be used to improve performance of browser client applications that render files stored in FMS such as thumbnails. This value should not be large and should not be larger than the normal ticket expiration intervals. If this value is not set, a default of 7200 seconds is used.

preference.name: blobbyVolume_NT
preference.preference_description: Alternate Volume Location to allow 24x7 Teamcenter availabity during Hot backup. Limit the string length of directory to 32 bytes.

preference.name: blobbyVolume_UNX
preference.preference_description: Alternate Volume Location to allow 24x7 Teamcenter availability during Hot backup. Limit the string length of directory to 32 bytes.

preference.name: TC_Journalling
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the calls to the ITK are to be logged. Valid values are ON/OFF. The data is written to <program>.jnl

preference.name: TC_allow_inherited_group_volume_access
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: TC_sfr_process_life_time
preference.preference_description: Set default value for Maximum Life time (in X minutes) of User initiated SingleFileRecovery process for recovery of files.

preference.name: TC_sfr_recovery_interval
preference.preference_description: Set default value for User initiated SingleFileRecovery process to check for recovered files every X seconds.

preference.name: Create_Subscription_mru_list
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of the most recently used types for Subscription creation.

preference.name: Create_Subscription_mru_max
preference.preference_description: Defines the maximum number of the list of most recently used types for Subscription creation, as captured in the preference "Create_Subscription_mru_list". A valid value is a strictly positive integer.

preference.name: SCM_execution_day
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default execution day if the preference "SCM_execution_frequency" is set to "Weekly". Valid values are days of week, with the allowed values being "Sunday","Monday","Tuesday","Wednesday","Thursday","Friday","Saturday".

preference.name: SCM_execution_frequency
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default subscription execution frequency, when the event will be processed by the subscription manager or action manager daemon. Valid values are: 1. Weekly 2. Immediately 3. Daily

preference.name: SCM_execution_time
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default execution time if the preference "SCM_execution_frequency" is set to "Weekly" or "Daily". The value shall be in the format "hh:mm", with hours in the 24-hour format.

preference.name: SCM_expiration_date
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default number of days before the subscription expires. A valid value is a positive integer. If the value is empty (default value), Subscriptions never expire.

preference.name: SCM_notification_mode
preference.preference_description: Specifies the delivery mode of Subscription notifications. Valid values are: *1 : Delivered as SMTP email. This is the default value. *2 : Delivered in the user's Teamcenter inbox. *3 : Delivered in both.

preference.name: SCM_notify_new_recipients
preference.preference_description: Activates sending e-mails or Message notifications to users added as recipients to Subscriptions. The preference SCM_notification_mode indicates the method of notification. The default value is false (nothing sent).

preference.name: TC_notification_msg_ext
preference.preference_description: Specifies the file extension for the notification file in the Subscription Manager application. For notifications to be sent as html formatted emails, valid values are txt, htm, html, HTM and HTML.

preference.name: TC_subscription_limit_class_based_notifications
preference.preference_description: Restricts posting of events by class-based Subscription objects to only when one of the criteria properties is modified as part of the event action. This restriction only applies to Modify events. When set to "false", posting of events is not limited. This is the default value.

preference.name: SCM_notification_history
preference.preference_description: Indicates if history record notification emails are being sent (true) or not (false).

preference.name: TC_actionmgrd_sleep_minutes
preference.preference_description: Defines the number of minutes in the sleep period of the "actionmgrd" process daemon between the dispatching of Subscription events. Low values can be used when a large number of events are expected, or to ensure events are processed close to their scheduled time. Large values can be used if few events are expected and their execution time is of lower importance. Valid values are a positive integer up to 1440 (the number of minutes in a 24-hour day).

preference.name: TC_subscription
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the Subscription mechanism is to be enabled or disabled. Valid values are ON/OFF. ON - Enable the subscription manager. OFF - Disable the subscription manager module.

preference.name: TC_subscription_log_event_and_action_status
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the status of TcEvent, TcAction objects are to be logged into the log file. Valid values are ON/OFF. It is recommended to turn ON this preference only for trouble shooting.

preference.name: ImanSubscription_ColumnPreferences
preference.preference_description: The list of property names to be displayed as columns in ImanSubscription table.

preference.name: ImanSubscription_ColumnWidthPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths of the shown columns in ImanSubscription table.

preference.name: Mail_subscription_notify_sub_groups_too
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the sub-groups are to be notified for subscription notification. Valid values are TRUE/FALSE. TRUE - Notify sub-groups also for subscription notification.

preference.name: SCM_notification_WorkspaceObject_props
preference.preference_description: Defines the default properties to be included in notification emails.

preference.name: TC_subscription_available_subscription_handlers
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of Action Handlers that the user can select when creating a Subscription object from a client. If the handler does not appear in this list, the user cannot select it as part of a Subscription. Valid values are the IDs of the handlers. If no handlers are specified, the handler "IMAN_Smtp_Mail_Notify" will be used by default. This handler will always be included even if it is not present in the list.

preference.name: TcActionColumnPreferences
preference.preference_description: The list of property names to be displayed as columns in TcAction table.

preference.name: TcActionColumnWidthPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths of the shown columns in TcAction table.

preference.name: TcEventColumnPreferences
preference.preference_description: The list of property names to be displayed as columns in TcEvent table.

preference.name: TcEventColumnWidthPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths of the shown columns in TcEvent table.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityCheckAllowableReturnedLines
preference.preference_description: Specifies the maximum number of lines that can be returned by accountability check. This includes all the source and target lines to be colored, as well as their parent lines. The default value is 10000.

preference.name: MECreateIdInContextforAssignedchildlines
preference.preference_description: Defines in-context IDs (IDICs) for child lines up to the specified level. When structure lines with children are copied from an engineering BOM (EBOM) to a manufacturing BOM (MBOM), the IDIC is created for the parent line only. If the parent line is deleted in the MBOM, all its children move up one level in the hierarchy but do not have any IDIC assigned to them. When you run an accountability check, these child lines are mistakenly displayed as missing in target. To rectify this problem, set this preference to a meaningful number of levels.

preference.name: MEMCN_management_enabled
preference.preference_description: Enables the Change Notice Revision related commands to be shown in "Manufacturing Process Planner" application. The default value is false.

preference.name: MEMCN_previous_effectivity_is_mandatory
preference.preference_description: Activates the mandatory presence of the previous effectivity on a ChangeNoticeRevision object. The default value is true.

preference.name: MEMCN_release_bvr_with_rev
preference.preference_description: Enables the release of a BOMViewRevision when an ItemRevision is released, only when changes in the BOMWindow are being tracked with ChangeNoticeRevisions. The default value is true.

preference.name: MEMCN_release_revision_mode
preference.preference_description: Controls how statuses are created on ItemRevisions being tracked by a Change Notice Revision. The "preferred" ReleaseStatus will be one of statuses in preference "MEMCN_release_statuses" that is found on the ChangeNoticeRevision. Valid values are (case sensitive): * Share: The ItemRevisions share the "preferred" status with the ChangeNoticeRevision. * None: The ItemRevisions will not get a status. * ShareEffectivityOnly: The ItemRevisions will each have a new ReleaseStatus, all of which will share Effectivity with the Change Notice Revision "preferred" ReleaseStatus. * Clone: The ItemRevisions will get new ReleaseStatuses and Effectivities that are clones of the "preferred" ReleaseStatus. The default value is Share.

preference.name: MEMCN_release_statuses
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of mutually exclusive Release Statuses internal names that must be associated to a ChangeNoticeRevision associated to a Bill of Material (BOM) Window. There must be only one of these statuses on the ChangeNoticeRevision at any stage. The default values are "Pending" and "TCM Released". These could be replaced with appropriate values as per business needs: e.g.if using the cmtmes template, these could be replaced with "Mei0PendingRelease", "Mei0Released", "Mei0WorkInProgress".

preference.name: MEMCN_solution_object_collection_rule
preference.preference_description: Defines the closure rule for collecting the children of a newly created/pasted BOM Line for use with ChangeNoticeRevision.

preference.name: MENEWMFG_DefaultDatumJTDatasetName
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the JT dataset which is by default attached to every newly created Datum object. Valid values are in the format: "datum_type:control_direction:dataset_name". Possible values for the "datum_type" are SphereDatum, PinDatum, MeasurementDatum. In Teamcenter 8.3, the "control_direction" portion is always "default". The value for the "dataset_name" portion depends on the "datum_type" and the "control_direction" sections.

preference.name: MENEWMFG_DefaultJTDatasetNameForSpecificWeldType
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the JT dataset which is by default attached to the specific type of newly created Weld Point object. Valid values are in the format: "weld_type:number_of_connected_parts:dataset_name". Possible values for the "weld_type" are Geo, Process, Respot. Possible values for the "number_of_connected_parts" are <2, 2, 3, 4, >4 The value for the "dataset_name" portion depends on the "weld_type" section.

preference.name: MENEWMFG_DefaultWeldPointJTDatasetName
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the JT dataset which is by default attached with every newly created Weld Point object.

preference.name: NX_supported_operation_types
preference.preference_description: List of MEOP types that are supported in the NXCAM/TCM integration.

preference.name: ACBatchPropagation_AdditionalAccountabilityCheckProperties
preference.preference_description: Additional list of properties for accountability check asynchronous propagation. The user can choose to ignore this list from the UI.

preference.name: ACBatchReport_AdditionalAccountabilityCheckProperties
preference.preference_description: Additional list of properties for accountability check asynchronous report generation. The user can choose to ignore this list from the UI.

preference.name: AbsOccData_ProcessSimulatePLCDetails_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default relation created between the 2 objects, when pasting an object of type "ProcessSimulatePLCDetails" under an Absolute Occurrence Data. It will be the default relation created between the object and the target Absolute Occurrence Data.

preference.name: AbsOccData_ProcessSimulatePLCInfo_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default relation created between the 2 objects, when pasting an object of type "ProcessSimulatePLCInfo" under an Absolute Occurrence Data. It will be the default relation created between the object and the target Absolute Occurrence Data.

preference.name: AbsOccData_ProcessSimulatePLCModuleInf_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default relation created between the 2 objects, when pasting an object of type "ProcessSimulatePLCModuleInf" under an Absolute Occurrence Data. It will be the default relation created between the object and the target Absolute Occurrence Data.

preference.name: AbsOccData_ProcessSimulatePLCPr_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default relation created between the 2 objects, when pasting an object of type "ProcessSimulatePLCPr" under an Absolute Occurrence Data. It will be the default relation created between the object and the target Absolute Occurrence Data.

preference.name: AbsOccData_ProcessSimulatePLCResConTab_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default relation created between the 2 objects, when pasting an object of type "ProcessSimulatePLCResConTab" under an Absolute Occurrence Data. It will be the default relation created between the object and the target Absolute Occurrence Data.

preference.name: AbsOccData_ProcessSimulatePLCRobotPrgm_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default relation created between the 2 objects, when pasting an object of type "ProcessSimulatePLCRobotPrgm" under an Absolute Occurrence Data. It will be the default relation created between the object and the target Absolute Occurrence Data.

preference.name: AbsOccData_ProcessSimulatePLCSignalTab_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default relation created between the 2 objects, when pasting an object of type "ProcessSimulatePLCSignalTab" under an Absolute Occurrence Data. It will be the default relation created between the object and the target Absolute Occurrence Data.

preference.name: AbsOccData_ProcessSimulatePLCToolInfo_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default relation created between the 2 objects, when pasting an object of type "ProcessSimulatePLCToolInfo" under an Absolute Occurrence Data. It will be the default relation created between the object and the target Absolute Occurrence Data.

preference.name: AccountabilityCheckUseRollUpQuantity
preference.preference_description: Activates Accountability Check to count equivalent lines based on the number of lines, their Quantity property value, and their parent's Quantities, in order to determine if they are full or multiple matches. When set to false, the count is based on the number of BOMLines, including packed lines but otherwise not taking the Quantity property into account. The default value is true.

preference.name: Activity.Template
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of rules to be used when cloning an Activity in the Manufacturing Process Planner application.

preference.name: Activity_Default_Duration_Time
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default duration time for the new activities. These new activities are created for instance through the "New Activity" window in the MSE application.

preference.name: AdditionalAccountabilityCheckProperties
preference.preference_description: Additional list of properties for accountability checks. The user can choose to ignore this list from the UI.

preference.name: AppInterface_TCPublishingTechnicalPortfolio_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default relation when a TCPublishingTechnicalPortfolio is pasted under an AppInterface. The relation specified for this preference will be the default relation that will be created between the source and the target AppInterface.

preference.name: AppInterface_TCPublishingTechnicalPortfolio_shown_relations
preference.preference_description: List of relations for TCPublishingTechnicalPortfolio on expanding an AppInterface.

preference.name: Baseline_omitted_occurrence_types
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of occurrence types for which baseline would not be performed. This list can be empty.

preference.name: CCApplication_open_collaboration_panel
preference.preference_description: Determines if the Collaboration panel is displayed when the CC application opens.

preference.name: CCObject_ColumnPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of columns to be displayed for objects of type CCObject.

preference.name: CCObject_ColumnWidthPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths of the columns for the column names as defined in CCObject_ColumnPreferences preference.

preference.name: CC_ExtraPLMXMLInstanceAttributes
preference.preference_description: Defines any additional options to be used when exporting a Tool Design Package to NX, or when using the "cc_writer" command line utility. The format is: [target:Instance(,key:KeyEntry, prop:PropEntry)+][,][target:Part(,key:KeyEntry,prop:PropEntry)+] Where: * KeyEntry: string that appears as "title" attribute in plmxml for UserValue element. * PropEntry: string that appears as "value" attribute in plmxml for UserValue element. An example of multi-entries value would be: "target:Instance,key:__PLM_CLONE_STABLE_INST_UID,prop:bl_clone_stable_occurrence_id,key:__PLM_APPUID,prop:bl_apn_uid,target:Part,key:__PLM_OBJECT_NAME,prop:object_name"

preference.name: ConfigureOutParentProcess
preference.preference_description: This preference is obsolete and replaced by the preference "typeAndRuleForProcessConfiguration". Configures Parent processes depending on their child occurrences. Accepted values are: * true: The parent process will be configured out if all of its children operations or subprocesses are configured out. This is the default value. * false: The parent process will not be configured out.

preference.name: CopyPasteTemplates
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rule names to be used when pasting processes, operations and partitions within Enterprise Bill Of Process(EBOP) structures Or Study structures.

preference.name: Cps0ConnectivityDefRel_relation_primary
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of valid primary object types for the relation Cps0ConnectivityDefRel.

preference.name: Cps0LBRel_relation_primary
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of valid primary object types for the relation Cps0LBRel.

preference.name: Cps0ModulesInfoRel_relation_primary
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of valid primary object types for the relation Cps0ModulesInfoRel.

preference.name: Cps0OpDetailsRel_relation_primary
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of valid primary object types for the relation Cps0OpDetailsRel.

preference.name: Cps0PLCInfoRel_relation_primary
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of valid primary object types for the relation Cps0PLCInfoRel.

preference.name: Cps0PortsDefRel_relation_primary
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of valid primary object types for the relation Cps0PortsDefRel.

preference.name: Cps0PropertiesRel_relation_primary
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of valid primary object types for the relation Cps0PropertiesRel.

preference.name: Cps0RobotProgRel_relation_primary
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of valid primary object types for the relation Cps0RobotProgRel.

preference.name: Cps0SensorDetVolumeRel_relation_primary
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of valid primary object types for the relation Cps0SensorDetVolumeRel.

preference.name: Cps0SignalDefRel_relation_primary
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of valid primary object types for the relation Cps0SignalDefRel.

preference.name: Cps0ToolInfoRel_relation_primary
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of valid primary object types for the relation Cps0ToolInfoRel.

preference.name: DefaultAccountabilityCheckProperties
preference.preference_description: Lists all the default properties that are used for accountability check ("Intermediate Data Capture").

preference.name: Default_Collaboration_Context_Type
preference.preference_description: Determines which type of Collaboration Context will be the default for a specific application. Accepts one or more strings as values; each string must be a valid one of the following format: <application_name>:<CollaborationContext_type>.

preference.name: Default_StructureContext_Type
preference.preference_description: Determines which type of Structure Context will be the default for an item type. Accepts one or more strings as values; each string must be a valid one of the following format: <Item_type>:<StructureContext_type>.

preference.name: EndItemState
preference.preference_description: Controls the End Item state in the Manufacturing Process Planner (MPP) and Product Structure Engineering (PSE) applications. Valid values are : * true: the "End Item" dialog is displayed in the Edit menu, and the End Item icon appears when an End Item is set on a line's occurrence. This is the default value. * false: the "End Item" functionality is totally hidden.

preference.name: FindCheckedOutColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the columns to display in the dialog of the "Find Checked Out Items" command. Valid values are the names of each column in the order you wish them to appear: value_1, value_2.

preference.name: FindCheckedOutColumnsShownWidthPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the width of the columns displayed in the dialog of the "Find Checked Out Objects" command, as defined by the "FindCheckedOutColumnsShownPref" preference.

preference.name: GCS_classify_type
preference.preference_description: Identifies whether item or item revisions shall be created and classified for components with CPs. Supported values are Item and ItemRevision. It's recommended that this be set to ItemRevision.

preference.name: GDT_formtypes
preference.preference_description: Activates geometric dimensioning and tolerance (GDT) symbols for Teamcenter objects of any sub-type of Form (e.g. "Master Form"). Once a value is given for this preference, the properties that may contain GDT symbols are defined through the "GDT_properties" preference. Valid values are the internal names of any sub-type of Form.

preference.name: GDT_properties
preference.preference_description: Indicates the properties that may contain geometric dimensioning and tolerance (GDT) symbols. The icons associated to GDT symbols addition will be displayed next to the properties fields, provided the property is not a list of values (LOV). Valid values are the properties internal names for the sub-types of Form specified in the preference "GDT_formtypes".

preference.name: GenericBOPAllowedTemplates
preference.preference_description: List of cloning rules to be used when cloning GenericBOP to other BOPs.

preference.name: GenericBOPTemplate
preference.preference_description: Cloning rules to be used when creating a ProductBOP from GenericBOP structure.

preference.name: IPA_OG_postfix
preference.preference_description: Defines the postfix added to the name of a new In Process Assembly Occurrence Group process name.

preference.name: Item.Item.CopyAssemblyInContext
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rules to be used for copying an assembly where the type of source Item is "Item" and target item type is "Item". The syntax allows for different rules and different combinations of item types. Typically, in this case the children are cloned.

preference.name: Item.Item.DuplicateAssemblyInContext
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rule names to be used when copying a subassembly within a Bill Of Material(BOM) structures.

preference.name: Item.Item.PasteDuplicateTemplate
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rules to be used when the "Paste Duplicate" operation is used to create new instances in a Product Bill of Material (BOM) starting from a BOM.

preference.name: Item.Item.ReplaceAssemblyInContext
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rule names to be used when replacing a subassembly within a Bill Of Material(BOM) structures.

preference.name: ItemRevision.Item.PasteDuplicateTemplate
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rules to be used when the "Paste Duplicate" operation is used to create new instances of classified object in a Product Bill of Material (BOM) starting from a Classification. Valid values are in the format: "primary:secondary:attribute_key.attribute_value:action", where: * the primary can be * for any class, class.<class name> for specific class or type.<type name> for specific type. * the secondary is the same format as primary * the attribute_key must be one of the following: Attribute, OccType, Relation. If the value is Attribute, the attribute_value must be the name of an attribute on the primary object. If the value is OccType, the attibute_value must be Null (no Occurrence Type) or * (any Occurrence Type) or the name of specific Occurrence Type. If the value is Relation, the attribute_value must be the internal name of a Relation Type. * the action must be one of the following: Clone, Reference or Ignore.

preference.name: ItemRevision.MEOP.PasteDuplicateTemplate
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rules to be used when the "Paste Duplicate" operation is used to create new instances of classified object in a Operation starting from a Classification. Valid values are in the format: "primary:secondary:attribute_key.attribute_value:action", where: * the primary can be * for any class, class.<class name> for specific class or type.<type name> for specific type. * the secondary is the same format as primary * the attribute_key must be one of the following: Attribute, OccType, Relation. If the value is Attribute, the attribute_value must be the name of an attribute on the primary object. If the value is OccType, the attibute_value must be Null (no Occurrence Type) or * (any Occurrence Type) or the name of specific Occurrence Type. If the value is Relation, the attribute_value must be the internal name of a Relation Type. * the action must be one of the following: Clone, Reference or Ignore.

preference.name: ItemRevision.MEProcess.PasteDuplicateTemplate
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rules to be used when the "Paste Duplicate" operation is used to create new instances of classified object in a Bill of Processes (BOP) starting from a Classification. Valid values are in the format: "primary:secondary:attribute_key.attribute_value:action", where: * the primary can be * for any class, class.<class name> for specific class or type.<type name> for specific type. * the secondary is the same format as primary * the attribute_key must be one of the following: Attribute, OccType, Relation. If the value is Attribute, the attribute_value must be the name of an attribute on the primary object. If the value is OccType, the attibute_value must be Null (no Occurrence Type) or * (any Occurrence Type) or the name of specific Occurrence Type. If the value is Relation, the attribute_value must be the internal name of a Relation Type. * the action must be one of the following: Clone, Reference or Ignore.

preference.name: ItemRevision.MEWorkarea.PasteDuplicateTemplate
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rules to be used when the "Paste Duplicate" operation is used to create new instances of classified object in a Plant Structure starting from a Classification. Valid values are in the format: "primary:secondary:attribute_key.attribute_value:action", where: * the primary can be * for any class, class.<class name> for specific class or type.<type name> for specific type. * the secondary is the same format as primary * the attribute_key must be one of the following: Attribute, OccType, Relation. If the value is Attribute, the attribute_value must be the name of an attribute on the primary object. If the value is OccType, the attibute_value must be Null (no Occurrence Type) or * (any Occurrence Type) or the name of specific Occurrence Type. If the value is Relation, the attribute_value must be the internal name of a Relation Type. * the action must be one of the following: Clone, Reference or Ignore.

preference.name: ItemRevisionColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of columns that will be displayed for the BOM tree table in Collaboration Manufacturing Engineering applications.

preference.name: ItemRevisionDisplayNameColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Stores the internal names of BOM Line properties which display names appear as columns from left-to-right for Product Structure objects in Collaboration Manufacturing Engineering applications. This preference value is only a repository, and it is not to be modified other than by the code itself.

preference.name: ItemRevisionOccGroupColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of columns that will be displayed for occurrence group tab of Product Structure objects in Collaboration Manufacturing Engineering applications.

preference.name: ItemRevisionOccGroupDisplayNameColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Stores the internal names of BOM Line properties which display names appear as columns from left-to-right for occurrence group tab of Product Structure objects in Collaboration Manufacturing Engineering applications. This preference value is only a repository, and it is not to be modified other than by the code itself.

preference.name: ItemRevisionOccGroupShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the column widths for the columns (identified by MEProductContextOccGroupColumnsShownPref) displayed for occurrence group tab of Product Structure objects within the Collaboration Manufacturing Engineering applications.

preference.name: ItemRevisionShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the column widths for the columns (identified by MEProductContextColumnsShownPref) displayed in the BOM tree table within the Collaboration Manufacturing Engineering applications.

preference.name: ItemRevision_ProcessSimulatePLCDetails_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default relation created between the 2 objects, when pasting an object of type "ProcessSimulatePLCDetails" under an Item Revision. It will be the default relation created between the object and the target Item Revision.

preference.name: ItemRevision_ProcessSimulatePLCInfo_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default relation created between the 2 objects, when pasting an object of type "ProcessSimulatePLCInfo" under an Item Revision. It will be the default relation created between the object and the target Item Revision.

preference.name: ItemRevision_ProcessSimulatePLCLB_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default relation created between the 2 objects, when pasting an object of type "ProcessSimulatePLCLB" under an Item Revision. It will be the default relation created between the object and the target Item Revision.

preference.name: ItemRevision_ProcessSimulatePLCModuleInf_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default relation created between the 2 objects, when pasting an object of type "ProcessSimulatePLCModuleInf" under an Item Revision. It will be the default relation created between the object and the target Item Revision.

preference.name: ItemRevision_ProcessSimulatePLCPr_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default relation created between the 2 objects, when pasting an object of type "ProcessSimulatePLCPr" under an Item Revision. It will be the default relation created between the object and the target Item Revision.

preference.name: ItemRevision_ProcessSimulatePLCResPortTa_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default relation created between the 2 objects, when pasting an object of type "ProcessSimulatePLCResPortTa" under an Item Revision. It will be the default relation created between the object and the target Item Revision.

preference.name: ItemRevision_ProcessSimulatePLCSenDtVlPr_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default relation created between the 2 objects, when pasting an object of type "ProcessSimulatePLCSenDtVlPr" under an Item Revision. It will be the default relation created between the object and the target Item Revision.

preference.name: ItemRevision_TCPublishingPage_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relation that has to be created when a TCPublishingPage is pasted under an ItemRevision. The relation specified for this preference will be the default relation that will be created between the TCPublishingPage and the target ItemRevision.

preference.name: MEAPCSearchType
preference.preference_description: Defines the type of the parts that are going to be searched by the Automatic Part Connector.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityCheckEnableFilteringRules
preference.preference_description: Determines whether the menu for the filtering rule verification should be enabled or not.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityCheckEnableNetEffectivity
preference.preference_description: Determines whether the net effectivities will be compared during accountability check partial match.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityCheckIncludedActivityProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the default list of properties to be included when comparing equivalent activities for partial match.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityCheckParentDelimiterInHierarchy
preference.preference_description: Defines the delimiter to separate the parents of a BOMLine in the hierarchy from root.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityCheckPropertiesInHierarchy
preference.preference_description: Lists the BOMLine properties to be concatenated for each parent in the value of the property "Hierarchy From Root" (mfg0BlHierarchyFromRoot), which is a concatenation of all parents of a BOMLine.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityCheckPropertyDelimiterInHierarchy
preference.preference_description: Defines the delimiter to separate the properties of a parent BOMLine in the hierarchy from root.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityCheckReportProperties
preference.preference_description: Lists the BOM Line properties to be added as columns to the Accountability Check excel report for each source line. Cells in the column contain the value of the property for each BOM Line.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityCheckSourceStructureExpansionFilterRules
preference.preference_description: Provides a list of closure rule names to be used for source structure traversal for accountability check.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityCheckTargetStructureExpansionFilterRules
preference.preference_description: Provides a list of closure rule names to be used for target structure traversal for accountability check.

preference.name: MEAccountabilityMarkBrokenLinksClosureRule
preference.preference_description: Defines the name of the closure rule used by the "Mark Broken Links" command in the Manufacturing Process Planner application, used to find broken links in Process structures. The default value is "MarkBrokenLinks".

preference.name: MEAccountabilityMarkBrokenLinksColor
preference.preference_description: Specifies the background color used by the "Mark Broken Links" command in the Manufacturing Process Planner application, to mark broken link lines. A valid value is the RGB (Red-Green-Blue) code of the color, where each value is an integer from 0 to 255. The value separator is the ',' character. The default value is "255,0,0".

preference.name: MEAccountabilityMarkBrokenLinksCountTrigger
preference.preference_description: Specifies the minimum number of broken links that causes an information panel to be displayed by the "Mark Broken Links" command in the Manufacturing Process Planner application. The panel shows the total number of broken links found by the command. The default value is "10".

preference.name: MEAccountabilityMarkInBaseViewColor
preference.preference_description: Specifies the background color used by the "Mark In Base View" command in the Manufacturing Process Planner application, to mark BOM Lines. A valid value is the RGB (Red-Green-Blue) code of the color, where each value is an integer from 0 to 255. The value separator is the ',' character. The default value is "153,153,255".

preference.name: MEAccountabilityUseCacheless
preference.preference_description: Activates the speed-up of the "Accountability Check" in the command "Check." of the applications Manufacturing Process Planner and Multi Structure Manager, when part of a BOM source is compared to an entire Bill Of Processes (BOP) target, and the option "Missing in Source" is not being selected. This functionality relies on the cacheless search in a BOP. In some cases, this is not fully supported, e.g. for Generic Design Elements (GDE). If the data has such lines, please set the preference value to false. The default value is true.

preference.name: MEActiveParentColorPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the color to be used when displaying a Active Parent (defaulted to sea green). The value can be a standard supported string, an octal number or a hexadecimal number. The standard strings supported are "black", "white", "lightGray", "gray", "darkGray", "red", "pink", "orange", "yellow", "green", "magenta", "cyan" and "blue". Example for a hexadecimal number is #50b080 which represents "Sea Green".

preference.name: MEActivityCustomTimeProperties
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of customer-defined properties of class CfgActivityLine that should be treated as times in the activity tree of Activities and Time view. The values of those properties are displayed in the time units selected in Manufacturing Options. By default this preference has no values.

preference.name: MEActivityTypeColors
preference.preference_description: Specifies the colors associated with the types of activities, as defined by the time_system_category property of MEActivity class. The format for a valid entry is: "activity_type;Red.Green.Blue", where Red, Green and Blue are the components of the RGB value for the selected color.

preference.name: MEAdditionalPropagatableProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of read-only properties which will be displayed in the "Propagation Settings" dialog. Each property will be displayed only if it was selected in the "Accountability Check" dialog for partial match.

preference.name: MEAdvancedSearchResultsViewColumnsShownWidthPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the width of the columns displayed in the "Advanced Search Results" view, as defined by the "MEAdvancedSearchResultsViewColumnsShownPref" preference.

preference.name: MEAdvancedSearchResultsViewDisplayNameColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the columns to display in the "Advanced Search Results" view. Valid values are the names of each column in the order you wish them to appear: value_1, value_2.

preference.name: MEAlignedPropertiesList
preference.preference_description: Specifies the supported BOM line properties for alignment initialization, out-of-sync detection and synchronization. This is site preference.

preference.name: MEAlignedPropertiesToExcludeFromDetection
preference.preference_description: Specifies the BOM line properties to be excluded from out-of-sync alignment detection. The entries are part of a subset of the "MEAlignedPropertiesList" preference. This is site preference.

preference.name: MEAlignedPropertiesToExcludeFromInitialization
preference.preference_description: Specifies the BOM line properties to be excluded from alignment initialization. The entries are part of a subset of the "MEAlignedPropertiesList" preference. This is site preference.

preference.name: MEAlignedPropertiesToExcludeFromSync
preference.preference_description: Specifies the BOM line properties to be excluded from alignment synchronization. The entries are part of a subset of the "MEAlignedPropertiesList" preference. This is site preference.

preference.name: MEAlignmentCheckReportDefinition
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the report definition object used to control the creation of the alignment check report. A default definition is provided out-of-the-box.

preference.name: MEAlignmentCheckReportLocation
preference.preference_description: Controls whether the persisted alignment check report is stored in the "Newstuff" folder (false) or in a dataset for the target window topline (true).

preference.name: MEAlignmentCheckReportStylesheet
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the stylesheet to be used with the creation of the alignment check report. A default stylesheet is provided out-of-the-box.

preference.name: MEAllocatedTimeReportDefinitionID
preference.preference_description: Specifies the report ID to be used for generating the allocated time report.

preference.name: MEAllocatedTimeReportStylesheet
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the xsl stylesheet to be used for the allocated time report.

preference.name: MEAllocationLevel
preference.preference_description: Defines the types of objects for which allocation of a process in Plant Bill Of Processes (BOP) is allowed. Valid values are the internal names of the Business Objects, for example "Mfg0MEProcArea" (for Process Area), "Mfg0MEProcLine" (for Process Line), "Mfg0MEProcStatn" (for Process Station).

preference.name: MEAllowDragDropInBetweenBomlines
preference.preference_description: Enables the drag-and-drop of BOM Lines in between any target BOM Lines in the Manufacturing Process Planning (MPP) application. Splitters are displayed when BOM Lines are dragged and placed in between the target BOM Line. Valid values are: *false: the drag-and-drop in between the BOM Lines is not allowed. Splitters are not displayed. This is the default value. *true: the drag-and-drop in between the BOM Lines is allowed. Splitters are displayed.

preference.name: MEAssignAttachmentAndRelationToUseInCopyRule
preference.preference_description: Defines the attachment types, relation types which will be referenced or copied after assignment. Valid values have the following format: AttachmentType:RelationType:CopyRule, where AttachmentType and RelationType are the internal name of the Attachment type and the Relation type, and CopyRule is either Copy or Reference.

preference.name: MEAssignAttachmentContext
preference.preference_description: Indicates the context of the in-context attachments after assignment. Valid values are: TopLine, DirectParent.

preference.name: MEAssignCustomizedOccurrenceType
preference.preference_description: Determines the Occurrence Type used by default for Paste, Assign and Drag-and-Drop operations. The syntax is "[targetType].[sourceType]:[occurrenceType]" The targetType (to) and sourceType (from) fields can be set to "All" to determine the default for all types that are not specifically listed in the values of this preference. The occurrenceType field can be set to "Empty" to enforce that by default no occurrence type is used.

preference.name: MEAssignProperties
preference.preference_description: Specifies the BOM Line properties for assign and propagation in the Manufacturing Process Planner application. Valid values are property internal names.

preference.name: MEAssignmentIndicationDefault
preference.preference_description: Defines the default Accountability Check favorite to be used internally for Assignment Indication feature. The format of the preference value should be "AssignmentIndication_<Source type><Target type>:<Default AC favorite name>". Example: AssignmentIndication_BOMBOM:AIACFavorite

preference.name: MEAssignmentIndicationGraphicsMode
preference.preference_description: This is an internal preference and do not modify this preference value. This preference holds the last selected graphics mode in Assignment Indication View. The default value is "Blank".

preference.name: MEAssignmentIndicationTransparencyValue
preference.preference_description: Defines the transparency value to be used in Assignment Indication. The value should be greater than "0" and less than "0.9". The default value is "0.9".

preference.name: MEAssignmentStatesForTarget
preference.preference_description: Specifies the assignment states that are considered to reference the consumed parts in the target structure when cloning or allocating a Bill of Process (BOP) structure. If no value is specified, all the consumed parts are referenced in the target structure. Valid values are: *No State *Pending *Accepted *Rejected

preference.name: MEAssignmentsViewColumnsShownWidthPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the width in pixel of the columns displayed in the "Assignments" view, as defined by the "MEAssignmentsViewColumnsShownPref" preference.

preference.name: MEAssignmentsViewDisplayNameColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the columns to display in the "Assignments" view. Valid values are the names of each column in the order you wish them to appear: value_1, value_2.

preference.name: MEAttachmentOpen
preference.preference_description: List of object types that support open functionality in the attachment view.

preference.name: MEAutoReviseWhilePropagation
preference.preference_description: Enables automatic revise of an object while propagating changes if the object is not modifiable due to it's release status(es). However, the object is revised only if the user has write access on it. Currently this functionality is only supported for Collaboration Planning Context (CPC) use-cases.

preference.name: MEAvailableTimeUnits
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of custom available time units. Each value contains a unique unit id in English and a multiplier to convert from this unit to seconds (default unit). Valid values for this site preference are to be formatted as follows: unitId:multiplierToSeconds For example: myTimeUnitID:112.25 By default this preference has no values.

preference.name: MEBlankDisplayTypes
preference.preference_description: Defines the types to be displayed in "Blank Display by Type" command. The format for valid values is "StructureType:TypeName". The preference is disabled for direct edit and is only editable through the "Options" panel.

preference.name: MECPCDefaultReleaseStatus
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default release status to be assigned to cloned objects that do not have any release status. If several values are provided, only the first value is taken into consideration. Valid values are internal names of release statuses.

preference.name: MECTRevisionChangeAddAdditional
preference.preference_description: Controls whether additional objects are output by the "MESINTEG_ValidateReleaseAndExport" and "ME-create-revision-change-xml-AH" workflow handlers delta XML for removed and replaced change elements, as controlled by the closure rule specified by the "MECTRevisionChangeClosureRule" preference. Valid values are true or false.

preference.name: MECTRevisionChangeClosureRule
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the closure rule to be used for outputting additional objects in the "MESINTEG_ValidateReleaseAndExport" and "ME-create-revision-change-xml-AH" workflow handlers delta XML for removed and replaced change elements as controlled by the "MECTRevisionChangeAddAdditional" preference. If not specified, the closure rule "AccountabilityAll" is used. Valid value is the name of a closure rule.

preference.name: MECTRevisionReportStyleSheet
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the Dataset that contains the XSL stylesheet to be used for the change tracker revision detail report in the Manufacturing Process Planner application.

preference.name: MECheckResultItemDisplayColumnPreferenceNames
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of properties displayed in the columns of "Check Result View Violation Tables" panel in the Manufacturing Process Planner application.

preference.name: MECheckResultItemDisplayColumnPreferenceWidth
preference.preference_description: Defines the width (in pixels) of the column in the "Check Result View Objects Table" panel as defined by the preference MECheckResultItemDisplayColumnPreferenceNames.

preference.name: MECheckResultViewViolationTableWidths
preference.preference_description: Defines the width (in pixels) of the violation and the description columns in the "Check Results View Violation Table".

preference.name: MECollectionTypeProcesses
preference.preference_description: Defines the Process types for which the allocated time calculation will ignore flows and will interpret the sub-processes or operations in sequence defined by the find number. For these types, the allocated time will be computed identically to the work time. The line balancing chart will only show children of processes of this type. Valid values are the internal name of the type Process (MEProcess) and any of its sub-types.

preference.name: MEConfigureStructuresDisplayNameColumnShownPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the columns displayed in "Configure Structures" dialog in the Manufacturing Process Planner (MPP) application. The valid column names are: revision_rule, variant_rules, Mfg0VisibilityUncnfVar, Mfg0VisibilitySuppOcc, Mfg0VisibilityUncnfChanges, Mfg0VisibilityUncnfOccEff, Mfg0VisibilityUncnfAssgnOcc, Fnd0EffectvtyGrpList, Fnd0Effectvty. The column names are the internal names of the properties.

preference.name: MEConsiderFlowsOnReSequence
preference.preference_description: Defines the default state of the "Consider flows" checkbox in the Re-Sequence Structure dialog. Valid values are true/false.

preference.name: MEConstraintsViewAutomaticLayoutOffAppendPositionPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the default position where new objects will be added to the layout in the Constraints View in the Manufacturing Process Planner (MPP) application. Valid values are: * LOWER_LEFT: to place the objects under the lower left bound of the current graph. * LOWER_RIGHT: to place the objects under the lower right bound of the current graph. * UPPER_RIGHT: to place the objects under the uper right bound of the current graph.

preference.name: MEConstraintsViewDefaultAutomaticLayoutModePref
preference.preference_description: Activates the automatic layout changes when modifications are made to objects in Constraints View in the Manufacturing Process Planner (MPP) application. Valid values are true and false. The default value is true (activated).

preference.name: MECopyAssemblyInContextTemplates
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rule names to be used when copying a subassembly within a Bill Of Material(BOM) structures.

preference.name: MECopyIdInContextLowerLevels
preference.preference_description: Determines if the context attribute is copied to the assigned line for the sub-processes and sub-operations during an assignment operation.

preference.name: MECopyIdInContextToAssignedLine
preference.preference_description: Determines if the context attribute is copied to the assigned line during an assignment operation.

preference.name: MECreateFipaStructure
preference.preference_description: Defines the type of "Filtered In Process Assembly" structure to be created in a Process structure. Valid values are "Nested" (default) and "Flat".

preference.name: MECurrentTimeUnit
preference.preference_description: Defines the id of the time unit in which all new time data will be displayed. The value of the preference must be one of the out-of-the-box Time Unit IDs (second, minute, 10th_min, 100th_min, 1000th_min, hour, day, TMU, MOD, FAC) or one of the IDs from the MEAvailableTimeUnits preference. This preference should be set using the Time Units option tab in MSE, in order for the change to take effect without restarting the application. The default value for this User preference is second.

preference.name: MECustomViewAttachmentColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of column names that will be displayed in the Attachment tree table in Manufacturing Process Planner (MPP) application. Valid values are the names of each column in the Attachment View.

preference.name: MECustomViewAttachmentShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the column widths for the column names (identified by MECustomViewAttachmentColumnsShownPref) that will be used by the Attachment tree table in Manufacturing MSE application.

preference.name: MECustomViewChildLinesColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths for the columns defined in the preference "MECustomViewChildLinesColumnsShownPref".

preference.name: MECustomViewChildLinesColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the ordered list of columns to display in the left hand side section in the Custom view in the Manufacturing Process Planner (MPP) application. Valid values are in the format "TypeInternalName.PropertyInternalName", e.g. "BOMLine.bl_indented_title", where TypeInternalName is the internal name of a Business Object of type BOMLine, and PropertyInternalName is the property that appears as column.

preference.name: MECustomViewChildLinesCommandNames
preference.preference_description:
Defines the ordered list of commands to be displayed above the table in the left hand side section in the Custom view in in the Manufacturing Process Planner (MPP) application. Valid values are the IDs of each command. The commands that are supported out-of-the-box are: com.teamcenter.rac.newMEOperation com.teamcenter.rac.remove
Refer to the documentation for details.

preference.name: MECustomViewConsumedItemsColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths for the columns defined in the preference "MECustomViewConsumedItemsColumnsShownPref".

preference.name: MECustomViewConsumedItemsColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the ordered list of columns to display in each table in the right hand side section in the Custom view in the Manufacturing Process Planner (MPP) application. Valid values are in the format "TypeInternalName.PropertyInternalName", e.g. "BOMLine.bl_indented_title", where TypeInternalName is the internal name of a Business Object of type BOMLine, and PropertyInternalName is the property that appears as column.

preference.name: MECustomViewConsumedItemsCommandNames
preference.preference_description:
Defines the ordered list of commands to be displayed above each table in the right hand side section in the Custom view in the Manufacturing Process Planner (MPP) application. Valid values are the ID of commands. The default values are: com.teamcenter.rac.cme.stylesheet.cut com.teamcenter.rac.cme.stylesheet.copy com.teamcenter.rac.cme.stylesheet.paste com.teamcenter.rac.cme.stylesheet.removeline com.teamcenter.rac.cme.stylesheet.assignconsumeditems:Mfg0consumed_material com.teamcenter.rac.cme.stylesheet.assignparts:Mfg0used_equipment com.teamcenter.rac.AssignResource:Mfg0used_equipment
Refer to the documentation for details.

preference.name: MECustomViewConsumedItemsOccTypes
preference.preference_description: Defines the occurrence types for each table to be displayed in the right hand side section in the Custom view in the Manufacturing Process Planner (MPP) application. Each entry in this preference will create a new table in the right hand side section of the view. Valid values are the occurrence types supported in MPP in the order that the tables are to appear. Values format is "value_1:value_2", where: * value_1 is the Relation property type * value_2 is the Occurence type for paste.

preference.name: MEDataPanelPosition
preference.preference_description: Defines where the data panel of a structure is opened when users click the "Show Data Panel" command in Manufacturing applications. Valid values are: "right" to open the data panel to the right of the structure. "bottom" to open the data panel below the structure.

preference.name: MEDataSetsToBeCheckoutForProcessSimulate
preference.preference_description: Indicates which data sets to check out when running any function for Process Simulate, that includes datasets. Valid values are pairs of data set types and relations separated by a ":" character.

preference.name: MEDefaultActivityType
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default type of a new activity created in the Activities tree table of the Operations Times tab.

preference.name: MEDelegatedOccurrenceProperties
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of internal BOM Line properties to be delegated for lines assigned from the Product structure to the Bill Of Process (BOP) structure. Only the following properties are supported: bl_occ_effectivity (Occurrence Effectivity), bl_formula (Variant Formula), bl_quantity (Quantity), bl_plmxml_abs_xform (Absolute Transformation Matrix), bl_occurrence_name (Occurrence Name), bl_abs_occ_all_ids (ID In Context All Levels), bl_variant_condition (Variant Conditions), bl_all_notes (All Notes).

preference.name: MEDisplayOccurrenceType
preference.preference_description:
Defines the conditions to display occurrence types while pasting objects in the Manufacturing Process Planner application of rich client. This preference is used, for example, in the "Paste as", "Paste Special" and "Assign Resource" commands and in the dropdown of occurrence type column in Bill of Materials (BOM) view.
