Valid format is list of * "[target type]:[source type]:[comma separated preference names]" (e.g. "MEProcess:Item:MERelationTypePartsAssembled,MERelationTypePartsAssigned"). Wild card ("*") is only supported for target and source. e.g. *:Item:MERelationTypePartsAssembled. The occurrence types specified in these preferences will be displayed to the user. The order in which preferences are specified is important as the occurrence type from the first preference is displayed first followed by occurrence type from other preferences.
The order of entries in this preference is important. For a given target and source type, the list is evaluated from top to bottom and the first matching entry is considered for the evaluation of occurrence type. Criteria for correct match is target and source object type should be same or sub class of respective types specified in the entry.
If value of this preference is blank or none of the conditions is satisfied, all occurrence types available in the system will be displayed to the user. For multiple target (or source) objects of different types, the common occurrence types will be shown. If one of the sources and targets pairs has no occurrence types defined, the system will assume all occurrence types are valid for that pair, and will perform intersection to find common occurrence types for the other pairs. If no common occurrence types are found, an indication of that will be shown to the user.
This preference could be edited to have new entries with custom defined preference type and custom defined objects, change existing condition and change the order of existing conditions. Following the edit, client/server relaunch is not required.
Note: If the default Occurrence type for a given source and target, as specified in the "MEAssignCustomizedOccurrenceType" preference, is not mentioned in the below preference list for that source and target, the system will automatically append it to the list.

preference.name: MEDisplayOnAssign
preference.preference_description: Enables the display of assigned parts in the corresponding graphics in the "Paste" command of the Manufacturing Process Planner application. The default value is "true".

preference.name: MEDoNotUseSCTypeForColumns
preference.preference_description: Defines the sub-types of Item Revision for which the name of preferences, controlling the columns to display in the primary view of a Structure Context, are prefixed with the type of the Item Revision. For sub-types not listed in this preference, the columns to display is controlled by preferences which names are prefixes with the type of the Structure Context object. Valid values are sub-types of Item Revision.

preference.name: MEDuplicateAssemblyInContextTemplates
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rule names to be used when duplicating subassembly within Bill Of Material(BOM) structures.

preference.name: MEDynamicIPADisplayName
preference.preference_description: Determines the property of the predecessor in the given Process Structure to be considered when generating the name of the In-Process Assembly. A valid value is one of the following Plant BOP Line properties: "bl_item_object_name", "bl_rev_object_name".

preference.name: MEDynamicIPAOccurrenceTypes
preference.preference_description: Determines which Occurrence types to aggregate from predecessors in the given Process Structure to generate the In-Process Assembly (IPA). The default value is the Occurrence type "MEConsumed".

preference.name: MEDynamicIPARemoveOccTypes
preference.preference_description: Determines which Occurrence types to consider for removal from aggregated parts of the predecessors in the given Process Structure to generate the In-Process Assembly (IPA). The default value is the Occurrence type "MEDisassemble".

preference.name: MEDynamicIPATraversalClosureRule
preference.preference_description: Determines the closure rule to be used for traversal of the Process Structure, to calculate dynamic In-Process Assembly. The default value is "DynamicIPAProcessOnlyWithPA".

preference.name: MEExpandFirstLevelOnLoad
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the root node is expanded when opened in ME. Valid values are true (default value) to expand the root node, and false to keep it collapsed.

preference.name: MEExpandToSelection
preference.preference_description: Specifies the mode for selection synchronization in Manufacturing applications. Valid values are: *false: The synchronizing view will highlight the selected line if it is currently expanded (if it was previously expanded and then collapsed, it is considered collapsed). Otherwise the selection in that view will be cleared. *true: The synchronizing view will partially expand to the selected line and highlight it. This is the default value.

preference.name: MEFIPAErrorLinesColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of columns that will be displayed for the Filter Assembly Tree error dialogs.

preference.name: MEFIPAErrorLinesColumnsWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the column widths for the columns (identified by MEFIPAErrorLinesColumnsShownPref) displayed in the Filter Assembly Tree error dialogs.

preference.name: MEFilterIPARefObjColumnsShown
preference.preference_description: Indicates the default columns of the Reference Objects Table displayed during Assembly Tree Filtering in MSE.

preference.name: MEFilterIPARefObjColumnsWidth
preference.preference_description: Indicates the width of default columns (identified by preference MEFilterIPARefObjColumnsShown) of the Reference Objects Table displayed during Assembly Tree Filtering in MSE.

preference.name: MEFormsToBeCheckoutForProcessSimulate
preference.preference_description: Indicates which forms to check out when running any function for Process Simulate, that includes forms. Valid values are pairs of form types and relations separated by a ":" character.

preference.name: MEGANTTColumnPreferenceWidth
preference.preference_description: Defines the width (in pixels) of the column in the Gantt tree as defined by the preference MEGANTTColumnPreferenceNames.

preference.name: MEGANTTDefaultDisplayMode
preference.preference_description: Defines the display mode of the Gantt charts in the Manufacturing Process Planner application. Valid values are: show_calculated_duration_time for calculated durations to be displayed in Gantt charts hide_calculated_duration_time to hide them.

preference.name: MEGANTTDefaultDurationTimeColor
preference.preference_description: Defines the RGB code for the color of the duration time bar of each element in Gantt charts of the Manufacturing Process Planner application. Valid values is a triplet of integer values from 0 to 255 separated by the ";" character.

preference.name: MEGANTTDefaultEditMode
preference.preference_description: Defines the edit mode of Gantt charts. Valid values are: restricted_edit_mode to restrict some elements modifications. full_edit_mode to allow all modifications.

preference.name: MEGANTTDefaultFlowColor
preference.preference_description: Defines the RGB (Red, Green, Blue) code for the color of flows in Gantt charts in the Manufacturing Process Planner application. Valid values is a triplet of integer values from 0 to 255 separated by the ";" character.

preference.name: MEGANTTDefaultMarkedColor
preference.preference_description: Defines the RGB( Red, Green, Blue) code for the color of marked elements in Gantt charts in the Manufacturing Process Planner application. Valid values is a triplet of integer values from 0 to 255 separated by the ";" character.

preference.name: MEGANTTDefaultSelectionColor
preference.preference_description: Defines the RGB (Red, Green, Blue) code for the color of selected objects in Gantt charts in the Manufacturing Process Planner application. A valid value is a triplet of integers from 0 to 255 separated by the ";" character.

preference.name: MEGANTTDisplayNameColumnPreferenceNames
preference.preference_description: Defines the TCComponents properties displayed in the columns of Gantt charts in the Manufacturing Process Planner application. Each entry is the internal name of a TCComponent property.

preference.name: MEGANTTElementHeight
preference.preference_description: Defines the height (in pixels) of elements in Gantt charts in the Manufacturing Process Planner application. A valid value is an integer between 1 and 40.

preference.name: MEGANTTElementRGBfillColor
preference.preference_description: Defines the RGB (Red, Green, Blue) code for the color of elements in Gantt charts in the Manufacturing Process Planner application. Valid values is a triplet of integer values from 0 to 255 separated by the ";" character.

preference.name: MEGANTTImplicitFlowColor
preference.preference_description: Defines the RGB (Red, Green, Blue) code for the color of implicit flows in Gantt charts in the Manufacturing Process Planner application. Valid values is a triplet of integer values from 0 to 255 separated by the ";" character.

preference.name: MEGANTTMarkedFlowColor
preference.preference_description: Defines the RGB (Red, Green, Blue) code for the color of marked flows in Gantt charts in the Manufacturing Process Planner application. Valid values is a triplet of integer values from 0 to 255 separated by the ";" character.

preference.name: MEGANTTName
preference.preference_description: Defines the property of the component that will be used to be displayed as its name in the Gantt charts of the Manufacturing Process Planner application.

preference.name: MEGANTTPropagateDurationUpToLevel
preference.preference_description: Defines the minimal distance for a node to the start node to have the duration propagation applied. Valid values are positive integer numbers and zero (default value).

preference.name: MEGANTTPropagateDurationUpToLevelEnabled
preference.preference_description: Defines if the level defined in preference MEGANTTPropagateDurationUpToLevel should be considered in duration propagation calculation. Valid values are true and false (default value).

preference.name: MEGenerateAssemblyTreeOccurrenceTypes
preference.preference_description: >Lists the Process types presented in Generate Assembly Tree command of the Manufacturing Process Planner (MPP) application.

preference.name: MEGenerateAssemblyTreeProcessTypes
preference.preference_description: Lists the Occurrence types presented in Generate Assembly Tree command of the Manufacturing Process Planner (MPP) application.

preference.name: MEGenericBOP.MEGenericBOP.CopyPasteTemplate
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rules to be used when the "Paste" operation is used to create new instances in a Generic Bill of Processes (BOP) starting from a Generic BOP.

preference.name: MEGenericBOP.MEGenericBOP.PasteDuplicateTemplate
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rules to be used when the "Paste" operation is used to create new instances in a Generic Bill of Processes (BOP) starting from a Generic BOP.

preference.name: MEGenericBOP.MEProductBOP.CopyPasteTemplate
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rules to be used when the "Paste" operation is used to create new instances in a Product Bill of Processes (BOP) starting from a Generic BOP.

preference.name: MEGenericBOP.MEProductBOP.PasteDuplicateTemplate
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rules to be used when the "Paste Duplicate" operation is used to create new instances in a Product Bill of Processes (BOP) starting from a Generic BOP.

preference.name: MEGenericBOP.Mfg0MEPlantBOP.PasteDuplicateTemplate
preference.preference_description: Defines the cloning rules to be used when pasting from a Generic Bill of Process (BOP) to Plant BOP. Valid values are in the following format: "primary:secondary:attribute_key.attribute_value:action", where: * the primary can be * for any class, class.<class name> for specific class or type.<type name> for specific type. * the secondary is the same format as primary * the attribute_key must be one of the following: Attribute, OccType, Relation. If the value is Attribute, the attribute_value must be the name of an attribute on the primary object. If the value is OccType, the attibute_value must be Null (no Occurrence Type) or * (any Occurrence Type) or the name of specific Occurrence Type. If the value is Relation, the attribute_value must be the internal name of a Relation Type. * the action must be one of the following: Clone, Reference, Ignore

preference.name: MEGenericBOPRevisionColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the columns to display in the base view of a Generic Bill of Process. Valid values are the names of each column in the order you wish them to appear: value_1, value_2.

preference.name: MEGenericBOPRevisionDisplayNameColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Stores the internal names of BOP Line properties which display names appear as columns from left-to-right for Generic Bill of Process in Manufacturing Engineering applications. This preference value is only a repository, and it is not to be modified other than by the code itself.

preference.name: MEGenericBOPRevisionPartitionColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the columns to display in the Partition tab of a Generic Bill of Process. Valid values are the names of each column in the order you wish them to appear: value_1, value_2.

preference.name: MEGenericBOPRevisionPartitionDisplayNameColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Stores the internal names of BOM Line properties which display names appear as columns from left-to-right of Generic Bill of Process in Manufacturing Process Planner application. This preference value is only a repository, and it is not to be modified other than by the code itself.

preference.name: MEGenericBOPRevisionPartitionShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the width in pixel of the columns displayed in the Partition tab of a Generic Bill of Process, as defined by the "MEGenericBopContextPartitionColumnsShownPref" preference.

preference.name: MEGenericBOPRevisionShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the width in pixel of the columns displayed in the base view of a Generic Bill of Process, as defined by the "MEGenericBopContextColumnsShownPref" preference.

preference.name: MEHideChangesIconsForAttributes
preference.preference_description: Controls the display of the incremental change and the in-context change symbols on the BOM structure in Manufacturing Process Planner. By default, symbols appear for all attribute changes in a structure. Adding an attribute to this list eliminates the display of the change symbols for this attribute. The changes are still recorded (either in the incremental change or the context), but the symbols are not displayed. Valid values for this site preference are valid property names for structure data overrides, for example bl_sequence_no.

preference.name: MEIgnoreICForReleaseStatus
preference.preference_description: Specifies the release statuses for which the changes will not be tracked in Incremental Change (IC) context even if IC is turned on. The valid values are internal names of release statuses.

preference.name: MEImportMFGsManufacturingFeatureIdAttributeName
preference.preference_description: Defines which BOM Line property is used as the Manufacturing Feature Id by the Import Manufacturing Features utility.

preference.name: MEImportMFGsPartIdAttributeName
preference.preference_description: Defines which BOM Line property is used as the Part Id by the Import Manufacturing Features utility.

preference.name: MEImportMFGsUseAbsoluteLocation
preference.preference_description: Indicates how the command "Import Manufacturing Features" (in the Manufacturing Process Planner application) applies the transformation to the Manufacturing Features, as written in the PLMXML. Valid values are: * true: the transformation is applied as absolute location. This is the default value. * false: the transformation is applied as relative location.

preference.name: MEIncrementalChangeMode
preference.preference_description: Defines the mode used by the "Incremental Change" command in the Manufacturing applications. Valid values are: - 'application': the Incremental Change will work per application. If an Incremental Change is being set it will be set for all the loaded structures. This is the default behavior. - 'structure': the Incremental Change will work per structure. If an Incremental Change is being set it will be relevant only for the selected structure and for the secondary views connected to the selected structure. In this mode, each structure can use its own Incremental Change.

preference.name: MELBBalancingOverviewReportID
preference.preference_description: Specifies the report ID to be used for generating the line balancing overview report in the Manufacturing Process Planner application.

preference.name: MELBBalancingOverviewStylesheet
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the XSL stylesheet to be used for the line balancing overview report in the Manufacturing Process Planner application.

preference.name: MELBChartColors
MELBChartDnDSourceTypes
preference.preference_description: Defines the types of objects which the user can drag in the line balancing chart. Valid values are internal names of the types Process (MEProcess), Operation (MEOP), or any their sub-types. The type "MEProcess" is not recommended, because it will include all process types.

preference.name: MELBChartDnDTargetParentTypes
preference.preference_description: Defines the types of parent objects under which dragged processes and operations can be dropped in the line balancing chart. This can include Processes as well as process Area types. Valid values are internal names of the types Process (MEProcess), Process Area(Mfg0MEProcArea), or any their sub-types.

preference.name: MELBChartProcessOperationTypeDefaultValues
preference.preference_description: Defines the possible values for MELBChartProcessOperationTypes preference in the line balancing chart. Valid values are internal names of the types Process (MEProcess), Operation (MEOP), or any of their sub-types. In the line balancing chart area of the rich client, the command "View Menu -> View Option" will show these types as contextual menu in order to enable a quick update of the "MELBChartProcessOperationTypes" preference.

preference.name: MELBChartProcessOperationTypes
preference.preference_description: Defines the types of objects used as 'Processes' or 'Operations' in the line balancing chart. The line balancing chart area will only show these types. Sub-structures will be ignored even if they contain objects of the types included in this preference. Valid values are internal names of the types Process (MEProcess), Operation (MEOP), or any their sub-types. The type "MEProcess" is not recommended, because it will include all process types.

preference.name: MELBChartStationNameDisplayPattern
preference.preference_description:
Defines the display pattern of the station line names in line balancing charts in the Manufacturing Process Planner application.
The line balancing chart uses regular expressions as patterns to show the wanted parts of the station line names. The parts to be displayed are marked by the groups. The corresponding part strings of the names will be displayed.
For example when applying the pattern ".*([sS]t)ation([ .0-9]*).*" to station line name "000140/A;1-station 1.1 for the assembling front axle" the string "st" matches the regular expression group "([sS]t)", and the string " 1.1 " matches the regular expression group "([ .0-9]*)". The result is that the display string will be "st 1.1" for this pattern.
If the pattern is not defined correctly or if no group is defined, the original line name text will be displayed.
The following examples show some patterns and the corresponding results for the line name "000140/A;1-station 1.1 for the assembling front axle": Pattern: "[ 0]*([0-9]*)/.*" result: "140" Pattern: ".*(station.*)" result: "station 1.1 for the assembling front axle" Pattern: ".*([sS]t)ation([ .0-9]*).*" result: "st 1.1 "

preference.name: MELBChartStationTypes

If this preference is empty, the value given in preference MEAllocationLevel will be used. If preference MEAllocationLevel is empty as well, the line balancing chart will use objects of type "Mfg0MEProcArea" as default value. Valid values are the internal names of Process Area (Mfg0MEProcArea) and any of its sub-types.

preference.name: MEMBOMAssessmentRepairAbsXformAngularTolerance
preference.preference_description: Defines the proximity value (in degrees) under which variations in the rotation section of a transform are seen as equal. The default value is 0.1 degree.

preference.name: MEMBOMAssessmentRepairAbsXformTranslationTolerance
preference.preference_description: Defines the proximity value (in millimeters) under which variations in the translation section of a transform are seen as equal. The default value is 0.001 millimeters.

preference.name: MEMBOMAssessmentRepairClosureRule

preference.name: MEMBOMAssessmentRepairDefaultSearchCriteria

Each criteria value describes a BOMLine property which will be taken into account by the search. It is a comma separated string. For one criteria value string, the format is defined as follows: Part 1: either Mandatory or Optional Part 2: internal BOMLine property name Part 3: operator, currently only "=" is supported. Part 4: value type, currently only "string" type is supported.

preference.name: MEMBOMAssessmentRepairSearchCriteriaList
preference.preference_description: A List of criteria that can be used for searching repair candidates in MBOM Assessment Repair View.

preference.name: MEMFGDisplayName
preference.preference_description: Customizes the display name of Weld Point, Arc Weld and Datum Point objects in the Manufacturing application. Valid values are following BOM Line properties: "bl_item_item_id", "bl_item_object_name", "bl_rev_item_revision_id","bl_rev_object_name","bl_occurrence_name". The final display name will be formed by concatenating the display name for each property specified above, using the character ";" as a delimiter.

preference.name: MEMFGViewDisplayNameColumnShownPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the columns displayed in MFG view.

preference.name: MEMFGViewShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the width of the columns determined by the preference MEMFGViewSubPanelColumnShownPref.

preference.name: MEMFGViewSubPanelColumnShownPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the columns displayed in the connected parts sub-panel of MFG view.

preference.name: MEMFGViewSubPanelShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the widht of the columns shown in connected parts sub panel of MFG View.

preference.name: MEMFGView_AssignmentFilterDefaultValue

preference.name: MENEWMFG_LastJTFilePathBrowsed

preference.name: MEOP.MEGenericBOP.PasteDuplicateTemplate
preference.preference_description: Defines the cloning rules to be used when pasting from a regular Operation structure to a Generic Bill Of Process (Generic BOP). Valid values are in the following format: "primary:secondary:attribute_key.attribute_value:action", where: * the primary can be "*" for any class, "class.<class name>" for specific class or "type.<type name>" for specific type. * the secondary is the same format as primary. * the attribute_key must be one of the following: "Attribute", "OccType", "Relation". If the value is "Attribute", the attribute_value must be the name of an attribute on the primary object. If the value is "OccType", the attribute_value must be "Null" (no Occurrence Type) or "*" (any Occurrence Type) or the name of specific Occurrence Type. If the value is "Relation", the attribute_value must be the internal name of a Relation Type. * the action must be one of the following: "Clone", "Reference", "Ignore".

preference.name: MEOP.MEProcess.PasteDuplicateTemplate

Valid values are: * Mfg0has_origin: allocation indication icon will be displayed if the operation was allocated from a product bill of process. * no value: no icon will be displayed. This is the default value.

preference.name: MEPerspectiveMode
preference.preference_description:
Defines the behavior of opening views in the Manufacturing perspectives. Valid values are "[perspective-id]:[mode]" , where [perspective-id] represents the ID of the perspective, and [mode] represents a valid view mode. Valid view modes are: * OpenExplicitOnly: Use existing views as much as possible. But if explicitly asked, open new views. * OpenAllStrategy: For each opened structure, a new view will be opened. When objects are opened in another perspective, a new view will be opened for them in this perspective too.
When a perspective's mode is not defined by this preference, the default applied mode is 'OpenExplicitOnly'.

preference.preference_description: Defines the columns to display in the base view of a Product Bill of Process. Valid values are the names of each column in the order you wish them to appear: value_1, value_2.

preference.name: MERelationTypeAssemblyTree
preference.preference_description: Defines the relation type that indicates that the assigned Occurrence Group is an Assembly Tree.

preference.name: MERelationTypeFeature
preference.preference_description: Defines which relations will indicate that the consumed item is an Manufacturing feature.

preference.name: MERelationTypePartsAssembled
preference.preference_description: Defines the assemble relation of assignment parts to operations.

preference.name: MERelationTypePartsAssigned
preference.preference_description: Defines the assignment relation of assignment parts to processes.

preference.name: MERelationTypePartsConsumed
preference.preference_description: Defines the default consume relation between assignment parts and operations or processes.

preference.name: MERelationTypePartsDefault
preference.preference_description: Defines the default assignment type selected in the "Assign Parts by Logical Designator" dialog in the Manufacturing Process Planner application. Valid values are internal names of occurrence type. The default value is "MEConsumed".

preference.name: MERelationTypePartsDisassembled
preference.preference_description: Defines the disassemble relation of assignment parts to operations.

preference.name: MERelationTypePartsHandled
preference.preference_description: Defines the handle relation of assignment parts to operations.

preference.name: MERelationTypePartsOtherAssigned
preference.preference_description: Defines the other types of assignments that are not consumption, handling, assembling or disassembling for operations and that are not assignment for processes.

preference.name: MERelationTypeUsedEquipment
preference.preference_description: Defines which relations will indicate that the assigned item is a Tool. The types defined here are used to assign Equipment (Tools) to operations and processes.

preference.name: MERelationTypeWorkarea
preference.preference_description: Defines the relations indicating that the assigned Item is a Workarea. The defined type are used to assign Workarea objects to operations and processes.

preference.name: MEReleaseStatusListForAutoRevise
preference.preference_description: Allows the customer to list the release status(es) for which the objects should be automatically revised while propagating changes. Currently this functionality is only supported for Collaboration Planning Context (CPC) use-cases. Valid values are internal names of release statuses.

preference.name: MEReplaceAssemblyInContextTemplates
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rule names to be used when replacing a subassembly within Bill Of Material(BOM) structures.

preference.name: MEReportColumnWidthForProcessSimulate
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths for the column displayed in the report for failed check-out objects (Process Simulate command), as defined in the MEReportColumnsForProcessSimulate preference.

preference.name: MEReportColumnsForProcessSimulate
preference.preference_description: Indicates the ordered list of column names displayed in the report for failed check-out objects in the Process Simulate command.

preference.name: MEResolverViewColumnsShownWidthForCLPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the width in pixel of the columns displayed in the "Tool Requirement Resolver" view. The columns are defined by the "MEResolverViewDisplayNameColumnsForCLShownPref" preference.

preference.name: MEResolverViewColumnsShownWidthForWAPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the width in pixel of the columns displayed in the "Tool Requirement Resolver" view. The columns are defined by the "MEResolverViewDisplayNameColumnsForWAShownPref" preference.

preference.name: MEResolverViewDisplayNameColumnsForCLShownPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the columns to display in the "Tool Requirement Resolver " view. This is specific to the Library tools table viewer. Valid values are the property internal names in the order to appear: BusinessObjectInternalName.PropertyInternalName.

preference.name: MEResolverViewDisplayNameColumnsForWAShownPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the columns to display in the "Tool Requirement Resolver " view. This is specific to the Work Area tools table viewer. Valid values are the property internal names in the order to appear: BusinessObjectInternalName.PropertyInternalName.

preference.name: MEResultViewSourceColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the columns to display in the "Accountability Check Result View Source Tables". Valid values are property internal names in the order they should appear.

preference.name: MEResultViewSourceColumnsShownWidthPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the width of the columns displayed in the "Accountability Check Result View Source Tables", as defined by the "MEResultViewSourceColumnsShownPref" preference.

preference.name: MEResultViewTargetColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the columns to display in the "Accountability Check Result View Target Tables". Valid values are property internal names in the order they should appear.

preference.name: MEResultViewTargetColumnsShownWidthPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the width of the columns displayed in the "Accountability Check Result View Target Tables", as defined by the MEResultViewTargetColumnsShownPref preference.

preference.name: MERetainResolvedParts
preference.preference_description: Specifies if the resolved parts under the Logical Assignment (LA) should be retained if the LA is resolved and the parts are configured out from the product. Valid values are: *false: the configured out parts will not be resolved. This is the default value. *true: the configured out parts will be resolved.

preference.name: MESaveAsSC_PasteType
preference.preference_description:
When a root object is created under the Structure Context, this preference defines which object will be taken from the selected BOM Line and pasted as a root under the Structure Context. Valid values are "Item", "ItemRevision", "BOMView" and "BOMViewRevision". If no "BOMViewRevision" object exists in the selection and that value is selected, the "ItemRevision" will be used instead. This happens with product root BOM Lines without children: they do not contain any "BOMViewRevision" object. If no "BOMView" exists in the selection and that value is selected, the "Item" will be used instead.
The default value is "BOMViewRevision".

preference.name: MESecondStructurePosition
preference.preference_description: Defines where the second structure is opened when users click the "Open Structure in Second Panel" and "Show Second Structure Panel" commands in the MSE, CC and Part Planner applications and the "Split Panel" command in the Requirements Manager application. Valid values are: "right" to open the second structure on the right. "bottom" to open the second structure on the bottom.

preference.name: MEShowConfigurationHeader
preference.preference_description: Enables the display of configuration headers in the "primary views" of the "Manufacturing" application. Examples of configuration header information are: "Revision Rule", "Variant Rule", "Effectivity", "Incremental Change Context". The default value is false (information is not displayed).

preference.name: MEShowHideUnconfiguredAll
preference.preference_description: Determines the visibility and content of the rich client selector to show or hide all unconfigured actions when the Manufacturing application is opened or a new BOM window is created. Valid values are : "Individual", "All", "Both" * Individual: the selector is not visible. * Both: the selector is visible. * All: the selector is visible but the show unconfigured toggle actions are not visible on the toolbar.

preference.name: MEShowSuppressedOccsDefaultState
preference.preference_description: Determines if the default state of the 'Show Suppress Line' toggle button is checked when the Manufacturing application is opened or a new BOM window is created. The default value is true.

preference.name: MEShowUnconfiguredAssignedOccurrencesDefaultState
preference.preference_description: Determines if the default state of the 'Show Unconfigured Assigned Occurrences' checkbox is checked when the Manufacturing application is opened or a new BOM window is created. The default value is true.

preference.name: MEShowUnconfiguredChangesDefaultState
preference.preference_description: Determines if the default state of the 'Show Unconfigured Changes' checkbox is checked when the Manufacturing application is opened or a new BOM window is created. The default value is true.

preference.name: MEShowUnconfiguredOccurrencesEffectivityDefaultState
preference.preference_description: Determines if the default state of the 'Show Unconfigured By Occurrence Effectivity' checkbox is checked when the Manufacturing application is opened or a new BOM window is created. The default value is true.

preference.name: MEShowUnconfiguredVariantsDefaultState
preference.preference_description: Determines if the default state of the 'Show Unconfigured Variants' checkbox is checked when the Manufacturing application is opened or a new BOM window is created. The default value is true.

preference.name: MEShowWeldPointsConnectedToConfiguredOutParts
preference.preference_description: Enables the display of weld points when connected parts are configured out, in manufacturing applications. A valid value is: - true: to show weld points even if their connected parts are configured out. - false: to hide weld points if at least one of the connected parts is configured out. This is the default value.

preference.name: MEStockAbleBomLinePropertyName
preference.preference_description: Defines the property used to decide whether a BOM Line is stock-able or not. A valid value is any property internal name.

preference.name: MESupportMultipleRootsInStructureContext
preference.preference_description: Enables the display of multiple roots drop down on BOM primary views. The default value is false (display deactivated).

preference.name: MESyncOccGroupConfig
preference.preference_description:
Controls the synchronization of the configurations between the Occurrence Group window and the base view.
Valid values are: - true: when the user changes the configuration of an Occurrence Group tab, the system will immediately apply the same configuration to the base view. - false: the configuration will only be copied from the Occurrence Group tab to the base view the next time the base view becomes visible. This will improve the performance when working with large structures in the base view, but has the side effect that other structures linked to the base view (like a process structure associated with a product) will only be updated when switching to the base view tab.
The default is true.

preference.name: METIMEAllocatedTimePopulationMode
preference.preference_description: Defines the mode of the allocated time population. Valid values are 0 - 3: "0" Estimated Time "1" Simulated Time "2" Time Analysis Duration "3" Customized

preference.name: METIMEPopulateAllocatedTimeUpToLevel
preference.preference_description: Defines the level to which the populate allocated time command should be executed. Valid values are positive integer numbers and zero.

preference.name: METIMEPopulateAllocatedTimeUpToLevelEnabled
preference.preference_description: Defines if the option to update the allocated time to a certain level is active in the populate allocated time command in time tab. Valid values are true and false (default value).

preference.name: METIMEPopulateAllocatedTimeUsedSources
preference.preference_description: Defines the sources which are used in "custom" mode of the allocated time population. Valid values for each element in the list are 0 - 3. Each number must only occur once in the list: "0" Allocated Time "1" Simulated Time "2" Time Analysis Duration "3" Estimated Time

preference.name: METIMEPopulateAllocatedTimeZeroValuesEnabled
preference.preference_description: Defines if zero values are populated during the populate allocated time command in time tab. Valid values are true and false (default value).

preference.name: METimeAnalysisReportDefinitionID
preference.preference_description: Specifies the report ID to be used for generating the time analysis report.

preference.name: METimeAnalysisReportStylesheet
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of the xsl stylesheet to be used for the time analysis report.

preference.name: METimeDataCardConversionFactor
preference.preference_description: Specifies the factor to convert from data card time units to seconds. It is applied to time values from a data card. The standard MTM data cards hold times in TMU.

preference.name: METimeDataCardPath
preference.preference_description: Specifies the location of the data card. A valid value is the full path (e.g. C:\MyDataCard\MyDataCard.htm). Teamcenter needs to be restarted for any value change to take effect.

preference.name: METimeDecimalPlaces
preference.preference_description: Defines the number of decimal places displayed for time properties. Valid values are -1, 0, ..., 6, where -1 represents all significant places. This preference should be set using the Manufacturing Options Time panel to take effect without restarting Teamcenter. The default value for this preference is 2.

preference.name: METimeSystemFieldMappingDataset
preference.preference_description: Specifies the dataset containing the XML mapping file between time system fields and activity properties. The value of each field in the mapping file is applied to the corresponding property whenever data is copied from the time system to Teamcenter. A valid value must have the format "name:type:reference", where "name" specifies the name of the dataset, "type" the dataset type, and "reference" the reference of the file.

preference.name: METimeSystemSearchCriterionFields
preference.preference_description: Specifies the time system fields that can be searched for. The fields can be grouped in different configurations. Each value (or configuration) must have the format "configuration:field_1,field_2,...,field_n", where "configuration" is the configuration name and "field_i" is the time system field. The fields appear in the default configuration if the "configuration" section of the preference value is empty.

preference.name: METimeSystemSearchResultFields
preference.preference_description: Specifies the time system fields that are displayed in the search result. The fields can be grouped in different configurations. Each value (or configuration) must have the format "configuration:field_1,field_2,...,field_n", where "configuration" is the configuration name and the "field_i" entries are of the format "time_system_field;column_width_in_pixel" (e.g. "code;80"). The fields appear in the default configuration if the "configuration" section of the preference value is empty.

preference.name: METimeSystemUpdateIncludeStructure
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the time element structure should be included in assign and update actions. Valid values are "true" or "false" (default value).

preference.name: METimeSystemUpdateStructureLevel
preference.preference_description: Specifies the level up to which the time element structure should be included in assign and update actions.

preference.name: METimeSystemWebServiceLocation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the location of the WSDL description for the time system web service. Teamcenter needs to be restarted for any value change to take effect. Examples: - http://localhost:4848/TiConService/?wsdl - http://www.your-company.com:52000/TiConService/?wsdl

preference.name: METimeTabFilteredComponents
preference.preference_description: Defines which objects to filter out in the Time tab, such as Forms, Datasets, or specific types (e.g. AllocationMap Master). Activities cannot be filtered out, and will be ignored if listed.

preference.name: METimesActivityShownColumnWidths
preference.preference_description: Lists the column widths of the attributed which are shown in the Activities table in the Operations Times tab.

preference.name: METimesActivityShownColumns
preference.preference_description: Lists the column names of the attributes which are shown in the Activities table in the Operations Times tab.

preference.name: MEValidStockAbleValues
preference.preference_description: Defines the value of the property (MEStockAbleBomLinePropertyName) that is used to decide whether a BOM Line is stock-able or not.

preference.name: MEWorkarea.MEWorkarea.PasteDuplicateTemplate
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rules to be used when the "Paste Duplicate" operation is used to create new instances in a Plant Structure starting from a Plant Structure.

preference.name: MEWorkareaRevisionColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of columns that will be displayed for BOM tree table in Collaboration Manufacturing Engineering applications.

preference.name: MEWorkareaRevisionDisplayNameColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Stores the internal names of BOM Line properties which display names appear as columns from left-to-right for Plant Structure objects in Collaboration Manufacturing Engineering applications. This preference value is only a repository, and it is not to be modified other than by the code itself.

preference.name: MEWorkareaRevisionOccGroupColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of columns that will be displayed for the occurrence group tab of Plant Structure objects in Collaboration Manufacturing Engineering applications.

preference.name: MEWorkareaRevisionOccGroupDisplayNameColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Stores the internal names of BOM Line properties which display names appear as columns from left-to-right for occurrence group tab of Plant Structure objects in Collaboration Manufacturing Engineering applications. This preference value is only a repository, and it is not to be modified other than by the code itself.

preference.name: MEWorkareaRevisionOccGroupShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths for the columns displayed (identified by MEPlantContextOccGroupColumnsShownPref) for occurrence group tab of Plant Structure objects in Collaboration Manufacturing Engineering applications.

preference.name: MEWorkareaRevisionShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths for the columns displayed (identified by MEPlantContextColumnsShownPref) in Collaboration Manufacturing Engineering applications.

preference.name: ME_Proximity_FilteredIPA_root_name
preference.preference_description: Defines the name of the flat list collection holding all the proximity result groups.

preference.name: ME_Proximity_FilteredIPA_suffix
preference.preference_description: Defines the suffix for the names of the filtered In-Process Assembly occurrence groups.

preference.name: ME_Proximity_search_result_occ_group_type
preference.preference_description: Defines the occurrence group type indicating a Proximity search result collection in the process structure. Value must be a valid occurrence group type.

preference.name: ME_Proximity_search_result_occ_type
preference.preference_description: Defines the occurrence type indicating a Proximity search result collection in the process structure. Value must be a valid occurrence type.

preference.name: MPPTemplate
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of rules to be used when cloning an Activity in the Manufacturing Process Planner application.

preference.name: MPP_BrokenLinkSearchCriteriaList
preference.preference_description: List of preferences which define candidate search criteria.

preference.name: MPP_DefaultCandidateSearchCriteria
preference.preference_description: Default list of properties used to determine candidates for the Repair Broken Links action. Candidates are those for which the values of the specified properties match the values of the broken link's properties. Format is [logical.property] where logical is either "Mandatory", meaning the property values must match, or "Optional", meaning at least one of the optional property values must match. The property is a BOMLine property.

preference.name: MRMClassifyResource
preference.preference_description: Determines how newly created resources from Resource Manager (MRM) are classified. When the user selects File->New->Resource in the menu bar or clicks the corresponding toolbar button, a new Item and Item Revision are created and either the Item or the Item Revision is classified, depending on the value of this preference. A valid value is "Item" or "ItemRevision" (default value). The "ItemRevision" value is recommended, otherwise the use of some functionalities (e.g. revisioning, propagated attributes, status) is limited. The other object (either "Item" or "Item Revision") can still be classified using the "Classify Item" or "Classify Item Revision" functionalities.

preference.name: MRMDefaultItemType
preference.preference_description: Defines the Item type selected as default in the "New Resource" dialog in the Resource Manager application, in case no resource is opened and the preference "MRMItemTypes" is not defined. Values must be a valid Item type. The default value is "Mfg0MENCTool".

preference.name: MRMExpandUptoLevelOnLoad
preference.preference_description: Defines the number of levels an assembly is expanded when it is opened in Resource Manager. The default value is 4.

preference.name: MRMGCSItemType
preference.preference_description: Determines the Item type used when the Guided Component Search (GCS) functionality creates new Items. This is the case, for example, in the Classification application when a new classification object (ICO) is created in a class that has defined GCS connection point definitions (CPDs) defined or if a GCS CPD is added to a class that has ICOs without Items. A valid value is any valid Item types. The default value is "Item".

preference.name: MRMGCSShowCount
preference.preference_description: Activates the display of the number of matching components for each class in the Classification search dialog after a Guided Component Search operation. This is a user preference.

preference.name: MRMGTC3DModelAttributeID
preference.preference_description: Defines the ID of the Generic Tool Catalog (GTC) class attribute that holds the filename of the 3D step model for a catalog component. The default value is -159003. If a future tool catalog uses a different attribute ID for this purpose, it can be reconfigured here.

preference.name: MRMGTCAdapterConnectionCodeAttributeIDs
preference.preference_description: Defines the IDs of the Generic Tool Catalog (GTC) class attributes that hold ISO adapter connection codes for a catalog component. The default values are -150046, -150048, -151011, -151012, -151021, -151022, -151031, -151032, -151041, -151042, -151051 and -151052. Those connection codes will be converted from ISO to DIN, when the ICO is mapped into another class.

preference.name: MRMGTCCloudAccess
preference.preference_description: Activates the availability of the "ToolsUnited" Cloud Access functionality in the Resource Manager application. The default value is "true".

preference.name: MRMGTCConnectionCodeWildCards
preference.preference_description: Defines the wild characters that are used in vendor Generic Tool Catalogs (GTCs). Those wild characters will be converted to Teamcenter supported wild cards, when the ICO is mapped into Manufacturing Resource Library (MRL) classes. The default values are *, ? and $.

preference.name: MRMGTCInsertConnectionCodeAttributeIDs
preference.preference_description: Defines the IDs of the Generic Tool Catalog (GTC) class attributes that hold ISO insert connection codes for a catalog component. The default values are -150165, -151241, -151242, -151243 and -151244. Those connection codes will be converted from ISO to DIN, when the ICO is mapped into another class.

preference.name: MRMGTCPackageClientDir
preference.preference_description: Specifies the directory on the Teamcenter client where Generic Tool Catalog (GTC) packages are saved by the user and where Teamcenter looks for Generic Tool Catalog (GTC) packages to upload them to the Teamcenter server.

preference.name: MRMGTCPackageServerDir
preference.preference_description: Specifies the relative directory where the Teamcenter server stores Generic Tool Catalog (GTC) packages that are uploaded form the Teamcenter client to the Teamcenter server. The ZIP file will be extracted to a directory below the $TC_DATA directory: $TC_DATA/relative-directory-from-this-preference In that directory, a new directory with the ZIP file name is created. If this directory already exists, a new directory with the ZIP file name and an appended timestamp is created.

preference.name: MRMGTCVendorCatalogRootDir
preference.preference_description: Defines the directories where the Teamcenter server accesses the vendor Generic Tool Catalogs (GTCs). The default values are "C:\VendorCatalogs" and "D:\VendorCatalogs" on Windows, "/VendorCatalogs" on other Operating Systems.

preference.name: MRMItemTypes
preference.preference_description: Specifies what Item types will be selected as default in the "New Resource" dialog in the Resource Manager application, based on the currently selected class. Those Item types will be used for the specified class and all its child classes. It is possible to "overwrite" the Item type in child classes. Each valid value is defined as a pair of preference entries: the first entry must be a valid Classification class ID; the second entry must be a valid Item type. There can be any number of pairs.

preference.name: MRMMappingSourceICOAttributeID
preference.preference_description: Defines the attribute ID of the source instance classified object (ICO) that is used to name the target instance. This algorithm is used when multiple ICOs are mapping in the Classification table. The default value is -40219.

preference.name: MRMNeutralCSYSPrefixes
preference.preference_description: Defines the prefixes for customized neutral coordinate systems names usable in order of preference by the Resource Manager automatic positioning in the Resource Manager application. The default prefix for neutral coordinate system name is "NEUTRAL". Note that prefixes are case-insensitive.

preference.name: MRMPlugCSYSPrefixes
preference.preference_description: Defines the prefixes for customized machine-sided (plug) coordinate systems names usable in order of preference by the Resource Manager automatic positioning in the Resource Manager application. The default prefixes for machine-sided coordinate system names are "PLUG" and "MCS". Note that prefixes are case-insensitive.

preference.name: MRMPropagationRevisionRule
preference.preference_description: used to tell the MRM what revision rule should be used during the propagation of attributes. For example, when the user saves a resource assembly and there is a Propagation Start Point (PSP) defined in the assembly, the system propagates the attribute values to the assembly level. The specified revision rule configures the component revisions that are used during this propagation. Possible values are all revision rules that are defined in the database. (e.g., "Latest Working" or "Latest by Alpha Rev Order") The default value is "Latest Working". Note that values are case sensitive.

preference.name: MRMSetupSheetTemplates
preference.preference_description: Specifies what drawing parts are used as templates to generate setup sheets for resources. Each valid value is defined as a pair of preference entries: the first entry must be a valid Classification class ID; the second entry must be an existing Item Revision (for example "MRM_DRW_resources_general/A", where "/A" is the revision ID) which contains the desired setup sheet template part file as a UGPart dataset. There can be any number of pairs. It is possible to specify a higher class for the Classification class ID, in which case the template is inherited to all lower classes. It can be, however, overwritten for specific subclasses.

preference.name: MRMSetupSheets
preference.preference_description: Activates the functionality to generate setup sheets for resources from the Classification table panel and from the Resource Manager application. The default value is "false".

preference.name: MRMSocketCSYSPrefixes
preference.preference_description: Defines the prefixes for customized workpiece-sided (socket) coordinate systems names usable in order of preference by the Resource Manager automatic positioning in the Resource Manager application. The default prefixes for workpiece-sided coordinate system names are "SOCKET" and "CSW". Note that prefixes are case-insensitive.

preference.name: MRMTUURL
preference.preference_description: Stores the URL to the access the "ToolsUnited" web page, which can be used to retrieve vendor tool components from an external tool catalog. This functionality can be found in the Resource Manager application when searching tool components. The default value is "https://www.toolsunited.com/tu_en.html".

preference.name: MRMToolCheckLevel
preference.preference_description: Defines what level of tool parameter checking is performed during Manufacturing Resource Manager save operations. Valid values are: "none": Suppresses all tool parameter checking during the save operation. "errors": Only checks for tool parameters that are mandatory but missing. "all": Also reports optional tool parameters that are not set, in addition to the errors.

preference.name: MRMToolCheckType
preference.preference_description: Defines the tool attribute categories that are checked during Manufacturing Resource Manager save operations. Valid values are: "NX CAM": Checks a tool assembly's attribute values that are sent to NX CAM, based on its NX CAM tool type. "MRL PFT": Checks a tool component's attribute values that are used in its class's Part Family Template. Together with the Part Family Template, they are used by NX Graphics Builder to create the tool component's graphics.

preference.name: MRM_MTL_macro_att_ids
preference.preference_description: Specifies the attribute IDs in which the Manufacturing Tooling Library (MTL) macro name and model name (that are needed for create graphic) is stored. Valid values are two integers. Each integer must be a valid Classification attribute ID. The first integer is the attribute ID for the MTL macro name. The second integer is the attribute ID for the MTL model name.

preference.name: Mfg0BvrProcess_AffectedChildrenProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of properties on a Process object that will be affected if children are added or removed.

preference.name: Mfg0MEPlantBOP.Mfg0MEPlantBOP.PasteDuplicateTemplate
preference.preference_description: Defines the cloning rules to be used when pasting from a Plant Bill of Process (BOP) to Plant BOP. Valid values are in the following format: "primary:secondary:attribute_key.attribute_value:action", where: * the primary can be * for any class, class.<class name> for specific class or type.<type name> for specific type. * the secondary is the same format as primary * the attribute_key must be one of the following: Attribute, OccType, Relation. If the value is Attribute, the attribute_value must be the name of an attribute on the primary object. If the value is OccType, the attibute_value must be Null (no Occurrence Type) or * (any Occurrence Type) or the name of specific Occurrence Type. If the value is Relation, the attribute_value must be the internal name of a Relation Type. * the action must be one of the following: Clone, Reference, Ignore, EBOPReference EBOPReference will only be applied for Origin Links if the paste is within the same Plant BOP structure. In all other cases it will be treated as ignore (for Enterprise BOP).

preference.name: Mfg0MEPlantBOP.Mfg0MESimStudy.CopyPasteTemplate
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rules to be used when the "Paste" operation is used to create new instances in a Study starting from a Bill of Process (BOP) structure.

preference.name: Mfg0MEPlantBOPRevisionColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the columns to display in the base view of a Plant Bill of Process. Valid values are the names of each column in the order you wish them to appear: value_1, value_2.

preference.name: Mfg0MEPlantBOPRevisionDisplayNameColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Stores the internal names of BOP Line properties which display names appear as columns from left-to-right for Plant Bill of Process in Manufacturing Process Planner application. This preference value is only a repository, and it is not to be modified other than by the code itself.

preference.name: Mfg0MEPlantBOPRevisionOccGroupColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the columns to display in the Occurrence Group tab of a Plant Bill of Process. Valid values are the names of each column in the order you wish them to appear: value_1, value_2.

preference.name: Mfg0MEPlantBOPRevisionOccGroupDisplayNameColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Stores the internal names of BOM Line properties which display names appear as columns from left-to-right of Occurrence Group of a Plant Bill of Process in Manufacturing Process Planner application. This preference value is only a repository, and it is not to be modified other than by the code itself.

preference.name: Mfg0MEPlantBOPRevisionOccGroupShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the width in pixel of the columns displayed in the Occurrence Group tab of a Plant Bill of Process, as defined by the "Mfg0MEPlantBOPRevisionOccGroupColumnsShownPref" preference.

preference.name: Mfg0MEPlantBOPRevisionShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the width in pixel of the columns displayed in the base view of a Plant Bill of Process, as defined by the "Mfg0MEPlantBOPRevisionColumnsShownPref" preference.

preference.name: Mfg0MEProdPrgCol_ColumnPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the properties for objects of type Production Program Context to be displayed as columns in the Open Production Program Context dialog of the application Manufacturing Process Planner (MPP).

preference.name: Mfg0MEProdPrgCol_ColumnWidthPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths(in pixel) of the columns for the columns defined by the Mfg0MEProdPrgCol_ColumnPreferences preference.

preference.name: Mfg0MESimStudy.MEOP.CopyPasteTemplate
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rules to be used when the "Publish" operation is used from Study to an Operation.

preference.name: Mfg0MESimStudy.MEProcess.CopyPasteTemplate
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rules to be used when the "Publish" operation is used from Study to a Process.

preference.name: Mfg0MESimStudy.Mfg0MEPlantBOP.CopyPasteTemplate
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rules to be used when the "Publish" operation is used from Study to a PlantBOP.

preference.name: Mfg0MEStudy_ColumnPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of columns to be displayed for objects of type Mfg0MEStudy.

preference.name: Mfg0MEStudy_ColumnWidthPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths for the columns defined in the preference "Mfg0MEStudy_ColumnPreferences".

preference.name: PLMXML_Pre_Expand_BOP_Rule_Name
preference.preference_description: Specifies the name of a closure rule used to pre-expand Process structures prior to a PLMXML export operation. Pre-expansion on large structures increases the performance of the command, and reduces the load on the database server. If the preference is not set, no pre-expansion is done. The default value is not set. However, a possible closure rule is "PreExpandProcess".

preference.name: PMPApplication_open_collaboration_panel
preference.preference_description: Determines if the Collaboration panel is displayed when the Part Planner application opens.

preference.name: PasteDuplicateAllowedPlantBOPTemplates
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of cloning rule names to be used when pasting duplicate objects (clones) between different types of Plant Bill Of Processes. Valid values are in the following format: "SrcRootObjectType.TargetRootObjectType.PasteDuplicateTemplate", where: * SrcRootObjectType matches the root object type of source structure * TargetRootObjectType represents the root object type of structure being pasted to. * There will be a type lookup based on hierarchy, if exact match is not found. The PasteDuplicateTemplate value should be the last part. For pasting from regular (Non Enterprise) BOP, the MEProcess and MEOP are the two valid source root object types.

preference.name: PasteDuplicateTemplates
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rule names to be used when paste duplicating objects (Product / Process / Operation / Plant / Partition / Process Area) within structures in the Manufacturing Process Planner (MPP) application.

preference.name: PertChart.AutoSizeMode
preference.preference_description: Enables or disables auto-size in the PERT chart. When auto-size is disabled (false), the size of all newly created PERT nodes is uniform. When auto-size is enabled (true), the size of all newly created PERT nodes is automatically fitted to the displayed text (it includes allowing for multiple lines).

preference.name: PertChart.BoxAutoSizeMaxWidth
preference.preference_description: Defines the maximum allowed width (in pixels) of PERT node boxes. If the node text is wider than this width, then it will be wrapped into the next line. The default value is 170 (pixels).

preference.name: PertChart.BoxDefaultHeight
preference.preference_description: Defines the default height (in pixels) of PERT node boxes when the auto-size mode is disabled. The default value is 50 (pixels).

preference.name: PertChart.BoxDefaultWidth
preference.preference_description: Defines the default width (in pixels) of PERT node boxes when the auto-size mode is disabled. The default value is 138 (pixels).

preference.name: PertChart.MEActivity.Text
preference.preference_description: Defines the text to be displayed in the PERT node of type MEActivity. The format for a valid entry are several segments structured like this: <free-text>[property-name]. <free-text> is any text except square brackets ([ and ]). The text can be empty. Use the formula editor (Edit -> Options -> Manufacturing -> Pert tab) to edit the values of the preference. <property-name> is a valid property name for MEActivity object. It must be wrapped in square brackets, e.g. [object_name].

preference.name: PertChart.MEOP.Text
preference.preference_description: Defines the text to be displayed in the PERT node of type MEOP. The format for a valid entry are several segments structured like this: <free-text>[property-name]. <free-text> is any text except square brackets ([ and ]). The text can be empty. Use the formula editor (Edit -> Options -> Manufacturing -> Pert tab) to edit the values of the preference. <property-name> is a valid property name for MEOP object. It must be wrapped in square brackets, e.g. [object_name].

preference.name: PertChart.MEPlant.Text
preference.preference_description: Defines the text to be displayed in the PERT node of type MEPlant. The format for a valid entry are several segments structured like this: <free-text>[property-name]. <free-text> is any text except square brackets ([ and ]). The text can be empty. Use the formula editor (Edit -> Options -> Manufacturing -> Pert tab) to edit the values of the preference. <property-name> is a valid property name for MEPlant object. It must be wrapped in square brackets, e.g. [object_name].

preference.name: PertChart.MEProcess.Text
preference.preference_description: Defines the text to be displayed in the PERT node of type MEProcess. The format for a valid entry are several segments structured like this: <free-text>[property-name]. <free-text> is any text except square brackets ([ and ]). The text can be empty. Use the formula editor (Edit -> Options -> Manufacturing -> Pert tab) to edit the values of the preference. <property-name> is a valid property name for MEProcess object. It must be wrapped in square brackets, e.g. [object_name].

preference.name: PertChartCreationLayout
preference.preference_description: Defines how the location of newly created PERT nodes will be calculated in the PERT chart. Possible values are "Vertical" or "Horizontal".

preference.name: Plant.Template
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of template rules to be shown when a Plant structure is being cloned.

preference.name: Plant.Template.Cloning
preference.preference_description: Defines the action rules for cloning a template of Plant in the Manufacturing Process Planner application. The syntax is "[*]:[*]:[RelationType]:[Clone]" or "[CLASS]:[CLASS]:[RelationType]:[Clone]".

preference.name: PlantBOPAllowedTemplates
preference.preference_description: Lists the cloning rules available for cloning a Plant Bill of Process (BOP) from another Plant BOP.

preference.name: PlantBOPTemplate
preference.preference_description: Defines the cloning rules to be used when creating a Plant Bill of Process (BOP) from another Plant BOP structure. The assignments are referenced.

preference.name: Process.Template
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of rules to be used when cloning a Process in the Manufacturing Process Planner application.

preference.name: Process.Template.Cloning
preference.preference_description: Defines the action rules for cloning a template of Process in the Manufacturing Process Planner application. The syntax is "[*]:[*]:[RelationType]:[Clone]" or "[CLASS]:[CLASS]:[RelationType]:[Clone]".

preference.name: Process.Template.Ignoring_Consumes
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: Process.Template.Mapping_Consumes
preference.preference_description: New Copy action rules for cloning a template in the MPP application.

preference.name: Process.Template.Referencing_Consumes
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: ProcessSimulate_DataPrep_AITypes
preference.preference_description: Defines the names of the Application Interface types used to export data to Process Simulate application. Those names are used to determine when checking for prepared PLMXML files should be performed.

preference.name: ProcessSimulate_DataPrep_DatasetNameDelimiter
preference.preference_description: Specifies the character used to separate the revision rule name and the variant rule name at the end of the dataset from the prefix. Name format is <prefix><delim><rev rule name><delim><variant rule name, if any>.

preference.name: ProcessSimulate_DataPrep_DatasetsType
preference.preference_description: Defines the type of the dataset attached to product top line item revisions, to which prepared PLMXML files may be attached as named references. The PLMXML in these datasets are assumed by Process Simulate application to contain all data relevant to the configured structure. A valid value must match the setting in Process Simulate as defined in the model mapping configuration file.

preference.name: ProcessSimulate_DataPrep_Enabled
preference.preference_description: Enables RAC to look for prepared product PLMXML files prior to sending data to the Process Simulate application. If set to TRUE, RAC will check for valid files. If they are not found, the user is given the opportunity to cancel the operation.

preference.name: ProcessSimulate_DataPrep_Expiration
preference.preference_description: Defines the maximum age in hours of a prepared PLMXML file before the file is considered to be invalid or stale by the Process Simulate application. A value equal to zero disables this check. A valid value can be a decimal number of hours (the decimal separator being a dot, e.g. 1.5).

preference.name: ProcessSimulate_DataPrep_ProductTypes
preference.preference_description: Defines the names of product item types used to identify product structures to be checked for prepared PLMXML files.

preference.name: ProductBOPAllocationTemplate
preference.preference_description: Defines the cloning rules to be used when allocating from a Product Bill of Process (BOP). Valid values are in the following format: "primary:secondary:attribute_key.attribute_value:action", where: * the primary can be * for any class, class.<class name> for specific class or type.<type name> for specific type. * the secondary is the same format as primary * the attribute_key must be one of the following: Attribute, OccType, Relation. If the value is Attribute, the attribute_value must be the name of an attribute on the primary object. If the value is OccType, the attibute_value must be Null (no Occurrence Type) or * (any Occurrence Type) or the name of specific Occurrence Type. If the value is Relation, the attribute_value must be the internal name of a Relation Type. * the action must be one of the following: Clone, Reference, Ignore or EBOPCreate. EBOPCreate is only for creation of Origin Links between original and cloned structures (for Enterprise BOP).

Let us consider the following example: "Mfg0BvrOperation:Mfg0consumed_material". This means that any modification to the "Mfg0consumed_material" property on an object of type "Mfg0BvrOperation" between the Isolated Study and the BOP, triggers a publication change from the Isolated Study

preference.name: TWP.AppearanceColors
preference.preference_description:
Defines the colors to be shown for various figures in the "Time Way Plan" view of Manufacturing Process Planner application.
The valid format is: Object:ObjectName;BackgroundColor:RGBCode;ConflictColor:RGBCode;DuplicateColor:RGBCode;ForegroundColor:RGBCode
Where: * ObjectName can be "Operation", "Station" or "ProductionZoneLine". * BackgroundColor: This is the color to depict an object. For "ProductionZoneLine", this is the boundary color. * ConflictColor: This attribute is applicable to Operations only, whenever a conflict is detected, e.g. overlapping operations, operations starting at same position, etc. * DuplicateColor: This attribute is applicable to Operations only, whenever an operation occurs in multiple execution Positions. * ExceedingColor: This attribute is applicable to Operations only, whenever an operation exceeds the cycle time of station. * ForegroundColor: This attribute is applicable only for Process Zone and Line boundaries (ProductionZoneLine), in order to show the color for text. * RGBCode: This represents the color to apply in the format "integer_1,integer_2,integer_3", where each integer is between 0 and 255.
Note: Values violating the mentioned format will be ignored, and the user will not be able to see the required colors. Instead, default colors will be applied.

Defines the text displayed as header of the column "Execution Position" in the "Time Way Plan" view of Manufacturing Process Planner application. The valid values are "object_string" (property name for execution position name) or "Mfg0Acronym" (property name for execution position acronym).

preference.name: TWP.Operation.Text

The valid format is "Legend [Property_Name]", where "Legend" is any string and is displayed as it is. "Property_Name" is the internal name of the property on the operation object. The string "[Property_Name]" is replaced by the property display name: e.g. the value "Name: [bl_rev_object_name]" will be displayed as "Name: Object Name".

The string "[Property_Name]" is replaced by the property display name: e.g. the value "Name: [bl_rev_object_name]" will be displayed as "Name: Object Name".

preference.name: TWP.Tooltips

Defines the properties to be displayed as tooltip for elements in "Time Way Plan" view of the Manufacturing Process Planner application.
The valid format is "Object:ObjectName;TooltipProperties:[Property_Name]", where: * "ObjectName" is "Operation" * "Property_Name" is the internal name of the property on the "Object".
The tooltip will contain the property display name along with its value (e.g. the value "[bl_rev_object_name]" will be trigger a tooltip as "Item Name: Object Name". Multiple properties can be added with separator chosen by user. For eg. TooltipProperties:[property_1],[property_2],[property_3].
Note: Values violating the mentioned format will be ignored, and the default value 'Object Name' will be displayed.

preference.name: TWP.VisibilityOptions

The valid format is "VisibilityOption:[true|false]", where the visibility options are: * ShowCarpet: This attribute controls the visibility of carpet in "Time Way Plan" view. * ShowOperations: This attribute controls the visibility of operations in "Time Way Plan" view. * ShowProductImage: This attribute controls the visibility of product image on stations in "Time Way Plan" view. * ShowBoundaries: This attribute controls the visibility of process area/line/zone boundaries in "Time Way Plan" view.
Note: Values violating the mentioned format will be ignored, and the default value 'true' will be used.

preference.name: controllingOccsForProcessConfiguration
preference.preference_description: Following preference is used for configuring Processes and Operations in TCM. controllingOccsForProcessConfiguration Values can be any valid occurrence type used in Process. The type has to be defined in admin->Type application before using it here. By default, it will be MEConsumed.You can remove this or add it as per your requirements. Note that you can have no occType defined for this functionality in which case, the configuration of operations is not affected by the configuration of consumed items. Note that this is site preference only.

preference.name: typeAndRuleForProcessConfiguration
preference.preference_description:
Configures processes or compositions in the Bill Of Process. This preference specifies what parent types in the process should be configured out depending on child occurrences of controlling types as defined by the "controllingOccsForProcessConfiguration" preference. You can also use this preference to configure out processes based on child relationships. If you do this, the "controllingOccsForProcessConfiguration" preference is ignored. Accepts strings separated by a colon as follows: parent-item-subtype:One | All | AllLoaded | OneLoaded[OCCType:occurrence-type | CHILD:child-type] parent-item-subtype specifies the item, operation, or process subtype as defined in the Business Modeler IDE application. This value is case-sensitive and must exactly match the business object specified in Business Modeler IDE. The second string after the colon must be one of the following:
"One" specifies that the parent will be configured out if any one of its controlling occurrence is configured out. "All" specifies that the parent is configured out only if all its controlling occurrences are configured out. "AllLoaded" specifies that the parent is configured out only if all its loaded controlling occurrences are configured out. Loaded occurrences are occurrences that are referenced from another top line that is defined as the configuring structure. This parameter is not relevant for defining child types. "OneLoaded" specifies that the parent process is configured out if one of its loaded controlling occurrences are configured out. This parameter is not relevant for defining child types. OCCType:occurrence-type | CHILD:child-type Specifies that the filtering is based on the designated occurrence types or the designated child types. You can enter multiple occurrence types or multiple child types separated by a comma. Specifying this optional group of values for the preference causes the configuration mechanism to ignore the value of the controllingOccsForProcessConfiguration preference.
The following examples show the preference without the optional parameters. The explanation of these examples assumes that the value for the controllingOccsForProcessConfiguration preference is MEConsumed. MEOP:One - Configures out parent operations of MEOP type if one of the consumed occurrences of MEConsumed type is configured out. MEProcess:All - Configures out parent operations of MEProcess if all consumed occurrences of MEConsumed type are configured out. MEPSD:AllLoaded - Configures out parent operations of MEPSD if all loaded consumed occurrences of MEConsumed type are configured out.
The following examples show the preference with the optional parameters: MEOP:One:OCCType:MEConsumed - Configures out parent operations of MEOP type if one of the consumed occurrences of MEConsumed type is configured out. MEOP:One:OCCType:MEConsumed,MEAssign - Configures out parent operations of MEOP type if one of the consumed occurrences of MEConsumed or MEAssign type is configured out. MEProcess:All:CHILD:MEOP - Configures out parent operations of MEProcess type if all of the child occurrences of MEOP type are configured out.
By default, it will be MEOP:One and MENCMachining:One to preserve old functionality. Note-If this preference has no value, parent lines such as operations are not configured out by their children or consumed objects. Note-No spaces(blanks) are allowed in the preference. Note-The input is case sensitive.

preference.name: PDX_pkg_file_name
preference.preference_description: Defines the name format for PDX packages (named references attached to Dataset objects). The format is based on the keywords ItemID (Item ID), RevID (Revision ID), ItemName (Item name), TargetSite (Remote site) and TimeStamp (time stamp) of the object being exported. The format is any combination of one or more of the above specified keywords. Any other word specified in the format will be treated as a constant. For example a value "PDX:ItemId:RevId:ItemName:TargetSite:TimeStamp" would result in the following generated filename: "PDX_00001_A_Assembly1_Site1_31-Jan-2008_19-48-30.pdx". This is a site preference.

category.category_description: All the preferences related to Teamcenter Product Master Management
