preference.name: LINEOFASSEMBLYINFO.COPYNEWVERSION.RENDERING
preference.preference_description: Defines the name of the XML rendering dataset for rendering the "Copy Version" screen for Line of Assembly in the Product Master Management application.

preference.name: LINEOFFABRICATIONINFO.COPYNEWVERSION.RENDERING
preference.preference_description: Defines the name of the XML rendering dataset for rendering the "Copy Version" screen for Line of Fabrication in the Product Master Management application.

preference.name: LINEOFUSAGEINFO.COPYNEWVERSION.RENDERING
preference.preference_description: Defines the name of the XML rendering dataset for rendering the "Copy Version" screen for Line of Usage in the Product Master Management application.

preference.name: PARTMASTERINFO.COPYNEWVERSION.RENDERING
preference.preference_description: Defines the name of the XML rendering dataset for rendering the "Copy Version" screen for Part Master in the Product Master Management application.

preference.name: PMM_ASMQTY_COMPARE_DIFF_COLOR_PREF
preference.preference_description: Stores the RGB (Red-Green-Blue) code for the difference in quantity of the Structures being compared in the Product Master Management application. Each component of the RGB value is an integer between 0 and 255, and the separator is a comma. The default value is "255,128,64".

preference.name: PMM_COMPARE_ANCHORROW_COLOR_PREF
preference.preference_description: Stores the RGB (Red-Green-Blue) code for the foreground color of the anchor row to which other rows will be compared in the Product Master Management application. Each component of the RGB value is an integer between 0 and 255, and the separator is a comma. The default value is "0,0,255".

preference.name: PMM_LOV_CONTROL_TYPE
preference.preference_description: Stores the control type used for the List Of Values (LOV) widget in the Product Master Management (PMM) application. Valid values are: * TableCombo: Sets the Nebula Table Combo as widget to display the List Of Values (LOV). * DynamicLOV: Sets the Dynamic LOV as widget to display the List Of Values (LOV). This is the default value.

preference.name: PMM_STRUCTCOMPARE_COMPLETEDIFF_COLOR_PREF
preference.preference_description: Stores the RGB (Red-Green-Blue) code for the difference in the Structures being compared in the Product Master Management application. Each component of the RGB value is an integer between 0 and 255, and the separator is a comma. The default value is "255,0,0".

preference.name: PMM_STRUCTCOMPARE_PARTIALDIFF_COLOR_PREF
preference.preference_description: Stores the RGB (Red-Green-Blue) code for the difference in attributes of the Structures being compared in the Product Master Management application. Each component of the RGB value is an integer between 0 and 255, and the separator is a comma. The default value is "255,186,117".

preference.name: STOP_TC_HEARTBEAT_PING_FROM_PMM
preference.preference_description: Defines if the user wants to stop the heartbeat ping to the Teamcenter server. The valid value is: * true: No heart beat call is sent by the rich client to the teamcenter server when users are working only in Product Master Management. This may cause Teamcenter server sessions to time-out. * false: The rich client sends heartbeat calls to the Teamcenter server.

preference.name: APPR_allow_separate_spatial_processing
preference.preference_description: When set to "true", specifies that spatial cache processing for Appearances will be done in a separate update package (in a separate appearance updater process). A value of "false" means that spatial cache processing will occur in the same updater process as the rest of the appearance processing.

preference.name: APPR_max_appearances_per_process
preference.preference_description: Specifies the maximum number of appearances that will be processed at a time by the appearance updater. A lower value will result in lower memory consumption at the cost of performance of appearance updates.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextSupportInstallationAssemblySelection
preference.preference_description: Enables the selection of Installation assemblies. The default value is false (disabled). This is a user preference.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextUseUnconfigurableSearchResults
preference.preference_description: Enables the addition of unconfigurable BOM Lines to search results. The default value is false (disabled). This is a user preference.

preference.name: TC_allow_appr_checking
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the appearances checking is to be enabled or not. Valid values are true/false.

preference.name: TC_allow_appr_query_auditing
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the appearances querying is to be audited or not. Valid values are true/false.

preference.name: TC_appr_allow_remote_query
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the querying for remote appearances (ones associated with a remote published appearance-root) is to be enabled or not. Valid values are true/false. NOTE: To publish an appearance-root, ensure that AppearanceRoot is in the list for TC_publishable_classes preference.

preference.name: TC_appr_checking_interval
preference.preference_description: Specifies the appearances checking interval in hours (how often do we check appearances).

preference.name: TC_appr_remote_query_timeout
preference.preference_description: Specifies the timeout period (in seconds) for remote appearance queries.

preference.name: TC_prevent_appr_query_on_corrupt_root
preference.preference_description: Appearances Logical: do we allow the querying of appearances associated with a corrupt appearance-root?

preference.name: APPR_allow_background_updates
preference.preference_description: Whether to allow the appearance_updater to perform background updates (using its "-background" flag).

preference.name: APPR_background_updater_admin_email_address
preference.preference_description: Whom to send emails regarding failure to process an appearance update package in background mode. Special values are: - $USER meaning the Teamcenter user that the appearance updater is logged in as - $OSUSER meaning the OS user running the appearance updater As shipped, the value is $OSUSER, to ensure that at least someone is notified.

preference.name: APPR_background_updater_auditing_enabled
preference.preference_description: Whether to create audit records when the appearance_updater performs background updates.

preference.name: APPR_background_updater_email_interval_for_different_package
preference.preference_description: The minimum interval (in minutes) to allow the sending of emails regarding the failure of the appearance updater to process any package in background mode.

preference.name: APPR_background_updater_email_interval_for_same_package
preference.preference_description: The minimum interval (in minutes) to allow the sending of emails regarding the failure of the appearance updater to process a particular package in background mode.

preference.name: APPR_background_updater_gap_between_tries
preference.preference_description: How long (in seconds) a background updater should wait between attempts (successful or otherwise) to look for packages to process.

preference.name: APPR_background_updater_interval
preference.preference_description: How often (in minutes) to expect a background appearance updater to be run (for example in a cron job or equivalent). When a new package is placed on the update queue, then if background updaters are expected to be running (as specified by the supervisor preference being 0) and such an updater has not recently enough, then an email is sent to the recipient specified by the Site Preference "APPR_background_updater_admin_email_address".

preference.name: APPR_background_updater_max_num_failures
preference.preference_description: How many background updater failures to allow for a particular package. Once the number of failures exceeds this value, background updates are disabled (by setting the Site Preference "APPR_allow_background_updates" to false).

preference.name: APPR_background_updater_max_num_heartbeats
preference.preference_description: How many heartbeat records to keep per machine. A heartbeat record is simply a note made by the background appearance updater to show that it has run; this serves as a way to find out from the database whether such updaters are running as intended.

preference.name: APPR_background_updater_max_num_records
preference.preference_description: How many records to keep about the appearance updater's background activity.

preference.name: APPR_background_updater_max_num_tries
preference.preference_description: How many times an individual background updater should look for packages to process before exiting.

preference.name: PUBLISH_AlignableSourceTypes
preference.preference_description: Specifies the types of Item which are valid as source for a PublishLink object. PublishLink is created between absolute occurrences and can be used for structure alignment.

preference.name: PUBLISH_AlignableTargetTypes
preference.preference_description: Specifies the types of Item which are valid as target for a PublishLink object. PublishLink is created between absolute occurrences and can be used for structure alignment.

preference.name: PartStructureDepthForCompletenessCheck
preference.preference_description: Controls how many levels should be traversed while doing Completeness Check of the Part structures of CAD BOM alignment. The default value is 10000. A null(0) or negative value will not process any level. The Teamcenter server needs to be restarted for any change in preference value to take effect.

preference.name: ACTLine_AutoSelect_UsageAddress
preference.preference_description: Indicates Collaboration Context application to load a corporate part by auto-selecting a Usage Address from usage server. This is a site preference.

preference.name: ALLOC_Group_Allocation_Types
preference.preference_description: Enforces the check on the type of Allocations that can be created in the context of an Allocation Map. Each valid value is in the format: "AllocationMap_subtype_internal_name:Allocation_type1,Allocation_type2,Allocation_type3". Multiple entries for different Allocation Map sub-types can be specified by entering additional preference values.

preference.name: ALLOC_Product_Representation_Types
preference.preference_description: Controls the structure View types that can be used for Allocation Map objects creation. Each valid value is in the format: "AllocationMap_subtype_internal_name:View_type1,View_type2,View_type3". Multiple entries for different Allocation Map sub-types can be specified by entering additional preference values.

preference.name: ALLOC_Source_Occurrence_Types
preference.preference_description: Specifies a list of components that can participate as source components for a given Allocation type. The components in this preference are the valid Sub-Types of Allocations and valid sub-types of objects that can be instantiated in the Product Structure Editor.

preference.name: ALLOC_Target_Occurrence_Types
preference.preference_description: Specifies a list of components that can participate as target components for a given Allocation type. The components in this preference are the valid Sub-Types of Allocations and valid sub-types of objects that can be instantiated in the Product Structure Editor.

preference.name: ALLOC_map_copy_allocations
preference.preference_description: If one of the following operations on an AllocationMapRevision (copy,saveAs,Revise) is mentioned as values in this preference, then for that particular operation - all the Allocations pointing to the AllocationMapRevision are carried forward. If the user DOES NOT want to carry forward the allocations on a particular operation, then s/he must omit/remove the name of that operation from the values of this preference.By default for the above mentioned 3 operations on an AllocationMapRevision, all the allocations are carried forward to the next entity. User can omit all the values, if desired!

preference.name: ALLOC_source_target_cardinality
preference.preference_description: Specifies the cardinality associated with a given Allocation type. For instance users may want only a certain number of components in source and target for a given Allocation type. The cardinality values can be any of the positive integers or "n" specifying no limit (e.g. n,n; 1,n; n,1; 1,6; etc.). A value "Allocation:5,6" means that the user can specify no more than 5 source and 6 target components.

preference.name: Cfg0ProductItem_OpenByName_ColumnPreferences
preference.preference_description: The OOTB columns to be displayed for the Cfg0ProductItem open by name pop-up

preference.name: Item_Cfg0ProductItem_default_relation
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default relation created between a Configurator Context and the Item under which it is pasted.

preference.name: PSM_default_configurator_context
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default Configurator Context used in the Structure Management application to configure the variability of Product Structures. This is an internal preference used by Product Structure and should not be modified manually.

preference.name: PSM_enable_product_configurator
preference.preference_description: Enables the use of Teamcenter Product Configurator to configure the variability of Product Structure. Any modification to the preference value requires restart of Teamcenter to avoid data integrity issues. The PSEVariantsMode preference will be ignored and Variants will be authored/configured using Configurator Context via association or setting the Default Configurator Context. Valid values are: * true: Product Structure will use the Configurator Context for Variability. This is the default value. * false: Product Structure will refer to the PSEVariantsMode preference for Variability.

category.name: Product Structure.Design Context.Clearance Integration
category.category_description: Defines preferences for clearance proxies in a site

preference.name: RDVClearanceProxyServers
preference.preference_description: Provides the values for the database connection, which will be used by the clearance proxy to connect to the clearance database. Valid values are formatted as follows: <your_clearance_server_1>:<port_nb>:<database_connection_name>

preference.name: CM_change_space_enabled
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether a corresponding Change Space should also be automatically created when an Enterprise Change Notice (ECN) is created. Valid values are: * true: Automatically create a Change Space for new ECNs. * false: Do not automatically create a Change Space for new ECNs. This is the default value.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextECObject.TYPE
preference.preference_description: Defines the type of Engineering Change Object that DesignContext uses for finding associated WorkParts objects. For New Change objects, the default value is ChangeRequestRevision. For Classic Change objects, the default value is EngChange Revision.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextECObject.WorkPartProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the DesignContext relationship properties for finding associated WorkParts objects upon adding an Engineering Change. For New Change objects, possible values are CMHasSolutionItem, CMHasProblemItem, CMHasImpactedItem, CMReferences, CMImplementedBy, CMImplements and CMHasWorkBreakdown. For Classic Change objects, possible values are solution_items, problem_items, affected_items, reference_items, addressed_by.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextECObject.WorkPartRelationships
preference.preference_description: Defines the DesignContext relationships for finding associated Engineering Changes upon adding a WorkPart. For New Change objects, possible values are CMHasSolutionItem, CMHasProblemItem, CMHasImpactedItem, CMReferences, CMImplements and CMHasWorkBreakdown. For Classic Change objects, possible values are EC_affected_item_rel,EC_solution_item_rel,EC_problem_item_rel,EC_reference_item_rel,EC_addressed_by_rel.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextAllowNoWorkParts
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the workparts are required to continue or not within the Context Configuration (2nd) screen. Valid values are 0/1. 0 - Requires at least one WorkPart to continue. 1 - Allows to continue without WorkParts.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextExcludedWorkPart.Types
preference.preference_description: The Item Types which whould not be added to the Work Part list in the DesignContext e.g.: EngChange.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextFindInstallationTreeWalkIncrement
preference.preference_description: Specifies the direction for the algorithm to walk the tree in order to find the Installation Assembly for a given BOMLine. Valid values are -1/1. -1 - Down from the top towards the BOMLine. 1 - Up from the BOMLine towards the root

preference.name: PortalDesignContextIsInstallationAssemblyMethod
preference.preference_description: Method to identify Installation Assemblies. The following methods are available: transformsComponents, isPrecise, hasIRType and has_bomline_prop.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextIsInstallationAssemblyMethod.hasIRType.Type
preference.preference_description: hasIRType method is one of the methods in identifying Installation Assemblies. The key word is used for getting the type of BOMLine.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextIsInstallationAssemblyMethod.has_bomline_prop.name
preference.preference_description: has_bomline_prop method is one of the methods in identifying Installation Assemblies. The key word is used for getting the name of the specified property which we need to lookup.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextIsInstallationAssemblyMethod.has_bomline_prop.value
preference.preference_description: has_bomline_prop method is one of the methods in identifying Installation Assemblies. The key word is used for getting the value of a specified property which we need to match.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextProductItemQuery
preference.preference_description: Saved query for DesignContext to find Product Items (Context Definition (1st) Screen).

preference.name: DesignContextIncludeSubComponentsForSpatialSearch
preference.preference_description: This preference is added so that components may be used for executing proximity search on sub-assemblies. This is useful in cases when the sub-assemblies may not have geometry of their own. Setting it to FALSE will execute the search only on the sub-assembly.

preference.name: DesignContextMaximumShownTabs
preference.preference_description: Specifies the maximum number of tabs in the third Screen of DesignContext application. The default value for this preference is 5.

preference.name: DesignContextOrphanBOMLineSupport
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the DesignContext Application in Teamcenter should provide the Orphan BOMLine support. Valid values are TRUE/FALSE. If this is set to "TRUE", DesignContext would load all it's parents till the top line is reached by default. If it is set to "FALSE", it would be treated as an orphan and would only be loaded on request.

preference.name: DesignContext_ItemID_Query_lookup_string
preference.preference_description: This is used for defining the look-up string corresponding to the saved query to find - WorkPart items by "ItemID" entry: The default search used by DesignContext is "Item...", which corresponds to the lookup string "k_find_item_name". The Saved Query corresponding to this string is looked up from TC_ROOT/lang/textserver/<language>/qry_text_locale.xml file. If the User desires to use a separate Query for this purpose, the user has to ensure that the query corresponds to the String defined for the following Preference and that it contains entries for ItemID.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextAttributeSchemaSuppressedAttributes
preference.preference_description: Used for the Attribute suppression in the Filter Configuration (3rd) Screen.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextQPLServers
preference.preference_description: Preference setting for Global QPL Server. This should be set to <hostname>:<portno> hostname corresponds to the machine where the QPL Server runs and portno corresponds to the port where it listens to requests. Default port number is 14730.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextSearchEnginePreference
preference.preference_description: Specifies the SearchEngine to be picked up by DesignContext Application for searching purposes. For Teamcenter Rich Client users it is expected that com.teamcenter.rac.tcapps/com/teamcenter/rac/designcontext/designcontext.properties defines properties that match the preference value. The value of these properties in com.ugsolutions.tc.designcontext.designcontext.properties are expected to define the Java class that instantiates the corresponding search engine. For the 3 COTS provided search engines, the corresponding COTS properties are provided. The value of the Key PortalDesignContextSearchEnginePreference should match the Key present in com.teamcenter.rac.tcapps/com/teamcenter/rac/designcontext/designcontext.properties file. If there is no value set to the Key, default value will be: QPLSearchEngineFactory. The possible values are QPLSearchEngineFactory, QPLJTSearchEngineFactory, AppearanceSearchEngineFactory, CachelessSearchEngineFactory

preference.name: CUSTOM_CLONE_SCRIPT
preference.preference_description: Specifies the custom clone utility to be called from "Export Configured UG Assembly" functionality from DesignContext application. If the value is not specified for this preference, the standard ugmanager_clone utility is used

preference.name: DesignContextBOMWriterNoDescendantsInPLMXML
preference.preference_description: Defines if PLMXML files, generated by the BOM Writer for interoperability (open in NX) in the Design Context application, should have descendants of the selected BOM Lines. Valid values are: - true: The descendants of the selected BOM Lines will not appear in the generated PLMXML file. This is the default value. - false: The descendants of the selected BOM Lines will appear in the generated PLMXML file.

preference.name: DesignContext_PSE_Synchronization
preference.preference_description: Valid values for this preference are 0/1. 0 - DC will not sync with PSE which is the default mode. 1 - DC will Sync with PSE.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextCADbookmarkType
preference.preference_description:
Interoperability option. 1 - Generate a bookmark that can be read by NX. 2 - Generate a bookmark that can be read by PV or NX. (Puts the entire assembly into the bookmark but has VISUALIZE=NO on all but selected BOMLines). 16 - Can be OR'd with "2"(Generate a bookmark that can be read by PV which contains ONLY the selected BOMLines and their ancestors to the root assembly - do not traverse the entire assembly. This should be used for the DesignContext Application to avoid traversing the whole of very large assemblies. This type will cause the children of selected assemblies to be added to the bookmark, loaded and displayed by PV. See below for options to modify this behaviour). 32 - Can be OR'd with "18" (Generate a bookmark that excludes children of explicitly selected children. Will cause PV to show a tree which does not have the children of selected sub-assemblies. If specified without 16 then this is ignored). 64 - Can be OR'd with "18" (Generate a bookmark which includes the children of explicitly selected assemblies but marks them with the Visualize="no" flag so they are not loaded and visualized in PV). The following are the values related to Edit-->Options-->ProductContext-->General of DesignContext Application.
The values will reflect in General Panel as: (1) - When NOTHING was selected from ugBookmarkType. (2+16 = 18) - When only ugPruneTreeCheckBox was selected 2+16+32 = 50 When both ugPruneTreeCheckBox and ugSupprCompCheckBox were selected. (2+16+64 = 82) - When both ugPruneTreeCheckBox and ugHideCompCheckBox were selected. (2) - When NOTHING was selected from pvBookmarkType. (2+16 = 18) - When only pvPruneTreeCheckBox was selected. (2+16+32 = 50) - When both pvPruneTreeCheckBox and pvSupprCompCheckBox were selected. (2+16+64 = 82) - When both pvPruneTreeCheckBox and pvHideCompCheckBox were selected CAD Bookmark Type.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextVISbookmarkType
preference.preference_description: Vis Bookmark Type.

preference.name: CLR_Timeout_Limit
preference.preference_description: Specifies the maximum time a user should wait for results in the clearance analysis for batch process (In Seconds).

preference.name: CLR_Wait_Time
preference.preference_description: Used to set a limit how long each iteration should wait for results in the clearance analysis for batch process (In Seconds).

preference.name: PortalDesignContextAlwaysResetFilterConfigurationPanel
preference.preference_description: Defines if the filter settings in the 3rd screen of the "Design Context" application will always be reset whenever switching between the 2nd and the 3rd screen. A false value retains the filter settings in the 3rd screen.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextCLRServers
preference.preference_description: Used to Locate the clearance Server and its port. e.g. hostabc:14740, hostdef:14740

preference.name: PortalDesignContextMaxMatchingBOMLines
preference.preference_description: Specifies a maximum number of assembly components a PSE search may match Context Configuration (2nd) and Filter Configuration (3rd) screen.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextMaxMatchingObjects
preference.preference_description: Specifies the maximum number of components a query may match (e.g. Workparts, ChangeItems, or CR Jobs) Context Definition (1st) screen.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextSetVariantRulesMaxTargetAppearances
preference.preference_description: Specifies the maximum number of target appearances for toggle button "Valid Overlays Only" Filter Configuration (3rd) screen.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextSetVariantRulesMaxVariantRules
preference.preference_description: Specifies the maximum number of variants (option permutations) for toggle button "Valid Overlays Only" Filter Configuration (3rd) screen.

preference.name: RDV_convert_ves_to_new_variant_model_by_default
preference.preference_description: Allows the conversion or migration of old format VES (Variant Expressions) to new variant model VES by default. If the value is set to "true", the old format VES will be converted into new variant model VES. The default value is "false".

preference.name: RDV_turn_audit_logging_on
preference.preference_description: Controls the way the audit log is appended by this functionality. The preference can take only logical values: True\False. If the preference "RDV_turn_audit_logging_on" is set to True, the audit log file will be updated whenever the PSVA wizards (Replace Design in Product, Add design to Product ) are used. In addition, this functionality will check if the preferred_abs_occ_id of the occurrence exists and would not use this occurrence for further processing.

preference.name: DesignContextLoadRDVContextObjectMode
preference.preference_description: Indicates in which mode a Structure Context Object would be loaded in DesignContext Application. A value of 1 is the default value for this preference and it indicates dynamic mode of loading. A value of 0 indicates static mode of loading.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextProductContextColumnsHiddenPref
preference.preference_description: Product Context hidden properties.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextProductContextColumnsHiddenPrefWidth
preference.preference_description: Product Context hidden properties widths.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextProductContextColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Product Context shown (composite) properties. Top-left table on Context Definition (1st) Screen. Example: To list object strings of "view" BOM View Revision - with Alpha status of ItemRevisions with Alpha status: view BOMView Revision.revision_list(release_statuses=Alpha):structure_revisions(release_statuses=Alpha,bom_view:view_type=view):object_string.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextProductContextColumnsShownPrefWidth
preference.preference_description: Product Context shown properties widths.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextProductContextProperties
preference.preference_description: List (composite) of properties of Product Contexts. Recommended alternatives: 1. Use a combination of properties on the Item Revision master form (Project_ID for product type, PLC_Stage for model year). It is recommended to add these properties also to the PortalDesignContextProductContextColumnsShownPref preference. PortalDesignContextProductContextProperties=ItemRevision.item_master_tag:Project_ID,ItemRevision.item_master_tag:PLC_Stage. PortalDesignContextProductContextColumnsShownPref=ItemRevision.object_string,ItemRevision.item_master_tag:Project_ID,ItemRevision.item_master_tag:PLC_Stage. 2. Use a naming convention on product context item revisions. PortalDesignContextProductContextProperties=ItemRevision.object_name. All ItemRevisions sharing the same values on all Product Context properties form collectively one product context.

preference.name: RDIP_report_invalid_thoughts
preference.preference_description: Indicates if an error message should be displayed when one of the thoughts is invalid while performing "Replace Design in Product" in the Structure Manager application. Valid values for this site preference are: *true: the error message is displayed. *false: no error message is displayed. This is the default value.

preference.name: RDVLoadAppearanceGroupMode
preference.preference_description: Specifies the path to follow while loading an Appearance Group. Valid values are 1, 2 and 3. 1 - Load the Item corresponding to first created Occurrence. 2 - Load the Item corresponding to last created Occurrence. 3 - Load the Item corresponding to occurrence configured by User's default Revision Rule.

preference.name: SYNC_PRODUCT_APN_BATCH_SIZE
preference.preference_description: Defines the appearance path node (APN) batch size for sync_product_apns utility. The default value is 10000. This is a site preference.

preference.name: DesignContextRDVContextObjectAddToECObjectPseudoFolderPreference
preference.preference_description: Indicates which pseudo folder to use while attaching a Structure Context Object to a Engineering Change Item Revision.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextProductItemColumnsHiddenPref
preference.preference_description: Product Item hidden properties.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextProductItemColumnsHiddenPrefWidth
preference.preference_description: Product Item hidden properties widths.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextProductItemColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Product Item shown (composite) properties. Top-right table on Context Definition (1st) Screen.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextProductItemColumnsShownPrefWidth
preference.preference_description: Product Item shown properties widths.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextProductItemProperties
preference.preference_description: List (composite) of properties of Product Items. Recommended alternatives: 1. Create a custom Item type (say "Product"). PortalDesignContextProductItemProperties=object_type. PortalDesignContextProductItemProperties.object_type=Product. 2. Change ownership of all product items to a new group (say "Vehicle"). PortalDesignContextProductItemProperties=owning_group. PortalDesignContextProductItemProperties.owning_group=Vehicle.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextProductItemProperties.object_desc
preference.preference_description: Required values for each element in the Product Item Property list

preference.name: PortalDesignContextProductItemProperties.object_type
preference.preference_description: Required values for each element in the Product Item Property list

preference.name: DesignContextSearchColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of columns to be used when displaying the DesignContext Search Results (left-to-right order). Valid values are property internal names.

preference.name: DesignContextSearchInstallationAssemblyColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of Installation Assembly columns to be used when displaying the DesignContext Search Results (left-to-right order). Valid values are property internal names.

preference.name: DesignContextSearchInstallationAssemblyShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths for the installation assembly columns displayed during DesignContext Search (left-to-right order), as specified by the values of preference DesignContextSearchInstallationAssemblyShownColumnWidthsPref.

preference.name: DesignContextSearchShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths for the columns displayed during DesignContext Search (left-to-right order), as specified by the values of preference DesignContextSearchColumnsShownPref.

preference.name: DuplicateAssignToProject
preference.preference_description: Sets the default mode displayed in the "File -> Duplicate" command of the rich client, for the "Duplicate Assign to Project" option. Valid values are: * true: the default selected mode is to assign to projects. * false: the default selected mode is not to assign to projects. This is the default value.

preference.name: DuplicateRunInBackground
preference.preference_description: Sets the default mode displayed in the "File -> Duplicate" command of the rich client, for the "Run In Background" option. Valid values are: * true: the default selected mode is to run in the background. * false: the default selected mode is to run in the current thread. This is the default value.

preference.name: DuplicateValidApps
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of rich client applications that allow running Duplicate operations in the background. The valid value is "com.teamcenter.rac.se.ui.SystemsEngineeringApplication". This is an internal preference that should not be modified by end users.

preference.name: MassUpdateDefaultRevRule
preference.preference_description: Specifies the revision rule used to find parents of the target for Mass Update.

preference.name: JT_File_Excluded_Refsets
preference.preference_description: should be set with a list of reference set names that user does not wish to view in the PSE Portal Viewer (e.g. Empty).

preference.name: BOMWriterNoDescendantsInPLMXML
preference.preference_description: Set this preference to TRUE, if the plmxml file generated for interoperability by the BOMWriter should not have any descendants of the selected BOMLines. If set to FALSE, the descendants of the selected BOMLines will appear in the generated plmxml file.

preference.name: BOMWriterNoDirectParents
preference.preference_description: Set this preference to TRUE, if the plmxml file generated for interoperability by the BOMWriter should only have the selected BOMLines and the root node, but not any of the parents of selected BOMLines. If set to FALSE, then the root node, parents of the selected BOMLines and the selected BOMLines will appear in the generated plmxml file.

preference.name: BOMWriter_export_key_properties
preference.preference_description: Activates Multi-Field Key properties in BOMWriter output file. The default value is true (activated).

preference.name: CFMOccEffMode
preference.preference_description: Indicates the Occurrence Effectivity upgrade mode. Valid values legacy/maintenance or upgrade. legacy - Old date based effectivity mode. maintenance - New effectivities use new model, old effectivities stay in old mode. upgrade - Old effectivities are upgraded to new model if they are edited.

preference.name: JTContentHintPropertyPolicy
preference.preference_description: Defines the lists of attributes possibly present in JT Content Hint forms that must be included in the JTContentHint BOMLine property.

preference.name: JT_File_OverrideChildren_Refsets
preference.preference_description: Defines the behavior of structure node expansion in the Structure Manager application. When expanding levels of a structure, nodes containing datasets, with names that match one of these preference values, do not expand. Instead, the viewer uses the monolithic JT files to display the sub-assemblies. Valid values are reference set names, with the character * being the wild card match. E.g., a value "*-mono" matches all file names that end with "-mono". The value shall not include the ".jt" file extension.

preference.name: JT_File_Priority_Refsets
preference.preference_description: should be set with a list of reference set names of the JT files. PSE viewer loads the JT files in the order mentioned in the preference.

preference.name: JT_File_Use_Monolithic_Icon
preference.preference_description: Defines whether a monolithic icon is displayed to indicate the presence of structure in a JT file in the BOM tree of the Structure Manager and Manufacturing Process Planner applications. Valid values are: * true: the monolithic icon is displayed when a monolithic JT file containing structure is loaded in the viewer. * false: the monolithic icon will still be displayed for nodes affected by the "JT_File_OverrideChildren_Refsets" preference.

preference.name: MoveICCreationToMenu
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the "Create IC" sub-menu is to be displayed. Valid values for this site preference are: false: the "Create IC button" will be seen only on the Incremental Change panel. This is the default value. true: the "Create IC" sub-menu will be visible under "Tools->Incremental Change" and the "Create IC button" will not be seen in the Incremental Change panel.

preference.name: PSEAutoViCreateEmptyVI
preference.preference_description: Controls behavior when a non-module is encountered during automatic variant item generation. If set to true, when a non-module is encountered, a variant item will still be created for a given structure line.

preference.name: PSEAutoViIDPrefix
preference.preference_description: This preference is used on when the preference 'PSEAutoViNewItemPopup' is set to OFF and is used to define an variant item (VI) Id as value of PSEAutoViIDPrefix+auto generated item id. For example, if this preference is set to 'VI' and a item id is auto generated for the VI is 001001 then the VI id will be "VI001001".

preference.name: PSEAutoViNamePrefix
preference.preference_description: This preference is used on when the preference 'PSEAutoViNewItemPopup' is set to false and is used to define an auto-generated variant item (VI) name as value of PSEAutoViNamePrefix+module name. For example, if this preference is set to 'VI_' and a VI is auto-generated for a module named 'Wheel', then the VI name will be 'VI_Wheel'.

preference.name: PSEAutoViNewItemPopup
preference.preference_description: Controls whether or not an item creation dialog should be displayed when a new variant item needs to be created during automatic variant item structure generation.

preference.name: PSEAutoViStopVICreationForUnconfiguredModule
preference.preference_description: Defines whether or not automatic variant item generation should stop if an unconfigured module is encountered. If set to false, a warning will be logged if an unconfigured module is encountered.

preference.name: PSESavedConfigRelationTypes
preference.preference_description: When saving a selected option set (or variant configuration), the user can choose whether to save to the Home folder, the Newstuff folder or to the module (item revision) that is being configured. This lists the relation types from which one is selected when saving to a module.

preference.name: PSEShowUnconfigdEffPref
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the unconfigured occurences are to be displayed. Valid values are true/false. Defaulted to true.

preference.name: PSEShowUnconfigdVarPref
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the unconfigured variants are to be displayed. Valid values are true/false. Defaulted to true.

preference.name: PSEVariantsMode
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the modular variants functionality is used or not. Valid values are "modular", "hybrid" or "legacy". "modular" - Use only modular variants functionality. "hybrid" - Allows modules to be defined in structures containing legacy variant data. "legacy" - Use only legacy variants functionality.

preference.name: PSE_VI_Search_Visibility
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the component reuse (VI) search option is used or not. Valid values are true/false. true - Allow the user to use component reuse (VI) search option. false - The component reuse(VI) search option is disabled.

preference.name: PSE_prompt_for_remote_import
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the import remote dialog is used or not. Valid values are true/false. true - Uses the import remote popup option. false - The iport remote popup is disabled.

preference.name: PSE_show_option_item_prefix
preference.preference_description: Displays the owning Item objects for options. It applies to any application where option names are displayed. Valid values are: - false: To hide the owning Item object for the option. This is the default value. - true: To display the owning Item object for the option.

preference.name: PS_variant_value_protect
preference.preference_description: Protects the specified Product Structure option value from unwanted modifications through the RAC. Valid values are: - "none": No option value is protected. - "all": All option values are protected (i.e. no option can be deleted). - "refd_by_expr": Option values referenced by any variant expression (except declarations) are protected. This is the default value.

preference.name: TC_JT_voxel_size
preference.preference_description: The size of the voxels used to generate spatial representation of the product when spatial data is generated from jt files. The voxel size is in millimeters.

preference.name: TC_Schematic_BOMView_Types
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of BOMView types that require the usage of Network Viewer.

preference.name: Where_Ref_Avoid_Duplicate_Expansion
preference.preference_description: Simplifies the tree view resulting from the "Where Referenced Search" command by not showing the sub-tree of duplicate nodes. Valid values are: false: all nodes are displayed when expanded. true: nodes that are duplicate of others will not show their sub-tree. This is the default value.

preference.name: TC_BOM_Precision_Preference
preference.preference_description: Specifies the BOM precision to be used during the creation of new BOMViews/BOMViewRevisions. Valid values are Precise/Imprecise.

preference.name: PSE_default_view_type
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default view type to be used in PSE.

preference.name: TC_config_rule_name
preference.preference_description: Indicates the default config rule that will be used when opening/printing Imprecise BOMView or BOMViewRevisions. If this rule does not exist, the system will default to "Latest Working".

preference.name: TC_show_open_in_pse_button
preference.preference_description: Specifies if the "Open in PSE" button should be displayed in the Teamcenter Rich Client. Valid values are true/false. true - Displays the button. false - Does not display the button.

preference.name: PSESearchColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of columns to be used when displaying the PSE Search Results (left-to-right order).

preference.name: PSESearchShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths for the columns displayed (PSESearchColumnsShownPref) during PSE Search (left-to-right order).

preference.name: PortalDesignContextConsiderProductItemQuery
preference.preference_description: Activates the usage of the query PortalDesignContextProductItemQuery during search operation in Design Context. The scope for this preference is all (environment variable, user, group, role, site). Valid values are: True: The search will use the query PortalDesignContextProductItemQuery. False: The search will not use the query PortalDesignContextProductItemQuery. This is the default value.

preference.name: QSEARCH_foreground_processing_halted
preference.preference_description: Enables foreground processing of QSearch index functionality. The scope for this preference is all (environment variable, user, group, role, site). Valid values are: True: The processing is in the foreground. This is the default value. False: The processing is in the background.

preference.name: QSEARCH_queue_recurring_background_updates
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether to create a recurring dispatcher request for qsearch_process_queue.QSEARCH_foreground_processing_halted preference needs to be set to true before setting this preference. Recurring dispatcher requests will be executed on a regular time interval by dispatcher. You also need to set the following preferences to specify the time interval and life span of the recurring dispatcher request. Valid values are: true: Recurring dispatcher request will be created. false: A dispatcher request will be created but it will not be a recurring request.

preference.name: QSEARCH_recurring_background_update_interval
preference.preference_description: Specifies time interval for recurring request being created for qsearch_process_queue utility. Valid values are Time in Seconds.QSEARCH_queue_recurring_background_updates preference needs to be set to true before setting this preference. Recurring dispatcher requests will be executed on a regular time interval by dispatcher.

preference.name: QSEARCH_recurring_background_update_survival_time
preference.preference_description: Specifies the life of recurring request being created for qsearch_process_queue utility. Valid values are Time in seconds.QSEARCH_queue_recurring_background_updates preference needs to be set to true before setting this preference. Recurring dispatcher requests will be executed on a regular time interval by dispatcher. Valid values are Time in Seconds.

preference.name: QSEARCH_types_to_avoid_processing
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of Item types that are skipped while generating qsearch indexes. Item types defined in this preference will not be searchable in spatial searches. Valid values are any valid Item types.

preference.name: PSEPreciseColorPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the color to be used when displaying a precise BVR in PSE (defaulted to sea green). The value can be a standard supported string, an octal number or a hexadecimal number. The standard strings supported are "black", "white", "lightGray", "gray", "darkGray", "red", "pink", "orange", "yellow", "green", "magenta", "cyan" and "blue". Example for a hexadecimal number is #50b080 which represents "Sea Green".

preference.name: PSEShowViewTypePref
preference.preference_description: Decides whether to append View Type information to the BOM Line.

preference.name: BOMCompareVisibleModes
preference.preference_description: Lists the compare modes that will be shown in the BOM Compare dialog and returned by BOM_compare_ask_modes (if visibleOnly flag is set). If this preference is removed then the default visibility (as set when the mode was defined) will be used. The compare modes are: IMAN_bcm_single_level_seq, IMAN_bcm_single_level, IMAN_bcm_var_level_seq, IMAN_bcm_var_level, IMAN_bcm_ext_var_level_seq, IMAN_bcm_ext_var_level, IMAN_bcm_lowest_level_seq, IMAN_bcm_lowest_level, IMAN_bcm_every_level, IMAN_bcm_single_level_ref. Use the following for item-based LBOM compare: IMAN_lbcm_var_level, IMAN_lbcm_single_level, IMAN_lbcm_lowest_level. Use the following for occurrence-based LBOM compare: IMAN_lbcm_var_level_occ, IMAN_lbcm_single_level_occ. Use the compare mode IMAN_bcm_single_level_substitute to include substitute lines during BOM Compare. This mode is to be used only if the preference PSEShowSubstitutesPref is enabled. For complete information on comparison modes, check the chapter "Understanding product structure (BOM) comparisons" in Structure Manager Guide in the Technical Documentation.

preference.name: BOM_Display_Attachments_Panel
preference.preference_description: Activates the display of the "Attachments" tab in Structure Manager. The default value is true.

preference.name: BOM_Display_Referencer_Panel
preference.preference_description: Activates the display of the "Referencer" tab in Structure Manager. The default value is true.

preference.name: BOM_Display_Variant_Super_Panel
preference.preference_description: Activates the display of the "Variants" tab in Structure Manager. The default value is true.

preference.name: BOM_Frozen_Column_Count
preference.preference_description: Controls the number of columns (from left to right), in the Structure Manager application, that are frozen for horizontal scrolling. The default value is 0, which means that no horizontal scrolling restriction exists.

preference.name: BOM_MARKUP_ADD_FONT_STYLE
preference.preference_description: Specifies the font style when adding a BOM Line Markup. Valid values are: 0, 1, 2, or 3. - PLAIN is 0. - BOLD is 1. - ITALIC is 2. - BOLD/ITALIC is 3. The default value is 0. This is a site preference.

preference.name: BOM_MARKUP_ADD_FOREGROUND
preference.preference_description: Defines the color used when adding a BOM Line Markup. A valid value is the RGB (red green blue) code of a color, using the "," character as a separator.

preference.name: BOM_MARKUP_STRIKE_FOREGROUND
preference.preference_description: Defines the color used for the BOM Line Markup strikethrough when removing lines and editing properties. A valid value is the RGB (red green blue) code of a color, using the "," character as a separator.

preference.name: BOM_Property_Cache_Convert_Exclude_List
preference.preference_description: Lists the BOMLine properties that will not be converted from display value to internal value on rich client side.

preference.name: Baseline_consider_all_statuses
preference.preference_description: Activates considering all release statuses attached to Item Revisions, while creating baselines for released Item Revisions. Valid values are: * false: Only the latest release status on Item Revisions is considered. * true: All release statuses present on Item Revisions are considered.

preference.name: Incremental_Change_Management
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the Incremental Change Management mode is to be turned on or not. Valid values are true/false. Defaulted to false. RAC needs to be restarted for change in the value of this preference to take effect.

preference.name: PSEAdditionColorPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the color to be used for an occurrence which has been added when displaying BOM Compare results (defaulted to red). The value can be a standard supported string, an octal number or a hexadecimal number. The standard strings supported are "black", "white", "lightGray", "gray", "darkGray", "red", "pink", "orange", "yellow", "green", "magenta", "cyan" and "blue". Example for a hexadecimal number is #50b080 which represents "Sea Green".

preference.name: PSEAutoPackPref
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the PSE display needs to be packed by default. Valid values are 0/1. 0 - Do not pack. 1 - Pack PSE by default.

preference.name: PSEChangedColorPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the color to be used for an occurrence which has been changed when displaying BOM Compare results (defaulted to orange). The value can be a standard supported string, an octal number or a hexadecimal number. The standard strings supported are "black", "white", "lightGray", "gray", "darkGray", "red", "pink", "orange", "yellow", "green", "magenta", "cyan" and "blue". Example for a hexadecimal number is #50b080 which represents "Sea Green".

preference.name: PSEDisplayTypePref
preference.preference_description: Indicates the type of display that the users see in the PSE. Valid values are 1/2/3. 1 - Vertical Tree. 2 - Horizontal Tree. 3 - Indented BOM.

preference.name: PSEImpreciseColorPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the color to be used when displaying an imprecise BVR in PSE (defaulted to white). The value can be a standard supported string, an octal number or a hexadecimal number. The standard strings supported are "black", "white", "lightGray", "gray", "darkGray", "red", "pink", "orange", "yellow", "green", "magenta", "cyan" and "blue". Example for a hexadecimal number is #50b080 which represents "Sea Green".

preference.name: PSEShowDataPanelDefaultPref
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the "Show/Hide Data" panel is shown by default in the Structure Manager application. The default value is false (i.e. the panel is hidden).

preference.name: PSEShowSubstitutesPref
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the substitutes are to be shown by default. Valid values are 0/1. 0 - Do not show substitutes by default. 1 - Show substitutes by default.

preference.name: PSESubstituteColorPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the color to be used when displaying a substitute BOM Line in Structure Manager. The value can be: * a standard supported string: "black", "white", "lightGray", "gray", "darkGray", "red", "pink", "orange", "yellow", "green", "magenta", "cyan" and "blue". * a hexadecimal number (e.g. "#50b080" which represents "Sea Green"). The default value is "#a0b6c0", which represents "lightGray".

preference.name: PSE_Display_Pending_Edits
preference.preference_description: Displays markings for pending edits.

preference.name: PSE_expand_on_open
preference.preference_description: Indicates if an object's root node is expanded when displayed in Structure Manager. Valid values are 0 to keep it collapsed, 1 to expand it (default value).

preference.name: PSE_icon_placement
preference.preference_description: Indicates the position of the Icon to be placed with the PSE display. Valid values are 1/2/3/4. 1 - Above. 2 - Right. 3 - Below. 4 - Left.

preference.name: ShowModuleIcons
preference.preference_description: Determines whether modular variants are indicated in Items and Item Revisions icons. If set to true, the icon of Items and Item Revisions containing a module are displayed in gray scale.

preference.name: Fnd0EffectvtyGrp_OpenByName_ColumnPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of columns to be displayed in "Open By" dialog for objects of type Effectivity Group in Structure Editor. Valid values for this site preference are all properties for Fnd0EffectvtyGrp.

preference.name: Fnd0EffectvtyGrp_OpenByName_ColumnWidthPreferences
preference.preference_description: Specifies the widths(in pixels) of the columns displayed in the "Open By" dialog, as defined by Fnd0EffectvtyGrp_OpenByName_ColumnPreferences preference. This is a site preference.

preference.name: PS_assume_legacy_transform_units
preference.preference_description: Indicates which units the legacy transforms are in. For customers using data all in inches or millimeters, the value should be set, respectively, to "Inches" and "Millimeters". Otherwise, "Unknown" should be set. Note that values are case sensitive.

preference.name: PS_allow_plmxml_transforms_with_no_legacy_factor
preference.preference_description: Allows the customer to set a PLM XML transform with PS_set_plmxml_transform without first having to set a legacy conversion factor with PS_set_legacy_transform_factor. Valid values are Yes/No. Yes - Ignore the legacy factor. No - Ensure a legacy factor is present. This preference is intended for customers not interested in converting legacy data.

preference.name: PS_assume_old_transform_format
preference.preference_description: Indicates to Teamcenter which format old database transforms are stored in. Possible values are "In_Legacy_Format", "Written_By_NX" and "Unknown" (default). If "In_Legacy_Format" is chosen, old transforms are assumed to be in the same format as legacy NX transforms. If "Written_By_NX" is chosen, old transforms are assumed to be written by NX (and therefore also in "legacy" format). Note that values are case sensitive.

preference.name: PS_check_empty_transform_on_copy
preference.preference_description: Influences the copy of an occurrence's position data, in the specific scenario where the occurrence to be copied has no position data (i.e. its relative transformation data field is empty) but position data does exist on one or more occurrences higher in the structure. Valid values are: - true: The system will check for position data on parent occurrences of the occurrence to be copied. If found, the occurrence will be treated as if it contained an identity matrix for its relative transformation field. - false: The system will not check any further for position data if the occurrence to be copied has no position data (i.e. empty relative transformation data field). This is the default value.

preference.name: PS_convert_legacy_transform_to_plmxml
preference.preference_description: Enables the display of old legacy transforms in a PLMXML format. This only works if a legacy transform exists and no PLMXML transform is assigned. Valid values are: - true: The system will try to convert the old legacy transform to the PLMXML format for display purposes only. - false: The system will display the old legacy transform (as is). This is the default value.

preference.name: PS_xform_precision
preference.preference_description: Allows the customer to set precision for transform values. Transform value difference smaller than the precision value will be treated as the same when comparing them.

preference.name: BOM_Additional_Packing_Criteria
preference.preference_description: Defines additional packing criteria for lines to be packed. If only property name is listed, then it means the lines to be packed should have the same value of the property. If the property name is followed by colon, the string after colon is the value when the pack is not allowed. No string after colon means empty value.

preference.name: BOM_Additional_Ref_Designator_Search_Criteria
preference.preference_description: Defines additional criteria for searching reference designator. The value should be valid BOMLine property name of string type. All values will be added to the searching reference designator dialog as input fields, user can use the additional criteria defined by the fields to search for reference designators.

preference.name: BOM_Enable_Quantity_Validation_Against_Ref_Designator
preference.preference_description: Verifies if quantity is blank or 1 when the reference designator is assigned. Valid values are true or false.

preference.name: BOM_Enable_Ref_Designator_Value_Packing
preference.preference_description: Turns on and off the packing of Reference Designator values for packed bomlines. If it is turned off, the reference designator value of the master line of the packed lines will be displayed. If it is turned on, all reference designator values of packed lines will be packed. For example, if reference designator values of the packed lines are: C1, C2, C3, C7, C100, C101, the display value of reference designator of the packed line is C1-C3,C7,C100-C101. Valid values are true or false.

preference.name: PS_Bypass_Occurrence_Condition
preference.preference_description: Configures the system to bypass occurrence condition validation, for the actions specified below. Valid values are "Import", "Duplicate", "Baseline", "Revise", "SaveAs" and "All". If no value is supplied, this is the equivalent to having set the values "Import", "Duplicate", "Baseline", "Revise" and "SaveAs". If the value is "All", occurrence condition validation will be bypassed completely.

preference.name: PS_Default_Rev_For_Occ_Cond_Validation
preference.preference_description: Defines the default item revision considered by the occurrence condition validation. Valid values are "Latest", "Latest Working", and any valid status (e.g. "TM Released").

preference.name: PS_Duplicate_FindNo_Update
preference.preference_description: Determines if duplicate find numbers can be updated when the line is not packed. Valid values are true or false.

preference.name: PS_Find_Number_Validation
preference.preference_description: Verifies if the find number is unique under the same parent and the find number should not be zero.

preference.name: PS_Reference_Designator_Validation
preference.preference_description: Verifies if the reference designator is unique under the same parent and the value is of format <Capital Letters><Numbers> like C1 or <Capital Letters><Numbers><Capital Letters><Numbers> like SK1SK22. When it is turned off, no validation of reference designator value will be performed. Valid values are true or false.

preference.name: PS_replace_with_substructure
preference.preference_description: Allows to replace a node which contains substructure with another node which may contain substructure, in which case, after the replace action, the node with its substructure is replaced with the new node and its substructure if any. When this preference is turned off, it is not allowed for either the replacing node or the replaced node to have any substructure to perform the replace action.

preference.name: PS_structure_change_condition
preference.preference_description: Specifies the actions that will determine if the BVR edit is significant. Valid values are Transform, SequenceNumber, ReferenceDesignator, OccurrenceName, Quantity, PartSource, UnitOfMeasure, PreferredSubstitute, NoteType:NoteTypeNames. Note: If this preference is used then it is mandatory to have the NoteType:UG NAME, NoteType:UG GEOMETRY, NoteType:UG REF SET, NoteType:UG ENTITY HANDLE and NoteType:UG ALTREP for NXManager Unigraphics.

preference.name: TC_BVRSYNCFORM_DELEGATE
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether user should have bypass privileges to set BVRSYncform properties when he has WRITE Access to UGMASTER dataset.The default value is true.

preference.name: QSEARCH_disable_bbox_for_product_scoping
preference.preference_description: Enables or disables sending translation requests to Dispatcher during spatial indexing when a non-indexable structure is added under an indexable structure. The dispatcher requests are used to create bounding box data for cacheless searches. NOTE: This preference applies only to product-scoped cacheless search functionality. It does not affect data for which non product-scoped indexing is in effect. Valid values are: true: Disables Dispatcher requests. false: Enables Dispatcher requests. This is the default value.

preference.name: QSEARCH_dispatcher_not_available
preference.preference_description: Deactivates the dispatcher use in spatial index generation for Cacheless search. The default value is false (dispatcher is configured and qsearch service is available).

preference.name: QSEARCH_filter_queries_by_product_scoping
preference.preference_description: Enables product-scoped cacheless search. The value must be set through the utility "qsearch_process_queue": * with the parameter "-enable_product_scoping", to set it to 1. * with the parameter "-disable_product_scoping", to set it to 0. Valid values are: * 1: Enables product scoped cacheless search. Spatial indexing and bounding box generation utilities are then working in the scope of one or more specified product(s). * 0: Disables product scoped cacheless search. This is the default value.

preference.name: QSEARCH_ignore_bbox_updates_for_non_product_scoped
preference.preference_description: Disables the generation of Bounding Boxes if the geometry dataset is attached to an ItemRevision or AbsoluteOccurrence that is not within the scope of products to be indexed for cacheless search. Valid values are: * true: Bounding Boxes are not be generated. * false: Bounding Boxes are generated. This is the default value.

preference.name: QSEARCH_update_enabled
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether QSearch spatial data updating is enabled or disabled.

preference.name: QS_BBOX_GENERATION_ENABLED
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether Bounding Box data generation from JT is enabled or disabled.

preference.name: QS_BBOX_GENERATION_FROM_NX_ENABLED
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether Bounding Box data generation from UGPART-BBOX form of NX dataset is enabled or disabled.

preference.name: QS_IGNORE_JT_USER_VOLUME
preference.preference_description: Activates the storage of trushape data files in the volume of the JT file owners for the "Create Or Update Bounding Box And TSO" command of the Cacheless search. The default value is false: TSO (TruShape Data) files will be stored in JT files volume.

preference.name: QS_NX_RELATION_POST_ACTION_ENABLED
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether to create a local Bounding Box on Remote import of the UGMaster Dataset. Valid values are: * true: the Bounding Box will be created automatically on UGMaster Dataset import. This is the default value. * false: the Bounding Box will not be created automatically on UGMaster Dataset import, and the user is required to generate the Bounding Box manually using "create_or_update_bbox_and_tso" utility.

preference.name: QS_QSEARCH_ENABLED
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether QSearch functionality is enabled or disabled.

preference.name: QS_SPATIAL_ENABLED
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether QSearch spatial (e.g. proximity, box etc) functionality is enabled or disabled.

preference.name: QS_TRUSHAPE_GENERATION_ENABLED
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether Trushape data generation from JT is enabled or disabled.

preference.name: QS_remote_master_site
preference.preference_description: Defines the site where cacheless search engine will perform the query. Format should be: <Product Top level Item Id:Site name> Remote search checkbox will be visible only for the Product Item IDs specified in this preference. No default value is required.

preference.name: StructureManagerIncludeSubComponentsForSpatialSearch
preference.preference_description: Activates the selection of sub-assemblies as targets for proximity search. Valid values are: * true: The search engine will consider all the components under sub-assemblies as targets for proximity. This is useful in cases when the sub-assemblies may not have geometry of their own. * false: The search engine will execute the search only on the sub-assemblies. This is the default value.

preference.name: TC_MAX_FACET_SIZE
preference.preference_description: Specifies the maximum number of facets of a JT that can be processed by the "create_or_update_bbox_and_tso" utility, in order to generate Trushape voxels and bounding boxes. The default value is 3000000.

preference.name: TC_qsearch_remote_query_timeout
preference.preference_description: Specifies the timeout period (in seconds) for remote qsearch queries. The default value for this site preference is 3600s.

preference.name: ArchitectureModeler_RemoveDesign_Max
preference.preference_description: Indicates the maximum number of designs which could be removed at one go in PSE Application using RDV remove action.

preference.name: ArchitectureModeler_add_design_business_rule_check
preference.preference_description: Specifies the process template which does the business rule check for compliance to standards, etc. The business rule check process would have the Architecture Revision, Architecture Breakdown element, Product Item and added/replaced/removed Design as target. This preference checks for the process template before adding a design to a Product.

preference.name: ArchitectureModeler_add_design_occurrence_business_rule_check
preference.preference_description: Specifies the process template which does the business rule check for compliance to occurrence. The business rule check process would have the Architecture Revision, Architecture Breakdown element, Product Item and the Installation Assembly as target. This preference pertains to adding a design occurrence.

preference.name: ArchitectureModeler_locking_retry_count
preference.preference_description: Indicates the number of tries the ArchitectureModeler application would make to explicitly lock the assembly for edits (Add, Replace or Remove).

preference.name: ArchitectureModeler_multiple_installation_assemblies_condition
preference.preference_description: Valid values for this preference are NONE, WARNING or ERROR. NONE - Implies that is decided by the preference ArchitectureModeler_use_all_installation_assemblies how many Installation Assemblies need to be shown. WARNING - Implies that the preference ArchitectureModeler_use_all_installation_assemblies drives how many Installation Assemblies would be shown. However, the User would see a Warning message if there are more than one suitable Installation Assemblies. ERROR - Stops the wizard, if more than one Installation Assemblies are found.

preference.name: ArchitectureModeler_remove_design_business_rule_check
preference.preference_description: Specifies the process template which does the business rule check for compliance to standards, etc. The business rule check process would have the Architecture Revision, Architecture Breakdown element, Product Item and added/replaced/removed Design as target. This preference checks for the process template before removing a design from a Product.

preference.name: ArchitectureModeler_remove_design_occurrence_business_rule_check
preference.preference_description: Specifies the process template which does the business rule check for compliance to occurrence. The business rule check process would have the Architecture Revision, Architecture Breakdown element, Product Item and the Installation Assembly as target. This preference pertains to removing a design occurrence.

preference.name: ArchitectureModeler_replace_design_business_rule_check
preference.preference_description: Specifies the process template which does the business rule check for compliance to standards, etc. The business rule check process would have the Architecture Revision, Architecture Breakdown element, Product Item and added/replaced/removed Design as target. This preference checks for the process template before replacing a design in a Product.

preference.name: ArchitectureModeler_replace_design_occurrence_business_rule_check
preference.preference_description: Specifies the process template which does the business rule check for compliance to occurrence. The business rule check process would have the Architecture Revision, Architecture Breakdown element, Product Item and Installation Assembly as target. This preference pertains to replacing a design occurrence.

preference.name: ArchitectureModeler_update_design_occurrences_business_rule_check
preference.preference_description: Specifies the process template which does the business rule check for compliance to occurrence. The business rule check process would have the Architecture Revision, Architecture Breakdown element, Product Item and Installation Assembly as target. This preference pertains to updating the design occurrences.

preference.name: ArchitectureModeler_update_designs_business_rule_check
preference.preference_description: Specifies the process template which does the business rule check for compliance to standards, etc. The business rule check process would have the Architecture Revision, Architecture Breakdown element, Product Item and added/replaced/removed Design as target. This preference checks for the process template before updating the designs in a Product.

preference.name: ArchitectureModeler_use_all_installation_assemblies
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the algorithm to find Installation Assembly stops or continues at the same node. Valid values are TRUE/FALSE. Any value other than TRUE or true is deemed to be false and in that case, the algoritm stops walking up the tree as soon as it finds one.

preference.name: EPM_tessellation_ignore_check_rendering_results
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether to ignore the past tessellation result log. Valid values are false/true. false - Do not ignore the past tessellation result log. true - ignore the past tessellation result log.

preference.name: EPM_tessellation_servers
preference.preference_description: Preference setting for Tessellation Server. This should be set to <hostname>:<portno> where hostname corresponds to the machine where the Tessellation Server runs and portno corresponds to the port where it listens to the requests. NONE represents the stand alone mode of Tessellation Server.

preference.name: EPM_tessellation_target_type
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of valid targets for tessellation. Valid targets will be UGMASTER, UGALTREP.

preference.name: LEGACY_GOI_DEFAULT_REVRULE
preference.preference_description: Defines the default Revision Rule to be used for retrieving the Global Option Item Revision (GOI Revision) in order to compute variability in the Platform Designer application.

preference.name: PDShowHidePartSolutions
preference.preference_description: Activates the display of part solutions in the BOM(Bill Of Materials) panel in the "Platform Designer" and "Structure Manager" applications. They are hidden by default (false). This is a user preference.

preference.name: PDShowUnconfigdEffPref
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the unconfigured occurrences are to be displayed in platform designer. Valid values are true (default) or false.

preference.name: PDShowUnconfigdVarPref
preference.preference_description: Indicates if the unconfigured variants are to be displayed in platform designer. Valid values are true (default) or false.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextProcess.WorkPartOrChangeAttachmentTypes
preference.preference_description: EPM Attachment Types that the DesignContext application should use for finding associated Workflow Processes upon adding a WorkPart or Engineering Change. 1 - EPM_target_attachment. 3 - EPM_reference_attachment. 4 - EPM_signoff_attachment). 5 - EPM_release_status_attachment. 6 - EPM_comment_attachment. 7 - EPM_instruction_attachment. 1000 - EPM_user_attachment.

preference.name: PortalDesignContextProcess.WorkPartProperties
preference.preference_description: DesignContext properties for finding associated WorkParts upon adding a workflow process e.g.: root_task:root_target_attachments, root_task:root_reference_attachments

preference.name: RDVArchMaxNVEsAllowed
preference.preference_description: Indicates the maximum number of Named Variant Expressions to be displayed in the form of XO chart (wherein the contents of the Named Variant Expression are represented by 'X's and 'O's in tabular form) without user confirmation.

preference.name: RDVIgnoreErrorConnectReleasedPartsServer
preference.preference_description: If this preference is set to false, then RDV-add-released-parts-queue handler expects that the Released Parts Collector server is running and the Item will be released if the server is up. If the preference RDVIgnoreErrorConnectReleasedPartsServer is set to false and the "Released Parts Collector server" is not running then, the Item will not be released. If the preference RDVIgnoreErrorConnectReleasedPartsServer is set to true and the "Released Parts Collector server" is not running then the Item will be released whether or not "Released Parts Collector server" is running

preference.name: RDVReleasedPartsCollectorServer
preference.preference_description: This preference should be set to the hostname of the machine and port number at which the "released_parts_collector" server is running.

preference.name: RDVReleasedPartsProcessAssemType
preference.preference_description: The preference "ReleasedPartsProcessAssemType" should contain the Item types which should be processed by the handler. The Item to be released should be one of the Item types mentioned against this preference

preference.name: RDV_CREATE_SCO_WITHOUT_APN
preference.preference_description: Enables the creation of Structure Context Objects (SCO) without creating the Appearance Path Nodes (APN), only for the "Design Context" application. If it is set to true (default value), SCO will be created without creating the APNs for the BOMLine objects. If set to false, SCO will be created with APNs for the BOMLine objects.

preference.name: RDV_QSEARCH_REFINE
preference.preference_description: Activates the use of true shape data for refining the searches in design context while using the cacheless search engine.

preference.name: RDV_QSEARCH_REVISION_RULE_NAMES
preference.preference_description: Specifies the revision rule names that are preferred for the searches using cacheless search engine.

preference.name: RDV_QSEARCH_STREAMING_MODE
preference.preference_description: Determines the way in which the third screen of design context is updated with search results using the cacheless search engine. Valid values are: true: updates the tables in streaming mode and enables the user to interrupt the update. false: updates the tables only once when all the search results are obtained. This is the default.

preference.name: RDV_authoring_override_user
preference.preference_description: Specifies the Teamcenter user id used to add part to the installation assembly. The access rule checks will be performed against this user.

preference.name: RDV_auto_populate_occ_notes
preference.preference_description:
Defines a list of note types that can be pre-populated in the "Part Data" screen of the "Add/Replace Part to Product" wizard of the Platform Designer application. The preference values are expected to be in the format as illustrated below.
For example, if there are following values in this preference: Usage_Product#PROP#PRODUCT_REV#items_tag:item_id Usage_PartNumber#PROP#PART#item_id Usage_Quantity#CONST#DEFAULT#1 Usage_ArchitectureId#PROP#ABE#generic_component_id
Format description: * Field 1: Display names of occ note types. * Field 2: Separator # * Field 3: PROP or CONST. PROP indicates the value would be retrieved from a property on the specified object CONST indicates a constant value * Field 4: Separator # * Field 5: Specifies the object. PRODUCT, PRODUCT_REV, PART, PART_REV, ABE, ABE_REV or DEFAULT When Field 2 is PROP, the valid values are PRODUCT, PRODUCT_REV, PART, PART_REV, ABE and ABE_REV When Field 2 is CONST, the valid value is DEFAULT * Field 6: Separator # * Field 7: Property name or constant value. When Field 2 is PROP and Field 3 is PRODUCT, PRODUCT_REV, PART, PART_REV, ABE or ABE_REV, then valid value is property name on the specified object When Field 2 is CONST and Field 3 is DEFAULT, then this Field should be constant value
The preferences RDV_product_code_mapping and RDV_part_occ_note_mappings are not used anymore and any changes on them will not take effect.

preference.name: RDV_build_intent_atth_type
preference.preference_description: For Global RDV Automation

preference.name: RDV_default_Architecture_Breakdown_RevRule
preference.preference_description: Default Revision Rule to be used by the Architecture Modeler Application to open a Architecture Breakdown.

preference.name: RDV_default_find_inside_parts
