preference.preference_description: Specifies the default option for searching parts that lie either inside or outside the 3D bounding box during spatial search applicable to the Structure Manager as well as the Manufacturing applications. Valid values are: * true: the option to find parts inside the box is set as default. This is the default value. * false: the option to find parts outside the box is set as default.

preference.name: RDV_default_find_intersecting_parts
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default option for including or excluding the intersecting parts with the 3D bounding box during spatial search applicable to the Structure Manager as well as the Manufacturing applications. Valid values are: * true: the option to include intersecting parts is set. This is the default value. * false: the option to exclude intersecting parts will be set.

preference.name: RDV_design_audit_info
preference.preference_description: Contains a list of BOM lines, user can see in AuditReport.

preference.name: RDV_install_configuration_rules
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of Revision Rules used to configure the installation assembly in a Product.

preference.name: RDV_modify_item_desc_on_rdip
preference.preference_description: Specifies if the Item revision's description needs to be modified during Replace Design in product. Valid values are: true : Modify description. false : Do not modify description. This is the default value.

preference.name: RDV_part_occ_note_mappings
preference.preference_description: This preference is not used anymore and changes will not take effect. Please refer to the RDV_auto_populate_occ_notes preference.

preference.name: RDV_platformdesigner_assign_bulk_variability
preference.preference_description: Activates the new user interface for the "Create Bulk Variability" command. Valid values are true (default value) to display the "Create Bulk Variability" user interface, and false to show the old user interface.

preference.name: RDV_product_code_mapping
preference.preference_description: This preference is not used anymore and changes will not take effect. Please refer to the RDV_auto_populate_occ_notes preference.

preference.name: RDV_set_default_3DBox_dimensions
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default option for 3D Box dimensions applicable to the Structure Manager as well as the Manufacturing applications. Valid values are: * 0: Centroid and size. * 1: Origin and size. * 2: Maximum and minimum extents. This is the default value.

preference.name: RDV_set_default_3DBox_search
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default option for spatial search type applicable to the Structure Manager as well as the Manufacturing applications. Valid values are: * true: the 3D Box search option is set as default. This is the default value. * false: the proximity search option is set as default.

preference.name: RDV_set_default_3D_Manipulator_ON
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default option for 3D Manipulators applicable to the Structure Manager as well as the Manufacturing applications. Valid values are: * true: the 3D Manipulators functionality is ON by default. This is the default value. * false: the 3D Manipulators functionality is OFF by default.

preference.name: RDV_set_default_slider_increment
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default value of the slider increment applicable to the Structure Manager as well as the Manufacturing applications. Valid values are positive and non zero numbers. The default value is "0.01".

preference.name: RDV_set_default_true_shape_filtering_ON
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default option for true shape filtering applicable to the Structure Manager as well as the Manufacturing applications. Valid values are: * true: the option of true shape filtering is ON by default. This is the default value. * false: the option of true shape filtering is OFF by default.

preference.name: RDV_set_default_use_selections_from_tree
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default option for using the target part selections from either tree or table applicable to the Structure Manager as well as the Manufacturing applications. Valid values are: * true: the option of using selections from tree is set as default. This is the default value. * false: the option of using selections from table is set as default.

preference.name: RDV_show_targets_on_results_dialog
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether the target parts table is displayed on results dialog or not during the proximity search applicable to the Structure Manager as well as the Manufacturing applications. Valid values are: * true: the target parts table is displayed. This is the default value. * false: target parts table is not displayed.

preference.name: RDV_show_targets_on_spatial_dialog
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether the target parts table is displayed on spatial dialog or not during the proximity search applicable to the Structure Manager application only. Valid values are: * true: the target parts table is displayed. * false: target parts table is not displayed. This is the default value.

preference.name: RDV_uneditable_part_occ_notes
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of Occurrence notes that should not be editable in the "Enter Part Data" screen of the "Add/Replace Part to Product" wizard.

preference.name: RDV_usage_audit_info
preference.preference_description: Contains a list of Occurrence Notes of LOUs, user can see in AuditReport.

preference.name: RDV_usage_occurrence_notes
preference.preference_description: Defines a list of note types that will be displayed in the "Part Data" screen of the "Add/Replace Part to Product" wizard.

preference.name: RDV_user_defined_units_of_measure
preference.preference_description: Indicates the user defined units to perform the spatial search in the Structure Manager, Manufacturing and Design Context applications. Valid values are METERS, MILLIMETERS,INCHES or UNKNOWN.

preference.name: RDV_variant_overlays_mode
preference.preference_description:
Valid values for this preference are 0/1/2/4. 0 - Indicates dynamic mode which is the default mode. 1 - Indicates static mode. 2 - Indicates hybrid mode. Static if the number of variable options is greater that PortalDesignContextSetVariantRulesMaxVariantRules else dynamic. 4 - Indicates tabular mode. Use the X-O Chart to calculate variant rules dynamically.
When set to static mode valid overlay variant rules are taken as the (static) subset of all variant rules available for the top-level for which the target BOMLines configure. This can be useful if the set of saved variant rules covers all or close enough to all valid option value combinations. In this case static overlay variant rules produce acceptable results without having rule checks available in PSE. When set to dynamic, valid overlay variant rules are dynamically computed based on the variabilty model in PSE (options affecting the target BOMLines, option defaults, rule checks). The default value is dynamic mode (0).

preference.name: ConfigureToLoadEnableDefaultVariantConfig
preference.preference_description: Enables the "Do not show this dialog automatically when opening BOM" check box in the "Variant Rule" or "Configure" dialog box in Structure Manager application.

preference.name: DisableSaveSos
preference.preference_description: Prevents saving of Stored Option Set (SOS) objects. Valid values are: false: Allows creating new or modifying existing Stored Option Set (SOS) objects. This is the default value. true: Prevents saving Stored Option Set (SOS) even if variant mode (Preference "PSVariantMode") is Hybrid or Modular.

preference.name: Fnd0ItemLineLite_bl_line_name_expression
preference.preference_description: Defines the property expression used for evaluation of line name for objects of type Fnd0ItemLineLite. Valid values contain property internal names (always preceded with the '$' character), the character '+' to signal concatenation, and strings (surrounded by double quotes). The default value is: $bl_item_item_id+"/"+$bl_rev_item_revision_id+";"+$bl_rev_sequence_id+"-"+$bl_rev_object_name

preference.name: Internal_VariantRuleConfiguration_MultipleOptionValueSupport
preference.preference_description: Holds the list of rich client applications that support multiple values for a variant option during variant rule configuration. Valid values are rich client application IDs. An application ID can be found in an application's plugin.xml under the extension point com.teamcenter.rac.aifrcp.perspectiveDefs. Look for the property value of legacyAppId under the perspective definition. The values are set by Teamcenter development and should not be altered by customers.

preference.name: Internal_VariantRuleConfiguration_OverlaySupport
preference.preference_description: Holds the list of rich client applications that support overlay of variant rules during variant rule configuration. Valid values are rich client application IDs. An application ID can be found in an application's plugin.xml under the extension point com.teamcenter.rac.aifrcp.perspectiveDefs. Look for the property value of legacyAppId under the perspective definition. The values are set by Teamcenter development and should not be altered by customers.

preference.name: PS_VariantCondition_option_prefix
preference.preference_description: Sets the display format for option name in Variant Condition dialog. Valid values are: * true: Shows a string in the format "[ItemId]Option_name". * false: Shows a string in the format "[object_string]Option_name" where object string is the display name of the Item in user interface.

preference.name: PS_option_value_delimiter
preference.preference_description: Defines the string delimiter to separate individual option values in Variant Rules that contain multiple option values.

preference.name: PersistFullyExpandedSVR
preference.preference_description: Activates the capture of all the values of a Variant Rule (which includes Default, Derived Default) when setting a Saved Variant Rule (creation or update). This is required if the Saved Variant Rule is used in Active Workspace BOM Indexing generation. Valid values are: * true: all values are captured. * false: only user set values are captured in a Saved Variant Rule during creation or update. This is the default value.

preference.name: TC_Undefined_Variant_State_Enabled
preference.preference_description: Enables the undefined variant occurrence '?' state. Valid values are: true: If any of the variant options used in variant condition is not set in the Variant Rule, the corresponding variant occurrence assumes an undefined '?' state. false: If any of the variant options used in variant condition is not set in the Variant Rule, the corresponding variant occurrence assumes a defined 'Y' state. This is the default value.

preference.name: TC_show_option_family_prefix
preference.preference_description: Controls the visibility of the option family information in the Variant Condition returned by the Variant Configurator in the Product Structure application. Valid values are: - false: Hides the option family for the option. - true: Displays the option family for the option. This is the default value.

preference.name: TC_show_option_item_prefix
preference.preference_description: Controls the visibility of the owning Item information in the Variant Condition returned by the Variant Configurator in the Product Structure application. Valid values are: - false: Hides the owning Item object for the option. - true: Displays the owning Item object for the option. This is the default value.

preference.name: PS_wu_configd_imprecise_only
preference.preference_description: In the results of a where used search, omits parent Item Revision objects that are not themselves configured by the Revision Rule.\n This happens when the preference is set to true and the specified Revision Rule contains only non-precise entries.

category.name: ProductView
category.category_description: Preferences affecting the behavior of Product views

preference.name: Vis_PV_AllowLateLoading
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether the late loading of ProductViews is enabled. Valid values are: * true: Allows the late loading of ProductViews. This is the default value. * false: Does not allow the late loading of ProductViews.

preference.name: Vis_PV_BlockingViewToggles
preference.preference_description: Specifies the list of view toggles preventing the creation of a Product view. Please refer to the description of the preference "Vis_PV_InvalidConfigWarnLevel" for more details. Valid values are: show_unconfigured_variants show_unconfigured_changes show_unconfigured_assignment fnd0show_uncnf_occ_eff show_suppressed_occurrences fnd0show_gcs_cps

preference.name: Vis_PV_Geometry_Asset
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether a 3D Geometry Asset should be captured when a Product View is created. It also specifies if an Outline Capture should be included with the 3D Geometry Asset. Valid values are "NoGeoAsset", "GeoAssetWithOutline", "GeoAssetWithoutOutline".

preference.name: Vis_PV_HowTo_Configure_BOM
preference.preference_description: Indicates how the BOM Window is to be configured before a Product View is applied to it. This configuration is captured in the Product View with the use of the VisStructureContext object. This object records the Revision Rule, Variant Rules, Assembly Arrangements and Occurrence Effectivity. Valid values are "UseCurrent" or "UsePV".

preference.name: Vis_PV_ImageCapture
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether an Image Capture should be added when a Product View is created. It also specifies how the Image Capture options will be obtained if one is created. Valid values are "NoImageCapture", "CaptureUsingPrefs" or "CaptureUsingDialog".

preference.name: Vis_PV_ImageCaptureHeight
preference.preference_description: Defines the height in pixel of the preview image created when saving a Product View from the Lifecycle Visualization application. This is only used if "Image Capture" is enabled for Product View save, and if the "Use Image Export Dialog" option is unchecked. Valid values are positive integer from 1 to 1040. Specifying a value of 0 for either width or height will result in both values being calculated automatically.

preference.name: Vis_PV_ImageCaptureResolution
preference.preference_description: Defines the resolution of the preview image created when saving a Product View from the Lifecycle Visualization application. A valid value is any positive integer from 1 (lowest) to 1040 (highest resolution).

preference.name: Vis_PV_ImageCaptureType
preference.preference_description: Defines the format of the preview image created when saving a Product View from the Lifecycle Visualization application. This is only used if "Image Capture" is enabled for Product View save, and if the "Use image export dialog" option is unchecked. Valid values are "BMP 24bit", "BMP 8bit", "BMP BW", "JPEG 24bit", "PNG 24bit", "PNG 8bit", "PNG BW", "TIFF 24bit", "TIFF 8bit", "TIFF BW".

preference.name: Vis_PV_ImageCaptureWidth
preference.preference_description: Defines the width in pixel of the preview image created when saving a Product View from the Lifecycle Visualization application. This is only used if "Image Capture" is enabled for Product View save, and if the "Use Image Export Dialog" option is unchecked. Valid values are positive integer from 1 to 1040. Specifying a value of 0 for either width or height will result in both values being calculated automatically.

preference.name: Vis_PV_InvalidConfigWarnLevel
preference.preference_description: Specifies the intervention level provided when user tries to capture a Product view in a view toggle enabled environment. Valid values are: *Off: The user is allowed to create/update the Product view without any intervention. This is the behavior prior to Tc10.0.0. *Warning: A warning message is displayed to the user alerting the presence of active view toggles on the BOM window. This is the default value. *Prevent: The user shall not be allowed to proceed with creation of the Product view.

preference.name: Vis_PV_LateLoadSaveOp
preference.preference_description: Specifies how late loaded ProductViews are to be handled during a save operation. Valid values are: * Ask - The user is prompted for their desired handling of late loaded ProductViews during save operation. * Ignore - All late loaded ProductViews are ignored for the save operation. * Abort - The save operation is aborted if any late loaded ProductView is present. * LoadAll - All late loaded ProductViews are loaded and included in the save operation. This is the default value.

preference.name: Vis_PV_Play_Motion
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether the motion file (if one exists) should be played automatically using the current view when the Product View is applied. Valid values are true (default value) or false.

preference.name: Vis_PV_Show_Name_Dialog
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether the dialog used to name a Product View during Product View creation should be shown. If set to false then a name for the Product View will be generated automatically. Valid values are true (default value) or false.

preference.name: Vis_PV_ThumbnailHeight
preference.preference_description: Defines the height in pixels of thumbnails created for Product view in the Lifecycle Visualization application. Valid values are positive integer from 1 to 1040.

preference.name: Vis_PV_ThumbnailQuality
preference.preference_description: Defines the resolution of thumbnail created for Product view in the Lifecycle Visualization application. A valid value is any positive integer from 1 (lowest) to 1040 (highest resolution).

preference.name: Vis_PV_ThumbnailWidth
preference.preference_description: Defines the width in pixels of thumbnails created for Product view in the Lifecycle Visualization application. Valid values are positive integer from 1 to 1040.

preference.name: Vis_PV_capture3DGeomAssetAsOutline
preference.preference_description: Activates the creation of outline capture during Product view save in the Lifecycle Visualization application. This is only used if 3D Geometry Asset Capture is enabled for Product View save with no menus. Starting with Teamcenter 10.0 this preference is no longer used but remains in order to maintain backwards compatibility with Teamcenter Visualization 9 releases. Valid values are true or false (default value).

preference.name: DEBUG_RBOBJECTS_LIMIT
preference.preference_description: Defines the maximum number of run-time Business Objects allowed for profiling.

category.name: Schedule Manager
category.category_description: Allows configuring of Schedule Manager functionality.

preference.name: SiteTimeZone
preference.preference_description: Stores the time zone. List of supported time zones is available in the documentation. For example: "America/New_York" is the ID for US Eastern Time. This is a site preference.

preference.name: CombinedAvailableAttributes
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of common Schedule and ScheduleTask object attributes displayed in the "Column Chooser" window of the "Schedule Manager" application when a Program View is opened. This is a site preference.

preference.name: DefaultActualToSystemDate
preference.preference_description: Determines whether to use the schedule date (false) or the system date (true) when setting the initial value for the actual start/finish date of a ScheduleTask. The default actual dates may also be affected by the SM_EnforceActualDatesBeforeNow preference. This is a site preference.

preference.name: Default_Base_Calendar_Preference
preference.preference_description: Preference for setting default base calendar for resource and schedule calendars.

preference.name: ProgramViewFilterProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of attributes for Schedule and ScheduleTask objects displayed in the "Filter" window of the "Schedule Manager" application when a Program View is opened. This is a site preference.

preference.name: ProgramViewGroupProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of attributes for Schedule and ScheduleTask objects displayed in the "Grouping" window of the "Schedule Manager" application when a Program View is opened. This is a site preference.

preference.name: SM_ALLOW_INPROCESS_REMOVAL_OF_SUB_SCHEDULE
preference.preference_description: Prevents removal of started sub-schedules. Valid values are true and false (default value).

preference.name: SM_ALLOW_USER_ABORT
preference.preference_description: Allows participant users to abort Tasks. * true: participant users will be able to abort Tasks. * false: participant users will not be able to abort Tasks. This is the default value.

preference.name: SM_Copy_Schedule_Async
preference.preference_description: Determines the default selection when the user performs the "Save As" or "Create A Schedule From Template" command. Valid values are true (asynchronously) and false (synchronously) (default value).

preference.name: SM_CriticalPath_Color
preference.preference_description: Defines the color for critical path in Schedule Manager application. A valid value is the RGB code (Red, Green, Blue code) specified using format: N1,N2,N3 where 0<= Ni <= 255.

preference.name: SM_DEFERRED_NOTIFICATION_TIME
preference.preference_description: Specifies the notification time in minutes before the user is warned that the deferred session is about to expire. This user preference can be set to 0 to turn off the notification. The default value is 0, i.e. no notification.

preference.name: SM_DEFERRED_SHOW_TIMEOUT
preference.preference_description: Determines if the deferred session expiration time will be displayed to the end-user. This user preference is effective only if the timeout is turned on (i.e. the preference SM_DEFERRED_TIMEOUT has a value greater than 0). The default value is false (the expiration time is not displayed).

preference.name: SM_DEFERRED_TIMEOUT
preference.preference_description: Specifies the timeout in minutes before the deferred session expires. This site preference can be set to 0 to turn off the timeout. The default value is 0, i.e. turned off.

preference.name: SM_DISPLAY_GANTT_SI
preference.preference_description: Activates the display of the Gantt status indicator in the Schedule Manager application. Values are: - true: Show Gantt status indicator (default). - false: Hide Gantt status indicator. This is a site preference.

preference.name: SM_Delete_Schedule_Async
preference.preference_description: Determines the behavior when the user chooses to delete a Schedule. Valid values are true (asynchronously) and false (synchronously) (default value).

preference.name: SM_Delete_Validation_Files
preference.preference_description: Determines if the Schedule Manager Translator should delete or preserve the temporary xml validation files. Valid values are "true"(default value) and "false".

preference.name: SM_ENFORCE_ASSIGNMENT_CRITERIA
preference.preference_description: Determines if the Schedule Manager should enforce the assignment criteria like Discipline, PlaceHolder or Qualification while assigning resources on Schedule Tasks. The valid values are: * true: enforces the assignment criteria. * false: any user can be assigned regardless of assignment criteria defined on Schedule Tasks. This is the default value.

preference.name: SM_EVM_Calc_Labels
preference.preference_description: Allows the user to choose whether they would like the Earned Value Management calculations to be displayed as EVM (Earned Value Management) or based on C/SCSC (Cost/Schedule Control Systems Criteria) labels. Valid values are "EVM"(default value) and "C/SCSC".

preference.name: SM_EVM_Calc_Preference
preference.preference_description: Allows the user to choose whether they would like the Earned Value Management calculations to be based on cost or based on hours. Valid values are "COST" and "HOURS"(default value).

preference.name: SM_EVM_Export_Units
preference.preference_description: Defines if units should be included when exporting Earned Value data. Valid values are true or false (default value) This is a user preference.

preference.name: SM_EVM_Work_Complete
preference.preference_description: Allows the user to choose whether they would like the Work Complete in Earned Value Management calculations based on actual hours or percent complete. Valid values are "PERCENT_COMPLETE"(default value) and "ACTUAL_HOURS".

preference.name: SM_EXEC_VIEW_PROPERTIES
preference.preference_description: Defines the fields shown in the "Execution View" in the Schedule Manager application. Valid values are internal attribute names of a Schedule Task object and "SI" (for the status icon). The code will retrieve the value for this preference in this priority order: user, role, group or site.

preference.name: SM_EnforceActualDatesBeforeNow
preference.preference_description: Determines if actual dates can be set to any date (false) or must be set to a date before the current time (true). The given value will affect how the default values set by the DefaultActualToSystemDate preference (for actual dates) are taken into account. This is a site preference.

preference.name: SM_GANTT_MONTH_ZM_B_DF
preference.preference_description: Defines the date format of the bottom of the Gantt chart for month zoom. Valid format is a combination of the valid characters that make up a date pattern: M for month character, d for each day number, y for each year digit, " ", "," and "/" as separators. The default format, whenever the value is empty, is MM/dd.

preference.name: SM_GANTT_MONTH_ZM_T_DF
preference.preference_description: Defines the date format of the top of Gantt chart for month zoom. Valid format is a combination of the valid characters that make up a date pattern: M for month character, d for each day number, y for each year digit, " ", "," and "/" as separators. The default format, whenever the value is empty, is MMMM, yyyy. The information below is specific to iconographic languages. The date format can include the following user preferences for year and month. "YearString" for year "MonthString" for month "WeekString" for week For eg. "MMMM 'MonthString', yyyy 'YearString'"

preference.name: SM_GANTT_QTR_STRT
preference.preference_description: Specifies the starting month of the first quarter. The value must be a number between 1 (for January) and 12 (for December). Default, whenever the value is empty, is 1 (January).

preference.name: SM_GANTT_QTR_ZM_B_DF
preference.preference_description: Defines the date format of the bottom of the Gantt chart for quarter zoom. Valid format is a combination of the valid characters that make up a date pattern: M for month character, d for each day number, y for each year digit, " ", "," and "/" as separators. The default format, whenever the value is empty, is MMM. The information below is specific to iconographic languages. The date format can include the following user preferences for month. "MonthString" for year For eg. "MMM 'MonthString'"

preference.name: SM_GANTT_QTR_ZM_T_DF
preference.preference_description: Defines the date format of the top of the Gantt chart for quarter zoom. Valid format is yyyy. The default display, whenever the value is empty, for the quarter is Qtr {n}, yyyy where n stands for a number indicating which quarter. The information below is specific to iconographic languages. The date format can include the following user preferences for year. "YearString" for year For eg. "yyyy 'YearString'"

preference.name: SM_GANTT_USE_ISO_8601_FOR_DATE
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether the calendar display in Gantt should follow ISO 8601 standard to display the week numbers. ISO 8601 standard denotes that the number of days to call a week as first week of the year should be greater than or equal to 4. The default value for this preference is False.

preference.name: SM_GANTT_WEEK_ZM_T_DF
preference.preference_description: Defines the date format of the top of Gantt chart for week zoom. Valid format is a combination of the valid characters that make up a date pattern: M for month character, d for each day number, y for each year digit, " ", "," and "/" as separators. The default format, whenever the value is empty, is MMM dd, yyyy. The information below is specific to iconographic languages. The date format can include the following user preferences for year, month and day. "YearString" for year "MonthString" for month "WeekString" for week "DayString" for day For eg. "MMM 'MonthString' dd 'DayString', yyyy 'YearString'"

preference.name: SM_GANTT_YEAR_ZM_T_DF
preference.preference_description: Defines the date format of the top of the Gantt chart for year zoom. Valid format is a combination of the valid characters that make up a date pattern: M for month character, d for each day number, y for each year digit, " ", "," and "/" as separators. The default format, whenever the value is empty, is yyyy. The information below is specific to iconographic languages. The date format can include the following user preferences for year. "YearString" for year For eg. "yyyy 'YearString'"

preference.name: SM_Hours_Per_Day_Preference
preference.preference_description: Defines the number of work hours per day, as used for calculating calendar end dates. The value can vary depending on the site (e.g 8 hours for the US, 7.5 hours for the UK). The default value is 8.

preference.name: SM_Hours_Per_Week_Preference
preference.preference_description: Defines the number of work hours per week, as used for calculating calendar end dates. The value can vary depending on the site (e.g 5 days * 8 hours for the US, 5 days * 7.5 hours for the UK). The default value is 40.

preference.name: SM_Hours_Per_Year_Preference
preference.preference_description: Defines the number of work hours per year, as used for calculating calendar end dates. The value can vary depending on the site (e.g 365 days * 8 hrs for the US, 365 days * 7.5 hrs for the UK). The default value is 2920.

preference.name: SM_LIMIT_SINGLE_MASTER_SCHED
preference.preference_description: Enforces a Schedule to have one and only one direct master Schedule. Valid values are true (default value) and false.

preference.name: SM_NEW_TASK_DIALOG_CLOSE_ON_FINISH
preference.preference_description: Determines if the new task dialog should be closed after the user clicks the finish button. Valid values are: * true: the dialog closes. This is the default value. * false: the dialog remains opened.

preference.name: SM_PLMXML_EXPORT_SUB_SCHEDULE
preference.preference_description: Enables exporting sub-schedules when exporting a master schedule. * true: sub-schedules are exported. This is the default value. * false: sub-schedules are not exported. This is a site preference.

preference.name: SM_PLMXML_IMPORT_EXISTING_SCHEDULE
preference.preference_description: Enables re-importing/overwriting a schedule which has already been imported. Valid values are: * true: if the schedule is already present, the import operation will proceed and overwrite the existing schedule. This is the default value. * false: if the schedule is already present, the import operation will fail. This is a site preference.

preference.name: SM_PREVENTION_OVERRIDE
preference.preference_description: Determines if the Schedule Manager should override the values specified in the preference "SM_PREVENT_UPDATE_STATES" during the check for execution data updates. Valid values are: * ALWAYS_ON : The execution data updates will be allowed regardless of the values of the preference "SM_PREVENT_UPDATE_STATES". * ALWAYS_OFF : The execution data updates will be enforced as defined by the values of the preference "SM_PREVENT_UPDATE_STATES". * Schedule Based : The schedule's flag "Enable Execution Override" will be used to determine if the override is turned on or off. This is the default value.

preference.name: SM_PREVENT_DELETE_STATES
preference.preference_description: Configures the states in which Schedule and Tasks cannot be deleted. The valid values are the internal state values: "in_progress", "complete", "closed", "aborted".

preference.name: SM_PREVENT_TASK_START_UPDATE_STATES
preference.preference_description: Configures the states to be considered as locked, and therefore for which updates of task start dates will not be possible. The valid values are the internal state values: "in_progress", "complete", "closed", "aborted".

preference.name: SM_PREVENT_UPDATE_STATES
preference.preference_description: Configures the states to be considered as locked, and therefore for which updates of Schedules and Tasks will not be possible. The valid values are the internal state values: "in_progress", "complete", "closed", "aborted". SM_PREVENTION_OVERRIDE preference will override this preference for execution data updates.

preference.name: SM_PV_FILTER_SHOW_SCHEDULES_ON_EMPTY
preference.preference_description: Indicates if schedule nodes are to be displayed when no tasks are returned from a filter-only criteria in the "Program View" command. This preference comes into play when a filter is applied but has no grouping condition. Valid values are true (default) and false. This is a user preference.

preference.name: SM_Run_Data_Inconsistency_Checks
preference.preference_description: Activates the automatic validation of schedules for data inconsistencies immediately after loading. Valid values for this user preference are: * true: automatically run the validation. * false: do not run the validation.

preference.name: SM_SCHEDULE_DATE_LINKED_TO_ACTUAL
preference.preference_description: Determines if the Schedule Manager should link actual execution dates to scheduling dates. Valid values are: * ALWAYS_OFF: The date linking capability will be always disabled. * ALWAYS_ON: The date linking capability will be always enabled. * SCHEDULE_BASED: The date linking capability will be enabled or disabled based on the value of the property "dates_linked" of the Schedule. This is the default value.

preference.name: SM_SCHEDULING_ENGINE_DATE
preference.preference_description: Sets the default behavior for new schedules, determining if they will be scheduled from the start or the finish date of the schedule. Valid values are "START" and "FINISH".

preference.name: SM_SchedulingEngineOptions
preference.preference_description: Manages the deactivation of scheduling and execution validations. Valid values are: * 0: Both scheduling and execution validations are disabled. This is the default value. * 1: Only the scheduling validation is disabled. The default value is 1. If the preference does not have any value, both scheduling and execution validations are enabled. System throws an error if the preference value is set to anything other than 0 or 1.

preference.name: SM_SetDefaultScheduleAsExternal
preference.preference_description: Manages the ownership of validation in a schedule. Valid values are: * true: Validation ownership is managed by an external application. * false: Validation ownership by the Schedule Manager application. This is the default value. If the preference does not have any value, validation ownership falls on the Schedule Manager. System throws an error if the preference value is set to anything other than true or false.

preference.name: SM_Structure_Partial_Context
preference.preference_description: Determines how a structured Schedule is loaded. Valid values for this user preference are: * 0: all structures and their siblings are loaded. This is the default value * 1: only the selected structure and its siblings are loaded.

preference.name: SM_TEMPLATE_DATE
preference.preference_description: Specifies the start date of schedules created from a template. Valid values are: * true: The start date of the template is used as the start date of the new schedules created from it. This is the default value. * false: The current date is used as the start date of the new schedules. This is a user preference.

preference.name: SM_Use_Milestone_Wizard
preference.preference_description: Determines if the "Milestone Creation" operation uses a creation wizard. Valid values are "false"(default value) and "true".

preference.name: SM_View_CriticalPath
preference.preference_description: Enables visualization of critical path in the Schedule Manager application. Valid values are true or false (default value is false for this User preference).

preference.name: SM_WBS_CODE_PREF
preference.preference_description: Enables/Disables Work Breakdown Structure (WBS) code generation and validation in schedules. Valid values are: * true: WBS code is generated and validated. This is the default value. * false: WBS code generation and validation is disabled.

preference.name: SM_WBS_FORMAT_PREF
preference.preference_description: Describes the default Work Breakdown Structure (WBS) format to be used by schedules when they are created. The format used by the individual schedules can be changed at the schedule level. The default value is "N.N". It is recommended you use the graphical interface to set this preference.

preference.name: SM_WBS_INITIAL_PREF
preference.preference_description: Sets the initial starting point for Work Breakdown Structure (WBS) codes based on the default WBS format. The initial starting point used by the individual schedules can be changed at the schedule level. The default value is "1". It is recommended you use the graphical interface to set this preference.

preference.name: SM_WORKFLOW_STATUS_MAP
preference.preference_description: Defines the workflow status rules mapping between the Workflow Task and Schedule Task statuses. The format for valid values is "workflow_task_status.schedule_task_status".

preference.name: ScheduleAvailableAttributes
preference.preference_description: Site Preference Used for Listing Schedule Attributes in Column Chooser Dialog in ProgramView.

preference.name: ScheduleColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: User Preference Used for Showing Default Columns in the Schedule Manager.

preference.name: ScheduleDeliverableWSOTypes
preference.preference_description: Defines the types allowed for the Schedule Deliverables within Schedule Manager. When adding a type, sub-types will not be considered. For example, adding the "Dataset" type allows "MSWord", "MSWordX," and "MSExcel" to be used. However, adding the "Item" type will not allow the "Document" type (sub-type of "Item") to be used. Valid values are the type internal storage class names for any sub-type of (and including) "WorkspaceObject" Business Object. Out-of-the-box values are Dataset, Folder, Form, and Item. This is a site preference.

preference.name: ScheduleTaskAvailableAttributes
preference.preference_description: Site Preference Used for Listing ScheduleTask Attributes in Column Chooser Dialog in ProgramView.

preference.name: ScheduleTaskAvailableAttributesWithRelations
preference.preference_description: Site Preference Used for Listing ScheduleTask Attributes in Column Chooser Dialog in Schedule Manager.

preference.name: SyncDispatcherClientUrl
preference.preference_description: Defines the URL used for communication between Schedule Manager and Dispatcher Services. An example of valid values is: http://host:port/axis2/services/AxisDispatcherClient.AxisDispatcherClientHttpSoap12Endpoint. This is a site preference.

preference.name: cost_default_currency
preference.preference_description: Specifies the default currency for cost based calculations. Currency values are based on ISO4217 (e.g. for USA the value is USD). This is a site preference.

preference.name: scheduling_graph_dataSource
preference.preference_description: Specifies data source for resource graph. Values are: - randomSample: use random sample generator. - TeamcenterDB: use Teamcenter database (default). This is a site preference.

preference.name: scheduling_graph_dataSource_filter
preference.preference_description: Specifies a filter in data source for resource graph. Values are: - none: no filter is applied (default). - selection: filter for selected schedules. - current: filter for current schedule. This is a site preference.

preference.name: scheduling_graph_date_format
preference.preference_description: Specifies date format in resource graph. Valid values can be any of the patterns that describe date and time format. The default value is 'EEE, MMM d'. This is a site preference.

preference.name: scheduling_graph_domain_interval
preference.preference_description: Specifies tick mark intervals on domain axis (x-axis) in resource graph. Valid values can be any segmented timeline such as 'day', 'week' or any integer numeric values such as '1' (for a day), '7' (for a week): The default value is 'day'. This is a site preference.

preference.name: scheduling_graph_domain_label_vertical
preference.preference_description: Specifies the orientation of domain labels in resource graph. Values are: - true: vertical (default). - false: horizontal. This is a site preference.

preference.name: scheduling_graph_font_name
preference.preference_description: Specifies font name in resource graph. Valid values can be a font face name or a font family name. The name is used together with the style to find an appropriate font face. There is no default value for the preference. Providing a valid value for this preference would override the font name provided by RAC. This is a site preference.

preference.name: scheduling_graph_font_size
preference.preference_description: Specifies the point size of the font in resource graph. Valid values can be any appropriate integer number. The default is 8. This is a site preference.

preference.name: scheduling_graph_font_style
preference.preference_description: Specifies font style in resource graph. Valid values are: 0, 1, 2, or 3. - PLAIN is 0. - BOLD is 1. - ITALIC is 2. - BOLD/ITALIC is 3. The default value is 0. This is a site preference.

preference.name: scheduling_graph_histogram_single_color
preference.preference_description: Specifies single or multi-colored bars in resource graph. Values are: - true : single color (default). - false: multi-colors. This is a site preference.

preference.name: scheduling_graph_reference_calendar
preference.preference_description: Specifies the calendar type to use for domain (x) and range (y) axis in the resource graph. Valid values can be one of the following calendar types; 'resource_calendar_type', 'system_calendar_type' : The default value is 'resource_calendar_type'. This is a site preference.

preference.name: scheduling_graph_task_legend
preference.preference_description: Enables display of legends in resource graph. Values are: - true : display legends for stacked bars. For this value, information in the tooltip would not include schedule and load information. - false: no legends are displayed for stacked bars (default). This is a site preference.

preference.name: scheduling_graph_view
preference.preference_description: Specifies the view to use for graph. Values are: - classic: view of graph with scroll bars. - native: view of graph without scroll bars (default). This is a site preference.

preference.name: S2clActivityStreamPurgeInterval
preference.preference_description: Defines the purge interval (in number of days) for managing auto-deletion of notifications in the activity for the Social Collaboration application of the Active Workspace client. Any read notification older than this value is deleted.

preference.name: S2clAnswer.CellProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the properties and associated values to display for Answer objects in the object cell in the Social Collaboration application of the Active Workspace client. Valid values are property internal names. Multiple comma separated values are permitted.

preference.name: S2clAnswer.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Answer objects.

preference.name: S2clAnswer.SocialCellProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the properties and associated values to display for Answer objects in the object cell in the Social Collaboration application of the Active Workspace client. Valid values are property internal names. Multiple comma separated values are permitted.

preference.name: S2clAnswerSummary.SUMMARY_REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Answer objects.

preference.name: S2clCommentary.CREATERENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of create stylesheet for Commentary objects.

preference.name: S2clCommentary.CellProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the properties and associated values to display for Commentary objects in the object cell in the Social Collaboration application of the Active Workspace client. Valid values are property internal names. Multiple comma separated values are permitted.

preference.name: S2clCommentary.INFORENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of information stylesheet for Commentary objects.

preference.name: S2clCommentary.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Commentary objects.

preference.name: S2clCommentary.SocialCellProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the properties and associated values to display for Commentary objects in the object cell in the Social Collaboration application of the Active Workspace client. Valid values are property internal names. Multiple comma separated values are permitted.

preference.name: S2clCommentary.TrendingLimit
preference.preference_description: Defines the number of objects to be returned from the "Fetch Trending Data" service for the Social Collaboration application of the Active Workspace client. If the value is 0 or less, all trending objects are returned.

preference.name: S2clCommentary.TrendingPeriod
preference.preference_description: Defines the number of days (trending period) for which Trending data needs to be retrieved in the Social Collaboration application of the Active Workspace client. The "Fetch Trending Data" service uses the system date minus the trending period to retrieve socially active objects.

preference.name: S2clCommentaryCreate.CREATE_REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Commentary objects.

preference.name: S2clCommentarySummary.SUMMARY_REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Commentary objects.

preference.name: S2clEnvelope.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Envelope objects.

preference.name: S2clEnvelopeSummary.SUMMARY_REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Envelope objects.

preference.name: S2clExperience.CellProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the properties and associated values to display for Experience objects in the object cell in the Social Collaboration application of the Active Workspace client. Valid values are property internal names. Multiple comma separated values are permitted.

preference.name: S2clExperience.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Experience objects.

preference.name: S2clExperience.SocialCellProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the properties and associated values to display for Experience objects in the object cell in the Social Collaboration application of the Active Workspace client. Valid values are property internal names. Multiple comma separated values are permitted.

preference.name: S2clExperienceSummary.SUMMARY_REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Experience objects.

preference.name: S2clNotificationPreferences
preference.preference_description: Defines the notification category and preferences. The format of this multi-value preference is as follows :"category name=pref value;pref name^pref value;pref name^pref value" New categories can to be added with a set of values to the multi-value preference.

preference.name: S2clQuestion.CellProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the properties and associated values to display for Question objects in the object cell in the Social Collaboration application of the Active Workspace client. Valid values are property internal names. Multiple comma separated values are permitted.

preference.name: S2clQuestion.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Question objects.

preference.name: S2clQuestion.SocialCellProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the properties and associated values to display for Question objects in the object cell in the Social Collaboration application of the Active Workspace client. Valid values are property internal names. Multiple comma separated values are permitted.

preference.name: S2clQuestionSummary.SUMMARY_REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Question objects.

preference.name: S2clScalarRating.CellProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the properties and associated values to display for Scalar Rating objects in the object cell in the Social Collaboration application of the Active Workspace client. Valid values are property internal names. Multiple comma separated values are permitted.

preference.name: S2clScalarRating.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Scalar Rating objects.

preference.name: S2clScalarRating.SocialCellProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the properties and associated values to display for Scalar Rating objects in the object cell in the Social Collaboration application of the Active Workspace client. Valid values are property internal names. Multiple comma separated values are permitted.

preference.name: S2clScalarRatingSummary.SUMMARY_REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Scalar Rating objects.

preference.name: S2clSubscriptionEventName
preference.preference_description: Defines the social collaboration custom event for users to follow other objects.

preference.name: S2clSubscriptionHandlerId
preference.preference_description: Defines the ID of the social collaboration handler for managing notifications with event type S2clSubscriptionEvent.

preference.name: S2clTag.CellProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the properties and associated values to display for Tag objects in the object cell in the Social Collaboration application of the Active Workspace client. Valid values are property internal names. Multiple comma separated values are permitted.

preference.name: S2clTag.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Tag objects.

preference.name: S2clTagSummary.SUMMARY_REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Registration of summary stylesheet for Tag objects.

preference.name: S2clToggleRating.CellProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the properties and associated values to display for Toggle Rating objects in the object cell in the Social Collaboration application of the Active Workspace client. Valid values are property internal names. Multiple comma separated values are permitted.

preference.name: S2clToggleRating.SocialCellProperties
preference.preference_description: Defines the properties and associated values to display for Toggle Rating objects in the object cell in the Social Collaboration application of the Active Workspace client. Valid values are property internal names. Multiple comma separated values are permitted.

preference.name: S2cl_EnableTagSuggestions
preference.preference_description: Defines a switch to turn on/off the tag suggestions while creating tags. All the available tag names are cached when the user tries to create a tag for the first time. As the number of tags grows over a period of time, caching the tag names might pose a performance bottleneck. Set this preference to false to turn off caching.

preference.name: S2cl_SocialTileHeightInLines
preference.preference_description: Defines the number of lines to show while rendering the Social Object Cell used for showing Commentary in grouped view. A value of -1 or 0 displays entire commentary text in Social Object cell. A value greater than zero limits the display of the commentary text to that many lines in Social Object cell. For example: if the value is set to 5 then commentary text is displayed on the Social Object Cell will not exceed 5 lines. If the commentary text is small and fits in less than 5 lines then only appropriate number of lines are displayed in the Social Object Cell.

preference.name: S2cl_SocialTileHeightInLinesInThreadedDisplay
preference.preference_description: Defines the number of lines to show while rendering the Social Object Cell used for showing Commentary in threaded display. Defines the number of lines to show while rendering the Social Object Cell used for showing Commentary. A value of -1 or 0 displays entire commentary text in Social Object cell. A value greater than zero limits the display of the commentary text to that many lines in Social Object cell. For example: if the value is set to 5 then commentary text is displayed on the Social Object Cell will not exceed 5 lines. If the commentary text is small and fits in less than 5 lines then only appropriate number of lines are displayed in the Social Object Cell.

preference.name: APN_absolute_path_name_separator
preference.preference_description: Indicates the separator between each connected lines. The BOM line property "Connected To Abs Name" displays the complete hierarchical path of the connected BOM lines. The separator between each connected lines is displayed by default as ->.

preference.name: BOM_objects_excluded_from_split
preference.preference_description: Specifies the type/subtype of objects for which Split Occurrence operation should not be allowed. If no entry is specified, all types are allowed for this operation.

preference.name: Connected_ToRules
preference.preference_description: This would allow the Connected_To relation only between the listed primary and secondary type combinations. If no rule is specified for a given primary type, its supertype is searched until PSConnection is found for which the secondary is considered as interface. The rules listed for this preference should not be removed. If required, sites should append the secondary list OR add rules for their particular primary types.

preference.name: Functionality.CREATERENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the create stylesheet for Functionality objects (type Functionality).

preference.name: Functionality.REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Indicates the types to which the Functionality stylesheet can be applied.

preference.name: Functionality.RENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the Properties stylesheet for Function objects (type Functionality).

preference.name: Functionality.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the summary stylesheet for Function objects (type Functionality).

preference.name: FunctionalityCreate.CREATE_REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Indicates the types to which the Functionality Create stylesheet can be applied.

preference.name: FunctionalityRevision.REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Indicates the types to which the FunctionalityRevision stylesheet can be applied.

preference.name: FunctionalityRevision.RENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the Properties stylesheet for Function Revision objects (type FunctionalityRevision).

preference.name: FunctionalityRevision.SUMMARYRENDERING
preference.preference_description: Registers the summary stylesheet for Function Revision objects (type FunctionalityRevision).

preference.name: FunctionalityRevisionSummary.SUMMARY_REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Indicates the types to which the FunctionalityRevision Summary stylesheet can be applied.

preference.name: FunctionalitySummary.SUMMARY_REGISTEREDTO
preference.preference_description: Indicates the types to which the Functionality Summary stylesheet can be applied.

preference.name: GDELink_default_type
preference.preference_description: Defines the type to use when a non-revisable connection is created without explicitly giving a type. The default value is "TC_Link".

preference.name: GDE_exclude_list
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of domain specific GDE types which along with their sub types will be excluded from the File->New->Item Element types list in My Navigator.

preference.name: GDE_objects_with_integer_quantity
preference.preference_description: Specifies the type/subtype of GDE objects that cannot have real numbers as quantity in Structure Manager. If no entry is specified, all types are allowed to have real numbers.

preference.name: Implemented_ByRules
preference.preference_description: This is used to validate the primary and secondary objects combination in Implemented_By relationship. If no rule is specified for a given primary type, its supertype is searched. If no rules are found for any of the super types, the primary-secondary combination is considered invalid for Implemented_By relationship. The default rules for the primary types for this preference should not be removed. If required, sites should append the secondary list OR add new entries for rules corresponding to their particular primary types.

preference.name: MECH_domain_list
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of Mechatronics Domains to which a Design Artifact object can belong. These Domain values are used in preferences named MECH_domain_types_"value" to define the list of Design Artifact types which belong to that Domain.

preference.name: MECH_domain_types_Automation
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of Design Artifact types, like "ItemRevision", which belong to the Automation Domain.

preference.name: MECH_domain_types_Mechanical
preference.preference_description: Defines the list of Design Artifact types, like "ItemRevision", which belong to the Mechanical Domain.

preference.name: Realized_ByRules
preference.preference_description: This is used to validate the primary and secondary objects combination in Realized_By relationship. If no rule is specified for a given primary type, its supertype is searched. If no rules are found for any of the supertypes, the primary-secondary combination is considered invalid for Realized_By relationship. The default rules for the primary types for this preference should not be removed. If required, sites should append the secondary list OR add new entries for rules corresponding to their particular primary types.

preference.name: SIG_asystem_source_rules
preference.preference_description: Restricts the creation of associations of type source for a frame and signal only to the types or classes that appear in this preference. If preference value is a class or a type, the Subtypes of the class or type are automatically included and considered as valid. This preference value must be set with valid values of types or classes for the primary and secondary, for the associations to be created. Customer specific types or classes previously being used as primary or secondary for this association MUST be appended to the values for this preference in order for the associations to be created with those objects. If the Preference value is not set then the user will not be able to associate any object of any type in the source role. The rules listed for this preference should not be removed. If required, sites should append the secondary list to include their valid secondaries for existing primary types OR add new values for their new primary types. Valid values are Message:Item, Signal:Interfaces,ProcessVariable:Interfaces,Item. Multiple values are allowed with each primary-secondary pair being comma-separated.

preference.name: SIG_asystem_target_rules
preference.preference_description: Restricts the creation of associations of type target for a signal only to the types or classes that appear in this preference. If preference value is a class or a type, the Subtypes of the class or type are automatically included and considered as valid. This preference value must be set with valid values of types or classes for the primary and secondary, for the associations to be created. Customer specific types or classes previously being used as primary or secondary for this association MUST be appended to the values for this preference in order for the associations to be created with those objects.If Preference value is not set then user will not be able to associate a PSSignal or its sub-type with object of any type in target role. The rules listed for this preference should not be removed. If required, sites should append the secondary list to include their valid secondaries for existing primary types OR add new values for their new primary types.Valid values are Message:Item,Signal:Interfaces, ProcessVariable:Interfaces,Item. Multiple values are allowed with each primary-secondary pair being comma-separated.

preference.name: SIG_asystem_transmitter_rules
preference.preference_description: Restricts the creation of associations of type transmitter for a signal only to the types or classes that appear in this preference. If preference value is a class or a type, the Subtypes of the class or type are automatically included and considered as valid. This preference value must be set with valid values of types or classes for the primary and secondary, for the associations to be created. Customer specific types or classes previously being used as primary or secondary for this association MUST be appended to the values for this preference in order for the associations to be created with those objects. If Preference value is not set then user will not be able to associate a PSSignal or its sub-type with object of any type in transmitter role. The rules listed for this preference should not be removed. If required, sites should append the secondary list to include their valid secondaries for existing primary types OR add new values for their new primary types. Valid values are PSSignal:PSConnection, ProcessVariable:PSConnection. Multiple values are allowed.

preference.name: SIG_pvariable_rules
preference.preference_description: Restricts the creation of associations of type ProcessVariable for a signal only to the types or classes that appear in this preference. If preference value is a class or a type, the Subtypes of the class or type are automatically included and considered as valid. This preference value must be set with valid values of types or classes for the primary and secondary, for the associations to be created. Customer specific types or classes previously being used as primary or secondary for this association MUST be appended to the values for this preference in order for the associations to be created with those objects. If Preference value is not set then user will not be able to associate a PSSignal or its sub-type with object of any type in process variable role. The rules listed for this preference should not be removed. If required, sites should append the secondary list to include their valid secondaries for existing primary types OR add new values for their new primary types. Valid values are PSSignal:ProcessVariable. Multiple values are allowed.

preference.name: SIG_redundant_rules
preference.preference_description: Restricts the association of redundant signals( or frames ) for a signal ( or frame ) only to the types or classes that appear in this preference. If preference value is a class or a type, the Subtypes of the class or type are automatically included and considered as valid. This preference value must be set with valid values of types or classes for the primary and secondary, for the associations to be created. Customer specific types or classes previously being used as primary or secondary for this association MUST be appended to the values for this preference in order for the associations to be created with those objects. If Preference value is not set then user will not be able to associate a PSSignal or its sub-type with object of any type in redundant role. The rules listed for this preference should not be removed. If required, sites should append the secondary list to include their valid secondaries for existing primary types OR add new values for their new primary types. Valid Values are PSSignal:PSSignal. Multiple values are allowed.

preference.name: TC_releasable_logical_types
preference.preference_description: No description available for this preference.

preference.name: RDV_usage_synchronized_architecture_type
