preference.name: RDV_variant_expression_overlap_checking_mode
preference.preference_description: Decides whether overlap checking considers the exact defined variability. If not set, overlap checks will assume unlimited variability. Possible values for this preference are: 1 - overlap checks assume unlimited variability (default). 2 - overlap checks use variability exactly as defined. 5 - overlap checks assume unlimited variability; NVEs can be added to Breakdown Elements even if they a) require more variability than currently available, or b) don't have any overlap with the current variability. 6 - overlap checks use variability exactly as defined; NVEs can be added to Breakdown Elements even if they a) require more variability than currently available, or b) don't have any overlap with the current variability.

preference.name: TCAE_installation_level
preference.preference_description:
Used to decide whether to check for TcAE/GMO licenses or not. Valid values are 1/2/3. 1 - No license. 2 - TcAE license. 3 - GMO license.
If this preference is not set, default value is 1.

preference.name: TC_Configuration_File
preference.preference_description: Preference for setting the conversion configuration file.The configuration file should contain data in the following format.Input_Type|Conversion Arguments|OutputFilename.Output_Type

preference.name: TC_Validation_Datasettype
preference.preference_description: This preference will be used by the CM to set the datasettype for file validation and Conversion

preference.name: TC_external_system_attr_value_separator
preference.preference_description: Defines the character used as separator between BOM attribute values (e.g. ",").

preference.name: TC_external_system_bom_attributes
preference.preference_description: Retrieves the values of bom attributes while traversing bom. For Ex:bl_item_item_id, bl_rev_item_revision_id, bl_rev_object_desc,bl_abs_occ_id

preference.name: TC_external_system_item_type
preference.preference_description: Item type to be searched while traversing bom

preference.name: TC_external_system_url
preference.preference_description: Preference to post the bom attribute information. For Ex: http://www.test.com/cgi-bin/printenv.pl/

preference.name: TC_external_system_url_value_name
preference.preference_description: To mention the variable to retrieve the information posted. This variable can be used by the URL script to retrieve the information

preference.name: TC_send_to_external_system
preference.preference_description: If this option is OFF, "Send to External System" in PSE->Menubar is unavailable

preference.name: MakeFrom_Without_Program_Preferred
preference.preference_description: Allows the creation of TC_Program_Preferred_Items relations between Non-Program Preferred Items. The default value is false (not allowed).

category.name: TC XML Import Export.Import
category.category_description: Preferences that control import of data in TC XML.

preference.name: TCXML_add_objects_to_newstuff_on_import
preference.preference_description: Defines whether root objects imported via TIE import will be added to the user's Newstuff folder. Valid values are TRUE/FALSE.

preference.name: TIE_TMTID_NOTETYPENAME
preference.preference_description: Defines the Note type name used to retrieve TMTID data (Total Maintenance Time IDentifier) for Absolute Occurrence import from Teamcenter Enterprise.

preference.name: TIE_Volume_Map
preference.preference_description: Defines the mapping of the source volume to the target shadow volume, as used in site consolidation.

preference.name: TCIF_BOS_service_url
preference.preference_description: Specifies the path that is appended to the Teamcenter Integration Framework server URL for login and logout requests to the Teamcenter Integration Framework server. This value must match the Teamcenter Integration Framework configuration.

preference.name: TCIF_BO_checkin_track_list
preference.preference_description: Identifies business object types for which Teamcenter should send a notification to Teamcenter Integration Framework when instances of those types are checked-in.

preference.name: TCIF_process_url_async
preference.preference_description: Specifies the path that is appended to the Teamcenter Integration Framework server URL for asynchronous requests to the Teamcenter Integration Framework server. This value must match the Teamcenter Integration Framework configuration.

preference.name: TCIF_process_url_sync
preference.preference_description: Specifies the path that is appended to the Teamcenter Integration Framework server URL for synchronous requests to the Teamcenter Integration Framework server. This value must match the Teamcenter Integration Framework configuration.

preference.name: TCIF_url
preference.preference_description: Specifies the URL location for Teamcenter Integration Framework services.

preference.name: TCIF_user_name
preference.preference_description: Defines the user name for logging into the Teamcenter Integration Framework server.

preference.name: TCIF_user_password
preference.preference_description: Defines the password for logging into the Teamcenter Integration Framework server.

preference.name: SE_Trace_Report_Layout
preference.preference_description: Changes the layout of traceability report to horizontal or vertical. Valid values are: * true: horizontal layout. * false: vertical layout (top-down). This is the default value.

preference.name: VIEWER.VIEWERCONFIGTOLOAD
preference.preference_description: Defines the default viewer configuration name to load. This is a user preference.

preference.name: defaultViewerConfig.VIEWERCONFIG
preference.preference_description:
Defines the default viewer configuration. This is a user preference.
Valid values are in the following format: DATATYPE.VIEWERID=OPTIONAL_NAMED_REF_TYPES.
Entries are in order of priority, with the exception of SEARCHORDER.ITEMREV2DATASET.
In order to enable Viewing NX .prt files please add the following lines: UGMASTER.DirectModelViewer=UGPART UGPART.DirectModelViewer=UGPART UGALTREP.DirectModelViewer=UGPART

preference.name: g4mClassViewer.VIEWERCONFIGTOLOAD
preference.preference_description: Defines the viewer configuration name to load for the G4M Class Viewer. This is a user preference.

preference.name: g4mInstanceViewer.VIEWERCONFIGTOLOAD
preference.preference_description: Defines the viewer configuration name to load for the G4M Product Vision Viewer. This is a user preference.

preference.name: g4mProductVisionViewer.VIEWERCONFIGTOLOAD
preference.preference_description: Defines the viewer configuration name to load for the G4M Product Vision Viewer. This is a user preference.

preference.name: g4mViewerConfig.VIEWERCONFIG
preference.preference_description:
Defines the viewer configuration used for the Classification Application. This is a user preference.
Valid values are in the following format: DATATYPE.VIEWERID=OPTIONAL_NAMED_REF_TYPES.
Entries are in order of priority, with the exception of SEARCHORDER.ITEMREV2DATASET.
In order to enable Viewing NX .prt files please add the following lines: UGMASTER.DirectModelViewer=UGPART UGPART.DirectModelViewer=UGPART UGALTREP.DirectModelViewer=UGPART

preference.name: HSM_integration_enabled
preference.preference_description: Administrators can use this preference to enable Volume Management application to work with 3rd Party HSM software. Valid values are TRUE/FALSE. TRUE -Volume Management application is enabled to work with 3rd party HSM software. FALSE -Volume Management application is not enabled to work with 3rd party HSM software. This is a site preference only.

preference.name: HSM_primary_tier_hosts
preference.preference_description: Used with Volume Management application and will be used to list the host names (node names) on which the primary tier volumes are managed by 3rd party HSM software. If all of Teamcenter primary tier volumes are managed by 3rd party HSM software, than the preference can bet set to keyword "ALL" rather than individually listing the host names.

preference.name: HSM_read_thru_supported
preference.preference_description: This preference is used with Volume Management application. If the migrated files are moved to higher tier on a read operation, due to limitations with hardware platform or 3rd Party HSM software, set this preference value to FALSE. Valid values are TRUE/FALSE. TRUE - if the migrated files are not moved to higher tier on read operation. FALSE -if the migrated files are moved to higher tier on read operation. This is a site preference only.

preference.name: HSM_secondary_tier_capacity
preference.preference_description: This preference is used with Volume Management application.This preference will be set to the estimated total capacity of secondary tier in GB.

preference.name: CR_allow_alternate_procedures
preference.preference_description:
Manages the visibility of workflow templates in the "New Process" panel of the Workflow application in the rich client. Valid values are: * any : The "All" option is pre-selected in the "All/Assigned" radio button group, which means that all templates are listed. * Assigned: The "Assigned" option is pre-selected in the "All/Assigned" radio button group, which means that only the templates assigned to the group and selected target object type are listed. * none: The options "All/Assigned" are not visible. Furthermore, only the templates assigned to the group and selected target object type are displayed (behaviour similar to the "Assigned" option). When no templates are assigned for the target group/type, the displayed list is empty. If no object was selected when initiating the workflow, all the templates assigned to the group are listed. This is the default value.
Process templates assigned to a group and a target object type are defined through the "Process designer->Edit->Template Filter" command.

preference.name: EPM_notify_url_format
preference.preference_description: Defines the type of client connection for URL generation by notify and CR-notify handlers. The valid values are "rich", "dhtml", "activeworkspace" and "none".

preference.name: TASK_MONITOR_SLEEP_TIME
preference.preference_description: Used to set the sleep time for the task monitor daemon. Sleep time should be an integer specifying the desired number of minutes. e.g. 30 for 30 minutes, 60 for 1 hour and 120 for 2 hours.

preference.name: TC_inbox_interval
preference.preference_description: How often to check the In-Box for new tasks (in minutes). 1 - Disable the checking. 0 - Check at the time of logging in. X - Check every X minutes.

preference.name: WRKFLW_change_target_lmu
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether the value of "last modified user" information for the workflow targets should be modified when modifying their release statuses during workflow. Valid values are: * true: the last modified user should be set to the current user. This is the default value. * false: the last modified user should not be modified.

preference.name: WRKFLW_use_legacy_template_filter
preference.preference_description: Indicates whether to use the legacy Type and Group based Template Filter or the new Condition based Template Filter. Valid values are: * true: Use the legacy Type and Group based Template Filter. * false: Use the new Condition based Template Filter. This is the default value.

preference.name: ENABLE_invoke_system_handlers
preference.preference_description: Specifies whether to enable/disable invoke-system-rule and invoke-system-action workflow handlers. Valid values are YES/NO. YES (which is the default setting) - Enables these handlers and are displayed in handler selection dialog. NO - Disables these handlers and will not be displayed in handler selection dialog.

preference.name: EPM_ARG_target_user_group_list_separator
preference.preference_description: Indicates what separator to user when a list of groups or users are returned. This preference is related to $TARGETGROUP/$TARGETOWNER keywords used in the handlers such as CR-fill-in-reviewers. Default value is ",".

preference.name: EPM_adhoc_signoffs
preference.preference_description: Enables the adhoc signoffs functionality in the Workflow application in the rich client. Valid values are: * ON: Enables adhoc signoffs. This is the default value. * OFF: Disables adhoc signoffs.

preference.name: EPM_enable_apply_template_changes
preference.preference_description: Enables template changes to all active workflow processes in the client. Valid values are: NONE: template changes will not be applied to active workflow processes and no option will be presented in the client. This is the default value. OPTIONAL: a) in Workflow Designer when the template stage is being changed to Available, a follow-up dialog will be displayed prompting the user if the template changes should be applied to all active workflow processes. b) an additional checkbox will be displayed in the "Workflow Template Import" dialog to determine if the template changes should be applied to all active workflow processes. AUTOMATIC: template changes will be automatically applied to all active workflow processes. The user will not be prompted to specify if the template changes should be applied.

preference.name: EPM_multiple_processes_targets
preference.preference_description: Enables/Disables multiple processes for same objects in the Workflow application. Valid values are: * ON: Enables Multiple processes. This is the default value. * OFF: Disables Multiple processes.

preference.name: EPM_resource_pool_restrict_subscription
preference.preference_description: Restricts the resource pools available for subscription based on user membership in the "Resource Pool Subscription" dialog. Valid values are: ON - the user can subscribe only to groups and roles for which he/she is a member. OFF - the users can subscribe to all groups and roles. This is the default value.

preference.name: EPM_sub_process_target_inheritance
preference.preference_description: Defines the default setting of the 'Inherit Targets' checkbox in the 'New Workflow Sub-Process' dialog. Valid values are ON/OFF: ON - the 'Inherit Targets' checkbox will be ticked. OFF - the 'Inherit Targets' checkbox will not be ticked. This is a site preference.

preference.name: EPM_task_execution_mode
preference.preference_description: Determines which task execution mode should be used to process a Workflow task. Valid values are: * FOREGROUND: Processes all tasks in foreground mode. This is the default value. * BACKGROUND: Processes all tasks in background mode. * CONFIGURABLE: Processes a task according to its task template's "ExecuteAsync" property setting. If the property is set to "ON", the task will be processed in background mode. If the property is set to "OFF", the task will be processed in foreground mode.

preference.name: EPM_valid_roles_to_assign_responsible_party
preference.preference_description: Determines the list of privileged users allowed to reassign the Responsible Party responsibility of a task. Accepts multiple strings as values. Each string must be one of the following values: responsible_party - Allows the current Responsible Party. active_surrogate - Allows the current surrogate user. task_owner - Allows the owning user of the workflow process. task_owning_group - Allows all users belonging to the group of the owning user. world - Allows all users. privileged - Allows the following users: Current task owner, Responsible Party, All Administrative users group::role - Allows members of a specific group and role. Accepts following format: group::role where group is valid group name and role is a valid role name.

preference.name: EPM_valid_user_to_apply_assignment_list
preference.preference_description: Lists all the values to determine the authorized users to to use Assign All Tasks functionality that assigns the resources to all tasks of the workflow process This preference takes the following values owner - Owning User of the Process owning_group - Workflow Process Owning Group Users world - all users privileged - All site admin users and the group admin users of the process owning group group::role - Group and Role Name to specify resource pool.

preference.name: ForciblyMakeDesignPrimary
preference.preference_description: Bypasses the write permission on Part Revisions for creating TC_Primary_Design_Representation relations between Part Revisions and Design Revisions. The default value is false. Please note that this preference applies only when PS-make-mature-design-primary handler is used to make a Design Revision primary through a Workflow Process.

preference.name: Global_transfer_access
preference.preference_description: Setting for global_transfer utilityall users regardless of this preference settings can use the Global transferfunctionality to transfer their own tasks to someone else. This preferenceconfigures who can assign other users task to someone else.0--> System Administrator can also transer tasks assigned to other users1--> System & Group Administrators can also transfer tasks assigned to others, for group admin it'll only enable this for users within the respective group2--> Every body can transfer tasks assigned to others.

preference.name: HasParticipant_relation_primary
preference.preference_description: Indicates the list of valid primary object types for the relation HasParticipant. Format is <Relation Name>_relation_primary=List of valid primary object types.

preference.name: INBOX_hide_suspended_tasks
preference.preference_description: Valid values are 0/1/2/3. 0 - Default condition to show Started & suspended tasks in the tasks to perform. 1 - Condition to show Only Started tasks in the tasks to perform. 2 - Suspend All Started Tasks of this job. Show Started & suspended tasks in the tasks to perform. 3 - Suspend All Started Tasks of this job. Show Only Started tasks in the tasks to perform. Also suspend all other started tasks of the job.

preference.name: PALColumnsShownPref
preference.preference_description: Specifies the columns (from left to right) displayed in the "Process Assignment List" dialog.

preference.name: PALShownColumnWidthsPref
preference.preference_description: Defines the widths for the columns specified in the preference PALColumnsShownPref.

preference.name: SIGNOFF_adhoc_quorum
preference.preference_description:
Indicates if the task quorum modifiable by Teamcenter user in select-signoff-team can be set lower than that defined by the task template when adhoc signoffs functionality is enabled (EPM_adhoc_signoffs=ON). Valid values are 1/2. 1 - User can set signoff quorum value either less than or greater than that set by task template. 2 - User can set signoff quorum value only greater that that set by task template.
NOTE: For setting 2, if the signoff-quorum is set as -1 (ALL), in that case, the user cannot modify the signoff quorum through select-signoff-team task.
This is a site preference.

preference.name: SIGNOFF_fill_in_reviewers
preference.preference_description: Setting for SIGNOFF_fill_in_reviewers Handler CR-fill-in-reviewers can have an argument -reviewer=User:$USER. Which attempts to assign current user to a required signoff. A user may have 1 to many group/role memberships. But a signoff assignment requires a specific user/group/role assignment. If the signoff profile in the process template specifies a named group and role then the attempt to assign the current user with that group/role will be made. If the signoff profile specifies a wild group or role then it may be ambiguous as to which of a users potentially many valid matching group/role should be used to match the signoff profile. In this way this preference controls how far to consider attempting to match the required group/role. If no match is found then the signoff assignment will not be made by this handler and will have to be completed via the UI. The following outlines the possible settings for this site preference. 1 --> will consider matching the current user's group/role values first, then the default values, then any other group/roles the current user is a member of. This will also be the default setting for this preference. 2 --> will consider matching the current user's group/role values first, then the default values the current user is a member of. 3 --> will consider matching the current user's group/role values

preference.name: SIGNOFF_required_group_and_role
preference.preference_description: Setting for SIGNOFF_required_group_and_role 0--> User must be a registered member of the signoff required group and role, but doesn't have to be logged in as a member of that group or role to perform the signoff. (Default) 1--> User must be a registered member of the signoff required group and role, and must be currently logged in as a member of that group or role to perform the signoff.

preference.name: TCVIEWER_default_workflow_view
preference.preference_description: Specifies what the users want to see as default viewer for viewing process tasks. Valid values are task/process.

preference.name: User.is_out_of_office.FORMATSTRING
preference.preference_description: Defines the property formatter for the "is_out_of_office" boolean property on User business object. Using this property formatter, the boolean property is displayed as the localized values of the keys "k_yes" for "True" and "k_no" for "False".

preference.name: WORKFLOW_adhoc_process
preference.preference_description: Site preference flag indicating if adhoc process functionalities are enabled. Valid values are 0/1/2. 0 - Enabled for all users. 1 - Enabled only if the user is a system administrator or user granted edit access to Workflow Designer. 2 - Enabled for System Adminitrators and Group admins or user granted edit access to Workflow Designer(default).

preference.name: WORKFLOW_advanced_paste
preference.preference_description: Preference to display the Advanced Paste icon in File New Process dialog. Valid values are ON/OFF. If it is set to ON, the icon will be visible. If it is set to OFF, the icon will not be displayed.

preference.name: WORKFLOW_new_route_task_panel
preference.preference_description: Site Preference to display the new route task panel with action column instead of route task panel with radio buttons. Valid values are ON/OFF. If it is set to ON, the new route task panel will be displayed.If it is set to OFF, the old route task panel with radio buttons will be displayed.

preference.name: WRKFLW_admin_for_inactive_user
preference.preference_description: Defines the mailing list to be notified when the workflow automatically reassigns a task or signoff to a resource pool if the user is inactive. It is a single value string type preference. Valid values are: * Any valid email address. For multiple email addresses use semicolon (;) to separate two email addresses.

preference.name: WRKFLW_allow_replica_targets
preference.preference_description: Defines whether replica objects should be allowed as replica proposed targets for workflows. Valid values are: true: The replica objects will be attached to the workflow as replica proposed targets. This is the default value. false: The replica proposed targets attachments will be used.

preference.name: WRKFLW_convert_backward_path_representation
preference.preference_description: Indicates if a checkbox option to convert backward branching paths will be displayed when a Process template is taken offline. Valid values are: * false: the checkbox option is not displayed when a Process template is taken offline. This is the default value. * true: the checkbox option is displayed when a Process template is taken offline and backward branching paths are present.

preference.name: WRKFLW_create_remote_workflow
preference.preference_description: Defines whether the workflow should be created at the remote site. Valid values are: true: An asynchronous request will be submitted to create the workflow at the remote site. This is the default value. false:Workflow will be created at the local site.

preference.name: WRKFLW_display_participants
preference.preference_description: Decides which participant types will be shown while assigning dynamic participants for an object. Valid values are: * allowable: Show all the dynamic participant types associated with the target object type. This is the default value. * assignable: Show all the dynamic participant types which are assignable by the current user and used in any of the in-progress workflows on the target object. If there is no in-progress workflow; all the assignable dynamic participant types will be shown.

preference.name: WRKFLW_error_on_invalid_dynamic_participant
preference.preference_description: Decides whether the workflow handlers will report an error if a dynamic participant is empty or has an inactive user assigned to it. The following handlers would use this preference: * EPM-auto-assign * EPM-auto-assign-rest * EPM-assign-team-selector * EPM-adhoc-signoffs * EPM-fill-in-reviewers * EPM-assign-signoff-dynamic-participant * EPM-assign-responsible-party-dynamic-participant Valid values are: * true: The handlers will report an error. * false: The handlers will not report an error. This is the default value.

preference.name: WRKFLW_mail_surrogates
preference.preference_description: Activates surrogate notifications in the Workflow application. Valid values are: * true: E-Mail notifications are sent to all active surrogate users. This is the default value. * false: E-Mail notifications are not sent to the active surrogate users.

preference.name: WRKFLW_modify_completed_workflow
preference.preference_description: Allows removing targets from completed Workflows. Valid values are: * true: Removal is allowed. * false: Removal is disabled. This is the default value.

preference.name: WRKFLW_modify_target_list_access_privilege
preference.preference_description: Indicates the access privilege to be used in order to enforce permission on modification of the Workflow target list. Valid values are any access privilege. The default value is the CHANGE access privilege.

preference.name: WRKFLW_multisite_apply_template_changes
preference.preference_description: Controls the application of template changes in a replica site after synchronization. If a replica template has active workflow processes, this preference will be consulted before applying the template changes to the active workflow processes when the replica template is synchronized with changes made to the master template. Valid values are: true: Template changes will be applied to the active workflow processes after synchronizing the template changes. false:Template changes will not be applied to the active workflow processes after synchronizing the template changes. This is the default value. This is a site preference.

preference.name: WRKFLW_retain_ACL_objects_on_release
preference.preference_description: Determines the state of Access Control List objects on a target when a release status is applied. Valid values are: true: Any pre-existing ACL objects will not be removed when the release status is applied. false:Any pre-existing ACL objects will be removed when the release status is applied. This is the default value.

preference.name: WRKFLW_show_user_assignment_options
preference.preference_description: Decides which participant tabs will be shown while assigning users to dynamic participants or workflow tasks. Valid values are: * org_default: The organization tree as well as project team list will be shown for assigning users. The organization tree will be the initially selected tab. This is the default value. * project_default: The organization tree as well as project team list will be shown for assigning users. The project team list will be the initially selected tab. * org_only: Only the organization tree will be shown and project team list will be hidden. * project_only: Only the project team list will be shown and organization tree will be hidden.

preference.name: WRKFLW_signoff_report_show_sub_process
preference.preference_description: Controls the details of Signoff, for the parent process and sub-processes, shown in the Signoff report in the Workflow application. Valid values are: 0 - Shows signoff details for the parent process as well as dependent or independent sub-processes. 1 - Shows signoff details for the parent process and only dependent sub-processes. This is the default value.

preference.name: WRKFLW_task_assignee_dynamic_participant_sync
preference.preference_description: Controls synchronization between a Task Assignee and Dynamic Participants of a Task's target object. When such synchronization is enabled, task reassignment will result in the reassignment of Dynamic Participants of the Task's target object, and vice versa. This synchronization behavior is possible only when the initial task assignment is based on a Dynamic Participant of the Task's target object. Valid values are: * true: Task assignments are synchronized with assignment of Dynamic Participants on the Task's target object. This is the default value. * false: Task assignments are not synchronized with assignment of Dynamic Participants on the Task's target object.

preference.name: WRKFLW_task_complete
preference.preference_description:
Defines the default selection some key components, in order to enable single-click in the "Perform" action for Tasks in the Workflow application in the rich client. The preference applies only to "Do" Tasks and "select-signoff-team" for Review and Route Tasks. If the value is true: - "Do" Tasks: the "Complete" value is selected by default in the "Done" radio buttons. - "select-signoff-team" for Review and Route Tasks: the "Ad-hoc done" checkbox is selected by default.
If the value is false, no value is pre-selected for either Tasks.
IMPORTANT: Setting the value to true also sets the associated Task result value (task_result property) to "complete" by default.
